This will , if not already , cause problems as there is very limited space for us .
The solution can be obtained by using technology to achieve a better usage of space that we have and resolve the problems of lands that are inhospitable such as deserts and swamps .
Some countries are having difficulties in managing to get a place to live for their citizens as they tend to get overpopulated .
This has caused problems like the formation and growth of slums which most of the time are not safe to live in due to their unhealthy environment .
The only way to satisfy the increasing demands for space is by achieving a better usage of land like designing taller building so the same area of land can accommodate a greater number of people .
It is also important to use better material that can support buildings during any natural disasters like earthquakes .
A good example is Japan , where there are a lot of tall condominiums despite the large number of earthquakes happening there .
Besides a better usage of land , better sanitation is also needed because a huge number of people will need a clean environment to maintain their health .
Countries with a lot of inhospitable space need not only to achieve a better space usage , but also to restore the land to a livable state and technology can help in a number of ways depending on the quality of the land .
For example , countries with a lot of desert can transform their desert to increase their habitable land and use irrigation to provide clean water to the desert .
Dubai will be a good example for this as previously the country got almost no natural water . But it uses irrigation to bring natural water to the country .
Another example is Netherlands , where most of the land is swamp under sea level . It has used a good irrigation system to counter their problem and to make their land habitable .
As the number of people grows , the need for habitable environment is unquestionably increasing .
In this era , engineering designs can help to provide more habitable environment by designing stronger material to build taller and safer buildings and a better and efficient sanitation system to prevent disease , and also by changing the condition of the otherwise uninhabitable environment .
Besides some technological determinists that allow the development of biometric identification , this technology is also shaped by three social factors , namely , the desire of the society for safety , convenience and economy .
Safety is one of the crucial problems that many countries and companies are concerned about .
On one hand more and more viruses and hackers can access personal computers , so secret data and documents may be stolen .
On the other hand , some important departments need strict rules for their staff members over the use of confidential information to avoid information leaks .
The United States Department of Defense ( DoD ) { Common Access Card } [ HYPERLINK : http : //en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_Access_Card ] is a successful example of biometric identification .
As we can see , the biometric identification employed in important security-sensitive areas is designed to identify people with accuracy and reliability .
Besides safety , convenience is also desirable for identification purposes .
We do not want to spend time and effort to remember passwords , and neither do we want to carry any cards or equipment to show our identity .
For government and other organizations , they are also looking for small size equipment for identification .
Therefore nowadays biometric identification process is designed to be very quick , and the equipment can be easily set up or can be combined with other equipment .
We can have a fingerprint verification reader combined with a built-in smartcard reader , and it only takes seconds to verify one 's identification .
Therefore , the equipment of biometric identification tends to be inexpensive .
For instance , Retinal Technologies , Inc. ( RTI ) , captures a retinal image at distances from the user 's eye with the means of just using a patented aspheric lens array .
This technology is widely used in our society and it brings benefits to the government , the military , the business and every individual .
All in all , biometric identification achieves great development as humans seek for better information protection , easier life style and greater economic profit , and it brings tremendous benefits to those who shape it .
Nuclear technology has come a long way since Ernest Rutherford first split the atom in 1917 .
The subsequent realization that the additional neutrons produced from fission reaction could induce a nuclear chain reaction has sparked off widespread interest in nuclear technology .
Since then , nuclear technology has been exploited for wars and arms races and has found many applications in the medical , industrial and energy fields .
The leakage of radioactive gas into the atmosphere prompted the many anti-nuclear demonstrations that sprang up across America in the following months .
Although the reactor was eventually cleaned up and decontaminated , the damage dealt to nuclear power was irreversible and caused its subsequent decline .
To partly offset this gigantic demand for energy , China has launched an ambitious program to produce 16 % of its electricity from nuclear power by 2030 .
This endeavor to produce more nuclear power has stimulated the development of safer designs of nuclear reactors .
Safety concerns characterize the basic concept of the Pebble Bed reactor with its passive safety design .
When machinery failure occurs and reactor temperature increase to extremely high levels , the reactor does not undergo a meltdown or explode ; instead , temperature just stays at the high level until the heat can be dissipated or cooled by coolant liquids .
In conclusion , nuclear technology development has always been driven by social factors .
World War 2 has given it momentum in its initial research , but it will be mankind 's need for a renewable and environmentally friendly energy source that will drive nuclear technology 's future developments .
Carbon dioxide is a greenhouse gas which traps heat within the Earth .
According to Khandani 's article on 'Engineering design process'1 , there are five steps to the process of designing such technologies .
To reduce heat trapped within the atmosphere , carbon dioxide level has to be reduced .
Presently in the market , there are already technologies which can replace present day equipment and emit less carbon dioxide .
As the subject has been discussed for quite some time , relevant information is readily available on the internet and in magazines and newspapers .
These solutions may be generated by analyzing existing products to find out how the weaknesses can be overcome while retaining the strengths .
They will then analyze the solutions based on economic and social considerations .
These products have to be sold in the market ; hence , consumers must be convinced that these environmentally friendly products are as good as the present equipment in terms of performance and cost .
Therefore careful analysis of a product has to be made before selecting a solution for testing and implementation .
According to Khandani 's article , engineers can test the solution by prototyping or concurrent engineering .
These computer simulations take significantly shorter time ; hence , they are a preferred choice as it means that the product can be sold in the market in a shorter period of time .
Through the five designing steps , a product can be designed to meet the need to decrease carbon dioxide level .
Research has shown that fuel consumption has increased twenty percent over the last decade , and has projected that the depletion of fuels is drawing near .
In addition , burning of fuels emits various harmful gases which pollute our fragile environment .
These green house gases are the main cause of worldwide global warming which gives rise to further catastrophes such as the rise in global temperature etc .
Engineers around the world have already started on working on this problem .
To guide themselves in this heavy responsibility of saving the earth , they have used a set of simple steps , known as the Engineering Design Process .
This process consists of five major steps , namely defining the problem , researching on information pertaining to the problem , brainstorming of ideas , filtering of the ideas , and lastly implementing the ideas .
Firstly , we can define this worldwide problem as the search for alternative resources to the existing near-depletion fuels .
Since fuels are non renewable and emit a lot of harmful gases , the alternatives that we are looking for should be a renewable energy source and should not emit harmful pollutants .
Studies have shown that an average of 2 lbs ( pounds ) of fuel is needed to produce 1kilowatt of power .
In addition , we realize that burning of fuels produces a large amount of greenhouse gases .
An example is water , which is a good renewable resource and is plentiful .
This is because a large body of water is needed to harness the same amount of energy produced by a small amount of fuel .
All the solutions will be thoroughly analysed by engineers before coming to a conclusion .
Lastly , engineers will put their solution to test and ensure that the solution is able to solve the problem .
As such , engineers make use of wind turbines and water hydraulic generators to harness the wind and water energy respectively .
Harnessing the wind and water energy may not be the best option , but both sources are renewable and are able to be used to slow down the depletion of fuel resources .
This has shown that the engineering design process is essential in solving problems , and it ensures that the problem is thoroughly looked into and that the engineers are generating ideas that address the main problem , the depletion of fuels and the emission of harmful gages .
Since the adoption of the reform and open policy in the 1970 's , China has been eagerly speeding up its process of industrialization and development .
Among them , education system and perception of innovation are two major difficulties .
However , China 's examination-oriented education system greatly throttles students ' creativity .
Not only parents and teachers but also the whole society pushes students to get outstanding marks in examinations .
Students spend most of their time reciting details in text books and doing tedious exercises again and again simply to get familiar with examinations .
As a result , students have no chance to develop their creative thinking abilities and gradually become .
Many years ago , the situation was different .
In 1931 , Qian Weichang entered Tsing Hua University , majoring in history with 0 marks in mathematics and physics .
However , after one year 's study , he found history not suitable for himself and became interested in physics and showed great talent .
After several years of researching and studying , Qian Weichang made many great breakthroughs in physics .
Recently , a student got a very good result in the National College Entrance Examination ( NCEE ) , but he did not enter the university which he applied for , because the secondary school offered him Â¥ 100,000 encouraging him to stay for another year in the secondary school for the next year 's NCEE , expecting that he could become the top student in his province .
Creativity is developed by students ' exploration through their self-learning .
Therefore , the lack of creative human resources seriously hampers engineering design processes for innovations in China .
This problem significantly discourages engineers from making more effort to do research and design , and they have little motivation to work hard .
Therefore , people are well motivated to do research and design , .
The 21st century present China a more competitive and challenging opportunity to develop .
Whether China can take this chance to catch up with those well-developed countries or even surpass them depends on China 's of solving the present problems .
If China can come up with an effective policy to change its education system and stimulate innovation , China 's pace to flourish may become even faster .
Statistics show that the number is only continuing to grow with the existing population explosion .
If the need of feeding millions of starving people is put forward to an engineer , he can view it as a broad topic with many possible solutions .
Some solutions would be to design plants/fertilizers that give higher yield or working with health experts introducing new ways to control population growth .
He could genetically modify the plants genome to match with a plant that gives greater yield potential or he could create a new genetic material for a higher yielding food plant .
Looking at this third step we realize why the second stage of an engineering design process of gathering information is important.Once all the information is put together into the different possible solutions , the engineer is put to decide which method out of the lot is suited best for the purpose and agrees with existing international laws .
This determines how accurate the engineer has been in his work and also if he has looked at nature as a factor during his designing process .
The testing stage is usually either the most rewarding or the most heart- breaking stage of a design process .
Even though the solution seems perfect according to calculations , there are " nature factors " that we can not control which still affect any process under the sun .
It is likely that this genetically modified plant with three hundred percent yield is actually not surviving until harvest .
If that is the case , what the engineer would do is to analyze the problem at hand and point out exactly which part of the solution needs to be modified .
With the many possible solutions , what a smart engineer does is to figure out the best solution and introduce the best way of executing it , so that the need is fulfilled immediately and effectively .
The process of developing a new product based on innovation is not an easy task for innovators .
Innovators , who normally work with a Research and Development department , have to recognize the needs from the public or through research , and are required required to spend countless days and nights to understand the problems , to produce solutions to the problems , to convert the solutions into practical products and to commercialize them .
Through distribution and adoption of the innovation products by the public or specific users , innovators have to face the consequences .
These are not the only challenges that innovators are going to deal with .
In order to proceed from the initial stage of innovation development to the final stage , the most important issue is to have a huge sum of fund for development and commercial purposes .
So , the manufacture company , for example , the company that innovators are working for , is one of the major investors that is providing the fund .
Innovators require development fund in order to meet their needs , such as hardware equipments to work on their prototypes .
But at times , critical situations can happen to or affect the manufacturing company ; then the innovators somehow need to be involve too .
For example , if the manufacturing company did not earn profit in the market , then in order to reduce the cost and prevent the loss from getting worse , the manufacturing company has to stop funding the innovators for the development of their prototypes .
Then the innovators have to stop all work for the development .
For another example , during this recent economic downturn , most of the major manufacturing companies are slowing down in manufacturing existing products and releasing new products .
This shows that manufacturing companies are trying to reduce the unnecessary burden to maintain the companies ' stand .
Therefore , this is one of the major factors that will definitely affect innovators from developing innovation products .
Another challenge that innovators need to be concerned about is commercializing the finalized products .
In this final stage , it is all about packaging , marketing and distribution of the products .
There are cases where marketing departments do not wish to market the innovated products due to various reasons .
For example , the marketing department thinks that the new products are not relevant to what the company is selling .
Therefore , the new products are unable to reach the consumers .
Another example is that the marketing department has set the price of the new product too high ; therefore , it fails to obtain the sales target for selling the new product .
So , this is another major factor that innovators have to consider .
In brief , innovators have to face many challenges when they want to develop new products .
They have to obtain fund from investors in order to develop their innovation prototypes and require help from the marketing department to have their innovation products for sales in the marketplace .
However , these procedures might become another challenge for the innovators .
Engineering design is defined as a process that brings ideas or theories into physical representations which satisfy human needs .
Because engineering designs are always related to real problems , during the five processes , the obstacles they face are more than theories and calculations on paper .
Political issues usually become relevant in the beginning and final steps , especially in the last step .
However , in some cities of China , the government wants to minimize the time spending on problem solving process to show their ability in handling problems and thus forces the engineers to skip the first step or just accept the information the government provides .
In the end such a design may turn out to be useless as it does not meet people 's demand .
In the last step of design , political issues can also disrupt the process significantly .
However , after the design had been carried out for a few weeks , it was stopped .
The government 's explanation was safety consideration for earthquakes and some other disasters .
But such an explanation was non-sense as the engineers did not see such a possibility during their designing ; otherwise the design would not be carried out at all .
Some evidences showed that the reason for the halt of the work was that the higher level authorities thought an underground traffic system was not necessary for Harbin .
In this example , there is nothing wrong with the original design work , but the design still can not be carried out due to political inconsistency between the city government and higher level authorities .
The similarities of political obstacles in both two steps are that such problems can not be easily solved by the engineering group ; in other words , the political problems are unavoidable to some degree .
Another problem , financial issue , is quite common during the design process .
It affects the analyzing and the testing step most seriously though it can affect almost every step of design work .
For most design work , engineers are usually employed by some organizations or companies .
Besides , the lack of financial support or sudden stop in the financial support may even lead to the incompletion of a project .
Compared to the political issues , the financial problem affects more steps and is more common around the world .
Both these problems , though affecting different processes , can lead to a complete failure of a project .
Humankind always has needs and demands because people want to lead a more comfortable and easier life .
There are various fields in which engineering plays an important role in our daily lives , such as entertainment , healthcare , transportation , real estate , and so on .
According to Khandani ( 2005 ) , a company 's survival depends on whether its products are in high demand by the society or not .
Most companies are more interested to invent entertainment electronic goods such as flat LCD screens , smaller and smaller mp3/mp4 players , touch screen hand phones , more portable laptops , and so on which are in greatest demand in the market .
Among quite a number of healthcare products available in market , prosthetic limbs play one of the most important roles .
They are needed for various reasons , including congenital defects , accidents or some diseases .
According to Khandani ( 2005 ) ,to design an efficient and safe artificial limb may usually need five basic design processes , which are defining the problem , gathering pertinent information , generating possible solutions , analyzing and selecting the best possible solution and finally testing and implementing it .
" This is the proof of how a successful design can be beneficial to a needy person .
Governments should also encourage more the research and development of these products .
The cost of raw materials has risen significantly from the year 2003 to the year 2009 and it has affected the electronics supply chain .
The price of gold has risen from about US $ 380/troy ounce in June 2003 to about US $ 960/troy ounce in June 2009 ( " Trend " ) .1 Gold is a very important component in electrical conductivity and thus is often used in contact points such as the communicating interface between the graphics card and the motherboard .
Hence designs that need a large amount of gold may not be feasible .
However , if the engineers are to stick to their original design , the cost of the end product will be high .
When electronic devices are not grounded properly , there is a probability that the user might get an electric shock when he/she accidentally comes into contact with the device .
Another example would be the case of Apple 's iPhone .
There are many reports around the internet and on newspaper stating that some users ' iPhones exploded and the main cause is due to the overheating of the lithium- ion battery .
Lithium-ion battery has a temperature tolerance of about 60OC and anything above that will make the battery unsafe for use . In the worst case scenario , the battery explodes , causing injury or death to the user .
Hazardous products can tarnish the reputation of the company and sometimes even result in the loss of innocent lives .
Thus it is very important for engineers to do repeated trial tests of the product to ensure that it is free of faults .
Lastly , engineers must ensure that the product is safe to use or it will end up not only spoiling the reputation of the company but even injuring or killing someone .
The engineering design process can be defined as a process by fellow engineers in the aid of developing either an entirely new system or improvising on the current to cater to .
This process has always been seen as indispensable to the country 's economic growth in the manufacturing sector .
As we understand the relevance and importance of engineering design , we will come to realize that in reality there are several factors that prevent the progress of engineering design .
Firstly , engineering design processes incur excessive costs .
As a result , research and development in these fields today have become significantly more costly compared to R & D costs in previous years .
In Singapore , there is a certain fixed amount in the country 's national budget allocated to the research and development sector .
Since it is more expensive to conduct creative engineering research , it is inevitable that there would be a slight reluctance in contributing more assets to engineering design on the part of the government ; hence , the actual support given by the government is weak .
Moreover , the government also has other areas to spend their resources on .
Some feel that in these tough economic times , it is wiser to spend the money on restructuring the economy or providing more incentives to encourage entrepreneurship , rather than investing in research in engineering design .
Hence , the area of innovative research and development in engineering is not driven to full swing .
Secondly , the number of creative people in Singapore is small , which may be a major reason for the hampering of innovative engineering design .
The population of Singapore is small compared to other countries in the region .
In countries like China and India , the population numbers in the billions whereas the population of Singapore is only 4.5 million .
For example , five percent of the population in Singapore is 1000 times less than five percent of the population in China .
Although there are many Singaporean-based driven engineering design projects like NEWater plants , much of our economic success is highly dependent on other countries .
In areas of mechanical engineering , our latest machineries are either bought from or are replicas of models in Japan .
The impact of having a limited number of creative people has resulted in Singapore having to resort to buying foreign-based engineering design equipment from overseas .
In conclusion , even though we realize the importance of engineering design processes in innovation , there are still problems like rising costs and population scarcity that hinders the progress of the engineering process .
Serendipity is usually defined as the phenomenon of making an unintentional discovery , and it often results in the invention of a new technology .
There are some similarities and differences between serendipity-based technology and technology developed through research such as the technology used in a refrigerator .
When people encounter problems or demand certain things , they will usually try to solve the problems through research and development .
The invention of the refrigerator came about in the 1910s as people were facing the problem of food storage in summer when no icehouse could be used .
Research and development was carried out to solve this problem and eventually resulted in the invention of the refrigerator .
This is how most conventional technologies have been invented .
Similarly , bearing the problems and needs in mind , when unexpected experiment or research results turn up , researchers or scientists would just apply these to solve some other problems which may be totally unrelated to their initial research objectives .
The Post-it note was invented in this way .
3M , the famous cellotape company , discovered an unsuccessful bonding agent that could not stick paper tightly hundreds of years ago .
However , the 3M researchers found that this failed bonding agent was suitable for attaching notes which satisfied many people 's needs .
Thus the post-it note was invented from this idea .
In this manner , many other serendipitous technologies have been discovered and have solved many problems .
Thus , it is fair to say that both conventional technology or serendipitous technology are stimulated by the realization of problems and needs .
, another similarity between conventional technology and serendipitous technology is the process of development and commercialization .
After the discovery of the creative inventions from either research or serendipity , the more important step is the integration of the inventions .
In this process , the attractiveness and practicality of the inventions are improved such that they can be converted into useful products which are accepted by most people .
If the refrigerator had remained as it was invented in the 1910s and no further development had been made to improve its quality , the refrigerator would just be an unsuccessful invention due to its low efficiency and high cost .
After converting a new technology into a useful product comes the process of marketing .
How other people get to know about your products and are convinced to use them .
For example , the 3M researchers sent their post-it products to Fortune 500 companies ' presidents and secretaries to publicize their products .
Finally 3M achieved a huge success as its products became world-famous through the Fortune 500 companies .
From these two examples , it is clear that another similarity between conventional technology and serendipitous technology is the process of development and commercialization which involve a lot of hard work .
Research is usually based in certain organizations and it requires some time , funds and resources before the researchers can finally obtain the expected results .
In the invention of the refrigerator , many companies like General Electric , Kelvinator and Postum organized research groups to invent and develop the refrigerator .
Many new ideas may just be generated from daily life , from mistakes made accidentally or during research for other technology .
For instance , the idea of the post-it pads was generated from a failed attempt by 3M researches to invent a new bonding agent .
In addition , serendipitous new ideas can be generated by anyone .
However conventional technology is limited to people with professional knowledge like researchers or scientists .
In conclusion , although serendipitous technology seems easier to achieve than research-based technology in the research process , it still requires a lot of hard work to further develop and one still needs to acquire the essential knowledge before one would know how the unexpected discoveries can been used to solve existing problems .
Thus , a serendipitous technology can be seen as a conventional technology obtained with less research .
In different parts of the world , however , there are various factors which slow down the process of industrial designing , and China , my home country , is no exception .
Instead of technical reasons , the main obstacles to innovative inventions are funding and the educational background of the Chinese .
There are two aspects with regard to the problem of funding for engineering innovation. .
First of all , the bigger problem is that the whole country lacks money .
Developing new inventions requires substantial funding , so engineers in China are faced with the difficulty of insufficient funding for innovating industries .
Thus , more resources are allocated to production instead of innovation .
Second , the average income of common Chinese people is relatively low .
An industrial invention needs to be marketed successfully immediately after it is created or it may soon .
Chinese engineers do not lack fantastic innovative ideas but they lack the market for their innovations .
For example , the electrical and gas cars have been on the market for some time .
Over 10 years ago , some states in the U.S. decided that 10 % of the total number of cars must be environmentally friendly , that is , cars running on electricity or gas .
This comparison does not mean that the Chinese people are ignoring the environment but most of us can not afford an electrical or a gas car which is far more expensive than a common one using gasoline as fuel .
Very similar to the case of the non-polluting cars , China also has many creative engineering innovations , but due to their higher cost compared to old products of the same kind , they can not be accepted by the market .
Apart from the issue of funding , the educational background of the Chinese is another factor that can not be ignored .
Chinese education has a history of over 2000 years .
Through the thousands of years , most Chinese scholars have been greatly affected by Confucianism .
One of the core theories of which is to teach people to obey rules and regulations .
This is , in fact , not encouraged by the traditional philosophy of Chinese people .
It is very complicated to find out reasons hindering innovation in China .
Despite the obstacles mentioned above , China is now moving its focus to encourage an innovative society .
Thus , I believe these problems obstructing engineering innovation will be solved in the near future .
This is also emphasised in organisations and bureaucracies , which are structured to provide stability and continuity , being inflexible towards nurturing innovations ( Rogers , 2003 ) because failures will tarnish their reputations .
Hence , have begun to adopt a secretive approach towards inventions and they go " underground " for research and development .
Understanding the differences and similarities between such a path that inventors take and conventionally generated technologies will help us to better appreciate their efforts & the hardships they have to go through in their endeavours .
For instance , during the pioneer year of the National University of Singapore 's Formula Society of Automotive Engineering ( NUS FSAE ) , outstanding undergraduates who show exceptional talents and skills among their peers were selected to work on a new project of building an eco-friendly race car to compete on the international platform .
Another similarity between skunkworks and conventionally generated technologies is that both are given adequate funds and resources by their sponsors to maintain their operations .
For example , being a highly classified project , the Lockheed 's Advanced Development Projects Division , an American aerospace company , was funded by the government to develop the latest aircraft to fight in World War II ( Roger , 2003 ) .
Likewise , the Singapore government has also invested heavily on the transportation system in her plan to build better and more cost efficient MRT stations over the next 6 years ( STBT , September 2009 ) .
The provision of funds and resources is critical towards the productivity of research projects and innovations .
However , in order to escape routine organizational procedures , inventors and researchers working in a skunkworks environment are more often abused in contrast to the people working within a conventional system .
For example , the creation of the Macintosh was the collaborated effort of fifty computer designers who worked day and night under an abusive and aggressive leadership ( Roger , 2003 ) .
On the other hand , within the conventional system , innovators are supposed to abide by strict workplace safety guidelines and routine organizational procedures .
They work in a conducive environment to accomplish their tasks .
However , they receive different forms of treatments and work in different environments .
This is to meet the society 's expectation for them to come up with inventions which are workable the first time round .
From the past to the present , many important innovations have surfaced .
Some of these innovations have been shaped by technology while others have been created from the needs and desires of society .
According to " Centuries of dreaming preceded the first successful flight " which suggests that the basis of this innovation was man 's dream to fly like the birds they see in the sky .
Hence , aircrafts were a socially determined technology which has developed over time , catering to the needs of humanity .
Firstly , the military factor was crucial in shaping the aircraft .
Planes of the present versus those of the past show a noticeable improvement in agility and speed .
In World War I ( WWI ) , for example , planes were fairly slower and more bulky ; as mentioned by " Huge biplane bombers with two , three , or four engines were introduced in World War I " .
However , the military learnt from the fighting techniques used in combats during WWI and required aircrafts which were able to negotiate tighter turns and break the speed of sound so as to evade enemies or catch up with them .
World War II showed improvements in the design and capability of aircrafts , making them smaller and therefore swifter .
In addition , fighters of today are even more advanced and able to break the sound barrier .
Take for example the " F-15 Eagle , which excels at air-to-air defence tactics and which has a maximum speed of over Mach 2.5 " , or " the F-16 Falcon , a highly maneuverable all-purpose fighter-bomber " ( AIRPLANE , 2009 ) .
These planes are a mark of development not only in speed but also in agility .
Most importantly , we see that the needs of the military were a driving force behind the development and enhancement of the aircraft .
Secondly , social factors have guided the growth of planes .
The globalised style of living which has translated to the need to transport increasingly large numbers of passengers , and the need for fast delivery of goods or documents have been some of the social issues that have shaped the airplane .
It is noticeable that the size of commercial planes has increased over the years in response to the rise in global travelers .
The Airbus ' A380 in our world today carries up to " 525 " passengers ( A380 Family , 2009 ) .
Moreover , the U.S. Post Office Department for domestic airlines between 1918 and 1927 as mentioned by
Likewise , in today 's world , global air freight agencies such as " DHL " or " Fedex " require planes that are able to travel long distances fast in order to ensure that mail is delivered to their recipients in the shortest time possible .
In conclusion , the aircraft of today , a socially determined technology , has developed from its ancient clumsy and slow predecessors to its current swift and agile models .
These modifications would indeed not have been possible if not for the varying social as well as military requirements during different eras .
When there is a need for something , a technology is created to solve the problem .
The same applies in the case of the eco-friendly car .
The factors are - political , economic , technological , environmental and social .
In 2006 , a documentary film , An Inconvenient Truth , written by former United States Vice President Al Gore , sparked a series of heated discussions after it was screened in cinemas .
This implied that automobile companies had to pull in large sums of money for research and development work to create and promote the sales of such cars .
Without pressure from the government , no automobile company would have taken the initiative to manufacture and market those vehicles .
Today , economic factors also stress the need for eco-friendly cars .
However the cost to finance this project will be high as much research and development has to be done .
Even though it is expensive to develop eco-friendly cars as they cost around two to three times more compared to gasoline powered cars , this move is vital due to the slow depletion of natural resources for vehicle consumption which leads to the increment of fuel prices .
One reason for this is that the servicing costs are lower for eco-friendly cars that operate on electricity as compared to gasoline powered automobile with internal combustion engines .
Compared to the fuel powered car , the eco-friendly car may be at the losing end due to its speed , its mileage and time taken for battery charging while
Fuel powered cars are capable of running longer distances , do not require battery charging time and are capable of reaching maximum speeds within seconds .
However , eco-friendly car developers are constantly coming up with newer technologies to improve their cars so that in the near future these cars would likely function just as well as the gasoline powered cars .
One of the main factors for the creation of eco-friendly cars is the environmental factor .
The need to reduce pollution levels plays a very important role in the development of eco-friendly cars .
In the past decade , people have been becoming more conscious of the damage that we have been inflicting on the earth .
As mentioned , the Inconvenient Truth has shown that there is a direct link between carbon emissions and the rising temperatures of the earth .
As carbon dioxide " stocks up " in the atmosphere over the years , it traps the sun 's heat , thus causing global warming which eventually leads to various climate changes .
One of the first things we can do to help conserve the environment is to switch from gasoline cars to eco-friendly cars .
As awareness of the effects of climate changes grows , people realize that it is their social responsibility to try to undo the damage to the environment to the best of their ability .
Hence , more people are seeking greener alternatives .
Even British Prime Minister , Gordon Brown , has urged that all cars in Britain should be green by 2020 .
In conclusion , the creation of eco-friendly cars are shaped by the factors mentioned above and I believe that not only is this creation one of a kind , but also that it is here to stay and that it is one of the key creations for the future generations to further develop .
Amidst the rapid economic development of the 21st century , the demand for energy is increasing .
However , the Earth can only provide us limited energy .
We can not increase the amount of fossil fuel .
.
Hence , the use of renewable energy is very important in our planet 's future development .
There are many alternative sources of energy that can be used and applied in our life , such as solar energy , light energy , wind energy , water power and so on .
Not only do all these alternative sources of energy help help reduce our dependence on non-renewable energy sources , but but the power generation processes for renewable energy are also environmentally friendlier .
Currently , since people realised the features of environmental protection and the economic efficiency of solar energy , the use of solar energy has been made use of more and it has become widespread in everyday life .
Energy from the sun 's rays is known to be very environmentally friendly as it is a clean form of energy .
only a solar collector and solar panels are needed to convert energy into electricity .
.
In return , but this also means there is no need to maintain the heaters .
However , solar energy is available in the evening , so that energy storage is an important issue in providing a continuous supply of energy .
In order to keep providing heating , an efficient method to store solar energy is by using heat-of-fusion units which use chemicals to change water to a solid form .
, except that the liquid absorbs the sun 's rays and then the chemicals convert the liquid to a solid so it traps the energy .
The world in the 21st century is faced with a severe problem of global energy shortage .
Industries require resources such as electricity , oil and petroleum for various outputs .
However , the rate of energy consumption by humans is much higher than what nature is able to produce .
Therefore , the last decade has witnessed increasing energy prices due to an insufficient supply of energy .
In response to energy shortage , engineers are designing more efficient products and systems .
Among the solutions such as and recycling natural resources , finding alterative resources seems to be the best solution to providing a sustainable supply of energy for various industries .
Natural movements such as the tide , the wind and the waves can all be used for generating power .
solar technology , which converts radiant light from the sun into heat , can also be applied to many industries .
The International Energy Agency reports that 2.1 % of all energy and 15 % of all electricity were provided worldwide by nuclear power in the year 2005 ( Key World Energy Statistics , 2007 ) .
This shows that nuclear power may gradually replace traditional oil and petroleum .
Although it seems very optimistic that many potential alternative energy resources can be found , there are , in fact , other economic and social constraints faced by engineers .
First of all , the costs of new energies such as solar electricity are much higher compared with traditional ones .
For instance , in the process of consuming hydrogen fuel , greenhouse gases will be generated , which may contribute to global warming .
Third , natural energy resources such as wind energy and wave power can only be used in large countries with sufficient land and water ; thus , small countries may encounter energy dependence on external resources and be forced to pay much more for energy .
To further improve the usage of alternative energies requires more efforts by engineers .
In addition , zero carbon technology should be encouraged in response to the concerns of climate change .
To conclude , engineering design processes can be applied to help solve the current problem of global energy shortage .
If engineers are capable of introducing environmentally friendly energies at reasonable cost and sufficient quality , we can expect a future balance between energy consumption and energy supply .
Technologies are usually developed to cater to certain needs of people , whether to provide better methods of doing things or to develop tools that facilitate working and living .
This also applies to virtual technology , which was developed within a specific social and technological context and which evolved to meet increasing needs in a changing environment .
Virtual technology was first developed to address the need for extensive communications .
The excitement brought by modern technologies increased the demand for more extensive interactions , not only with friends but also with strangers .
At the same time , new technologies also raised the issue of privacy .
Thus , it was not surprising to observe an increasing need for a convenient and cost effective platform where a large group of people are able to communicate , transcending geographic barriers , while retaining a certain level of independence and privacy at the same time .
To address such increasing social needs , the concept of a virtual world was .
Virtual technology was first designed with a series of unique properties to address the observed social needs by engaging a large user population .
This made interactions among a great number of users possible .
The user-friendly operation platform designed made the virtual world more accepted by the public and the simplified navigation process also made virtual technology more accessible to IT laymen .
In addition , with the establishment of facilities and the popularization of computers , virtual technology became more and more accessible and engaged increasing numbers of people .
The low cost of virtual technology , as compared with that of other types of communications such as the telephone , also attracted numerous users .
However , as the social environment changes , the initial virtual technology developed has become insufficient to meet increased social needs .
Virtual technology has hence been refined to meet the evolving needs .
Factors such as the business environment , changing educational styles and new military demands have shaped the development of virtual technology and solutions making use of virtual technology have been designed designed to address each specific need .
The development of virtual technology has been largely influenced by the world 's booming economies since the start of the 21st century .
New technologies have made people realize the underlying economic opportunities beyond geographic barriers and national boundaries .
People have been looking for more convenient and cost effective methods for transactions and business cooperation .
Catering to this need , a series of solutions have been developed based on virtual technology .
One of them is e-commerce websites where virtual interfaces enable convenient and efficient transactions of goods and services .
Another example is E-conferencing which allows a staff to attend meetings even while away on business trips and which has made business processes much more efficient .
This especially applies to places where educational resources are limited due to geographic barriers .
E-learning has provided an alternative way to attend lessons conducted by teachers in classrooms .
Another example of virtual technology being developed to meet educational needs is business simulation games where the real business environment is simulated and students can learn from .
Such business simulation games have been largely used as innovative learning tools in various business all over the world .
Apart from the demands from business and education , other factors have also shaped the development of virtual technology and solutions have been designed to meet these needs .
An example is virtual training devices used by the U.S. army .
To sum up , virtual technology , like other types of technologies , was socially and which has evolved to meet the changing needs of the society .
Thus , the development of virtual technology has been shaped by social factors such as the business environment , educational needs and military demands .
Meanwhile , the level of development of science and technology is an important symbol of a country 's strength .
However , problems inevitably arise and affect the process of innovation due to improper strategies or methods .
, there are two major problems in China .
One is that some engineering designs do not meet the needs of the market .
In other words , these designs are produced without adequate market survey , so they turn out to be unwelcomed by the public .
Though the designs are products of fantastic conception , they become useless like rubbish once booted out of the market .
After China adopted the policy of reform and opening-up , the Chinese government has long been encouraging people to make varieties of innovations .
Nevertheless , it does not mean that every design can be turned into a product .
The key is still the needs of the market .
In addition , among all applicants of patents , .
An individual has an obvious disadvantage compared with a team , and that is to say an individual can not handle everything well at the same time .
Without market survey and access to , it is inadvisable to make designs blindly by divorcing oneself from reality .
No amount of such designs would be useful .
The second problem that hampers engineering design processes is the patent policy .
China has long been a great country of patents , but the commercial success of these patents is quite rare .
Most Chinese patents are " Appearance Patents " , not " Innovation Patents " .
Appearance patents are a rather tough issue and among the patent infringement cases in China , more than 90 % belong to this kind .
appearance patent applications do not need to be censored .
As long as the application documents meet the required format , the patent will be approved .
The enormous number of applications for patents have caused large numbers of patent infringement cases .
" Now patent disputes have become the most serious obstacle in the development of some companies .
Conditions in developed countries may be different .
For example , in America , all patents must be censored so the cases of patent infringement are fewer than China .
Normally patent infringement lawsuits can be settled out of court due to the high cost and complicated procedures .
While in China , with the simple procedures and low cost , patent infringement lawsuits have even become a tool for unfair competition between companies .
The Chinese government is now paying attention to reforming the patent law and the new law will be put into practice in October .
In conclusion , China is sparing no efforts to solve problems in order to make innovations real intellectual products .
Every country will encounter problems in its development .
As a developing country , China is now facing problems in many fields .
The two problems are the education system and public policy on industry .
The problems affect engineering design in two aspects , independent innovation and engineering application .
First , the education system in China is a problem for innovation .
It is accepted that Chinese students are good at science .
They have a solid foundation for math and physics and they can solve complex and difficult problems quickly .
China 's education is a typical exam-oriented education .
Now , this situation has become a problem for the nation because the present generation lacks creativity and innovation .
In China 's education system , students are only required to receive knowledge and do drill exercises to consolidate their knowledge but they neglect to explore the knowledge further .
Chinese students are taught to remember many formulas and rather than ask questions .
Having undergone this mode of education for a long time , people 's thinking is limited and rigid .
The president of the Chinese University of Science and Technology pointed that students ' lack of innovation would become the bottleneck of development of China in the future ) .
In addition , there are still many inadequacies in the policies regarding science and industry .
In China , economic policies are very flexible but policies on developing the scientific industry are strict .
For example , the investment and attention that the nation puts on technology research and engineering are deficient ( Xin , 2005 ) .
which needs much support to .
However , the policy of engineering and industry can not meet these needs .
The state only invests in specialized research institutes .
In the actual production and application of new inventions , the support from the government is not nearly enough .
These two problems affect engineering design and innovation in China .
First , because of the mode of education , most engineers and scientists are relatively weak in creativity .
This directly affects the process of innovative engineering design especially in .
In the technological age , since independent innovation is very important to a nation 's development , the society needs people with innovative talent .
If engineers do not come up with new ideas , they can not find the best solution for different problems .
Moreover , the policy on science and engineering also affects the process of engineering application . Due to insufficient investment in research and engineering practice .
Many theories can not be applied .
As a result , the field of engineering design is slow in progress and there are still a lot of complex problems left unsolved .
In conclusion , the structure of China 's education and China 's policies on engineering and industry are two significant problems which hamper innovative engineering design processes in China .
If engineers lack creativity and innovation , it would be difficult for them to and make improvements .
Although China is expected by a lot of people and countries to prosper , there are still problems that hamper its development .
This article will focus on two major problems that hamper the innovational process of engineering in China and their impact on a particular stage of the process .
China 's design and innovation industry is mostly at the lower end of the world production chain , which means that production in China is energy-consuming , labour-intensive , but not very profitable .
Although China devotes many resources to production , the added value for innovation is low .
Out of 10 dollars made , this factory only has 1 dollar , while the Japanese company gets 9 .
The reason why this factory gets so little is that the design belongs to the Japanese company .
In reality , there are thousands of such factories in China , which reflects China 's low-end industrial structure .
As a consequence of its low-end production which gains profit from mass production and resource consumption , Chinese companies mainly focus on lowering cost , rather than creating innovative ideas .
Therefore , very little money is devoted to the design process for innovation and these companies only reproduce this low-end production circle .
In addition to China 's low-end industrial structure , the bad state of intellectual property protection also hampers the engineering innovational process .
in China , intellectual property rights are not well-protected .
People can find pirated versions of software in most cities .
There are some products which directly copy designs of foreign companies .
Due to certain reasons , this situation is not expected to improve substantially in the near future .
Therefore , innovation is discouraged because of lack of protection for intellectual property in society .
To sum up , China 's low-end industrial structure and bad state of intellectual property protection are the two major problems that hamper the engineering design process in China .
the low-end production pattern makes companies focus on cutting cost , rather than making innovation , while lack of protection for innovation makes people unwilling to generate new ideas .
If China tries to promote the engineering design process for innovation , these are the two problems it should tackle .
On September 4th , 2009 , a piece of startling news quickly spread all over the world .
After several years ' effort , magnetic monopoles were detected by researchers from the Helmholtz- Zentrum Berlin fur Materialien und Energie , in cooperation with colleagues from Dresden , St. Andrews , La Plata and Oxford ( Magnetic Monopoles Detected In A Real Magnet For The First Time , 2009 ) .
Obviously , the discovery of magnetic monopole indicated a great progress in the field of physics .
People may think about what led to the success of the discovery of magnetic monopoles .
In this case , the discovery of magnetic monopoles was most likely to have been brought about by advanced technologies .
However , social determinism , which can be defined as technology being boosted by social factors , is also an important factor in the development of technologies .
To explain further , social determinism can be further categorized into several important factors , such as economic , military , and government .
Nowadays , it is common to see a person carry a laptop everywhere , which was unimaginable thirty years ago .
The appearance of the laptop was due to demands from workers in companies .
In the old days , there was no laptop , only desktop that workers had to share to do their work , causing great inconvenience .
In order to solve this problem , a person called Mizoguchi in Toshiba Company came up with the idea of inventing the laptop ( Rogers , 2003 ) .
With the help of engineers , he finally invented the laptop that we currently use , and undoubtedly , his achievement became a great success in computer marketing .
Until now , the laptop is still a necessary tool in people 's daily life .
One of the reasons for its success was that laptop greatly catered to people 's needs .
Thus , after briefly discussing the development of the laptop , we can conclude that the appearance of this marvelous invention was initially driven by the demands of the people , and then its development was supported by technologies .
For many years , people have always been trying to develop technological innovations which are environmentally friendly .
Thus , , electric cars were invented .
Instead of using gasoline , electric cars used only battery power , which no longer caused air pollution and reduced the cost as well ( Rogers , 2003 ) .
However , because electric cars could not travel far distances , and it was not convenient to get their batteries charged , electric cars finally lost out in the market , due to its limited usefulness .
Nevertheless , electric cars are still regarded as a great trial innovation which needs further technology support to make improvement .
From the examples above , we can conclude that generally , the development of technology is determined by both technological factors as well as social factors .
More precisely , the appearance of innovation is initially motivated by social determinism , and then it needs technological support in the process of development .
Last but not the least , any technology must be designed well using advanced technology skills , otherwise it will most likely lose out in the market .
This is undoubtedly true because inventions throughout history have greatly improved the quality of people 's lives , and people 's endless desires have stimulated development of new technologies .
In the 21st century , new desires , as well as new problems have emerged , such as environmental pollution , bionics , exploration of outer-space and so on .
Among all of these needs , the most urgent and necessary technologies should be the ones that deal with the effect of global warming .
Among the possible solutions to global warming , the technology that should be developed is solar cars , because it could not only effectively reduce the emission of greenhouse gases , but could also take advantage of natural resources .
It is stated that a significant part of carbon dioxide emission is due to burning of fossil fuels , such as gasoline and natural gases .
1 ) Thus , continuing to use a large number of traditional cars would destroy the environment at a shocking rate .
Moreover , solar cars take advantage of solar energy which is easily available and cheap .
In this way , people no longer have to worry about exhaust of gasoline resources .
Besides , using solar energy actually costs nothing , which ensures that solar cars could be affordable in the long run .
However , solar cars are still not popular in the market due to high cost of production and low feasibility .
it is not easy to lower the price of solar cars since currently the materials used to make solar cars are high-tech aero-materials which are quite expensive .
Therefore , in order to lower their cost of production , development of new materials is crucial .
Besides , the current capacity of solar battery is not enough to allow long-distance driving .
Though a newly developed solar battery can support hundreds of miles of driving , it requires a rather critical weather extremely sunny days .
In conclusion , replacing traditional cars by solar cars can effectively control the deterioration of global warming , but further improvements are needed to widely popularize the use of these cars .
" ( " Air pollution causes early death , " 2005 ) . Many people may not think much about air pollution because they can hardly feel the effects of it .
However , results have proven otherwise .
This is the reason why better air quality is a human need that should be given priority .
Air pollution is the main reason why the world is suffering from bad air quality thus we should look at ways to cut down air pollutant emission .
There are some current solutions available such as primary regulations , control devices and increased fuel efficiency .
Hence , we should look at other alternatives like engineering design processes that might provide a solution .
Engineering design processes such as improving battery technology for automobiles , and designing better control devices are possible solutions .
Health issues caused by air pollution not only affect the individual but also the world economy because those who are affected will not be able to work .
In order to solve the problem of air pollution , we need to improve the current battery technology and come up with better control devices .
Improving the current battery technology is one of the engineering design process that can solve air pollution .
A recent report from Toronto Public Health ( 2007 ) states that related air pollution contributes to about 440 premature deaths and 1,700 hospitalizations per year in Toronto .
However , gasoline vehicles are still more in demand as compared to non-gas emission vehicles , electric vehicles .
The reasons are ; the short lifespan of the battery its relatively more costly price .
" By improving battery technology to meet these shortcomings , the world may be willing to switch to electric cars , the more environmental-friendly choice .
Besides improving the current battery technology , designing better control devices will be another engineering solution to industrial needs .
Air pollutants from industrial sources made up to more than half of man-made emissions .
For scrubbers , there are external and system parameters that affect efficiency .
Thus , they can not maximise their capabilities .
However , coming up with scrubbers and nitrogen oxide control devices that are more costly but control efficient will definitely reduce a significant amount of pollutant emission .
In conclusion , even though there are many available solutions to air pollution , the world is still suffering from bad air quality leading to many health problems .
In the article , " The Generation of Innovations " , , Rogers ( 2003 ) stressed that the engineering design process for innovation includes " problem recognition , research , development , commercialization , diffusion and consequences ( p. ? ) " .
For my home country , China , although its design process for innovation has improved a lot , there still remain several factors which hamper significantly the innovation process .
Based on this observation , this essay will focus on two factors and explain their corresponding effects on certain design stages .
According to " Wikipedia " ( 2009 , para.1 ) , a state-owned enterprise is defined as " a legal entity created by a government to undertake commercial activities on behalf of an owner government , and are usually considered to be an element or part of the state " .
Employees of state-owned enterprises do n't have to worry financial matters and .
Due to political interference in stated-owned enterprises , state-owned enterprises and other type of enterprises do not compete against each other on an equal basis .
Firstly , the directors and managers of the state-owned enterprises exploit their position and power in the company to advance their own private interests .
Thus , the money which goes into operation is largely reduced .
Furthermore , the motivation for most employees working in state-owned enterprises is to pursue high salaries and excellent welfare .
As a consequence , most managers and employees have no sense of professional dedication and responsibility .
They are lazy and not interested in discovery .
Even if employees discover some good ideas by chance , they may not want to put some effort into doing research and converting the ideas into production .
Thus , the above two impacts will affect the design stage , the especially stage .
State-owned enterprises which play important roles in controlling and leading other types of enterprises in China will hamper China 's design process for innovation .
Apart from the loopholes in the system of state-owned enterprises , financial problems among China 's private companies also hamper the innovation process .
They have to prepare for competition and the possibilities of bankcruptcy .
One is undesirable production .
Since most high quality and accurate equipment is very expensive , some private companies can not afford it .
Poor equipment in private companies may lead to much uncertainty in the design stage .
This could further lead to undesirable production .
In addition , due to economic problems , private companies may not be able to hire people with high education and rich experience .
Loopholes in the system of state-owned enterprises and the economic problems of private companies are the two main causes .
If these two factors are improved , the whole design process for innovation in China will be enhanced significantly .
It is widely believed that there is no strong connection between technology innovation and examinations based on MCQs .
However , there still is .
.
Comparing two typical examples of innovation , penicillin and vaccine , we see some similarities as well as differences in three main areas : progress of research , financial inputs and overall impact .
With the discovery of penicillin , the technology was a huge serendipitous observation .
Upon investigation , the cause turned out to be the first antibiotic to be discovered ,
By contrast , the discovery of vaccine involved a kind of technology based on a sequence of basic research , followed by applied research , leading to the the development of the vaccine
Here , all the processes were often set up from the beginning , though sometimes mistakes were found .
Many people are strongly convinced that conventional research is often more costly than a serendipitous one .
However , in some cases the opposite is true when an unexpected observation observation in requires financial support that of a scientific one .
The reason for this seemingly-contradictory surprise is that .
For instance , the discovery of penicillin still cost as much as the discovery of vaccine .
In short , it can be concluded that kind of research , whether conventional or serendipity , does say nothing about how much financial support it requires
Of course , it would be a mistake not to mention the importance of these two kinds of research in our society .
Both vaccine and penicillin can be considered a huge success because provide better preparation for diseases .
However , their impact on the whole society is still different because
In conclusion , both the discoveries of vaccine and penicillin are regarded as meaningful improvements in the field of medicine .
However , the way these innovations were produced or generated , the amount of support for them and their overall impact were slightly different , resulting from the essence of research involved : conventional or serendipitous
In 2005 , the Hisense Company solved the problem with Core Technology which used to be a concern of the color TV industry of China .
China , the first to produce TV , can now produce 75 million color TVs with homemade chips
( Hisense Achieves Significant Breakthrough for Core Technology through Independent Innovation , 2005 ) . In order to acknowledge the Hisense Group 's significant achievement and encourage more Chinese innovation , the chairman of Hisense Company was chosen as the economic figure of the year 2005 .
However , many companies in China are still plagued by a lack of innovation and many enterprises are merely waiting for revolutionary innovation to come their way .
This paper will identify two main problems which hamper engineering design processes for innovation and explain their respective impact on certain stages of these processes .
Low technological standard is one of the significant factors which hamper engineering design processes .
This problem refers to " immature technologies , mismatch between new technology and production capacity , lack of technical personnel or brain drain " .
( Environmental Innovation in China , 2008 ) . Among all these , brain drain is the root of the problem .
In China , some of the graduate students from design schools may go overseas to seek more professional training while some of them change their profession since they do not have much opportunity to develop their talents .
For those who manage to enter the design industry and start innovative work , their exposure to advanced technology is limited
( Mootee , 2009 ) . Due to these reasons , some Chinese entrepreneurs do not pay much attention to innovation but concentrate more on copying and modifying western technology instead of investing on innovation .
This problem curbs the development of engineering design processes at the start .
Therefore , most Chinese entrepreneurs focus on short-run products and expect instant profit .
Another problem hampering engineering design processes is that proprietary intellectual property is not highly valued in China .
Inventors of decoded products fail to benefit from them .
Since their Intellectual Property Rights are not protected , people are discourage from engaging themselves in the design processes .
Recently , the Ministry of Science and Technology of the People 's Republic of China announced that Intellectual Property Rights are the key to the development of enterprises
( Cabinet Approves Intellectual Property Rights Guidelines , 2008 ) . Related regulations and laws were also issued and implemented to protect the rights of inventors .
The government believes that this will improve the engineering design processes for innovation in the near future .
To sum up , two main problems hamper engineering design processes , namely low technological standards and intellectual property rights .
In order to improve its engineering design processes and increase its people 's passion for innovation , China needs to solve these problems .
It may appear as a high-tech term but , in fact , it has been put into use in various areas : radiometric dating , food irradiation , x-ray and chemotherapy in medicine and so on .
Since nuclear weapons may result in mass destruction , policymakers of countries all over the world prohibit research of nuclear technology 's application in military aspect and a non-proliferation treaty has been in place since 1968 ( International Atomic Energy Agency , 1970 ) .
This act hinders further work on nuclear technology since it restricts the enrichment of uranium .
Thus , due to nuclear technology 's special application in military work and the complex international situation , it may be difficult for some countries to master nuclear technology resulting in what is described as proliferation resistance ( International Atomic Energy Agency , 2004 ) .
Other than this international regulation , environmental concern is also an important determining factor in shaping nuclear technological innovation .
The notorious Chernobyl accident which caused 30 immediate deaths and affected an area within a 30-kilometer radius also reminds us of nuclear technology 's potential for causing disasters ( World nuclear association , 2009 ) .
Hence , environmental factors also contribute to the difficulties in nuclear technology 's popularization . Many rules regarding safety matters in nuclear technology application have been ratified after the Chernobyl accident .
Since uranium reserves are difficult to find through present technologies , the cost of applying uranium technology as energy source is relatively high compared with gasoline and natural gas ( Du & Parsons , 2009 ) .
Besides , it also costs a large amount of money to dispense with spent fuel and radioactive waste .
According to a report on energy solutions , designing , building of a nuclear plant and " cleaning up the plant after its operating license expires " will cost as much as 2.5 to 3 billion US dollars ( Maryland pirg , n.d. , para 3 ) .
Nuclear technology 's military uses make international cooperation in this technology extremely difficult ; the radioactive character of this technology causes a lot of environmental issues and its cost in some applications is still high .
However , with increasing industrial demands , oil reserves are at critical levels , thus it is highly likely that we will have to resort to nuclear technology solutions in the near future .
In an era where the scale of our industrial system is growing larger and larger , the consumption of resources becomes an incredible burden on the environment and people start to suffer the consequences . For the destruction and pollution we have done to the environment , a series of social issues concerning engineering and environment have been raised .
Among them is the paradox between the decreasing natural resource deposits and people 's increasing energy consumption .
according to Khandani ( 2005 ) , engineering design of products and systems may provide us a way to solve the problem .
In this essay , how engineering design processes can cope with the energy crisis will be discussed in terms of gathering pertinent information and analysis and selecting an optimized solution .
Gathering pertinent information is a crucial stage in engineering design processes ; however , it is neglected quite often .
As stated by Khandani ( 2005 ) , collecting enough information before finding solutions will reward us with great benefits .
Because designing a new industrial system or product which works more efficiently with less energy consumption is a complicated process , sufficient analysis of information is rhus needed .
Only by doing this can we be clear what the status quo of energy consumption is and whether a proposal is applicable .
Suppose an engineering designing group is working on a project that should come out with a new energy-saving system in the architecture .
Besides gathering information , making a wise selection among all the options is yet another must-do in engineering design processes .
When going through this process , various factors will be considered such as function , ergonomics , liability and so on ( Khandani , 2005 ) .
Therefore , the selected proposal can hopefully be expected to be environmentally friendly , less energy consuming and safe for use at the same time .
In a sentence , when dealing with energy crisis , doing analysis and selecting the best solution are of great importance .
In conclusion , in order to deal with the energy crisis and work out a solution that is applicable , we need to do well in every step in engineering design processes .
Starting design without adequate information is risking the whole project and choosing a solution carelessly is rather a waste of all the efforts may have put into the project .
Therefore , only a carefully and wisely done engineering design can meet the needs of reducing energy consumption while being environmentally friendly at the same time .
Simply by scanning the item you buy , the cashier can tell its price .
This shows the power of bar codes .
Using bar codes , those black lines with numbers , is a " method of automatic identification and data collection " ( Bellis , n.d. , para 1 ) .
Through decades of development , the bar code has been shaped by social factors to some extent .
The users , especially retailers and product manufacturers , play important roles in improving the bar code .
First and foremost , the bar code emerged and developed as the times required .
The urgent demand of retailers to increase efficiency and accuracy in operation predicted its emergence .
According to Seideman ( n.d. ) , as early as 1890 people realised their need and invented punch cards which played like the bar code .
However , the first application area of the bar code was not the supermarket or grocery but railroads .
Unfortunately , the implementation of the bar code in the railroad industry failed because it did not fit the industry perfectly and its functions were not completely utilized .
On the other hand , retailers then were just in need of a system like the bar code .
In 1966 , a grocery industry meeting regarding implementation of the bar code was held by RCA ( Seideman , n.d. ) .
Today , the demands of users are still shaping the bar code , expanding it to more application fields like libraries and the postal industry .
Another factor that affects the bar code 's development is economic concerns .
As the bar code is designed to store information of products , all products have to be labelled .
Besides , users have to buy devices that read bar codes as well .
So economic cost became a big concern .
Due to this reason , the bar code was not broadly implemented as soon as it was invented .
These concerns pushed the technology forward , thus eventually came the bar code we use nowadays .
Having settled the economic concerns of users , the bar code won users ' hearts quickly .
Since its first read in 1974 , the bar code has been adopted for 35 years ( Shih , 2009 ) .
The economic factors have been shaping the bar code and making it survive even in the midst of the great competitor RFID ( Shih , 2009 ) .
In addition to demands and economic concerns , the wide range of users helps to improve the bar code .
It promotes the bar code to be developed into an internationally recognized and commonly readable system .
It is clear that globalization is inevitable which means the bar code has to adjust itself to meet it .
Apparently , a standard system is needed ; otherwise it will be difficult to trade .
The bar code has been standardised since 1970s and it is being improved accordingly ( Seideman , n.d. ) .
Besides globalization , the various kinds of users shape it to be an easily used technology .
To sum up , the bar code is an important technology .
Because of users ' demands , financial capability of users and wide range of users , it has been shaped to an innovation which is globally recognized and essential to the world .
The shortage of natural resources means that all raw materials required for engineering design process for innovations would have to come from imports .
This by itself poses problems such as greater costs incurred for innovations , shipment fees , as well as a delay the design process .
The higher cost makes it expensive for engineering designing processes . Hence groups that do not have funding or sufficient funding will be held back .
This is because the designing process usually involves a lot of trial and error , using various materials for different parts of the innovation , in order to optimize the best working conditions for the item of innovation .
Professor Seah ( 2009 ) mentioned that for Formula Society of Automotive Engineers ( FSAE ) their first formula race car took 2 years instead of 1 to be produced , partly because of a lack of raw materials and funding .
The long shipping time and greater cost due to importing of raw materials delayed the engineering design process as they only had a plan of the race car but no chance to physically fabricate the parts and build the car , while the raw materials were still on their way to Singapore Another problem which could greatly affect the engineering process for designing is a lack of funding .
The designing process requires a large amount of raw materials for repeated fabrications of each part with different materials in order to obtain the most suitable material to optimize the function of the product of innovation .
Even for the same kind of material , it might have to be used several times as the part fabricated is not necessarily always in the expected condition when it is first made , resulting in a wastage and hence greater consumption of raw materials and therefore a greater cost incurred in the designing process .
Without funding , this step of designing would be impossible especially if the raw materials are required in large quantities .
Water supply has always been a key issue for consideration by the Singapore government .
This dependence on neighboring countries for water creates a need for Singapore to become more self-reliant
Hence when the idea of water desalination first came out , it was greatly funded by Singapore government for further improvements in Singapore .
