But there still existed a lot of discoveries that were made as a serendipitous result of normal research which always had some interesting stories behind them .
Although these two types of discoveries could both influence society , there are two interesting differences between them in the process .
.
All the processes in the research are to serve the purpose .
In contrast , there is always no specific need for the serendipitous discovery and the research which makes the discovery is usually for other purposes , and the serendipitous discovery is usually due to unexpected result of a normal research .
3M Company wanted to find a kind of super glue but unexpectedly found this kind of glue that was not strong but could be used several times .
this unexpected result led to the successful production of a new kind of notes which is now the well known Post-it .
For normal discovery , this is not a big problem because the discovery is to serve a specific purpose .
But for serendipitous discovery , as the discovery is , will know the potential use of it after the discovery is made .
There is even the possibility that nobody will notice it .
So it is much harder to put it to use .
But fortunately , we had very smart and careful people who were able to find them and find a way to use them .
But he only invented a kind of material which had brighter luster than other materials but was not strong enough .
But later he thought why not make this beautiful material into a set ?
