Anyway both of them have made a great contribution to the human society and I there will be more discoveries being made , no matter which type they are .
Living in a small country like Singapore has various limitations is more challenging for her to compete with larger nations .
A majority of these limitations would increase the cost of the innovation and hence require careful design .
One of these problems includes the city-state 's lack of land space which would affect the structural design of the innovation particularly if it was on a large scale .
This issue particularly affects innovations that are on a larger scale , as large costs will be incurred in the construction of their foundations .
This increase in cost will hence affect the market value and affect the economic analysis stage of the design process .
Take for example the housing in Singapore , which comprises mainly Housing Development Board [ HDB ] flats .
In view of the collapse of Nicoll highway back in April 2004 , HDB has put up very strict requirements for the piling process and the materials used , like grade 30 concrete should be used in piling .
Similarly , the steel structure that forms the backbone of the buildings require a minimum of 3mm steel gauge .
Contrary to its limited land area as discussed earlier , it houses more than 4 million people .
innovations thus have to consider its design rather seriously given the circumstances .
All these will seriously affect the functionality analysis stage of the design process , as more time and consideration will have to be channeled into this stage .
One example of a properly located and well-designed amenity would be the Mass Rail Transit [ MRT ] stations .
Some stations are connected to shopping malls while others to bus interchanges , thereby making transport in Singapore relatively convenient .
In addition , some of these stations like City Hall and Dhoby Ghaut station , not only play the role of an important hub in Singapore 's transport system , but also an internal shopping center within itself .
City- link , which is connected to city hall station , is an underground network of shops that is linked to other larger shopping facilities .
Such an example shows how proper planning of the amenities to the success of the application .
Compare and contrast about guncotton and explosives
Considering new explosives , in order to find new explosives ,Nobel spent nearly all his time doing experiments in his library .
However , some technology was invented from a serendipitous discovery .
Guncotton was invented by Schoenbein by chance .
The difference between these two inventions is the ideas about how to invent them emerged in different ways .
Nobel a very hardworking and brave man .
He used nearly all his time to work for new explosive and his younger brother died in a failed experiment .At the same time his brother 's death had an unbalancing effect on his father .
His father died right after his younger brother ( Nils .
The story about how Schoenbein invented guncotton is quite an interesting story .
According to Yang ( 2007 ) , " when Schoenbein was doing experiments , he overthrew a bottle of chemical solution , and the solution flowed on the table . Schoenbein found nothing but his wife 's apron to clean the table .
After he had finished cleaning he thought that his wife will blame him after she saw what he had done .
When he walked near the stove the apron burned without any smoke and left ashes .
" Nobel could invent the explosive successfully because of his diligence and the attitude towards science
Schoenbein came up with his idea accidentally and finally made a great invention for the word .
First of all they are both invented by prudent chemists .
If Noble was not a prudent person and did not do his experiments and observe the phenomenon though he is hardworking he may never have invented the new explosive successfully .
But without the prudential attitude towards science he may have missed his good luck and did not go on finding how can this phenomenon occur .
Secondly these two technologies both made great contributions to the industry and military affairs .
As both of them are explosives people use them to exploit mines , tear down great buildings and provide a high temperature for many chemical experiments .
Engineers use them to make all kinds of weapons .
Technology , whether it was developed via research or resulted from a serendipitous experiment scientist 's greatest contribution to the world
