In truth , the hospital would not be allowed to renovate unless it discarded ten beds
As Michael Keane ( 2007 ) has noted , the common assumption existing long among the Chinese was that productivity directly equals material production .
In the current stage , political environment and people 's mindset are two of the problems that may hamper engineering design process for innovation .
While can be classified as a kind of special glue , the history of post-it notes and super glue seems rather different .
post-it notes resulted from a serendipitous discovery , while the super glue was developed gradually via standard research process .
However , it turned out later that the serendipitous discovery actually had no real target in this stage , because the real use of post-it note seems totally different from what was expected at the beginning .
The next stage of research was to use the scientific method to fulfill the previous target .
So we can see that the super glue 's inventor successfully found what he needed while the post-it notes ' inventor created a strange glue that is low adhesive but re-adherable .
In this stage , the difference between the two kinds of discoveries turned to be that the serendipitous discovery 's inventor could not meet his initial needs like the normal inventor but accidently create a totally different product instead .
from the third stage onward , the post-it notes and the super glue finally shared the similarity .
One was low adhesive but re-adherable so it was used to make notes that can be attached to documents and other surfaces freely .
The other one was high adhesive and functioned quickly so it could be used to glue many materials quickly with great strength .
The inventors both found their usages and successfully made them more practical
So it is not surprising that the two products both become very popular among the consumers as soon as they come out .
Technological determinism means the belief that a technology causes changes in society ( Rogers , 2003 ) , while social determinism argues that technology is constructed by social factors .
One important technology which was shaped by a specific group of users is electric vehicles , which have been shaped by four different factors namely technical , economic , social , and political
Technical factor is one of the four elements that have determined the development of the electric vehicle .
Compared to the structure of a conventional automobile , the electric vehicle has a similar structure but different components .
The electric vehicle has a lighter weight as most of its parts are made of aluminium .
In addition , the electric vehicle is safe to drive as it is uses solely electricity , while most conventional vehicles require gasoline , which is inflammable .
On the other hand , the electric vehicle utilizes electrical energy from batteries , so the engine is relatively clean , emission-free and quiet .
However , there are fewer charging stations and the electric vehicle requires a long recharge time .
Economically , technology for electric vehicles have not widely met the need because less promotion was held and there was a mass production of gasoline type automobiles .
Furthermore , electric vehicles were not advertised in a precise manner .
Besides , declining cost in oil in the past encouraged people to buy gasoline cars .
At that point , there was a mass production of gasoline cars .
In the end , gasoline vehicles controlled the monopoly on automobiles in the market .
Compared to conventional vehicles that are available now , electric vehicles are socially determined by several reasons : limited range of electric vehicles , beliefs and values of the society today .
Despite several advantages , their interest in electric cars is fading .
They also feel that these cars are less attractive compared to conventional cars
In addition , political factors can affect how the sales of vehicles go , which include the government 's adherence to this technology .
People lose interest as the government is not supportive .
The government not only provides subsidies and incentives to users , who use gasoline cars , but also constructs and designs roads for conventional vehicles .
All in all , we can easily see from these examples that , many factors that specified by other group of users have led electric vehicles to a decline .
Nowadays , with the ever-accelerating technology , many inventions have come into being , and many new words have come with them as well .
It is the most widely used rat poison in the world !
Link then did research and found coumarin inside the sweet clover hay , which resulted in punctured cattle 's stomachs and internal bleeding .
This chemical enlightened Professor Link on applying them to killing rats .
Thus , the famous warfarin came into use !
It is a typical serendipity example , which in fact shares some common points with conventional research .
The first similarity is that at the first step , they both require scientists to make every effort to get the expected results .
The second similarity that I consider is luck .
Take Nobel 's invention of dynamite for example .
Without luck , he may have died during the explosion of the dynamite and would not shout that excitedly " I make it !
" Thus , luck is required in every successful experiment , let alone serendipity , which requires more luck to achieve another result to just meet a certain kind of people 's need coincidentally .
Although there are similarities , they differ from each other in several respects .
Do you know something about the invention of the microwave oven ?
At first , Spencer cooperated with the British to study microwaves in military use .
By accident , he found that the chocolate bars in his pocket melted when exposed to microwaves .
This phenomenon caused him to use an egg for experiment .
Then the microwave oven came into being !
To conclude , both serendipity and conventional research require luck and they are similar in their own first step , but the difference is that a serendipity finding is not on purpose and it sometimes results from an additional discovery through a research .
However , both of them are needed to make the scientific world a more magical and wonderful world !
Recent data indicate that well-known Xiaonei.com is the largest social networking site in China , open to the public , mainly university students .
free , Xiaonei.com stands out with 63.4 % share of the social networking site market ( Wang , 2008 ) .
In my humble opinion , its success is due to both social and economic factors .
On the social part , Xiaonei.com builds its success on the true networking environment it provides -- well-rounded functions and convenience in looking for friends and classmates .
As mentioned before , undergraduates are predominant among its of users .
Undergraduate students may probably feel secure and thus free to share diaries , pictures and updates with friends , which may not be the case in other sites in the virtual Internet world .
Furthermore , Xiaonei.com incorporates all kinds of functions such as the instant communication of MSN , online games and other applications like daily forecast of fortunes .
Instead , when you log in to Xiaonei.com , almost all the expected functions are available
Last but not least , users save time in looking for their friends and can simply get things done in a second as long as the information on the school and class is obtained .
In fact , many have been Xiaonei.com 's partners , believing that their advertisements can boost their reputation and influence .
The popularity and market size not only benefit Xiaonei.com on advertisements , but also earn Xiaonei.com a large amount of investment which in turn brings Xiaonei.com further .
On the strong basis of capital and reputation Xiaonei.com is reaching out to students beyond mainland China and the world .
To add on , network effect , an Economics jargon meaning that people are inclined to stay in the network unless their followers leave , also does help Xiaonei.com secure its market share .
In .
All in all , market share , obtained from the social factors , does and will secure the achievement of Xiaonei.com by profit from advertisements and advanced service and most importantly , investment .
The true identity of users of Xiaonei.com is indefinitely the outstanding social factor , which matches university students ' expectation to share their true lives in a secure way .
