First and foremost , the government should improve the facilities in the current agricultural system to satisfy the fundamental needs .
To be more accurate , in the developing countries , the government should make a good plan to build irrigation canals and banks based on the analysis of local climate and geography .
The government should provide stable surroundings for farmers to plant food .
Protecting plants from droughts and floods is necessary to have a good harvest .
Besides the infrastructure construction , another advisable method to increase production is to mechanize the agricultural system .
Armed with machinery , farmers can make the most of limited farmland and time .
In addition to the improvement of facilities in the current agricultural system , high-tech support also plays a crucial role in increasing food production .
It is effortless to come up with the idea that we can use biological engineering to change certain properties of plants .
The government should also make some regulations to urge experts to teach farmers how to farm scientifically .
Then a better harvest is obtained .
Having made a good plan to help farmers to produce more food , the government must use the food properly .
