Regardless of the fact that the technology has resulted from a long period of research or a serendipitous discovery , this technology must have been must have been made by a group or an individual who has already acquired certain knowledge .
Unclear pronoun reference are believed to have undergone many research and discussions .
According to Rogers ( 2003 ) , six main stages are involved in the involved in the research process , They are...ecognizing a problem , research , development , commercialization , diffusion and adoption and consequences .
This is not an easy process and it requires time and effort to deal with it .
Moreover , although the serendipitous idea may not result in desirable outcome , it benefits the world .
This antibiotic was the first drug that is effective against the syphilis and staphylococcus infections .
It successfully has successfully saved the people people who suffered from the diseases and given them happiness to have the chance to live again .
Similarly , the discovery of the laptop has benefited the individual , the society and the world .
It has saved the people whose surrounding space is small and compact , has brought a lot of convenience to society .
Nowadays laptops have combined many functions such as camera , microphone , wi-fi receiver and so on .
We do n't need to buy the devices and this will actually save a lot of space .
Every time Every time we we want to discuss assignments with friends , we ca n't bring along the conventional desktop desktop. .
With the invention of portable personal computer , we can now bring it along to wherever we like !
In spite of the benefits that both serendipitous discovery and research discovery have given us . , there actually exist differences between the two technologies .
The laptop is a product that resulted somebody generated the idea and planned the procedures to make it .
Therefore , it is a safe design for us to use .
However , we actually incur a higher risk of the side-effect when consuming the penicillin .
We only know that the penicillin can cure syphilis , but we will never know what diseases might be caused by consuming penicillin as there exist a lot of uncertainties .
In brief , the two products , the laptop and penicillin , are either generated through a long period of research or a serendipitous and they have both been made to meet the people 's requirements .
Although they may not be the best outcome to fulfil people 's needs people 's needs , they still lead the world in technological inventions technological innovation .
Topic : How an electronic dictionary is shaped by students ' needs and the specific factors that have shaped its innovation .
I have witnessed the development of the electronic dictronary .
From the huge one with the simplest function to today 's lovely and multi-functional one , electronic dictionaries have been refined again and again .
The development of electronic dictronary is shaped by the needs of students , who are the majority of their customers .
In the latter paragraphs , I will talk about how students ' needs determine the development of electronic dictronary .
The most obvious change is that the functions of electronic dictronary have greatly improved due to the change in students ' demand .
At the very beginning , the electronic dictionary could do nothing but look up words .
In comparision , nowadays electronic dictionaries are much more multi-functional .
For example , they can not only look up words in Chinese and English as the old ones did , but also many other languages languages like like Japanese and French as well .
And what they need to do is simply download programms and install them in the electronic dictronary .
Moreover , as students are not content with a boring study tool , an electronic today can act as good company during leisure time because it possesses the functions of an MP3/ MP4 player and even a PSP !
Another significant improvement is the appearance of the electronic dictronary .
Instead of the hand-hand-sized one , it is only the size of a lemon now and and much lighter much lighter .
As a direct result , it is convenient to carry and wins students ' favour .
As English is a complusary course to learn in China , the electronic dictronary has almost become a necessity to students .
Thus it is not simply a tool , but a personal belonging to represent their appetite to modernise modernise .
Last but not least , the price of electronic dictionaries is also influenced by students .
As students do not have jobs , they have to ask their parents for money .
In addition , the limitations of electronic dictionaries , such as the lack of access access to the the Internet , also determine that the price of electronic dictronary which can not be too high .
In conclusion , the electronic dictronary plays an important role in students ' study , and students in turn shape and decide the development of electronic dictronary in many aspects like price , appearance and function .
It can be seen that as technology develops , the electronic dictronary will be more and more helpful to students .
