However , for it to replace the gasoline vehicles will be an uphill task that requires a concerted effort from both the industry and the governments .
According to Rogers , E. M. ( 2003 ) , the development of an engineering design process consists of a total of six main stages : , needs/problems , research ( basic and applied ) , development , commercialization , diffusion and adoption and consequences .1 The whole design process of creating new products is tedious and will take a very long time to complete ; especially the stages on research and development. .
Due to the limited resources in Singapore , the commercialization stage may not be able to materialise .
Therefore , most of the development of engineering design processes are carried out in Singapore at the end of the development stage .
Examples of such projects are " NUS Eco-car''2 and " NUS Haptic Chair''.3
In Singapore , moving on to the commercialization stage of the design process is not easily achieved without going through tough brainstorming .
Thus , problems may arise and hinder the commercialization stage of the design process .
First of all , for the NUS eco-car innovation process , it is true that the development of eco-car is indeed environmentally friendly .
However , if the eco-car is to proceed to the commercialization stage in the engineering design process , the problem encountered by my home country is capital cost .
This is because most of the parts contributed to the assembly of the eco car are bought from overseas and these better grade materials can be rare and hard to acquire .
Furthermore , hiring skilled workers and buying machines to assemble the car are costly as well .
Hence , for the eco-car to be launched in Singapore during the commercialization stage of its design process , the production of car will significantly increase the retail price because of the high prices of raw materials in constructing the car .
The high retail price of car will significantly affect the decision of the committee to commercialize the product as consumer would not pay much for it .
On the other hand , for the NUS Haptic Chair innovation process , the researchers had successfully developed the chair for the convenience of deaf people in Singapore .
The problem that hampers the design process is the shortage of testers to test the product , for which according to the article3 there were not enough deaf children in Singapore to test this product .
Therefore , there will be no guarantee to the effectiveness of the design to see how the product can be utilized and the researcher will not be able to modify the chair for better performance .
In conclusion , capital cost and the shortage of human resources are two problems which will significantly hamper engineering design process innovation . This may result in the commercialization stage being unable to realise .
Based on E.M. Roger 's paper on " Generation of innovation " , a typical engineering design process for innovations can be broken down into 6 main stages . They are : identifying the needs of the market , designing the research process , developing the product , commercialising , diffusing and adopting and finally , examining the consequences .
Out of the 6 stages , I will elaborate on problems in the research and development stage using examples in Singapore .
In Singapore , the research sector is one of the most funded fields , besides education and defense .
With a population of only about 4 million , coupled with lack of natural resources , Singapore has no choice but to make the most of whatever resources that are available .
Hence , it is significant to develop the research sector in Singapore .
Some of common problems in the research sector are lack of skilled labour , time constraint and limited .
One example is the NUS eco-car project which was still at its research stage .
However , in NUS , the project is at student level only .
With additional guidance from experienced engineers , the eco- car could have been better designed and probably would stand a better chance of being marketed .
The lack of skilled labour in the project caused it to be at the research stage of the innovation process .
Hence , the development of the eco-car was not consumer friendly and it was unable to move into the commercialization stage .
Maybe it would be take a few more years before the eco-car has a potential to be marketed .
Sometimes , problems may also occur during the development stage of the innovation process. .
One example is the NUS FSAE race car. .
After all the research that have been done , through software rendering and such , the problems starts when one is trying to develop it .
After all , the simulation done on computers can not be compared to what the students have experienced .
The success of the design will be based on the yearly race competition held at international level .
To sum up , the lack of skilled labour and the inability to re-create computer simulation in real life are not the only 2 problems commonly faced in the engineering design process in Singapore .
However , these 2 problems are enough to cause the downfall and failure of the product when it is placed in the market .
Engineering design processes consists of five different stages starting with defining the problem , gathering pertinent information , generating multiple solutions , analyzing and selecting a solution and finally testing and implementing the solutions .
Fund is an important factor that determines whether the design process can be carried out .
To begin with the design process , there is a need to have a team of experts and researchers to spearhead the project which requires hiring cost .
Fund also plays an important role in the purchase of materials to manufacture the product .
Therefore , the purchase of materials can be quite costly as plenty of them will go to waste .
As a result , the lack of fund will hamper the progress of the design process because there will be no material to manufacture a physical product to test its usefulness .
The design process does not stop after the development of a final product a final product .
This is because the product may not be perfect , and minor yet important changes may need to be done to improve the product .
For example in the aeroplane design process , one needs to determine the material to be used as the body of the aircraft .
Without the knowledge of the characteristics of different materials , one will not be able to choose the best material , which must be strong yet light in weight , to be used .
Due to the fact that it was their first attempt , they realized that the lack of race car knowledge had hampered their design process , and this in turn had also led them to perform badly in the competition. .
However , the engineering faculty has since built up the race car knowledge after taking part in several annual competitions , and in the recent competition it came in 19th place .
In the case of lacking of funds , companies need to find sponsorships to fund the cost of their design processes .
However , knowledge is something that can not be achieved overnight .
Having past experiences and studies will be useful in gaining more knowledge .
As a living being , maintaining is of vital importance .
In fact , whether one can keep leading a high quality of life largely depends on a reliable energy supply .
To illustrate this simply , one current need of modern people is the demand for a consistent energy source .
Therefore , the engineering design process aims to invent a technological approach to meet people 's need .
After identifying the problem and listing all the possible solutions , it will figure out the best energy source and try to utilize it to supply energy .
After that , gradual improvements will be made to its practicality , and this will subsequently help to serve the public better .
It is known that we all live in a new era where every social activity or industrial activity we do is closely relevant to energy utilization .
Hence , the demand for effective energy supply is a major need of modern people .
Nowadays , the main energy source is fossil fuel which has a limited storage supply on earth .
In 10 years ' time , the supply of oil and gas will fail to meet people 's need .
) To avoid future energy crises from happening , engineers are expected to find a new energy source which is sustainable .
The next step is to consider all possible new energy supply sources and selecting the best one .
Their main advantage is that they are all renewable energy sources .
Among them , solar energy is the best choice because it is safer than nuclear energy and easier to obtain as compared to geothermal energy .
Hence , solar energy comes to our attention as an ideal energy source .
After that , engineering design process applies the engineering theorem and latest technology to practice , and this is equivalent to using solar energy effectively. .
The whole process is like installing a solar panel containing many tubes on the roof of the house where the panel can be exposed maximally to sunlight .
Then the bath water may be let to flow through the tubes and to absorb the heat collected by the tubes .
Through heat transfer from tube to the water , the bath water is heated .
The production cost of solar energy is higher than that of fossil fuel energy , which therefore impedes its popularity .
Hence , engineering designer should consider how to cut cost in future , in order to let solar energy be utilized more successfully .
In sum , the demand for energy supply is a current need that is closely relevant to people 's lives , as it is the basis for maintaining a high living standard .
Yet we still have to work on reducing its production cost .
Nowadays , people are more health conscious .
This can be seen when they are willing to spend hundreds to thousands of dollars on medical bills .
Doctors , drug researchers and biomedical engineers face the challenges to collaborate in this matter in order to come out with the best solution to address current health problems .
Engineers play an important role .
Engineers assist medical professionals such as doctors by designing medical devices such as the pace maker , defibrillator and ventilator which are often used in life threatening situations .
Their roles include handling technical difficulty of medical devices , giving advices to doctors and nurses , collaborating with clinical research personnel , liaising with hospital administrator and regulations agencies as well as ensuring a safe hospital environment . Maintaining a safe hospital environment would include tasks like the power cabling , performing maintenance and safety inspection .
One can see that engineers play the crucial role of delivering professional health service needed for a patient .
Many health problems can not be addressed without the help of medical devices
Engineers are faced with various challenges to design medical devices which are safe , efficient , accurate , serviceable , user friendly , manageable , durable and environmental compatible .
An example is the latest medical device called the IVDD machine ( Intervetebral Disc Decompression Therapy ) .
This idea is discovered when researchers realized that space travelers were relieved of lower back pain and their disc height were actually increased .
A design idea can be developed from various sources. .
Another challenge faced by design engineers is the availability of technology .
Technology is often the limiting factor when it comes to designing a sophisticated medical device .
An example of this is the electrosurgical device .
The Electrosurgical device was not invented until it was realized that very high frequency of current can actually burn a tissue when the contact point is relatively small .
This idea and discovery have led to the invention of the CUSA Excel System --- a device that performs bloodless tissue cutting which is used now in every hospital in Singapore .
The design can also come from the need and request of people .
A social need often has to be addressed by engineers .
For example , in this advanced and fast changing society , many working adults , especially women have found it extremely difficult to achieve a balance between their family and work .
The milk pump allows milk storage and feeding without the presence of the mother ; and this allows them to go to work without having to worry about breast-feeding their babies .
It is very interesting to see how engineering ideas can come about .
There are hundreds of ways from which an idea can originate .
A design is developed to improve older designs , ; or to address psychological problem in patients , such as their fear of going through surgical operation ; or to assist medical personnel such as doctors to deliver better health service .
Other challenges faced by engineers include patenting their designs , devices testing , performance benchmarking , training of medical personnel , custom modification of devices , law 's requirements , safety concerns , compatibility with other medical devices ,durability and usability .
The challenges faced are never ending for an engineer in their attempts to come out with state-of-the-art medical devices to be used currently and also in the future .
When you are enjoying ice-cream in a sweltering summer , do you know that you are enjoying a privilege reserved for rich people roughly 100 years ago ?
Then how does the refrigerator come into being ?
Some factors such as the demand of lead user , economic factors , and environmental concern actually play important roles in shaping the refrigerator into its shape today .
In the first place , the lead user of the refrigerator is the first and most important factor that drives the development of refrigerator .
Lead users can be defined as a group of people that have the greatest need for a potential invention .
According to Hippel ( year , cited in Rogers , 2003 ) , lead users play an important role in most of the innovation-designing process , because they usually have the needs of innovations that are " well ahead of the general market " .
In the case of the refrigerator , lead users can be regarded as the food businessmen in 20th century , mainly because most food would perish very quickly under normal temperature .
Since the lead user has such a great need of a product that could help them keep the food cool easily , the refrigerator was first commercially introduced to long distance food transportation in 1900s ( Bowden & Offer , 1994 ) .
Lead users therefore started the application of the refrigerator on business .
Besides the factor of lead users , economic factor also plays an important part in shaping the refrigerator .
For example , the use of the refrigerator has only become widespread after its price has dropped to a level that could be accepted by the norms .
Another evidence is the dominance of electric refrigerator in the development of refrigerators in general .
Before the release of the refrigerator into the market , there is an ideal substitute for the electric refrigerator . This is the gas refrigerator , which has a quieter operation and longer use duration ( year , cited in Roger , 2003 ) .
The reason why all of us now are using the " huming " electric refrigerator instead of the gas one is because corporations have decided that the electric refrigerator would bring them larger profit , and therefore they went all out to promote the electric refrigerator .
For example , one of the reasons why the refrigerator was not widely used by many common households before 1930s is because the refrigerator at that time was using a toxic gas system , which would destroy the environment and be unsafe for home use .
One of the most popular refrigerants for refrigerator , Tetrafluoroethane , has been banned by the governments in a lot of countries because of its ability to deplete the ozone layer .
The environmental concern therefore helps the refrigerator to develop in a more environmentally friendly direction .
Due to the number of words being limited this essay only scratches the surface of what leads to the invention and diffusion of the refrigerator , and picks out the three most obvious factors to discuss .
