With much credit to swift medical advancements , the average life span of a human being in America has shot up by 5 years in just a decade to 82 years today .
Such increase in longevity and the reduce in birth rates , will no doubt lead to an inevitable rise to the problems of aging , as there are fewer and fewer young people to support the rising number of elderly , both financially and/ socially .
Aging is a big issue , governments from all over the world are pushing forward policies and Research and Developments to stem its economical and social impacts on a country .
In Singapore , our government has recently implemented a policy known as Lift Improvement and Facilities Enhancement , which aims to improve the living conditions of single elderly or those who have been abandoned by their families .
The setting up of the senior citizens ' corner can also act as a platform for interaction among the elderly , especially when travelling out of their house is made easier . They would be more willing to engage in more social activities , thus becoming more receptive to happenings around them and learn to be more self reliant .
This current policy of facility upgrades is very comprehensive as it ensures convenience , security , entertainment and thus the social well-being of elderly .
, allows the elderly to enter the workforce and maintain a spot in the society .
But in the case of elderly employment in Singapore , they tend to be given menial jobs , due to their physical and mental handicap as compared to younger workers . these menial jobs are unattractive to the career-driven adults in Singapore are filled up by these older workers .
