Although some elderly who suffer gentle heart failure could still maintain a relatively normal life , those who suffer to a severe extent have their day-to-day activities affected .
However with R&D in the area of heart-related diseases , has led to the developments of new drugs and treatments to control and reduce the effects of heart failures in their everyday life .
Policies to upgrade housing in Singapore have improved the living conditions of the elderly , together with the setting up of the senior citizens ' corners I am convinced that the elderly can now participate more actively in the society and live off with a higher social well being .
Also , having the elderly joining the workforce can increase the total productivity and reduce the burden piled on family members .
Nonetheless , I am convinced that current research and developments policies do play an important role to help ease the arduous aging process .
The state has a certain responsibility to provide for the old .
To simply cut back funds on the grounds that the elderly can no longer yield any economic profits is an irresponsible act .
The old are worthy of every resources spent on them as they are still important assets to the nation .
Changing norms and mindsets coupled with an increasingly high standard of living , is driving children to abandon their parents .
For countries with a small population such as that of Singapore , there exists the need to recruit foreign talents to fuel the economy .
One way to retain these foreigners is to improve the welfare system for the aged .
The state shares a part in supporting the elderly for these are the people who had a hand in nation building and morphing the society which we live in now .
Therefore , whether it is due to moral obligation or for fulfilling one 's responsibility , compromising public spending on other areas of the country 's development for the aged is unavoidable .
Without the hard work of the older generation , we would not have the fundamentals of our society .
The government should also engage in long term solutions , like Research and Development , to save money .
To add on , less spending on the aged could have caused social problems .
Cases of conflicts over money problems at home ; elderly loitering in void decks and parks ; lonely elderly found dead and only discovered after a few days , are not unheard of .
Nonetheless , government intervention can minimize the possibility of having these problems .
The Maintenance of Parents Act is one good example of government intervention where taking care of elderly is .
Working class Singaporeans would be motivated to work hard as they know the government would contribute in taking care of them as they aged .
