As implemented in Singapore , filial obligation is drafted in law , which means that children are compulsory to take care of their parents ' elder life . " It would be agreed that children owe to their parents respect and kindness generally and assistance in case of infirmity or any special need... " ( Henry Sidgwick 1907 ) .
For the layer of aged population who is still healthy but has lower income , they might have problems in accumulating wealth .
