Numerous countries experience aging population
The dramatic shift in age structure has caused the Singapore government to introduce many related policies .
However , some policies introduced by the government are causing much problems for the society which outweighs the effect of easing the ageing process .
In 2007 , the government introduced a CPF ( Central Provident Fund ) reform scheme , which will push retirement age to 65 years in 2012 which will then be on par with Japan .
This , coupled with other initiatives such as the and incentives for companies to hire elderly workers , serves to encourage longer working lives and decrease dependency among elderly workers .
However , according to the Singapore National Census in 2007 , 68 % of the elder workers are unskilled and most of them are employed as cleaners or laborers , working long hours per day for mostly as little as $ 5 an hour ( 2009 ) .
However , many might argue that through employment , older workers will be able to earn their upkeep , save up for future medical needs and live an active and healthy lifestyle ( 2009 ) .
But on the contrary , it has been statistically proven that older workers tend to suffer from occupational injuries that were inflicted and accumulated since younger working days , thus accidents are more prone to occur , especially for jobs which require substantial amount of physical strength such as lifting or carrying ( 1996 ) .
In addition , if they were to be subjected to demands of work performance and long work hours in most jobs , how could they ever live a healthier lifestyle ?
With a healthy supply of young workers from other countries , Singapore can fill up job vacancies quickly and replace those older workers .
As the saying , to kill two birds with one stone , it can be said that foreign immigration solves both the ageing problem as well as the shortage of babies. .
According to a survey published by the Institute of Service Excellence ( ISES ) last year , Singapore has a lower service level satisfactory score of 68 compared to 72 in South Korea and 75 in the States . One of the reasons is the ease of foreign immigration here .
Nowadays , many semi-skilled foreign immigrants are working in service sectors , and even greet many customers in their mother tongue .
Nowadays , we are facing the old aging matter as it increases the pressure on our society .
Some policies such as later retirement age or increasing the responsibility of children for their parents have been applied .
Though there are still dubious opinions around these solutions , they really bring us hope for a better future .
Some researchers are still skeptical about the later retirement policy , which has been saving millions dollar for countries .
( 2006 ) in her article " Can they carry on working ?
Later retirement , health and social inequality in an aging population " questions the opposite sides of higher retirement age .
She worries about its bad impacts on older people 's health , which may increase the health care fees for government and about the unemployment of that will cut down the GPD .
( 2009 ) finds out that longer working time may help us fight against dementia , one of the most terrible illnesses of old people .
In fact , working helps the elderly become more independent , more enjoyable and healthier .
Ian Ziskin , chief of human resource and administrative office of Northman Grumman , says that it 's necessary to have a new brand of workforce in a company and his company will keep hiring young workers for the next 5 to 10 years ( , 2008 ) .
In short , encouraging later retirement of employees is an effective solution to reduce the burden of old age .
The second solution being discussed in many countries is raising the children 's responsibility to care for their older parents .
Every year , the government has to spend around 0.2 % to 3 % of total GDP to take care of old people and the number is increasing year by year ( , 2005 ) .
In fact , this caring plays a critical role in easing the spending of government and citizens on health care for the elderly .
It means you have to pay nearly $ 6000 per month for caring for your parents , which is such a large amount especially in the economic crisis recently .
According to ( 2006 ) , home care saved up to $ 350 billion in 2006 , which is even over the Fed 's budget .
In USA , just only 50 % of adults say that they are caring for their parents ( home caring or supporting money ) so if we can raise this number up by increasing the grown children 's responsibility , we can save our budget to pay attention to other necessary fields .
Although there is still skepticism around the two policies which are used to ease the pressure of aging population , a number of study and facts have shown us their benefits to our society .
Later retirement not only helps elders feel more active and healthier but also brings us a large sum of money .
Similarly , increasing adult 's responsibility for their older parents particularly assists the government in caring a number of older people and saving health care fees .
Nobody can deny the adverse effects of aging process in society today .
Imagine a country where nearly one-fourth of its citizens can not work and have to depend on its younger generations . Such a heavy burden will be placed on that country 's sustainability .
Recent policies , particularly the Later retirement policy and Central Provident Fund ( CPF ) Board 's Saving for retirement have illustrated the efforts of our Governments .
The fertility decline and the expected shrinking population will subsequently increase the dependency ratio. .
And if the situation gets worse , the young generation would not be able to pay tax and we would have insufficient funds to care for the elderly .
Although they have not been perfectly completed , based on fair judgment , such ideas have helped to lighten the aging effects in our society .
According to a scientific survey , 41 percent of people want to retire after 65 .
However , this policy has been strongly opposed .
One of the opposing views was about the strength and perspicacity of the aged .
They fear that old people would not respond well enough to the fast changing world .
Although their knowledge may be old-fashioned , their experiences are invaluable .
About 50 thousand people step into retirement each year , which will then contribute to the dependency ratio .
After many years of hard work , people can now enjoy their lives without having to worry about financial difficulties .
This scheme helps people to plan way ahead . Therefore , they would not have to rely on their children later .
Since there are many people suffering to support their families , it is just harder for them to save for later years .
People with higher income will have better retirement life compared .
Old homeless people , for example , will have to depend on the Government for their livelihood .
As a result result , although financial difficulty is not a serious problem for the majority of senior Singaporeans , we still have to find greater plans so that all people are all well supported in their old lives .
These two policies are just representatives of many researches , studies , policies given out to alleviate the harmful consequences caused by this so-called " silver tsunami " .
Additionally , we are encouraging young couples to have more children , urging working-aged immigrants to come , inventing more ways to reduce the cost for health . Tackling this fast aging problem is tremendous because it is hard to be eliminated absolutely .
To tackle these issues commonly encountered by these elderly people , the government has put in considerable effort towards alleviating their problems .
The solutions which Singapore has adopted and the policies that they have implemented aims to help the aged lead a more comfortable life .
A liberal country such as America operates in the form of nuclear families whereby the young adults leave their parents at an early age in search for their new home
( Diderich , 2005 . Thus , it will be very difficult for them to take care of their parents on a day-to-day basis .
In Singapore , a significant legislation known as the " Maintenance of Parents Act " in 1995 requires children to support their parents during the latter 's old age which has the effect of preventing problems related to the neglect of elderly parents
( Khalik , 2009 . Such a forward-looking policy helps to ensure adequate care and concern for the elderly , helping to ease their aging process .
In Singapore , the cost of living is high , in particular , medical cost .
The government has thus taken measures to counter these problems such as setting up the Central Provident Fund ( CPF ) so as to allow people to save when they are economically active
( Sarkar , 2009 These savings can be set aside for retirement purposes so that they can be self-dependent .
This is worsened by the fact that older workers have relatively lower education levels .
On the contrary , we can also tap on the vast experience and knowledge of the older workers who can then continue to contribute as economically productive members of the society and help sustain the creation of the " silver industry " targeted at older people
( Princeton , 2007 . In addition to that , the Ministry of Manpower ( MOM ) launched the " People-for Jobs Traineeship Programme " to help older workers who are prepared to take on a second career
( Chia , 2001 . This programme provides tax subsidies and grants to companies which re-trains older workers to help them be re-deployed effectively and to remain gainfully employed .
In conclusion , although the aged in Singapore face increasing number of problems each day , the government is actually implementing many policies , funding , facilities , programmes and services such as the Central Provident Fund Scheme to ease the problems the aged faces .
In light of the above , current research and governmental policies have , to a large extent , help ease the aging process .
This increases much pressure for the government when dealing with every aspect like economic issues , or infrastructure systems .
Despite some opposite opinions on how science makes aging a serious problem in many societies , the benefits science brings to ease this process seems to severely outweigh its detriments .
The discovery of gene activation or brain reaction to environmental factors has little impact in comparison with money spent on research , which can be more efficient to be spent on healthcare services and retirement pension .
This gene when activated can produce some types of proteins relating to diseases of the aged ( ) .
This has led a way for scientists to find treatment , such as in 2009 , Frank LaFerla and Mathew Blurton-Jones of the UC Irvene found a potential treatment for Alzheimer 's disease by using neutral stem cell .
In this point , there might be arguments that the new technique , if available , will result in a larger number of old people , increasing pressure to an already aged and crowded population .
This may not be a way to stop the aging process of a population , but is likely to be a good way to ease the stress and difficulties both government and each individual have to face .
Science with the invention of many toxic chemicals either used for fertilizer , pesticides or nuclear weapons , is responsible for higher infertility rate in humans and many mutant babies born .
However , though it is undeniably true how chemicals increase mutation in tissues , it is still unclear whether infertility rates of human beings can rise due to chemical usage .
While this seems to be a controversial issue , , a large quantity of babies are born from infertile couples .
This can be achieved because of biology and medical science , as well as new technology .
It is estimated that more than 100,000 babies have been born through in vitro fertilization ( Trounson and Gardner , ) .
The aging process has many negative influences globally . However , these may be eased with the help of new science applied to technology . .
According to the UN , life expectancy is projected to reach 76 globally over the next half century , and fertility rate is also predicted to drop more than a half from 5.0 to 2.1 children per woman globally by 2050 .
It 's called global aging and it threatens to bankrupt the great powers " .
As a result , the social economy will be affected dramatically in a negative way , one of which is the lack of a labour force .
This essay will discuss t some suggested solutions to the lack of a labour force that the demographic aging issue brings about based on the context of Singapore .
Initially , increasing the certain age of retirement would alleviate the burden of an aging population .
In addition , the more time older people can work , the more savings or pension they will have to secure their life sufficiently during old age without being dependent on their children or the governmental fund .
The policy , however , has its own hindrances .
Later retirement could cause a decrease in productivity because old people tend to be less healthy or less up-to-date with the new technology and information than the younger ones .
Secondly , the attempt to raise the fertility rates could also be one possible solution .
In fact , this solution somehow could ensure the economy that there would be a sufficient new generation or workforce to provide for the labour market when it comes to the time for the previous generation to retire .
how to ensure that there will be enough space for all people to be accommodated in a condition of land scarcity , especially in Singapore , a country with a total area of 710.2 square kilometres .
But in recent years , the Singapore 's government has put more effort to tackle the housing issue , which can be seen through HDB 's building programme to provide more public housing for residential use and allow citizens to take loans up to 80 % of the value of the flat to make it more affordable for everyone .
In the mean time for the next new generation of the workforce , the government can consider employing immigrants for a short period of 10 or 20 years .
This solution seems to have been adapted fairly well by the Singapore government since the beginning of the 21st century , and the immigrant workers have been closely associated with the economic development of the country .
Furthermore , since a lot of immigrant workers with different nationalities , their skills might not be similar or adequate enough to meet with the requirement of the jobs .
To solve the problem , a new standard of skills for immigrants should be established or the government should have the immigrant workers re-trained for the country 's purposes although it might take time and quite a lot of money .
In conclusion , the problem of an aging population is rather a problem of rigid and outmoded policies and institutions than only a problem of a demographic change .
Policies need to be developed that account for the natural incentives individuals have to adjust their behaviour in the face of an aging population .
Today , the aging problem has begun to draw people 's attention .
Firstly , an aging problem can lead to many economic issues .
It can cause a drop in the labour force and population .
Therefore , later retirement is encouraged by the writer of " A Graying World " .
People who are aged over 35 are considered old .
For example like employers should be fined heftily if they are found to refuse employing people whom they consider " old " .
Besides , aging can lead to a low population .
Some of them even refuse to give birth because they think that children are a burden .
As people get older , they are facing more and more health problems like kidney failure and other chronic diseases .
For example like machines for radiotherapy , dialysis , etc have helped people to recover from the sicknesses .
However , not every person can afford to undergo such treatment because they need to pay up to thousand dollars in order to undergo such treatments .
Besides , scientists have begun to create more healthy food through bioengineering , that is , the gene of the food can be altered so that the nutrition of certain food can be levelled up .
For example scientists altered a gene of the tomato so that the vitamin " folate " can be levelled up .
Thirdly , the introduction of many new medicines has helped to ease the aging problem .
Furthermore , besides medicine that are used to treat sickness , there are supplements which can make our body to become healthier .
For example like vitamin , iron , calcium , etc .
In conclusion , the aging problem is getting more serious , therefore , we have to pay more attention to this topic so that the problem can be eased .
The increase in the number of aged people has seriously slowed down the development of a country and burdened the government in terms of healthcare and financial aid packages for the elderly .
The Singapore government has set up the Central Provident Fund ( CPF ) , one of the many pension funds around the world , which requires employees to save almost 12 % of their income in their CPF accounts . The money can not be withdrawn except for housing , education , investments or medical care purposes .
However , Adam Smith ( 1766 ) suggests that governments should not interfere with the free trade of society . Trade should be free from affectation as the policy has been speculated that it reduces cash flow , and in turn reduces purchasing power .
Department head for example should be an older person so that they can impart their experience to the young worker .
The payoff of this investment is a highly efficient and productive workforce .
Not only that , better working environments should be provided for the elderly workers .
These costs are on an average of $ 34,000 per year . Working from home is another option that can be considered .
If one looks back into the past just only 20 to 30 years ago , he/she can see a big step in the improvement to the quality of life thanks to the rapid development of modern technology .
However , the question is whether we are ready for the increase in an aging population or not ?
We usually hear Singaporeans complaining about stress , primarily from work or from the education system .
All of these troubles that the application of this policy brings about may outweigh the benefits .
Though the elders have a lot of experience , they may not work as effectively and make decisions as quickly as the younger generations do .
There may not be enough jobs for both young and old people , especially in an economic downturn like today .
Therefore , finally , governments may need to spend a large amount of money on creating incentives for companies to hire old people , namely : tax reduction , subsidy for each elder employed , etc .
Moreover , old people may not be strong enough to withstand the stress at work and the cost for healthcare and insurance for old working people will surpass the profit , which all companies try to earn as much as they can .
Having such advanced technology in the current world , the aging population will be expecting a longer and healthy life expectancy .
Despite these economic constraints , there is still an urgent need for the government to increase the amount of children per household to replace the huge retiring labor force in order to maintain the economic growth within a country .
With these policies in place , infertile couples will less likely be a burden to the social and economic aspect of an aging population .
" Nevertheless , this is a difficult task as the efficiency and productivity of elderly workers decreases with their increase in age .
These schemes will equip the aging community with sufficient technological/technical knowledge to remain productive and efficient in the labor force despite their disadvantages .
With these in place , the impact of an aging population on the social and economic aspects will be greatly reduced .
Such policies include social policy like increasing the retirement age , allowing more employable immigrants into the country and introducing retirement schemes to ease basic needs after retirement .
Karen Holden ( 2003 ) suggests that as people work longer , it can help to reduce the likelihood of the elderly falling into poverty when they reach a certain age .
On the other hand , the increase in retirement age does not necessarily mean that people will be able to maximize their working years as some might be faced with health issues even before their retirement age .
Forcing oneself to work beyond his/her limit might cause one 's health to further deteriorate and have a negative impact to the economy .
A greying population has created pressure for the younger generation as the ratio of young adults supporting one elderly has been constantly decreasing .
Therefore , allowing more employable immigrants into the country may be one of the social policies that can help to ease the aging process .
Increasing the number of employable immigrants will help to lower the median age of the population and at the same time , result in a rise in the efficiency level because of a more competitive workforce .
On the contrary , such policy can lead to social problems as the increased competition can result in citizens losing their job to the foreign immigrants and eventually causing them to lose confidence and feel demoralized .
Policy to introduce retirement schemes is also believed to be one of the factors in easing the aging process .
Take Singapore as an example , the government has made it compulsory that every working adult must contribute a certain percentage of their monthly income into their individual CPF ( Central Provident Fund ) account in preparation for retirement .
This retirement scheme helps to reduce pressure on the economy as it allows the elderly to have a considerable sum of money in the future to support themselves .
People classified under lower income groups will usually face problems with insufficient savings and will ultimately still need support from the government .
In summary , Social policies such as increasing the retirement age might result in lesser dependency on the younger generation while lowering the barrier of employable immigrants will decrease the median age of the population and lastly , the introduction of a retirement scheme can allow people to save for their retirement .
Therefore , it can be concluded that social policies do play a part , to a large extent , in easing the aging process .
The concerns that will be discussed if funds should be put into funding education and its facilities , and the growth of the country itself is more paramount with regards to the country 's development .
Afonso 's view supports my stand that public funds being diverting into the education system is fundamental .
In this case , governments can help parents to save whilst bringing up their children , this provides sufficient support due to aid by government for educating children .
With support provided by the government to educate children , parents can save a substantial amount while allowing their children to receive education .
Conversely , as stated by Mackenzie ( 2009 ) , Canadians benefit amounts to $ 17,000 from the public services from tax funds , about the same amount a Canadian working full-time would earn .
In addition , economic growth can come about through diverting funds into more valuable areas like education .
