It can be argued to a certain extent that current public spending on the aged should be limited so that the money saved could be used in other areas of the country 's development .
The problem of an aging population is an issue for most developed countries .
Judging from the statistics , the elderly will form a relatively big portion of the country 's population structure in the near future .
This implies that the impact of the aging society will increase with time .
Therefore , it is important for countries to tackle the situation before it reaches its peak .
But nonetheless , countries that are already dealing with the problem of their aging population have identified the limitations of the policies that are implemented .
This indicates that perhaps the emphasis towards the investment of the country 's revenue should be diverted to other area such as economic investments and improving the education system to further boost the rate of advancement of a country .
in additionl , a pool of reserve funds should be available to cope with the rise in aging population as well .
This is because the problem of an aging population affects the rate of development of a country in the long run .
And if this problem persists , it will gradually become a roadblock for the future advancement of society .
The approaches that countries usually adopt to solve the aging issue include the prolonging of the working lives of the elderly and the provision of an array of welfare pension schemes for them .
But the controversy of the ability of the elderly to generate more wealth in comparison to the remunerative younger working adults had deterred many private companies .
As a result , the government has to provide funding for companies to encourage them to retain their elderly workers .
But this move is viable as the vast knowledge and experience that these elderly workers have gained over the years of working in the company .
This will in turn generate more economical benefits for companies .
This two tier solution would definitely help the progress of a country .
It provides a sense of financial security for the elderly as high medical costs would be highly subsidised .
As a result , it helps to reduce the reliance on the public welfare schemes , allowing a more of the funds in other aspects of the country .
But on the other hand , there are also other important areas that public spending could be used on to facilitate the country 's development .
This would allow additional financial iinput for the country to tap upon to provide greater welfare benefits for its citizens .
Besides , focus could also be placed upon education for the younger generation .
Equipping students with essential technical skills would require a considerable amount of funds .
However , considering the future financial input that these well-equipped workforces would generate , proves that it is a worthwhile investment for the country .
Finally , all in all , a country should deal closely with the issues of an aging population .
Being flexible about the limitations of funds and not rigidly capping the maximum budget for the elderly , will allow more room for a greater variety of solutions to be carried out .
In addition , there is no need to neglect the developments of other areas of investments such as the dual approach of slowing down the process of the aging population . Lastly , improvements in other areas of society will bring about a quantum leap in the country 's development .
Since the aging process has given the country 's economy ,
scientists have invented methods , compounded medicine and also introduced a solution for the aging process .
Medical scientists create treatments which are able to prolong human longevity .
For example , stem cells recently have been an effective way to make the human dream come true .
In medical science , there has been promising break-through research in finding the application of stem cells in anti-aging .
Stem cells , coming from the umbilical cord of a mammal , can successfully regenerate tissues destroyed by diseases such as old age .
Its options are limitless for regenerating skin , muscle tissue , lost eyes etc . If successful , they also help organ breakdown .
Nowadays , with medical treatment , people can be " young " for a longer time bringing about better health when they reach their old age .
That 's why when they are able to live in their physical condition of 30-years-old even if they are over 70 , they will work longer and will be able to accumulate more wealth which they could use to support themselves in their old age .
Secondly , medical science has also come up with many types of anti-aging drugs such as Deprenyl , one of the best anti-aging drugs currently available .
Anyway , not all the drugs are good and cheap so finding a suitable drug is a tough task .
Furthermore , the nutrition industry has also jumped in this battle against the aging problem with milk and other products like Quintessence that .
It would not only help the government to reduce the amount of money they have to spend on the welfare program for the elderly , but also provide the elderly with a chance to have a rich old-life .
Therefore , they may get even more money on their own rather than receiving money from government welfare .
Natural solutions to the anti aging process include fruits and vegetables .
Fruits like apples , strawberries , etc contain ellagic acid that has the capacity to hinder the growth of tumors within the body and those such as cantaloupe , peaches , etc contain lycopene gthat guard the body 's cells and organs like the heart and bladder from damage caused by free radicals .
Vegetables would also demonstrate the same benefits in antioxidant capabilities , for example , Genistein in soybeans works as cancer gene enzyme inhibitor .
Besides , people who usually do gymnastics will live longer and healthier than those do not .
Some may argue that fruit and gymnastics do not play any part in easing the aging process .
In fact by doing physical exercise , their immunity increases , making them immunized against lots of bacteria and viruses .
A healthy diet along with gymnastics will prevent .
