In a nutshell , the above mentioned arguments and reasons point to the fact that public spending on the aged should not be limited as if it is limited , dire consequences ,such as the country itself might be seen as neglecting the aged , will surface .
This might lead to foreign corporations being discouraged to invest in Singapore as Singapore might be perceived as not having an effective system . Therefore it can be concluded that the aged should have a bigger portion of the pie that is the public spending , while other areas will still have their share
To a large extent , current research and development have helped to ease the aging process .
Through the use of these specific reasons and examples , this essay will demonstrate why especially in the field of medicine .
Firstly , modern medicine is now able to cure or treat many diseases that were once terminal .
Today , modern medicine can even prolong the lives of people who have diseases for which this is still no cure .
Secondly , people today are more aware of the effect of healthy living on their life expectancy .
This is due to developed countries having an aging population coupled with a higher cost of living .
These include education , technological research and welfare programs for the needy .
Welfare programs , such as free healthcare services that are introduced in some countries , do improve the quality and lifespan of the aged in those countries .
Firstly , funds that are needed to support these welfare programs will come from taxes on the working-age adult .
The high cost of healthcare services results in high taxation on citizens
These countries like Britain and the United States generally have low Gross Domestic Product ( GDP ) and high public expenditure , with few exceptions like Sweden .
With a lower GDP , Sweden generates less revenue to divert to other areas of a country 's development .
( Jonathan Eyal , 20 August 2009 ) Studies have shown that Britain 's National Health Service , " devours 17.5 per cent of Britain 's annual fiscal budget , almost as much as defence and education combined .
The elderly in Singapore are dependent on government subsidies in various areas due to the current high cost of living .
However , public spending on the aged is only a short term solution to the problem of the aging population .
This short term solution poses a burden to the economy without actually addressing the root of problem of the aging population in the long run .
Public spending will only continue to spiral upwards if the government is committed to healthcare spending on the aged .
The government should look at this problem from an economic perspective in the long run .
This long term solution of diverting the country 's resources from spending on the aged to education lessens the squeeze on the already fully exploited economy .
Fewer opportunities , in the form of job security and stability arise from less money being diverted to education and development of the economy .
This will lead to emigration and brain drain from the country , which will in turn lead it to lose/losing its competitive edge , and thus it will be less attractive to investors .
More money should be diverted to education for the development of the younger generation to deal with .
An example is Singapore providing free education and offering one of the world 's best childcare services and facilities .
Nonetheless , the younger generation forms the pillar of a country 's economy and more attention should be given to nurturing them .
The issue of an an aging population has become an increasing important issue in our society today .
The problems caused by an aging population are increasing and it has placed great pressure on society .
Hence , the government is paying more attention to solving these problems caused by aging population through various means .
One of them is to increase public spending on the aged .
However , some may argue that doing so may limit the country 's development .
Therefore , public spending on the aged should not be limited because the issue of an an aging population has become a major problem in the society .
Other areas of the country 's development are equally important and hence government funds should also be directed to areas such as education and health care , instead of just focusing on the aged .
Education is equally important because the young will determine the country 's development in the future since they are the ones who will lead the country .
In addition , the healthcare sector is also very important as it can help increase the standard of living of people .
Nevertheless , public spending on the aged should not be limited as some of the elderly are in need of financial aid .
Some may point out that there are increasingly more people attaining higher levels of education hence they are able to afford the increasingly expensive healthcare services .
This problem is occurring in Singapore .
Therefore , public spending on the aged should not be limited .
In addition , public spending on the aged should not be limited as people have longer life expectancy as compared to the past and as a result will face larger financial health risks .
They may not be able to afford the increasingly expensive health care services .
In Singapore , the government has come up with policies such as Medisave and Medishield to prepare people by saving a portion of their salary in these accounts .
Hence , when they are ill , they are able to use these accounts to pay for their medical bills .
In conclusion , even though the issue of an aging population is important , other areas that are essential to a country 's development can not be neglected .
Hence , public spending on the aged should not be limited. .
Therefore , public spending on the aged should not be limited .
In recent years , many countries have begun to face the issue of ageing demographics and undeniably , Singapore is one of the fastest ageing populations in Asia .
Indeed , money has to be spent to curb ageing problems , but it is society 's responsibility to ensure a desirable standard of living for the elderly and to constantly fulfill the varying needs of this group of senior citizens .
The government has to ensure that all the elderly have a permanent roof above their head even after retirement and can also finance their day-to-day living expenses .
It is important to promote preventative measures as it will mean less expenditure on taking care of people who are sick .
It is a recognized fact that education helps the young to secure a quality job in future and also prepares them with
It is certainly worthy of the public funding to build the best educational facilities and ensure that every child has the chance to receive education .
It important to make sure that education remains affordable in the country and this can be achieved through subsidies by the government .
Moreover , part of public funding should also be spent on re-training schemes for working adults so as to improve their work quality and efficiency , as well as to keep them skilled and valuable for industry .
Education will harvest long term benefits for both individuals and the country as an educated pool of citizens will definitely generate greater economic growth .
With this additional economic revenue generated , more public funding can be channeled to help the aged .
In today 's context , industry changes get obsolete very quickly .
It is important to be innovative and constantly produce new ideas in order to stay ahead of competitors and to improve a society 's performance .
For example , Research and Development in pharmaceuticals is particularly important as the creation of new drugs will help in the advancement of medical and clinical studies .
More sophisticated health care systems will in turn help to reduce medical spending on the aged and might even help the elderly to sustain good health .
Other than areas in education and Research and Development , the defence force should also have a share of the public funding .
Nothing can be achieved in a chaotic environment , thus it is important to set aside public funding to effectively build an army , the navy and the air force .
Many considerations have to be made when it comes to the topic of dividing public funding .
No doubt it is essential to take care of the elderly who have contributed much to society during their younger days , but the government must still ensure that there is enough funding on other areas of the country 's development .
Economic growth must never be sacrificed as the society as a whole must progress and achieve further advancement .
Since Neil Armstrong left the first human footprint on the moon , it has always been a dream for human beings to explore more about the outer space .
As a country possesses over five thousand years of history , China never stops seeking the outer space .
Later on 15th October 2003 , the first manned spaceship was sent to the outer space .
Moreover the Chinese government is proposing a plan that will send spaceships to the moon and build an observation station on the moon .
Currently China has become the third strongest country in terms of the space technology , only after America and Russia .
First , the development of space technology is a basic need for an economic boost .
For a country which has an area of 960million square kilometers , having enough communication satellites is the first security for information communication , which then provides a good environment for the development of the economy .
For example , until 1994 China had built 8100 telecommunications systems , 11 satellites TV broadcast systems and 30 radio broadcast systems in response to the needs of communication in the remote areas in China , such as Xinjiang , Inner Mongolia , and Yunnan ( Baidu , 2008 ) .
Currently 80 % of China is covered with communication satellites not only for TV broadcast but also for world wide webcast ( Baidu , 2008 ) .
The innovation of space technology is an indirect result of the economic development in China .
Second , the military force of China needs the support of space technology .
Most of today 's military devices need the guide of artificial satellites .
As the deterrence policy and capability to meet the new threat , China has developed several kinds of precision guided weapons and nuclear missiles ( XinHua news , 2007 ) .
In addition to the use of space technology for building military devices , the natural resources of the outer space are also important for military aims .
Generally speaking , the development of space technology is an inevitable result of the economic development and military development in China .
With the development of its economics and military forces , the space technology will develop in response to it .
When the space technology has reached a certain level , the economic and military forces will reach a higher goal .
Under such circumstances , Chinese people will finally stand on the place where Neil Armstrong once stood .
The world is changing continuously because of various kinds of inventions that have been designed and developed .
Mobile phones , bicycles and electric appliances are examples of the application of technological creativity .
In designing a product or system , one priority requirement is that the invention should be easy to operate and require less human effort .
When one accepts a new product , the first thing that comes to mind is " How to use it ? "
The next question that will appear to the mind is " What is the easiest way to operate it ? "
An invention which is easy to use is very important to help them to reduce the time consumed yet achieve greater efficiency for their work .
This helps to reduce the time consumed to find the information from thick books in the library .
An oven , which is also easy to operate , helps humans to cook food in a short time .
If the way to operate a product is complicated , humans will prefer not to use it because the time spent in operating the product is not worth to be wasted .
All the information has to be collected before going further into the process .
This step begins with generating new ideas that may solve the problem .
The solutions that are conceived need to be analyzed and decision has to be made on which solution is the most suitable for implementation .
In conclusion , inventing a product which is easy to operate is essential .
The five steps in engineering design process should be wellfollowed to produce a good product and fulfill human needs .
The development of technologies in the context of the innovation-development process may be observed from either a technologically determinist or a socially determinist perspective .
Technology determinism proposes that technology progresses along its own path , independent of social development .
Another perspective is social determinism , also known as social constructivism , which supports the view that society influences and shapes technology , and not vice versa .
One important technology which is socially determined is the mobile phone .
There are several factors that have contributed to the shaping of this technological innovation .
The first factor that has shaped the mobile phone technology is the market forces .
There are several reasons for this situation .
The demand was still there because there were those who could afford them and mobile phones were important to those who were always on the go .
Mobile phones now have many funky designs and have added features like music players , cameras and e-mail readers .
Secondly , personal communication is also one of the factors that have shaped this technology .
Keeping in touch with friends have become much easier .
Short calls help in bonding relationships as they show that the caller is concerned enough to give a call even on a busy day .
Another factor that has shaped the mobile phone technology is personal display .
With this , mobile phones have become more like a fashion accessory and trends have been created .
As we all know , Singapore is a small country with no natural resources , having humans as our only resource .
As such , we face several problems that are not encountered by other nations , like inadequate technologically inclined talents and insufficient support from citizens , resulting in adverse societal attitude towards failure .
Singapore , a country with only 4.4 million population , has not enough professionals in the field of technology and science as most technological innovations are created by scientific research ( Roger , 2003 ) .
As manpower is the fundamental element of any process , without sufficient quality manpower , the commencement of processes is already hindered .
In short , this problem will hit hard directly on the first step of innovation , 'needs/problems ' ( see Figure 1 below ) .
As the world becomes more IT savvy , Singapore needs to set her foot onto the technological industries .
The easiest way to recruit technologically inclined talents is attracting foreign professionals .
This act will effectively increase the quantity of technicians , allowing the kickoff of innovation process temporarily .
However our heavy reliance on foreign talents will put Singapore in a vulnerable position in the long run as the foreigners do not have loyalty towards Singapore .
To reduce this over- reliance , Singapore has been taking careful measures in her education system . For instance , Singapore implemented her first IT Masterplan for education ( MP1 ) in 1997 ( Keng , 2007 ) , ensuring that Singaporeans have sufficient IT skills for future endeavors .
Scarce talents in Singapore is not the only problem we face . Another crucial worry is our adverse societal attitude towards failure .
Few local citizens have the risk venturing attitude , fearing failure , as when one moves into innovation several sacrifices need to be made , for example , family , current job .
Thus this worry will affect both the Research and the Development stages , from figure 1 .
.
In conclusion , if Singapore is to survive in the high risk volatility of the global economy , more pervasive idea generation skills throughout the population ( Lambe , 2002 ) are required for innovation process to begin .
Education should focus on producing not only 'exam-smart ' students but also those who that can react flexibly with the changes and needs of the current society .
At the same time , the society should also give ample supports to those creative thinkers of our civilization .
However , we should know that for these problems to be solved , it will require long term investment and there will certainly be some problems that can not be completely unraveled .
The main cause for this phenomenon is the ineffectiveness of the current education system in Malaysia .
Upon facing new problems that they have never encountered , they will just give up and take other short-cuts instead .
That 's why the whole process of innovations tends to stop after problems or needs arise .
By chance the process might proceed to the research and development stage but that is where more and more problems and troubles will appear and try to block the way out .
Another factor that contributes to Malaysia 's failure is the policy made by the government .
In order to gain political advantages , the government or the ruling party has implemented plenty of policies to constrain the freedom of individuals in giving opinions .
Mass media in Malaysia might be seen to have a lot of freedom in reporting news and views , but the truth is that they are all being controlled behind the veil .
Wondering how all these are connected with innovations ?
If you are the government , what will you do if problems arise in your country ?
Since identifying problems is the first stage of the generation of innovation , the government is actually blocking the entire flow of innovation process .
A country ruled under such a government will certainly enjoy very limited development in terms of creativity and innovation .
As a conclusion , the government plays an important role in deciding the overall development of innovation and innovative design of a country .
But one thing is for sure - our Earth 's resources are depleting and engineers , being the problem solvers , have to come up with ideas to reduce fuel consumption and the risk of greenhouse effect and global warming .
All these harmful effects bring us to this certain human need that should be given the utmost priority - health .
To address this need , an engineering process has to be developed and this requires a methodology or a process of steps to help us arrive at the solution .
The five step process , developed by Seyyed Khandani ( 2005 ) in http : //www.iisme.org/etp/HS % 20Engineering- % 20Engineering.pdf , is essential to help reduce the amount of pollution in our atmosphere .
The problem has to be clearly defined so that researchers and engineers alike understand the problem and recognize the need for a new product or system .
The emission of harmful pollutants into the atmosphere by motorcars and factories has affected human health and this needs to be rectified .
Details such as whether the issue of global warming is real has to be consolidated before ideas , such as replacing our motorcars with hybrid cars , can be generated .
Brainstorming at this stage is often a team effort when people from different backgrounds are involved in generating multiple solutions to the problem .
Products or systems have to go under a real condition test .
Graphs and charts , and information pertaining to the testing have to be recorded and reported to understand what has been created .
Nowadays , the technology of developing alternative and renewable sources of energy is rapidly gaining popularity due to their many advantages over the traditional sources of energy .
They are the supply of traditional sources of fuels , such as coal , petroleum and natural gas , which are known as non-renewable fuels .
Biofuels are obtained from living or lifeless organisms ( T.scheper & L.Olssen , 2007 ) , and it may be in solid , liquid or gaseous forms ; plant oil , ethanol and biodiesel are all examples of biofuels .
Hydrogen fuel refers to using hydrogen gas as an energy carrier ( Gupta , 2009 ) .
Fossil fuels like coal and petroleum a large amount of carbon-based polluting agents and greenhouse gases which contribute to global warming .
Let us take ethanol as an example .
" Ethanol contains 35 % oxygen " ( Helping the Environment ) ; this high percentage of oxygen allows for a more complete combustion , thus reducing the harmful emissions .
In fact , ethanol reduces exhaust carbon monoxide and toxic emissions by 30 % ( Helping the Environment ) .
The mankind 's battle against climate change is the catalyst that has fueled the search for renewable sources of energy ; it 's one of the few positive impacts of the global catastrophe that we are heading to .
Unlike alternative fuels , fossil fuels are finite resources .
At the current rate of consumption , all the natural gas and petroleum will be used up in less than 50 years ( Tan , Chen , Sadler , & Clare , 2007 ) .
It is impossible to imagine a world without them ; this leaves us with another ethical issue to chew on : is it fair to take away the luxuries of fossil fuels for future generations ?
Due to the shortage of petroleum and the ever-increasing dependence on it , the price of crude oil will continue to go higher .
In comparison with fossil fuels , renewable fuels will be much cheaper and more stable due to their wide availability without freight cost .
Hence , affordability and market stability are other factors that propel the development of renewable resources .
Last but not least , alternative fuels do not rely on oil from the Middle East , owing to the advanced technology used to make renewable fuels . The advanced technology opens up an entire dimension of .
The technology can build a a country 's energy independence , and thus regional geo-political stability .
To conclude , not only are the renewable fuels a lot more eco-friendly , but they are also widely and cheaply available .
In addition , the technology can help governments maintain economic and political stability .
Regrettably none of the alternative sources of energy is ready to replace fossil fuels at the moment .
Nevertheless , it is crystal-clear to the world that alternative renewable fuels ' technology is the only way ahead .
After analysing the topic , I understand the main issue is about the problems and obstacles which slow down engineering design processes for innovations , and the place I will discuss about is my own country China .
I should be able to interpret two significant problems and analyse their influences on certain stages of the process .
First of all , in my opinion , the hugest problem throughout all the innovations is lack of certain resources , raw materials , some necessary tools and high-tech devices or equipments .
The next significant one is that the Chinese government used to be unstable and provide bad leadership such that some big loss was caused to the industry .
There are some other problems such as lack of help from some developed countries , lack of engineers with brilliant knowledge and conflicts between conventional Chinese culture and western cultures in terms of some certain designs which are not so essential , so these problems are not discussed in this essay .
I will examine innovative engineering designs in the following industries in China : :
As the aviation industry is a significant symbol of a country 's strength and a vital sign of the level of a country 's industrialization , I would like to look further into this industry .
Do you know when China made its first aircraft ?
The first aircraft that was made all by China was on 30 July 1923 , 26 years before China became independent .
However , things have not always been going well .
In the first place , it is quite a challenge for China to set up its factories to produce planes on a rather big scale because of lack of resources and equipments ; then frequent changes of governments emerged and pulled back the entire industry dramatically .
In the early 1910s , the government of China started to prepare for setting up aircraft factories .
However , till 1949 , there were only over a dozen small factories with shabby devices and few planes were produced .
Worse , the necessary raw materials , tools , accessories and advanced equipments were all dependent on imports from other countries , let alone setting up an independent aircraft manufacturing system .
The problem really adversely affected the aviation industry for a while .
After China got independent , under the special care and proper guidance of Chairman Mao and some other leaders of China , the aviation industry started to enjoy a pleasant time .
The government spent a lot of money sending engineers to study advanced technologies and importing experts from abroad ; the other various industries of China have all given a great support to the aviation industry , especially by providing resources and funds .
In a few years ' time , China 's aviation industry grew from small to rather large and became able to produce aircrafts of many kinds .
As the pleasant time moved on , in 1953 China was able to make its first five year plan for its aviation industry .
The government guaranteed a lot of labour , materials and funds for the industry and the engineers and workers showed much initiative and creativity in work .
However , after the great success of the first five year plan , in 1958 a dim and chaotic period of governance arrived .
A three year period of " The Great Leap Forward " took place .
The government began to think that the industries of China had already been developed so well that the government started to require the industries to pursue higher quality , huger plans and greater speed of construction blindly , which in turn led to many serious quality problems .
Worse , taking advantage of this , reactionaries inside the government planed some sabotage in order to achieve their own goals .
As a consequence , a huge loss was caused to the whole industry .
Fortunately , people started to realize how wrong the leadership was and crushed the reactionaries .
The aviation industry started to stick to a solid and standard guideline when producing aircrafts and production gradually recovered .
Finally , we could say that the process of aircraft innovation was quite tortuous .
The lack of resources and equipments in the first place cost China a few decades . Then the whole industry went on well for several years as many aircrafts were produced ; however the government started to give wrong guidance and became unstable and caused a huge damage to the industry .
Looking back at the whole process , two serious problems came about and hit the industry so hard .
However , they were all resolved through proper guidance and much effort .
One such important technology is the wireless communications technology .
All over the world we see that there are many devices that use this technology .
For example , the remote controllers which help us to open and close our auto-gates and switch on or off our televisions , lightings , security alarm systems of our cars and homes use the wireless communication technology .
Besides these , other examples that use this technology are devices that use the Bluetooth , Wi-Fi , Wi-Max , wireless LAN , mobile phones , etc. Life would not have been as easy and as enjoyable without these devices .
Thanks to the many inventors , researchers , developers and governmental agencies , these products have been made available to the general public .
The evolution of this technology is somewhat driven by social needs .
Today , because of the growing demand of high-speed broadband internet connections , in areas where cabling can not be run such as outdoors and historical buildings the use of Wi-Fi is a good solution .
For example , in the United States it is governed by the Federal Communications Commission ( FCC ) , in Singapore by the Info-Communications Development Authorities of Singapore and in Malaysia by the Malaysian Communications & Multimedia Commission .
For example , in 1985 [ 2 ] , a decision by the FCC of the United States to open several bands of wireless spectrum , so-called " garbage bands " ( 900 - 928 MHz , 2400 - 2483.5 MHz , 5725 - 5850 MHz bands ) without the need for government license has spawned growth in R&D in that area .
Due to this decision many " unlicensed " wireless technology products for communication purposes were developed , such as the Bluetooth , Wi-Fi , Wi-Max applications which use the spectrum of the garbage band .
Unlicensed wireless devices are devices that emit low power radio frequency energy without specific devices or user authorization through either registration or grant of a license .
This policy has great economic significance .
The chain effect is that it encourages innovation to develop new communication products which help to fill consumers ' needs , which in turn helps to generate jobs in the manufacturing of these products , the transportation of these products to various countries around the globe and finally the marketing of these products to the end consumers .
" Need " here refers to a desire or shortage of a commodity , and sometimes this " need " can be considered as a neccessity or a form of luxury .
For example , Tetsuya Mizoguchi , an engineer from Toshiba Corporation , saw the need for portable personal computers and came up with the idea of laptop ; and as of recently , one of the human needs that have gained unremitting attention would be transportation .
As the struggle between man and nature continues to be unabated , it is the engineers ' job to design cars that are environmental-friendly to mitigate what has already been done to our environment .
The process of defining a problem involves identifying a need , developing a problem statement and establishing a criterion for success .
It must be clear , concise and unambiguous to avoid any ambiguity .
Creativity is one of the biggest emphases in this step in order to generate techincal solutions to the problem .
Engineers must also be willing to take risks and make mistakes , and not to be afraid of being criticized for their ideas .
Analysis of all possible solutions is to be done and reasons of why the final solution overrides the others must be clear .
In the design of environmental-friendly cars , it must be in such a way that the designed car would be less polluting than the existing ones , coupled with lower price and better performance .
Greenhouse emissions must be reduced to the lowest level as much as possible .
" exclaimed Archimedes , A Greek mathematician and physicist , when he noticed water flowing out of his bath tub as he submerged himself into the tub .
Despite their differences in definition , a research technology and a serendipitous technology both share a similarity : the technology is ultimately used to tackle the problems of Man .
However , despite their similarity in resolving problems of Man , the two technologies also share one difference : the process in which it was discovered .
Throughout history , we mankind have always sought to improve the quality of our lives .
Singapore has no other natural resources ; hence , our most urgent need will be to find a reliable source of sustainable energy .
According to Khandani ( 2005 ) , the design process consists of five main parts : Defining the problem , gathering required information , generating multiple solutions , selecting a solution and testing the solution .
Wind energy requires a vast open area to place the windmills , but Singapore does not have such space to spare .
The infrastructure required is much simpler , as only the solar panels and necessary wirings are needed .
The majority of housing in Singapore are HDB flats , and these flats add up to form a considerable amount of land area .
This scheme is highly probable because the government has control over a large number of HDB flats , which constitutes a large land area .
To design a environmentally-friendly product
Since the 19th century , the environment has been polluted because of the fast development of industries and economics .
Nowadays , the pollution is very severe and has threatened living conditions of human beings .
To have environmentally-friendly products is a human need that has to be given priority , so that the products people use wo n't be harmful to neither the environment nor the health of people .
To define the problem , three main needs can be identified : firstly , design products that can minimize the pollution during manufacturing .
Secondly , design products using environmentally-friendly material and consuming green energy .
Thirdly , design products which minimize emission pollution .
And one of the criteria for the success of the product is whether the product is environmentally friendly .
According to Khandani ( 2005 ) , traditional publications , libraries and internet are major sources to find out the information needed .
Since our problem is very academic and needs in-depth search , journals and books should be the main sources to consult .
Besides , our problem has three aspects , which are diverse , so we need to focus on aspects that are well developed .
Then it is time to generate multiple solutions for the problems .
To analyze those design solutions , a lot of factors need to be considered .
Functional analysis , ergonomics , product safety and liability are all important elements to evaluate those solutions .
To compare one solution with another , ranking according to the attributes of a solution is necessary for us to see which one is the best ; in our case , being environmentally friendly should be the major criterion .
At last , choose the highest ranked one for the next process .
Methods such as prototyping and concurrent engineering can be applied for implementation , and we need to know how effective the product is regarding its environmentally friendly features .
In that case , we need to repeat the design processes to solve the problems .
To sum up , the design processes can help to solve the problem we have effectively , since in each step we do our job based on the problem we want to solve and on how efficient we are in solving the problem .
New and clever technologies are constantly being developed by people all around the world to tackle problems that they face .
One of them is that they both exist to address problems that people are facing at that time of creation , but differ in the process in developing develop the product .
Another is that both types of technology require people to ultilise a certain amount of creativity and good peception to develop them completely but differ when it comes to the type of people the technologies usually involve .
Teflon , for example , is being used in a variety of products as anti-stick or anti-stain coatings .
Cooking utensils coated with Teflon are now easier to clean up since burnt food no longer stick to it .
Clothes coated in a variety of Telfon became stain resistant , which means less chance of it becoming damaged permanently by tough stains and an easier time washing the dirt off the clothes .
This problem is the space constraint due to small living space .
By being foldable , space could be made available for use where the bed would have been .
Ultimately , both technologies are beneficial to the human population .
The two ways of developing technologies use different processes .
The development of murphy bed , for example , is driven largely by the problem it was trying to solve .
This results in a process where identifying the problem comes first , after which time and effort are put in to solve that one problem .
However , Telfon has seen itself being used as coatings to cloth , coating on cookware , insulations and even as stenotic arteries in medicine .
One reason for this versatility is that the brainstorming is now focused on the various problems where Telfon could be used to solve to great effect .
With a large pool of possible uses for Telfon gathered , the next step would be to modify this new technology so that it may be used for as many problems as possible .
By observing this , it could be possible that people would combine some of the key aspects of the processes to create a better model for developing new technology .
Therefore , as we humans are running out of energy we can make use of , providing sustainable , green and reliable energy has been crucial for the survival of the whole human society .
Before setting out for possible solutions for our energy problem , rigorously defining the problem itself is indeed necessary so that we can make sure that we are always in the right direction and know what properties the right solutions should possess .
" An energy crisis is the shortage of energy accompanied by the fact that now we can not find enough reliable energy as substitute , " a definition of energy crisis given by Prof. McLaren Hill from the University of Edinburgh .
Such solutions contain hydro and solar energy generation .
But whatever the result might be , we must apply scientific methods in every stage , from building a prototype to conducting concurrent engineering , from planning to maintenance .
Technologies have been developed since long ago ; however , not all of them are planned .
There are many pathways that lead to a technology being created , mainly through serendipitous discovery or through research .
While most of the events appear to be non-significant , there are some where people actually get ideas from them .
This is what we call serendipitous discovery , when people make discoveries that they did not seek .
One of the examples of technology being discovered from research is the development in automobile safety and a better design of roads in the United States ( U.S. ) while an example of technology resulted from serendipitous discovery is the Post-it pads .
The technology created via research has significant differences from the technology resulted from serendipitous discovery in several aspects .
One of the major differences is whether there is a need for the technology .
In this case , the development in automobile safety and a better design of roads in U.S. is to reduce the massive casualties from road accidents where the annual vehicle death rate reached 50,000 in the early 1960s ( statistics taken from Rogers , E. M. ( 2003 ) .
Decades ago , the 3M researchers found a new bonding agent during their research but it was not what they had wanted to achieve as the bonding agent did not stick paper very tightly to the surface .
Therefore , it can be said that technologies created from research are due to a need for them while technologies created from serendipitous discovery do not originate from a need .
Technologies developed through research are used for their intended purpose .
However , technologies developed from serendipitous discovery are not used for their intended purpose .
The bonding agent was initially thought as a failure as it did not meet the expectation of the researchers,which was to stick tightly to the surface of paper .
However , it is later converted into a successful product when it is used to create " Post-its , " the little stick- on squares of colored paper that can be used to attach a note to a letter or other documents , which is not the intended purpose of this technology .
In a nutshell , technologies created from research will be used for their intended aim while technologies developed from serendipitous discovery might not serve its intended purpose .
Lastly , one final difference between the 2 lies in the background research .
This is proven just by looking at the amount of research needed before measures are to developed a safer automobile as well as better design of highways .
There is no background research needed for these technologies , as they are created out of pure coincidence .
With reference to Post-it pads , they were created without any background research .
Hence , it can be said that there is background research for technologies originated from research while there might not be any background research for technologies created from serendipitous discovery .
Despite the differences between the ways by which the technologies are created , they help to improve the life of mankind be it through convenience or through any other means .
In conclusion , there are significant differences between technologies developed from research and serendipitous discovery ; however , these differences does not change the fact that both technologies are key to the future for mankind .
The development and advancement in science and technology has brought much convenience to the human society today .
Technology is something which is created to help solving the problems we face in our daily life and at the same time , improve the quality of our life .
Generally , most of the technological innovations are created through basic research , followed by applied research , leading finally to development .
The differences between these two types of technological inventions can be perceived in terms of their research backgrounds , cost of the invention of the technology , and time consumption .
Technology developed via research and technology resulted from a serendipitous discovery have different research backgrounds .
Technology based on scientific research requires a wide range of knowledge to conduct the research .
Special skills are also needed to carry out certain experiments and to record the results and data of the experiments .
For example , to create a miniaturized medical submarine which can be injected into human bodies to destroy the blood clot that threatens a human life , there are many technical problems to overcome , such as how to make , power and steer the medical submarine .
The technology based on research and the technology created by serendipitous discovery require different amounts of cost to be carried out .
For technology based on research , a large amount of money is needed to purchase materials that are essential for the research and investigations to be conducted .
Moreover , specific apparatus , for instance , machines and robots , which are usually expensive , are also needed in order to carry out certain experiments .
Apart from that , time consumption for the technology based on research is much different from that for the technology created by serendipitous discovery .
In order to carry out extensive research and analysis , much time has to be spent for the technology to be successfully invented .
For instance , Thomas Edison had spent his whole life to invent a light bulb with almost tens of thousands of failures before he succeeded .
For technology created from serendipitous discovery , less time is as it comes out unexpectedly .
One popular example is penicillin , which turned out to be the first antibiotic because of its property of killing biological materials when it was left in Petri dishes containing biological organisms .
To sum up the salient points , technology created via research requires more researches and investigations than technology resulted from a serendipitous discovery .
Besides , cost of creating a technology via research is much higher as compared to that of technology resulted from a serendipitous discovery .
Technology based on scientific research consumes more time than technology resulted from a serendipitous discovery as many researches and experiments need to be carried out .
Although all technology serves a common purpose , there are many differences between inventions resulted from research and those resulted from serendipitous discoveries .
Looking at an example of invention that resulted from research - the laptop and an example of serendipitous discovery - the implantable pacemaker , a few distinct differences such as the cause leading to the research , final usage of the technology and the research procedures can be spotted between them .
Firstly , the most distinct difference between an implantable pacemaker and a laptop is the intentions which led to their discovery .
In the case of the laptop , the inventors of the laptop started with the intention of creating a " DynaBook , " which is a concept conceived in 1968 .
Therefore , it is obvious that the cause which led to the invention is very different in that in the case of the laptop , , it was already intended before its creation whereas in the case of the implantable pacemaker , its creation was never intended .
In the case of the laptop , the final usages are what the laptop was intended for during its conceptualisation stage .
However , in the case of the pacemaker , the final usage is not what it was intended to be .
It was intended to be a machine to record the sound of the heartbeats but ended up as a device to stimulate the heart and to serve as a cure for certain heart problems .
As shown above , in the case of most serendipity discoveries , they will normally not be used for the initial purpose of the experiment that led to its discovery whereas in the case of an invention through research , it will be the used for its intended purposes .
Lastly , the pace of advancement that led to the invention of the laptop and that of the pacemaker is different too .
The experiment that led to the discovery of the implantable pace maker was done in 1958 and within months of its discovery the first implantable pacemaker was being used on a human being .
However , for the laptop , its concept was developed in 1968 and the first " laptop " only came into existence in 1975 .
Despite all the differences , there are undeniably some similarities between serendipitous discoveries and discoveries made through conventional research methods .
In both examples , regardless of their methods of discoveries , both are beneficial to mankind and help to improve the quality of life .
The laptop has simplified human work whereas the pacemaker has helped prolong life of some stricken with life threatening diseases .
In conclusion , though there are many differences between the discovery of the laptop and that of the pacemaker shown above , they both help to propel the human race forward into the future .
The first step in the engineering design process is to identify the problems that our product will face .
The most convenient way to collect the appropriate information is through the use of internet , as there are always search engines available to help get our sources more accurately and quickly .
Through more brainstorming within our group , we would arrive at more solutions .
The best solution would be chosen from the few ideas that we have thought of during the " generating multiple problems " process .
We should come out with a series of tests to prove whether the products work in real life environments .
Even if one of the tests fails , we could apply the engineering design process to solve the problems that have emerged in the process of the testing .
In this long time period , technology has developed together with the human society .
Technology has been developed in different ways .
Technology developed via research and technology resulted from a serendipitous discovery differ in some aspects but are similar in some other aspects .
The process for the development of technology developed via research is very systematic with a very clear target .
They do not have the target but they finally stumble upon some new technology .
These inputs include time , effort , fund , and so on .
Unlike technologies developed via research , technologies resulted from serendipity need almost zero input .
This kind of technology is just like a gift from God .
Scientists need such luck to get this God 's gift .
So , these two kinds of technology need different inputs .
They develop certain technology which satisfies certain consumer domains ; in comparison , scientists usually do not know the use and the specific consumer domains when they accidentally discover a technology .
They help make our life easier and more comfortable , thus improving our living standard .
Even though these two kinds of technology are developed in different ways , they both can benefit the society and our daily life .
This can be done by considering the environmental friendliness of inventions as one of its major factors in the five steps of engineering design process , which are as follows : Defining the problem , gathering information , generating solutions , analysing and selecting a solution and implementing the solution .
It sets out the whole purpose of the process in the right direction .
For example , eco-friendly gym equipment today are able to harness the energy generated during its use to power the machine itself .
Moreover , new inventions should not be the only products with a " green " factor as old inventions can be re-designed in order to achieve the " green " status .
It also allows them to consider existing solutions , if any , and consider various factors which will determine the success of the product such as its economic viability and its effectiveness .
Thus , solutions generated from these ideas should be able to resolve the problems identified as well as conform to the requirements of the society .
Moreover , not only should the product solve the initial problem , it should also meet the society 's demand in terms of usability , ergonomics and economical concerns .
Each problem is different and unique ; thus , they would have different factors to consider for analysis .
Every design is rated based on the consideration of various factors such as functionality , ergonomics , mechanics , manufacturability , safety , cost-effectiveness and compliance with regulations .
( Khandani , 2005 ) The solutions would then be rated according to different criteria corresponding to the analysis and the best would then be selected .
After functionality , safety is another area of concern .
In conclusion , engineering design process is a general process through which ideas can be generated to resolve current issues .
Engineering design process is able to address this issue by encompassing and focusing on the element of environmental friendliness for every invention .
Technological developments are divided into two different categories : the conventional method of developing technology through research or the unusual method of developing technology through serendipitous discovery .
The two technological innovations discussed would be the Laptop Computer and Sildenafil ( Viagra ) .
Though they are on the opposite spectrum in terms of the field of technology , both have similarities in their own way .
One difference , aside from their uses , is the manner in which they were developed .
The development of the laptop in Toshiba took on a systematic and direct approach towards an apparent goal : to reduce the size of a personal computer so it would be compact enough and portable .
Yet , aside from being products of different fields , both technologies were able to be commercialized into products successfully .
( Keith A 2000 ) The laptop was a radically different innovation then ; nevertheless , it was marketed furiously and soon had majority market shares in Europe , United States and Japan ( Rogers 2003 ) .
Another similarity between the two technologies was that they had competitors .
Offices in Japan are crowded and homes are small with no space to install a desktop , giving rise to a need for smaller personal computers .
The problem of male erectile dysfunction was solved by the innovative development of Viagra , though it was a 'coincidence ' that the compound Sildenafil causes penile erection .
The number of cars on the road keep on increasing year by year and so does the pollution that arises from it .
As stated by Khandani in " Engineering Design Process , 2005 " , consumers are the one that ultimately establishes the need for a product .
This includes brainstorming sessions to find new alternative fuels and designing a new engine that can run on such fuels .
Engineers also need to make comparison between the latest hybrid cars such as electric cars , hydrogen fuel cell cars and solar powered cars to see which one is more efficient and suitable .
Willingness to take risks and experiment with new alternative fuels is also important so that more creative ideas can be generated .
Lastly , after going through rigorously analyzing and selecting the final design , we need to make a prototype of the hybrid car and test its overall function in real world situations .
This will reveal the weaknesses in the design ; hence the engineers can improve on it .
Creative engineering design can produce a paradigm shift for people to start using environmentally friendly cars due to all their positive advantages .
However , in the process of looking for new energy source to take place of coal and oil , a more urgent problem of the energy system has been neglected -- the storage of the energy .
Ironically , compared with the primary energy carriers , the battery is far less popular and is only used in some specific fields .
The process can be divided into three parts , defining the problems , finding the solutions and selling the new products .
The birth of the battery can be traced back to several hundreds years ago , but it failed to dominate the energy carrier market because of its two obvious weaknesses , which can not be improved easily .
It can only be used in some trivial electric devices such as mp3 players .
The second weakness of battery is its charge time : compared to the refueling of the fossil fuel , the battery charge takes too much time .
These two elements together impede the battery to be an instant energy carrier , and finally lead to today 's situation of energy carrier market .
To enhance the capacity of the battery , keeping trying new materials is important .
Since the new battery is designed to be used in the big machines to replace engines , the capacity will have the priority .
The popularization of battery is not isolated ; as an energy carrier , it should go together with the innovation of electrical cars and other engineering products to form an industry chain .
The chain will also include the battery charge station , which will replace the refueling station with the popularization of battery .
To sum up , the engineering design process can be a good way to innovate a new generation of battery .
A process that includes defining , solving and selling will build a whole industry chain around the new batteries , and finally meet the energy carrier need of the society .
In cities around the world , a large amount of energy is consumed by electrical appliances every day .
By designing better electrical appliances that could perform the same function with less energy used , we could save a large amount of energy .
With less energy used , costs of living are reduced and the economy would improve with more people having more money to spend .
Another way to improve the economy would be through the designing of new forms of energy sources .
As the natural resources are depleting , the price of using it as source of energy is becoming increasingly high .
Therefore , through the discovery of new forms of convenient and renewable energy , the price of energy could be more stable .
A more stable price reduces the chance of a big change that could lead to economy problems .
To sum up , a stable and better economy is the current human need that should be given priority to .
With a population of 1.15 billion , a total area of 3.2 million square kilometers , twenty eight states , seven union territories , diversity in culture and around a hundred different languages , India has certain significant problems in the hampering of engineering design processes for innovations .
Though engineering design is considerably well established in the country , some practical problems unclear meaning .
Having a literacy rate of 61 percent , it is quite difficult to introduce new technological innovations , as not all the people in the country would understand and know how to utilize a product well .
This is because the job opportunities are better in foreign countries in comparison with those in India .
Problems such as the second highest population , vast size , low literacy rate and 'Brain Drain ' have made it difficult for India to take a step towards technological innovations in the field of engineering design .
Right from education every other field in India is flooded with corrupt officials who primarily work with a self centered mindset to misappropriate and amass a huge amount of money .
These individuals are indifferent to the fact that the majority of India 's population is below the poverty line .
This multi faceted economic problem becomes the main hindrance to India 's technological development and is the mother of all other social and political problems that India faces .
The 5 stages are sequential , which means that an interruption in any of the 5 steps can hamper the engineering design process .
In Malaysia , engineering design processes for innovation have not been evolving as much as the government would them to .
The problems that contribute to this are that there are not many quality engineers left in Malaysia and because of the local society 's mindset .
The value of the ringgit is rather low so engineers tend to favor working overseas as there , the salary is higher and the working environment is much better .
For example , Malaysians who study in Singapore are required to sign a bond which ties them to work in Singapore for a few years .
After working in Singapore , most of them will not return to work in Malaysia as the pay in Singapore is almost double compared to the pay in Malaysia .
In addition , the engineers produced in local universities are not able to fill the gap left by the engineers who leave the country .
They are not willing to take new risks in terms of design innovation .
Malaysians are easily contented and refuse to improve on existing innovations and technologies .
Malaysians are also uncooperative in their work .
Furthermore , they are not willing to seek help from foreign countries and contract most of the work to unqualified local companies .
The problems listed above can have an impact on all or one of the 5 stages of the engineering design process .
First and foremost , the conventional thinking of Malaysians can affect the first stage of the process of defining the problem .
We need to work together with other nations to tackle a problem because other countries may have different views of a problem .
Most significantly , because of the insufficient number of engineers in the country , we are just not able to get enough manpower to accomplish the design process .
In conclusion , the progress of engineering design is being disrupted by the mindset of the local society and the lack of engineers .
As the rest of the world continues to improve technologically , we can only advance at a slower pace .
There is a need for an attitude change in both the government and the society .
They should consider helping to improve the level of design innovation in the country so that we can compete globally .
Incredible as it seems in such a resource-rich earth , the energy crisis has become one problem .
As Tennessee Valley Authority disclosed , the normal 60-day store of coal now can only supply ten to twelve days ( Business : The Energy shortage worsens , 1997 ) .
This means that our resources can not meet our increasing demand .
However , there are some concerns about it , such as security , costs and performance , which have limited the popularization of this promising substitute .
In order to resolve these problems , a new generation of nuclear energy system which is called the Fourth Generation reactors is undergoing tests .
One of the six approaches , named supercritical-water-cooled reactor , can give us the solution to meeting future energy needs with further research .
Supercritical-water-cooled reactors ( SCWRs ) share the benefits of Generation IV and some further benefits compared with other kinds of reactors . SCWRs may also resolve some concerns about safety and cost with some further development .
The SCWR as one of the six reactor concepts for Generation IV nuclear fuel shares the same advantage with all other reactors and some further advantages compared with other reactors .
Sustainable means that the system should generate power by some natural fuel , while at the same time minimizing its environmental impact .
Being viable means that the generating cost should be competitive with other energy resources , while the capital investment should also be low enough to allow access to a large number of countries .
'Safe and reliable ' mainly emphasizes that the future reactors should perform better or at least as well in terms of the safety and reliability as current ones .
The focus is to decrease the emission of radiation and ensure the safety of civilians once an accident happens .
Compared with other reactors , the SCWR is advanced as its higher thermal efficiency ( about 45 % versus 33 % for the ? ) and simple plant
( Nuclear Power Energy , 2002 ) . The SCWR is effective because only one cycle is involved .
Furthermore , the SCWR does not require steam separator plates , heat exchangers nor turbines compared with the ?
( Tilkki V. Supercritical Water Reactors : A Survey on International State of Research in 2006 , 2006 ) . the simple design reduces the construction cost of the nuclear electrical station .
Moreover , the coolant of the SCWR is water which is cheaper compared with the coolants used in other kinds of reactors .
Although the SCWR has many benefits , two main concerns about the cost and safety limit the population of this reactor .
Opponents may argue that the cost of nuclear energy is not equivalent to what we pay for it .
This means that the electrical power which is generated by nuclear stations is very costly .
For the operating cost , the cost of producing electricity has decreased from 3.63 cents per KWHr to 1.68 cents since 1987 .
In the USA , the nuclear power operators are charged 0.1 cents per KW-Hr for the disposal of nuclear waste and the average decommissioning cost is $ 300 million .
In fact , these costs are all affordable compared with other kinds of energy generation methods .
The main cost is the construction cost which may vary from 1 billion to 5 billion ( such as the station on , Long Island , 1985 ) dollars .
Nowadays , the in China .
But the new can promise a cost of $ 1000 per KW construction cost and only take 3 years to construct
( Everything you want to know about Nuclear Power , n.d. ) . Thus , in the future , the nuclear electricity may share the same price as other fossil resource electricity .
some doubt the safety of the SCWR .
Their worries are based on the accidents that have before .
For instance , during the short period of just 3 years from 1989 to 1992 , there are more than ten accidents which occurred in India , USA and Japan ( Calendar of Nuclear Accidents , 2004 ) .
All of these incidents tell us that nuclear power is really dangerous .
Some processes for the SCWR can not be safely achieved with present technology , but scientists are really working hard on them and some breakthroughs have been made .
Thus , .
To conclude , we can see that the SCWR is a sustainable , economically viable , safe and reliable approach .
If all its disadvantages can be overcome , we will have got a suitable replacement for fossil resources .
Not only does design entail a magnificent facade or the strange opinion of a maverick , but it also involves pragmatism , cost and efficiency .
All these requirements are fully met by those who are well educated .
However , while there is a highly increasing demand for engineers with acuity of design , even in the education system of my own country , there are two major setbacks for engineering students getting adequate design skills : the lack of practice in school and the insufficiency of co-curricular activities .
Although the curriculum has been continually improved to gradually reduce the use of conventional teaching methods , .
The reason is that the acquisition of new equipment needed for experiments is not in tandem with the changing of textbooks .
Only in the urban areas can students have opportunities to get access to the required equipment .
For students in other places , they can only see the teacher do a sample experiment in the lecture but can not try the experiments themselves .
According to the Labor Newspaper , in Hung Yen , a southern province of Viet Nam , there are thousands of students studying without sufficient lab equipment due to the delay in purchasing new equipment and due to corruption .
In these regions , another factor that breaks the camel 's back is the exodus of young lab teachers to cities where they can have a conducive environment to develop their own career and earn a better living .
The residue of this migration is an old generation of teachers who are not very familiar with modern devices in labs .
Consequently , students do not have the chance to gain the priceless pragmatic experience of how to design .
This can be accounted for by the fact that there are few organizations in almost all schools .
There was , in fact , only one organization , namely the Youth Union , in my secondary school .
Though activities held by the above organizations ranged from learning history to acquiring leadership , not many students benefited from them .
That is due to the fact that the number of participants for one activity just covered a small portion of all the students in school .
Moreover , since co-curricular activities are not compulsory in our country , and the studying in other learning centers takes up almost all the time of students , students tend to drop co-curricular activities in school .
The Youth Newspaper recorded a New Zealand professor saying that Vietnamese students spend so much time on gaining academic knowledge that co-curricular activities have become a luxury .
The two aforementioned issues leave engineering students .
For one thing , students who are not used to doing lab research usually have just a vague idea of what should be done .
For them , the first step of the design process seems to be far away as they can not define the problems completely since " people have a natural tendency to attack the current solution to a problem rather than the problem itself " ( Khandani , S. , Engineering design process , page 8 ) .
As a result , the rest of the process can be ruined because of the first steps ; for example , if the problem statement is not broad enough , the statement will preclude new thoughts on the issue .
it is arduous to undo the whole process , these novice engineers have to accept low-quality products and , consistently , low profit .
Another thing is that without experiments in co-curricular activities , fledgling engineers can not fulfill the second and the third steps : collecting pertinent information and generating multiple solutions .
This is because they lack confidence in communicating with other colleagues to gather information as well as learning experience , so they can hardly find out the most information .
Co-curricular activities also help engineering students develop creativity and imagination to come up with many answers to a single question .
If students do not actively join various activities , they will be prone to solely apply rules and theory in school to work .
Losing creativity and imagination means that they are losing their advantage in .
However , with efforts to reform the education , I optimistically believe that we can overcome these obstacles to be competitive engineers in the global market .
In Singapore , there are problems that hamper engineering design processes for innovation .
These problems may impact the market resulting in consequences such as the unavailability of new products , poor design outcome and changing mindsets of potential designers .
First , there is a lack of creativity .
In Singapore , a number of us are of the lazy type , which means we are lazy to design .
Moreover , there are some that are shy to speak up about their ideas .
Another problem would be individuals with fixed mindsets , thinking that designing is not a good path to take .
For example , in Marcelo Ang 's ( 2009 ) talk , he mentioned that it is always the mental block of an individual that makes everyone think of not going for designing .
Hence there is a need to remove that mental block , so that individuals will have the opportunity to design and invent what they desire .
This mindset may cause the market to lose good designers , who could potentially help boost the design industry .
Without people designing new products , there will be no new products in the market .
This in turn will cause the market to suffer . In the article " Designing engineers to change the world " , Chan ( 2009 ) mentioned that market users always demand new products which they are fascinated with .
Second , is due to the time taken to create a full design product .
A design process is not the outcome of one night 's work .
These included tests on humans to confirm that Newater was fit for drinking before it was produced for public consumption .
They took more than a year to complete .
leads to other effects and impacts the market .
People tend to go for simpler designs , because of the long time required to create a proper full design .
The reason is that a simple design is much easier to design and time required to produce such a design would be much less .
This results in poor designs being produced in the market .
Hence market users will not be tempted to buy the product , which would cause sales and the market to be low .
Additionally , this also leads to lost income for designers as they might not earn their production cost back .
Eventually potential designers would have second thoughts and step out of designing .
In conclusion , the lack of creativity and the time to create a design could cause impacts on the market in Singapore .
These problems that may hamper engineering design would impact the market causing the unavailability of new products , designers taking shortcuts in design and designers ' mindsets about design .
In addition , this would lead to a market downturn .
It 's hard to change it once it 's fixed .
I believe that if an individual takes up the courage to change , and design a proper design , it would resolve the problems that are hampering the design process for innovation .
If we were n't always greedy for more , just imagine how different the world would have been .
Just an hour without electricity would make life intolerable for everyone .
The boom of innovation and technology in the past few decades has been tremendous .
However , the standard of research and innovation in every country varies to a great deal .
This is influenced by the different prevailing social and economic atmospheres .
The first thing that comes to one 's mind when one reads about India is its vast size and a whopping population of over 1.1 billion ( Population Council , 2009 ) .With such a vast population , the onus on the government to ensure the welfare of the people is tremendous .
With India being a democratic country , the major revenue for the government is taxes paid by the people .
With the standard of living not being quite high , the revenue earned by the government is also quite limited .
Therefore , the amount of money the government can afford to spend on research projects is quite little compared to other countries .
One of the major responsibilities of the government of any country is providing quality education to the nation 's children .
These children then end up in manual labour .
These children may one day have turned into great thinkers and scientists ,but due to the lack of proper facilities , they drop out of school .
It is no wonder that India lags behind in technological innovations and research .
However , in the cities , the quality of education is world class .
Some of them leave the country in search of better prospects in the developed countries .
The chance of earning huge sums of money and of obtaining a quality lifestyle makes them leave their country as though they are leaving their house to take a leisurely stroll .
With the government spending huge sums of money on them and these people not even repaying the government by working here and paying taxes here , their departure is a huge blow for the government .
With such highly educated individuals leaving the country , the scope for leading research becomes quite limited .
Another factor is that a lot of the developed countries attract foreign talent .
With all these factors playing a role , the engineering design and innovation in India is significantly hampered .
Steps have been taken to minimise the effects of these factors , but there is still a long way to go to see all these factors vanishing altogether .
Innovation engineering has been a commonly recurrent phrase in the industries in the recent years .
The process of concept generation , product testing and product implementation requires a lot of resources .
In the Singapore society which is relatively result orientated , people tend to be afraid to try out new ideas as they are afraid they will lose out to the intense competition they face from others .
Hence , engineers would rather stick to tried and proven methods that are seen to be effective , instead of exploring alternative methods .
Without having gone through failures , new and better processes would not be properly developed , and thus optimisation would not be achieved .
Due to this problem , fresh ideas would not even have a chance to be developed , not to say move towards the implementation of the idea .
has gradually developed into an inflexible culture , where our workers choose to stick to current beliefs rather than try out new ideas .
Generating new concepts does not just require a single day of effort , as people believe , but instead requires a longer thought process which may take days or even months .
This has given rise to various government bodies efficient in international operating and manufacturing standards .
Innovative engineering requires the engineer to venture into areas which have yet to be explored , which makes experience even more vital , as it would allow problems to be identified even before they occur .
Such problems would most probably not have been explored by current engineers .
As the third biggest country with the largest population in the world , China still faces some unavoidable problems of engineering design processes for innovations .
Two major problems among these are : the low acceptance of engineering design and the complex procedures of verification for licensing for engineering projects .
The majority of Chinese citizens only receive junior middle school or primary school education as a result of the large population and the developing economy .
Therefore , it is not hard to understand the lack of knowledge on engineering design which results in the low acceptance of engineering design .
Except in flourishing cities such as Shanghai and Beijing , in most parts of China , people seldom hear of engineering design , not to mention understand it .
People do not know how to make use of new technologies and new products so it is easy to imagine the situation where engineering design processes for innovations receive not much or little support from the Chinese government and people .
Sometimes engineering design may interfere with some persons'interests in the short term .
For example , when a kind of new technology is being marketed , perhaps some people who earn a living by the old technology or products like hand embroidery will suffer market competition and even make huge losses .
Without the proper understanding , most people would object to engineering design , not to say support it .
There is no doubt about the trouble caused by such a perspective to engineering projects .
Another serious problem for engineering design is the complex verification procedures for licensing for engineering projects due to the incomplete law system .
In most cases , it costs quite a lot for project managers to get the licence for an engineering project , not just money and time , .
In China , interpersonal relationships are still one of the most important factors necessary to survive successfully in a complex society like China and one has to put in much effort to establish and maintain interpersonal relationships .
Taking into account all of the above elements , there is no wonder high cost in terms of time and labour is required to obtain a licence for an engineering project .
This does not just waste a lot of time in the case of an innovation project , but also .
All the above problems are related to people 's attitudes towards engineering design and the political situation for engineering innovations , implying the difficulties in improving engineering design .
Even though it is a journey of hardships for Chinese innovations in the field of engineering design , which is really suffering quite a lot at the moment , the future for Chinese engineering innovations is still bright with the government striving to achieve the goal for a healthy environment of engineering supervision .
In some countries , nuclear energy plays an important role in power production .
Currently , " nuclear energy supplies about 80 % and 30 % of the electricity in France and Japan respectively " ( ) .
However , these powerful weapons were not within scientists ' imagination of how nuclear energy would be utilised .
Scientists probably had intended to use nuclear energy for peaceful purposes like using it as an alternative source of energy .
Hence , we shall examine how nuclear energy and how it is important to the world now and in the near future .
Nuclear energy was discovered in the early 1990s ( ) .
We shall not go down to the details of that process but it was a major scientific discovery as it led to another form of energy production .
Naturally , nuclear weapons became increasingly sophisticated as nuclear countries reinvented these weapons and vied to be the most powerful nuclear state in the world .
However , the use of nuclear weapons on another country has been non-existent since WWII as countries realize the chaos they could cause .
Using more nuclear energy and less carbon-generated energy to produce electrical energy could mean a significant decrease in greenhouse gases and a cleaner earth to live on .
Countries like France rely on nuclear power as much as other countries rely on carbon to generate electricity .
Hence , nuclear energy might become essential in the near future as the world seeks to solve the energy-related problems such as global warming .
At the same time , just like any other forms that could be used to generate electricity , nuclear power is not a perfect source of energy .
In conclusion , nuclear energy would probably play an important as the Earth 's carbon resources are gradually being depleted .
The creation of NEWater , a technology where used water is treated to become potable , is one of the few examples of success in the research of technology in Singapore .
Prior to this achievement , the PUB ( Public Utilities Board ) faced many obstacles and that included the lack of engineering technology which made the cost of implementation unrealistic .
At the same time , the comfortable state of living in Singapore poses a challenge to provoking the minds of its people to improve their current state of living .
All these may then lead to the slowdown of technological advancement in Singapore .
Parents and teachers emphasize a lot on obtaining 'A ' grades and hence students have a misconception towards education .
Moreover , achieving academic promotion mainly requires students to reproduce their knowledge conservatively without much consideration .
As such , less time is made for attending brain teasing courses which , in almost all cases , are made optional to students and whose importance is not highlighted .
Hence , 'students from Singapore top results in Mathematics and Science among their peers from 41 other countries but when it comes to designing , Singaporeans are way behind their foreign peers ' ( Boston College , n.d. ) .
It is thus evident that Singaporean students are proficient in examination questions yet fail in creativity .
In view of the limited development in creativity of the people here , there is no doubt why the ability to design novel engineering processes is beginning to be seen as an outstanding talent in our society .
Given the comfortable lifestyle they are enjoying , the idea of bringing about a change is not the people 's priority .
For instance , the government has upgraded the facilities in housing estates through the implementation of schemes such as the Lift Upgrading Scheme , and this has brought about the 'tardiness ' in Singaporeans in thinking about further improvements to their life .
Their focus , instead , is directed at their routine occupational job and their own family matters and therefore , the element of creativity is not part of their daily life .
Consequently , these problems result in the failure to generate creative ideas as a solution or improvement to the people 's surroundings .
Surprisingly , what Singaporeans have in mind as the ideal solution may not be in tandem with that of foreigners .
Eventually , without a niche in designing , they will lose out to the 'brains ' from other countries when it comes to employment for 'a designer is a planner with an aesthetic sense'
( Bruno Munari , n.d. ) . Not only is knowledge important , but originality too plays an important role when it comes to being a great innovator .
For example , Singapore needs to , and has already begun to , deviate from its regimental approach of learning .
( ChannelNewsAsia , 2007 ) . The bold decision to invest billions of dollars into R&D will make people realize the importance of innovations to the sustainability of Singapore and no doubt open up more avenues for new discoveries to be made .
All in all , both measures that the Singapore government is taking clearly reflect on its intention to drive Singapore to become one of the leading countries in terms of technology .
This is the sentence that we have all heard many times before when it comes to innovation .
To be able to capture the consumers in the market , we have to be innovative in product design .
However , I think problems like the fixed mindset of the person and the lack of resources may hamper engineering design processes for innovations .
They tend to worry about what others might think and are afraid of criticism by others .
Hence , during a presentation , they present their ideas with little or no confidence because they are afraid of making fools of themselves .
Moreover , if someone receives a negative response , there is a high chance that he will not pursue any innovative attempts anymore .
Sometimes , people have the tendency to make products too complex or are too focused on factors like usability that it results in a design barrier .
Not everyone encourages new ideas .
This will also further hinder creativity .
As a result , the cost of production will be expensive and people would rather choose to design a simple product instead of investing in product innovation and research .
In addition , we have a small talent pool of people with innovative ideas .
As a result of the problems that hamper the engineering design process for innovation , many fail to identify unmet needs of the market , causing the market to suffer .
Instead of having new products in the market to capture the attention of the consumers , the market ends up with many different products having similar features and functions .
Furthermore , as mentioned by Chan in his lecture , many people are willing to pay more for design as well as for new products that they think are simple , practical and useful .
For instance , Apple iPhones were in high demand in the market during its launch because of their design , simplicity and reliability although the features of the iPhones are generally the same as many other smartphones in the market .
In conclusion , it is possible to avoid all aspects which will hamper engineering design processes for innovations by changing the mindset of the people as well as finding alternative ways to solve the problem of the lack of resources .
We should attempt to make changes to our way of life in order to begin a larger change in our lives .
The engineering design process plays an important role in innovation and creativity .
Since the resources in the world are limited and decreasing , many countries are making efforts to develop the designing process to use the resources more efficiently to improve the standard of life .
However , in my country there are still some problems that hamper creativity and design , especially the lack of resources and the behavior of customers .
In this essay , I will discuss these obstacles and how they affect the design process .
First of all , one of the biggest obstacles that hamper the engineering design process in my country is the lack of resources , which includes both human resources and natural resources .
Human resources , in this case , refers to the labor force needed to design products with skill and knowledge .
As a result , the lack of human resource affects the design process at the very first stage .
Another factor that also hampers creativity is the lack of natural resources such as space , time and materials for designing .
For example , in my country , many projects have to be postponed because there are not enough materials to make the products .
When waiting for the resources to be imported from other countries , these projects were still on the paper .
Secondly , the behaviors of the users also cause many problems when putting the products on the market .
Customers are usually afraid of changing the products they are currently usingt to new ones when they think the old ones are satisfactory .
Once they are used to a current product , it is hard to persuade them to switch to a new one because they have to learn how to use the new device .
This may not be a big matter for the young but with the old people , the problem is much greater .
For example , my mother will only use the traditional line-phone and not the cell-phone because making a call with the hand-phone is more complex than just picking up the line-phone handset and dialing the number .
Consequently , a new product , although functionally well designed , could be easily refused if it was not friendly to users .
In this situation , the behaviors of the customers are the key factors which directly determine the success of the product in the last stages of the engineering design process : making the product and bringing it to the market .
In conclusion , the two factors of lack of resources and behaviors of the customers cause great problems to the engineering design process in my country .
They affect most stages of the design process as they can postpone the process or even stop it .
Unfortunately , these problems can not be solved in the short term ; it will require much effort to bring back the knowledge and materials into my country .
Have you ever wondered how many vending machines the National University of Singapore has ?
Believe it or not , it is reported that there are over 100 vending machines in this university alone
( National University of Singapore , 2009 ) . Vending machines are available almost everywhere .
We can see them in hospitals , parks and even jungles !
There is no doubt that this invention has influenced our modern life to a great extent .
However , this technology only came on the market in the early 1880s , although the first vending machine was invented by a Greek engineer named Hero of Alexandria many centuries ago around 10 A.D. to 70 A.D. CITATION Eri06 \ l 1033 ( Jaffe , 2006 ) .
Various factors have contributed to allow such an invention to be widely adopted in today 's world .
The major reason for the popularisation of the vending machine is due to the rising wage cost during the 1880s .
" CITATION Pam09 \ l 1033 ( Schehl , 2009 )
Pennsylvania , the southern state which once supported the idea of slavery , abolished its slavery system .
As the overall standard of living of the public began to rise in cities in the following years , most people were unwilling to take up the job of selling items like chewing gum and newspaper .
therefore the chewing gum company , Thomas Adams Gum , decided to build the first commercial vending machine , selling gums on train platforms CITATION Gum08 \ l 1033 ( Gumballs , 2008 ) .
This effectively saved the cost of employing a worker and improved the efficiency of the sales .
Ever since the first vending machine appeared , many companies have adopted this idea as the public has welcomed such an invention .
The convenience it has brought has definitely played a big part in its success .
From the consumer 's perspective , cumbersome long queues can be avoided when he only needs to have a can of drink .
Furthermore , the simple manipulation of the vending machine and the hygienic storage is widely accepted by the masses .
From the vendor 's perspective , the vending machine is favourable because it allows the selling of stocks that have a very long shelf life .
and the reliability of these vending machines is guaranteed .
Practically , they can be placed at any place , including rural locations .
In countries like Japan and Singapore , where there is a lack of space , the need for a condensed merchandiser which improves space efficiency is furthermore amplified .
As time gradually goes by , the population density of many countries increases .
Devices that free up more available spaces are gaining popularity .
CITATION Nat091 \ l 1033 ( Nate , 2009 ) The need to concentrate all stocks in a small space .
In conclusion , the rising wage costs , demand for a more convenient way of selling certain products and the lack of space have shaped this technological innovation .
In addition , improvements of the vending machine have not come to a halt as it continues to accommodate more human needs .
In years to come , more improved versions of the vending machine will be introduced to the society and bring more benefits to human kind .
The commercial nuclear power industry witnessed the worst nuclear power plant accident in its history in Chernobyl .
The accident raised the question about the safety of the nuclear power plant and the ways that people can prevent such accidents in future .
According to an article by Bernhard Wilpert from Technical University of Berlin , Germany , we can see that if psychology had been applied in the design process of the Chernobyl nuclear reactors , the disaster might not have happened .
After the accident , people tried to analyse what were the reasons that caused the malfunctioning of the power plant .
Several theories were proposed , but they mostly concentrated on two issues : the mistakes of the reactor crew and the deficiency in the design of the RBMK reactor ( a high-power channel reactor called reactor bolshoy moshchnosty kanalny ) ( World Nuclear Association,2007 ) .
These two factors-- one relating to humans and one relating to machines--can be eliminated by carefully using psychology in the design process .
Since a nuclear reactor is described as a " complex high hazard systems " ( Wilpert,2007 ) , adequate and clear cognition is very important not only for but also for all the workers in the manufacturing plant , where their collaboration plays the key role in the work of the plant .
If the Chernobyl reactor crew had had enough information about the danger caused by the reactor when working in low power settings , they would never have performed the test to determine how long the turbines would spin and following a loss of main electrical power supply .
Unfortunately , such tests were still carried out despite the instability of the plant under risky circumstances .
If we had applied psychology in the nuclear power plant , the workers would have been trained well and they would have given the right responses during the accident while running the plant .
However , the operators had broken many important rules of safety just to complete the test quickly : they had diminished the flow of coolant water , disabled the automatic shutdown mechanisms and released the control rods from the machine over the acceptable limit .
These actions resulted in increasing the amount of the energy produced to an uncontrollable level within a very short time and caused the explosions of the reactor .
Once again , the .
Without proper knowledge and problem-solving skills , and behaved in the wrong way when problems appeared .
Secondly , the other reason is the flaws in the design of the RBMK reactor , especially the control rods .
However , the engineer who had created the rods had not expected the chemical structure inside the rod to actually increase the reactions between the radiation atoms the moment they are put into the reactor .
the point is that the designers had made the rods for working in stable conditions , not for such tests like this .
If the designers had applied psychology in the design process , they would have thought carefully and predicted the unexpected problems which might happen with the rods when using them .
Instead , they neglected the standard criteria just to make them simpler and cheaper but , unfortunately , more dangerous .
In addition , when the disaster happened , another serious mistake in building the nuclear power plant that reflected the weak cognition of the importance of psychology in design is that the wall around the reactor was not tough .
As a result , the wall was and radioactivity was released freely into the atmosphere , which was extremely dangerous for humans and wildlife within a large area around the plant .
An absolute evidence that proves the necessity of psychological design is a similar accident with the Three Miles Island nuclear reactor in the US .
In this case , the wall of the reactor which had been built with Europe 's high standards of safety had prevented the radiation from spreading into the air and no one had to die because of it ( Grunwald , 2009 ) .
These examples show that even machine errors can be eliminated by carefully designing and applying psychology in the design process to predict all the scenarios that may happen in the future .
Since the horrible accident of Chernobyl , the old technologies used to build the Chernobyl reactor have never been used again .
In addition , people have been doing research to improve the efficiency , the feasibility and most important the safety of the power plants so that such disasters will never happen again .
It is said that " " ( p ) sychological methods , theories , and findings are becoming increasingly important to design " ( Benson , 2006 ) .
With the increasing collaboration between psychology and design , engineers have been using for the design process to make more reliable and stable products .
Therefore , we can minimize the damage caused by accidents or even avoid them and increase the efficiency of .
According to the news report by Rita Zahara ( 2005 ) , " Singapore is only ranked 15 in the world for its innovative capabilities .
" Despite having a high GDP and a pool of savvy engineers , there are still quite a number of problems in Singapore that are hampering its engineering design processes for innovation .
There are many social and economic factors in Singapore that are hampering the country 's engineering design processes for innovation .
Compared to other countries , although Singapore does not have much technological constraints , there are still a lot of factors hampering inventions and innovations in Singapore .
Two main problems are Singapore 's small economic market and its population holding a resistance to change .
Due to the small geographical size of Singapore , its population is only less than six million people .
Most inventions , be they new or improved from previous inventions , take a vast amount of time and money before they might become an innovation .
Most engineers or designers are reluctant to even try inventing or making innovative products as they know that their inventions will most likely not make much profit , or even worse , might make .
Secondly , Singaporeans ' refusal to take risks and their contentment with their current lifestyles are also causes for the hampering of engineering design processes for innovation in Singapore .
The mindset of resistance to change in Singaporeans greatly prevents good innovative ideas and the acceptance of such ideas .
They do not want any changes to what they already have .
this will cause them not to expect anything more or better and thus , not think of new ideas on how to improve what they already have .
Furthermore , Singaporeans have a strong aversion to risk .
Most Singaporeans do not dare to try new ideas as they fear failing , which usually results in time and money loss .
Singapore 's small economic market and its population holding a resistance to change have some bearing on the engineering design processes for innovation .
According to the book by Ullman ( 2009 ) , there are ten building stages in the engineering design processes .
It will be very hard for Singapore to discover what it still needs when its people are contented with what they already have .
A small economic market is preventing engineers and designers from defining problems and conducting research as they fear it will most likely be non-profitable .
In conclusion , the two main factors contributing to the hampering of engineering design processes for innovations in Singapore are Singapore 's small economic market and its population holding a resistance to change .
The process of inventing and innovating are crucial to all of us .
It is viewed as the most important need among the others .
Therefore , I think medical needs are the one which I should give priority to .
Engineers play a very important role in designing new medical products to suit these human needs .
There are many different medical research areas which engineers could lay their hand on and design products according to stipulated requirements .
The most recent leading medical research areas are medical imaging , tissue engineering , pharmaceutical engineering , stem cell engineering and genetic engineering .
It helps the doctor to diagnose diseases at an earlier stage .
Throughout the years , various types of medical imaging technologies have been invented .
There are two main types of medical imaging : invasive and non-invasive .
The invasive imaging method requires radioactive means to produce medical scanning which would have a possibility of causing harm to the human body but could be used on the majority of human body parts .
The engineering design process could be used on the invention of a new imaging technology .
This new imaging technology must have the advantages of both the non-invasive and invasive imaging .
Furthermore , it has to address the operation cost problem and the type of human body parts where the imaging device can be used on .
Another major concern in the engineering design process of the new imaging technology is providing higher resolution 3D/2D clinical image .
This will help the doctors to analyse a patient with improved detailed images .
Since modern computers continually increase on processing speed and volume of memory , they will provide a huge support in designing better resolution image devices .
The only portion which engineers would need to figure out is how to lower the operation cost of such an imaging device .
In my opinion , the materials of the films and the simplicity of the devices would be important .
With the new resolved imaging technology , more humans would be able to make use of such technology since its cost would be reduced .
Better clinical images would also be provided to the doctors ; as a result , doctors would be able to provide a clearer diagnosis of the disease/illness of the patient .
Eventually , the average lifespan of a human would be prolonged with such devices since early detection of illness would be easier to treat and cure .
Lastly , engineers should view the medical imaging area as their priority since their innovations could resolve a lot of medical problems existing in the modern world .
Good health is still the most crucial area where everyone would wish to make their achievements in after all .
