Have you ever wondered how many cars there are in the whole world ?
According to the article , " World 's Most Congested Cities " ( Malone , 2006 ) , there are about 750 million vehicles ( and counting ) in the world , and at least 50 million cars are being manufactured in the world each year .
And out of the 750 million vehicles , 240 million come from the United States of America ( USA ) , and 850 thousand come from Singapore ( US Commercial Service , 2008 ) .
From the above figures , the ratios of human beings to vehicles are approximately 5 : 4 , 1 : 3 and 8 : 8 respectively .
all these figures are crucial in pointing out that vehicles , gasoline-powered vehicles to be more specific , are important and have blended into our lives .
Although this technology is important , many do not know its history and that the development of the gasoline-powered vehicle was actually heavily influenced by political , economic and social factors .
Firstly , there were the economic factors , and these factors can be seen as " natural " and " man-made " .
The " natural " factor that caused a spike in the number of gasoline-powered vehicles was the declining cost of oil at that point in time , which made gasoline-powered vehicles a stronger competitor over the electric-powered vehicles , which were the more commonly- used vehicle .
In addition to the above-mentioned " natural " factor , there were several " man-made " economic factors .
One of the key economic factors that Henry Ford induced was that he collaborated with banks and introduced car insurances and loans ( only if people purchased Ford 's vehicles ) , which actually amplified the effects of the declining cost of oil .
as a result , the gasoline-powered vehicle became even more economically competitive and appealing .
Furthermore , it also became more affordable in the sense that the insurances covered certain repair costs incurred by mishaps ; and loans allowed people to pay up slowly because there was no " pay by instalments " scheme back then .
Consequently , by the laws of supply and demand , Ford increased the supply of gasoline-powered vehicles due to an increase in the demand for gasoline-powered vehicles .
During World War I , the military realised that gasoline- powered vehicles were more convenient to use as compared to electric-powered vehicles because it was difficult to charge the battery of the electric-powered vehicle right in the midst of a battle where there was no electrical source .
This convenience was due to the fact that gasoline was portable and could be brought around on vehicles which allowed vehicles to be re- fueled at any time and place and this could be done very quickly .
Apart from the influence of the military , the government had a part to play as well , because the government implemented biased policies that involved building more gas stations and roads to cater to the gasoline-powered vehicles .
As a result , the electric-powered vehicle continued to lose support , and gasoline- powered vehicles took another point home .
the presence of these social factors actually determined the fate of the electric-powered vehicles .
However , these social factors , which were partly caused by the overpowering economic and political factors , " pushed " people to choose the gasoline- powered vehicles .
The people were made to believe that the gasoline-powered vehicle was the " byproduct of market competition and engineering advancement , not a product of compromise and negotiation " ( Dr. Sovacool , 28 August 09 ) , which , in actual fact , was not the case .
Due to meritocracy and freedom , people eventually " chose " the gasoline-powered vehicles , and brought electric-powered vehicles to eternal rest .
The above factors gave gasoline-powered vehicles their place in the market , even though electric-powered vehicles were better in terms of the technical aspects .
For instance , electric-powered vehicles were cleaner because they did not produce any harmful byproducts from combustion , and they were quieter , more luxurious and safer because they did not deal with any forms of combustion or heat .
Even though electric-powered vehicles were relatively more superior in the technical aspects , due to the factors mentioned above , the technical aspects were and people were not fazed by the potential problems they might face if they chose the gasoline-powered vehicles .
In this case , if vehicles are not as important , and we do not depend on them to such a large extent , World War I would not have had such a drastic effect on the extinction of the electric-powered vehicle and banks might not have approved the implementation of the insurances and loans .
" Engineering is the creative process of turning abstract ideas into physical representations " , says Khandani .
This means that engineers need creativity to make new useful things , and this is exactly what engineers in Indonesia lack , along with a sense of innovation .
The two main cause of this situation are Indonesia 's education system which limits the student 's creativity and the lack of structured government programmes regarding research and technology .
The first problem is that the education system does not allow students to express themselves freely , causing students to be less curious and therefore not creative .
Some are even so conservative that everything must be done exactly like how they have done it .
On top of that , the questions given in school are usually too straightforward as the questions themselves do not test the deeper understanding of the concepts of the students .
For example , the questions in the national examination are all multiple choice questions .
Therefore , to be able to pass the exam , students do not need to really understand concepts as they just need to memorize and use the correct formula or even try their luck .
This kind of rote learning makes defining problems , which is the very first step of the engineering design process , hard for Indonesian students .
Furthermore , this forms a habit among the students that they also apply in real life , which makes them ignorant about how things work as they become concerned only about how to use those things .
Instead of discovering and solving problems around them , they tend to avoid them and wait for someone else to solve them .
With this kind of attitude , it is quite impossible for someone to innovate .
To make matters worse , even when someone survives that kind of education and has bright ideas , the government will not give him the needed support to innovate , such as providing enough funding for Research and Development ( R&D ) in Science and Technology , or facilitate ease of taking loans for new businesses in these areas .
This is because most developing countries ' governments , like Indonesia 's , still do not yet realize that a good innovative culture in the country can actually solve other problems like poverty and basic education opportunities .
The minuscule R&D expenditure of less than 0.2 % , in 2001 , of the GDP clearly shows this lack of priority ( Krishna , n.d. ) , especially when compared to Singapore 's 2.19 % , in 2002 ( Agency for Science , Technology and Research , 2003 ) .
Therefore , as they do not have structured programmes regarding research and technology , there are only a few job opportunities in the science and technology sector , further discouraging engineers to innovate .
Thus , , prefer to have secure jobs in other more profitable sectors such as finance and banking .
This leads to a situation of no improvement in engineering in Indonesia .
Despite the poor education system , there are still a lot of innovative and creative people in Indonesia who want to become real engineers .
This makes Indonesia lose many of its best people .
" Build a better mousetrap , and the world will beat a path to your door " , said Ralph Waldo Emerson .
Eleven years ago , Singapore welcomed its first Newater plant , which was a turning point in the history of the development of Singapore 's technology .
Newater represents the technology that purifies used water to make it clean and drinkable again ( The Write Staff ) .
During the last decade , the number of Newater plants has increased to four .
Currently , a new one is under construction .
What is more , in the near future , 30 % of the supply of water in Singapore will come from Newater .
In the history of Newater , the government , the lack of water resources and the development of other technologies have had a significant influence on the development of Newater .
First of all , the government has played a determining effect on the development of Newater .
Concerned about the water supply situation in Singapore , government officials decided to focus on the Newater technology to meet the water demand in Singapore especially for the industry and for commercial use ( The Write staff ) .
Thus , the successful development of Newater is due to sufficient funding invested by the government .
With the support of the Singapore government , the technology of Newater has blossomed and the fifth Newater plant was successfully set up in the Chanqi area this year .
Besides the support of the Singapore government , a lack of water supply pushed the development of Newater .
What is more , about 40 percent of the population around the world and more than 80 countries are dealing with the problem of the lack of water ( ) .
In the case of Singapore , shortage of water results from several reasons such as its geographic position , its climate and its increasing population .
These reasons contributed to the development of Newater .
With the pressure of water shortage , having its own water supply system became more and more necessary for Singapore .
That is how the resource shortage led to the development of Newater .
The government and the lack of water resources are not the only factors that have affected the development of Newater ; the development of other technology has also played an important role in accelerating the development of Newater .
In the 1970s , Singapore was already paying attention to the technology of its own water supply system ; however , the cost was enormous and the technology was immature ( The Write Staff ) .
However , the development of material science has made the technology of microfiltration succeed .
Meanwhile , there have also been some other breakthroughs in the technology which have helped the development of Newater .
The development of Newater is a good example to demonstrate this .
The government invested funds to support the research on Newater .
In addition , resource crises , especially the shortage of water , pushed the development of Newater .
Meanwhile , the development of other technologies made Newater possible .
All of these factors have had a positive effect on the development of Newater and made it succeed .
As time passes , more and more new technologies are being discovered or created . These technologies can be classified in two main categories : one is the technologies which are developed by research , the other type is the technologies which result from serendipitous discoveries .
This article will discuss the similarities and differences between these two types of technologies .
" ( Bellis , 2009 ) Penicillin was discovered by Alexander Fleming while he " ( was observing ) that colonies of the bacterium Staphylococcus aureus could be destroyed by the mold Penicillium notatum .
" ( Bellis , 2009 ) After Fleming observed that , he paid much attention to Penicillin and discovered that Penicillin could kill many kinds of bacteria .
This important finding , however , was not given a lot attention until the 1940s when " Howard Florey and Ernst Chain isolated the active ingredient and developed a powdery form of the medicine .
" ( Bellis , 2009 ) Penicillin is " the first drug that was effective against many previously serious diseases " ( Wikipedia , 2009 ) . Although many bacteria are resistant toward Penicillin now , it is still in wide used .
Secondly , the telephone was invented by Alexander Graham Bell in 1876 and " by 1884 , long distance connections were made between Boston , Massachusetts and New York City .
" ( Inventor , 2009 ) Bell was very interested in helping deaf people which led him to invent the telephone .
In addition , " the telephone came as a direct result of his attempts to improve the telegraph .
" ( Bellis , 2009 ) The invention of the telephone was not a coincidence , but the result of long-term research .
nowadays , the telephone plays a very important role in our life , as we can hardly live without them .
From the above paragraphs on Penicillin and the telephone , we can easily see some similarities and differences between the two .
First of all , both of these two technologies have benefited us and improved our life very much . Both have helped us in some aspects : Penicillin has helped us to deal with some diseases which were hard to cure , while the telephone has helped us to communicate with others more easily and made the world much smaller .
Secondly , both technologies have matured after a long time of conscientious research .
Both Penicillin and the telephone were not used for years after they were discovered ; many people put a lot of effort to make them more and more useful .
The only difference between them is that Penicillin was found by accident while the telephone was invented with clear aim .
In conclusion , both Penicillin and the telephone help people significantly and both are the products of hard work and .
The difference between them is whether the inventor had a clear purpose or not , which Bell had and Fleming had not .
Human needs are always unsatiable .
At the same time , health problems also created great needs for advanced medical technologies and facilities .
As years went by , industrialization emerged in many countries to meet various people 's needs , like job opportunities and economic growth .
However , the big success of industrialization has created a problem for our modern people : how can we save our fast degrading environment ?
Thus , designing technologies in an environmentally friendly manner is one of the greatest necessities in order to protect our living environment and to ensure sustainable economic development .
After a problem has been defined , which is the first step of engineering design , engineers need to gather pertinent information about the problem .
For example , engineers who focus on designing environmentally friendly transportation tools must have the basic knowledge about the products of different types of fuel combustion and how they affect the environment .
They should also be updated about the latest methods to generate energy in environmentally friendly ways , such as through generating renewable energy like solar energy , tidal energy or wind energy , and their respective advantages and drawbacks .
Engineers can move on to the next step once they are equipped with the necessary knowledge .
The second step of the design process is generating different solutions to problems .
For example , engineers basically come up with two main ways to make machineries and transportation tools .
The first way is changing the way energy is generated , such as changing petrol engines which produce carbon dioxide and hydrocarbons to fuel cells which only produce water and oxygen .
This solution can be further by considering different types of methods to generate energy in less polluting ways .
The other solution is to deal with the polluting products generated along the way .
For example , catalyst convertors are installed in cars to convert the toxic gases carbon monoxide and hydrocarbons produced from incomplete combustion to the non toxic gases carbon dioxide and water .
Although different ways of solutions may be found , not all are practical , so engineers also need to analyze and select a suitable solution .
For example , both of the two solutions discussed above are theoretically correct , but today we only see converters being installed in cars .
This is because changing the ways to generate energy is very costly and the safety of such methods is unpredictable .
For example , fuel cells are very expensive , so their cost of production will be so high that they will be unmarketable .
Another example is that of hydro-powered cars , which actually have been produced but not used widely due to the fact that hydrogen is flammable , so there are still big concerns of consumers ' safety .
In this step , engineers will also look at other factors like economic and social factors to filter the solutions .
When we look around , we can see the efforts put in by engineers in products such as energy saving light bulbs light bulb , solar water heaters , car catalytic converters and so on .
These products are produced only after a long and complicated designing process .
We should really be grateful to engineers who work so dedicatedly to satisfy our needs .
Roger ( 2003 ) explains the difference between technological determinism and social determinism or the social construction of technology .
Indeed , technology is a product of society and obviously is influenced by norms and values of the social system .
On the other hand , technological determinism is the belief that technology causes changes in society and this implies that technology is somehow autonomous .
Roger does not agree with this belief .
Let us take a look at one example of a great human work in the late centuries : nuclear weapons .
We are going to look at the definition and some factors that make a nuclear weapon become a weapon .
First of all , let us look at the definition first .
According to Wikipedia , " ( a ) nuclear weapon is an explosive device that derives its destructive force from nuclear reactions , either fission or a combination of fission and fusion .
" Let us recall the Nagasaki and Hiroshima tragedies , during which both cities were destroyed completely because of this thing .
From that time onwards , nuclear production has been getting more popular all the time .
In " 50 Facts About U.S. Nuclear Weapon " , it is stated that the cost of the Manhattan Project ( through August 1945 ) was 20,000,000,000 USD .
Although it costs a great amount of money , those nuclear countries are still improving their nuclear capabilities .
Some wonder why people want to spend so much money on such things .
Usually when a country creates nuclear power , the main purpose is to make other countries respect and fear that country .
This is very useful in the military aspect .
My former history teacher one day said , " To create peace , we need big power .
" This means that if I have enough power to knock you , your friends and your family down , then it is very logical that you would want to make peace with me because you know that I am capable of doing awful things to you .
That is why people ( in this case , countries ) want to be strong so they try to develop something powerful .
As technology gets better and better , the way people fight with each other is also becoming more advanced .
A long time ago , people fought using wood , rocks , bones , etc. And then they knew about metals , so they used spears , swords , arrows , etc in their wars .
The next phase was the gunpowder stage .
Finally , we have arrived at this nuclear stage .
, including war .
That is , we just need to type some commands on our computer and click a button to launch a rocket .
I have noticed that people are actually trying to be more efficient ( from going to the field and using rocks as a weapon to using buttons on the computer only ) and this is the second reason why people keep spending money to improve nuclear weapons .
To conclude , technology depends on social factors .
It is just like a knife ; you can use it for good ( such as to peel fruits ) or for bad ( such as to kill someone ) .
Nuclear power is one such example .
The military aspect has contributed a lot to technological improvements .
In addition , there are still a lot of aspects that contribute to technology as well .
Before the 1950s , most electricity was created by burning fossil fuel , and no one was aware of other forms of energy .
After the second world war , the whole world was busy building their economies and industry .
Hence , the need for fossil energy became more and more serious .
At that time , a few countries found that only relying on fossil energy was not enough and that there should be another efficient energy source to tap from .
A few years later in the U.S. , the world 's first nuclear power plant was set up .
Although some scientists and politicians in a few countries felt that some time in the future fossil energy would be used up , the governments did not give enough attention to developing another efficient energy source because there was still enough fossil energy in store for the near future .
It was only decades later that people found out that the fact that fossil energy is nonrenewable and fast depleting is only a minor problem , and that the more serious is that the world 's average temperature is increasing since the final product of burning fossil fuel is carbon dioxide , which is the main source of aggravating the greenhouse effect .
The use of fossil fuel causes much pollution and even ruins the lungs of many kinds of creatures , including human beings .
From an ecological standpoint , the world should decrease the use of fossil fuel and try to find other ways of generating energy .
As a consequence , to invest in nuclear energy has become quite important and urgent .
And the development of nuclear energy has been invigorated .
However , when fossil fuel prices fall , can any country resist ?
During the 1970s and the 1980s , influenced by excessive industrial development , the world 's economies reached a high point but at that time , fossil fuel prices were decreasing .
This made those nuclear power plants which were under construction less attractive to develop .
However , in 1973 , France and Japan suffered an oil crisis .
Their governments could not pay for their high oil debts so these two countries decided to depend on nuclear technology .
In other words , France and Japan were forced to invest in nuclear technology .
What is surprising is that today 80 % of the electricity in France is supplied by nuclear energy .
In Japan the percentage is also as high as 30 % ( Beder , 2006 ) .
However , not all countries can afford the price of building up a nuclear power plant .
Take the U.S for example .
The U.S. is the country with the most nuclear power plants , and is well known for their technology in this area .
However , in the U.S. , to build up an ordinary nuclear power plant will cost as much as $ 6- $ 10 billion .
However , it is certain that in the future , .
When all the countries are aware of this point , it is only a matter of time nuclear energy will be generated all over the world .
.
No wonder the destructive force of nuclear weapons is terrible .
The original goal of developing nuclear technology was to invent weapons .
It is a fact that if a country has nuclear weapons or technology , it can produce a nuclear deterrent , which helps the country gain a higher position in international negotiations .
However , this is prohibited by UN laws .
As nuclear technology becomes so important , it is necessary to have an international organization to supervise the process of every country 's nuclear development .
Thus , WANO ( World Association Nuclear Operator ) has been set up .
As WANO begins to discharge its duties , the world 's nuclear development is now progressing the right way .
In 2007 , 14 % of the world 's electricity came from nuclear power and it will be seen a few years from now that nuclear energy will benefit the whole world .
As many big cities in the world are facing water crises , as acid rains become increasingly frequent , and as the number of lung cancer patients keeps going up , environmental protection has become one of the most vital needs of humans .
To satisfy humans ' need and contribute to protecting the environment , engineers seek to design and invent products in an environmentally friendly way .
Through the engineering design process , we can see how engineers satisfy that need .
According to Khandani ( 2005 ) , there are five steps in solving designing problems .
To design and produce something more environmentally friendly , engineers should pay more attention to environment-related information when searching for pertinent information to help them in their design .
For example , suppose an engineer is looking for a material for meal boxes of take-away food .
Apart from information about cost , weight , water resistant ability , and so on , he needs to pay extra attention to environmental information like whether the material can be biodegraded or recycled .
Taking this environment-related information into consideration helps make more environmentally friendly decisions .
The second step is to analyze and select a solution .
Usually , engineers will come up with more than one plan as they design a product .
They need to analyze and evaluate the plans and decide on a final plan .
In the Engineering Design Process , Khandani ( 2005 ) shows us how engineers evaluate different plans .
Firstly , they need to decide the criteria for evaluating design plans .
They need to perform several types of analysis on each design plan .
These types of analysis are the criteria for evaluating the plans .
Next they value each criterion according to its importance , and give a mark representing how important it is .
After that , they evaluate each aspect of the design against the corresponding criterion .
Based on how well that aspect fits the criterion , they give a mark .
Lastly , they calculate the points for each plan and compare them .
Then the mark of each aspect of the plan is multiplied by the number representing the importance of this criterion and the total mark is added up .
By comparing the total mark of the different plans , they decide on the final plan .
If he can increase the importance of the factors related to environmental protection , he may use a substitute for phosphorus , or cleanse the waste water before discharging it .
Then the process and product would be more environmentally friendly .
If engineers can think more about the environment when designing , the product will become very environment-friendly .
Government Regulations and Public Opinions of the Development of Electric Bicycles in China
One typical image remembered by the world about China is its astounding number of bicycles on the roads : swarms of people riding bicycles filling the roads which are not really narrow .
since the year 2000 , another phenomenon has occurred on the roads of the cities in China : electric bicycles .
According to data on reliable Chinese websites , in 2004 alone , 6750000 electric bicycles were produced by more than 1000 factories all over China and these numbers are expected to increase by many times by the end of 2010 .
With the maturing of the technologies of electric motors and long-life batteries , multiple types of electric vehicles could have been created .
Previously existing government regulations and public opinions on road safety have played important roles in shaping the electric bicycle in China into what it is today .
previously existing government regulations had a tremendous effect on the development of electric bicycles when it comes to the size and speed of these bicycles .
Before the e-bike ( electric bicycle ) we see now which is light ( lighter than 20kg ) and slow ( maximum speed is less than 20km/h ) , there are also a number of other kinds of electric vehicles being developed .
They are more like electric motorbikes which are much more powerful and , of course , heavier .
However , because of the government regulations on city transportation under which all means of transportation on the road are grouped as either motor or non-motor and nothing in between , the prototype of the heavy electric bicycles was nipped in the bud as it could not be categorised as either of the two because of its variety of performance .
The later electric bicycle was then designed to be more like a normal bicycle and was only allowed to be ridden on non-motor roads . It is light but moves automatically .
People can even ride it just like riding a bicycle when it runs out of power .
Apart from government regulations , public opinions have also had significant effects on the development of the e-bike .
Data on road traffic accidents were collected .
In Hangzhou , the capital city of Zhejiang province , the number of accidents caused by e-bikes increased over three years
Though the number was relatively small compared with those caused by cars and motorbikes , people were becoming more and more concerned about the safety of e-bikes and a series of public discussions were then carried out to discuss how to make the e-bike a safe vehicle on the roads .
Finally , the speed limit was set at 20km/h which is quite at the lower end of what the technology allows the e-bike to do .
Then all the e-bike industries began to improve performance in other areas of the e-bike like battery life and noise rather than speed and loading ability .
In order to meet the requirement of government regulations and public opinions , the development of the e-bike has gone through several changes ; therefore it has been shaped to the e-bike we see now .
Hopefully , the next typical image left by China to the world will be that of the e-bike .
In 1936 , the first public video telephone was developed .
At that time , both interactants of a video telephone had to simultaneously go to special post office video telephone booths to use this service .
It was n't until the 1980s that , with the development of the IT chip , transmission technology , digital communication , video codec technology and integrated circuit technology , the videophone became truly usable .
At that time many predicted that the videophone would be very popular someday and it would be loved by the public .
However , in recent decades , there has been almost no market for the videophone and the videophone has not been integrated into our lives .
One of the reasons why the videophone could not become popular is that there were technical problems .
But apart from the technical factor , the development of the videophone was mainly limited by some social and economic factors .
The videophone was very expensive when it was first launched .
Even today when the technology is so advanced , the price is still quite high .
One videophone roughly ranges in price between S $ 200 and S $ 1000 .
In addition , the videophone costs much more than the normal phone to use especially when a user takes a long distance call .
The second reason is privacy issues .
When they are talking , they want to be relaxed and feel at ease .
Videophone users also commonly look at the video screen and not at the video camera , causing the eyes to take on an unnatural awkward glance , as the camera is usually just positioned away from the screen ( Videophone , 2009 ) .
For a long time , although there were some companies producing videophones , different kinds of videophones from different companies could not communicate with each other because they did not share a standard .
texting and instant messaging , which are commonly available on all video-enabled cell phones and web chat programs ) ( Videophone , 2009 ) .
Nowadays , with the fast development of the Internet , more and more people are accepting the idea of video chatting through some Internet chatting software .
Thus , the appeal of using the videophone is becoming lower and lower .
It sounds like a tragedy that this great innovative device has not been used or even seen by most people since it was invented in the 19th century .
The lesson we should gain from this is that social and economic issues can indeed shape the development of a new product .
Hence , considering social and economic aspects before the implementation of an innovation is important .
Normally , skunk works generate innovations more quickly than the conventional R&D organizations , for workers in skunk works work " on a crash basis to create an innovation " ( Rogers , 2003 , p.144 ) .
On the other hand , conventionally generated technology probably takes a longer time ; for example , another revolutionary invention , light bulb , was first generated in the 1800s .
Workers in skunk works have stronger motives than those in the conventional organization .
The result is that researchers in skunk works generate innovation faster .
Besides the differences of time and cost , nevertheless , when coming to the commercialization stage , products transferred from technology in skunk works are sometimes not so mature as those transferred from conventional R&D organizations due to the time limitation .
On the contrary , conventional R&D organizations have more time to make their innovation more customer-friendly and more mature in technology .
However , they have higher requirements for the personnel and capital , which are difficult for some companies that are in shortage of capital .
Prior to the Industrial Revolution in the 19th century , the needs of people were just basic-food , clothing , air and last but not least , shelter .
Well , in order to have better transportation , design processes are needed to fulfill the need .
Transportation which is cheap and safe , environmentally friendly and uses alternative source of energy , is most desirable .
One of the eminent challenges faced by modern transportation is to depend less on fossil fuels .
With the rate of usage of fossil fuels - at three billion barrels per year now - , it will not take long before fuels get depleted .
According to a presentation made by Osman Chughtai and David Shannon fossil fuels will run out in 17 years minimum or a maximum of 50 to 70 years .
Nevertheless , other transportation problems like producing too much pollutants such as nitrogen oxides .
Pollutants produced have been proved to have had an enormous effect on the Earth 's ozone layer , corroding the ozone layers and exposing humans to deadly ultraviolet rays .
To add to the problems stated above , the world currently needs better transportation , in terms of safety and functionalities as well as cost .
First of all , engineering processes provide the foundation for research to get a new state-of-the-art design .
Recently , there was groundbreaking news stating that engineers found a technology called H2CAR process , a process for producing fuels from plants or what they call the process-biomass .
Besides research , development processes enable engineers to produce designs that will be tested on real ground .
In this case , transportation like cars must be able to withstand extreme weathers and must be aerodynamically shaped for maneuverability .
In a nutshell , design processes are the main essence for a better future transportation , in terms of fuel type , environmentalenvironmental friendliness , functionalities as well as cost .
This need must be taken seriously in order to secure a brighter future -- a future where people do not need to travel on bicycle or on foot .
