But seven out of ten mobile phonephone users are not using Chinese brands .
How can Chinese enterprises compete against foreign mobile phone companies ?
History has witnessed how mobile phone markets have always been broadened by new features of the phone .
Motorola 8900 which was available in market in the year 1995 was firstly featured with a cover so that wrong press of button was avoided .
In the same year the first self-chosen ring tone was heard from Ericsson GH398 .
The first folding phone was Motorola 328C born in January 1999 . Nokia 7110 is the first mobile phone with a wap browser which was released in October 1999 .
Hagenuk CH9771 was the first mobile phone with its antenna inside the phone .
As the mobile phone is built up by so many parts , there are various ways of innovation .
Appearance means much because people treat mobile phones not only as communication tools but also as a kind of beloved toys .
I phone has conquered the whole world but failed to enter Japan 's market because of two reasons : First , Japanese like to own a unique style of phone but iphone has only one style which would cause embarrassment when Japanese meet other iphone users .
But iphone does not have them .
As for appearance there are four major designs : straight , flip , slide and rotation .
Such as a straight phone with 3-row,4-column keyboard .
To protect the fragile touch screen , the keyboard can act as the cover and leave only a little part of the screen outside when not used .
There are plenty of functions now but the newer the better .
A phone can act as a telescope in Birdnest during the Beijing 2008 Olympic Games by using the camera and its zoom function .
It can also design a diet for its owner to lose weight .
Innovative mobile design is important also because designers can dominate both and market .
A new design is protected by its copyright so .
To conclude , China 's mobile industry needs to work on innovation of phones ' appearance and function .
Problems significantly hamperhamper innovation in engineering design processes for innovations . Along with the rise in living standards , people 's demands for goods increase .
At the same time , people pay more attention to the quality of the goods .
In order to meet the demands of modern society , we need higher efficiency and more advanced technology .
Thus , the innovations in engineering processes are more and more important .
But in real life many problems hamper engineering design processes for innovations .
The two most significant are the state of information communication which is not smooth and corruption .
In practical production , only the workers directly use production equipment .
The senior management and the boss , who have the right to change and introduce new equipment and technologies , seldom care about the real condition of production .
And the state of information communication is not smooth , workers can not relay the problems that they found in production to the people who have the power to make decisions .
In this case , after a long time the workers lose enthusiasm to think about how to solve the problems .
At the same time , it loses the opportunity to save costs and increase production efficiency .
It often causes more serious problems than other problems .
It is a very serious problem that exists in almost every area .
For leaders in companies and factories , if they are corrupt , they only care about their own benefits and ignore many others .
There are many cases of corrupt leaders leading their whole companies or factories to go bankrupt .
And there are also some cases which are more scary .
Some set up a company just to cheat ; all their actions are about cheating for money from consumers or other companies .
For the staff , if they are corrupt , they would not focus on their jobs any more .
Furthermore , they would envy others who have a higher position or make more money or make greater contributions .
In such case , they may create a lot of bad things , maybe to frame others , in order to get more benefits for themselves .
For workers , they would only care about how to please their leaders to receive more benefits and not care about production .
The worse influence is for corrupt people to affect the general mood of a company or a factory .
To conclude , there are many existing problems hampering engineering design processes for innovations .
In this era of globalization , engineering design has been emphasized by governments all over the world , such as the United States , Russia and France .
This is because the development of engineering design could bring many advantages to a country 's economy and society .
Currently , scientists perceive a future problem and launch some research to overcome it .
If we observe our surroundings , we can see many inventions with technological creativity such as computer , automobile and other electrical appliances .
Nevertheless , there are some problems which significantly hamper engineering design processes for innovations in my home country , Malaysia , and impact certain stages of engineering design .
As we all know , if we want to improve our engineering design , we need to launch much research .
Subsequently , a lump sum of money to be used to launch all such research , but our government is not able to invest much money on all .
So , financial problem arises and constrains the engineering design processes for innovations .
Malaysia is a country which is still developing and not as wealthy as other western developed countries such as the United States , France and Germany .
Hence , we lack money to improve our facilities for research such as well-equipped laboratories and other highly technological instruments .
In fact , this will cause engineering design processes to be interrupted halfway because of lack of highly technological instruments .
For instance , if we want to design a race car , we need some highly technological instruments to do research on car engines and other parts of a car .
And although we have already found important information through research , we still can not continue analyses of design solutions because of lack of highly technological instruments to be used for investigation .
Much of the research engineering design carried out in modern countries been done successfully .
In fact , the lack of professionals in engineering fields has resulted in the failure of some research .
For instance , some of the automobile research due to the lack of professionals .
The stage of analysis of design solution has been constrained because of limited knowledge and lack of professionals .
Hence , some forums on engineering design should be held between our country and other modern countries .
In a nutshell , financial problem and lack of professionals in my home country should be solved as soon as possible to improve our engineering design processes .
Hence , the private sector , the government and also citizens should work hand in hand in order to encourage more investment in engineering design research and produce more professionals in the field of engineering design in the future .
Indonesia , a country with more than two hundred and thirty million citizens , is South East Asia 's largest country and economy to date .
Yet Indonesia still trails behind its neighboring countries such as Malaysia , Thailand , and even The Little Red Dot : Singapore , in terms of advancement in design-based technology .
It is commonly believed that the slow rate of technological growth in Indonesia is caused by two major problems which may hamper the innovative engineering design process .
Firstly , Indonesia lacks a culture of innovation .
According to statistics published by UNICEF in 2007 , only fifty percent of Indonesian citizens are urbanized , which means the other half live in rural areas with little exposure to the modern world and technology .
People living in traditional villages live very simple lives .
They keep their ancestors ' traditions , and sometimes prefer the traditional way of doing things to labor-saving modern devices ; for example ; some farmers prefer buffalo-driven ploughs to tractors .
Moreover , farmers still rely on government supplies and subsidies , which run into a lot of logistical problems , instead of innovating their own way of solving problems .
Besides , most universities in Indonesia are more teaching based based and less research intensive than those in Japan or The States ; that makes Indonesian university students less creative and innovative in problem solving .
The second problem that may hamper the engineering design process in Indonesia is due to its excessive and cheap natural resources , space , and workforces .
As mentioned above , Indonesia has more than two hundred and thirty million citizens , and its unemployment rate is considered high at 9.1 % ( Reuters , 2008 ) .
Thus , Indonesia needs to create jobs for its people ; one way is by developing its agricultural businesses , which have been a hot topic lately during the presidential campaign .
Prabowo Subianto , son of Sumitro Djojohadikusumo , former minister of economics for both Indonesia and Malaysia , during his vice presidential campaign opposed a solution to current Indonesian problems . He promised to create jobs by developing bio diesel producing palm plantation in Indonesia , which may absorb about 6 million workforces .
It is apparent that innovative and labor-saving devices will not work in Indonesia ; the new invention seemed to be more expensive compared to the traditional way .
After the invention is patented , there is nobody who is willing to buy it because in Indonesia 's case it is not cost efficient .
Another effect is demotivation of young engineers from designing new products , because the rewards the society gives them is not equal to their long-time hardwork .
To tackle them , the Indonesian government has to work hard in developing an innovative culture in the society , and decreasing the people 's dependability on the government .
According to Khandani 's statement " What distinguishes engineers from painters , poets , or sculptors is that engineers apply their creative energies to producing products or systems that meet human needs " , all engineering designs aim to meet human demands .
Now , when society develops , people are looking for new designs to satisfy their comfortable lives .
ThThesese new designs may be demands for entertainment , education or even something beyond our imagination .
However , in my opinion , one of the main concerns in our society is finding a new energy supply to substitute for the old ones which have been depleted due to human exploitation .
In order to solve this urgent demand , engineering plays an important role in finding other alternatives such as nuclear energy , solar energy and geothermal energy .
Evidently , energy has become vital and indispensable in our life , relating to most of everything we deal with .
Because of the influence of energy , natural resources have invisibly caused wars and conflicts between many countries over time .
The recent war between the United States and Iraq in 2000 might be considered to be a typical example .
Although the U.S. has been saying that this war is for anti-terrorism , or more importantly for maintaining peace the world , it is clear that one of the reasons why American troopers stay in Iraq is the benefits of petroleum .
This is a typical example of how important energy is since it has a great impact on our daily life .
Due to the non-renewability of natural " fossil " resources , the more demands society needs , the more exhausted these resources become .
According to the online newspaper Financial Times ( 2006 ) and USA Today news ( 2004 ) , the oil reserves in Trinidad and Tobago will run out in the next 20 years and the world oil reserves will become exhausted just in 40 years .
The process of finding a new alternative energy source , which is not only renewable but also environmental-friendly , has been undertaken for a long time and regarded as an ultimate goal for engineering .
It is extracted from usable energy from heavy atomic nuclei ( for example Uranium 235 ) via of nuclear reactions .
The first nuclear plant was built in Russia in 1984 whose initial electricity production was about 5000KW .
However , the design of nuclear reaction has to meet many rigorous requirements to avoid nuclear releases as well as to isolate radiation from life .
All of these conditions have to be followed strictly ; otherwise it may cause immeasurable consequences .
For instance , one of the most tragic accidents involving radiation release was the Chernobyl disaster which happened in 1986 .
This disastrous accident resulted from weakness in design . Up to now , the neighboring areas still suffer from the radiation .
Another solution is the perpetual resources known as solar , geothermal energy , etc.The solar energy is drawn from sunlight 's energy by many solar panels which are designed to fit house roofs .
This energy is converted into electric or thermal energy to serve our life .
Geothermal power takes the thermal calorie in the entrails of the earth and translates into other energies which contribute an important role in operating turbines and machines .
Geothermal energy is considered as the most potential alternative for nonrenewable energy in the future .
Also , these resources may not be applied and used everywhere on earth due to geographic differences .
In conclusion , I contend that energy problem should be classified as first priority for humans to solve not only because of many huge benefits it provides for people but also because of the critical shortage of energy resources .
In this context , engineering design process meet these urgent needs by finding many feasible solutions such as nuclear energy , solar energy and geothermal energy sources .
Although this process has just had initial achievements , it promises a fully potential energy source in the future which may permanently serve human kind .
Thus , many countries spend more money and time on developing new resources which can be used as a substitute for petroleum .
This can be seen through the increase in research and development of solar cars or other products .
The use of solar energy-related goods has been highly encouraged by environmentalists .
So , I would like to discuss the reasons for innovation in such technology based on economic , governmental and environmental factors .
First of all , as earlier mentioned , petrol price has been fluctuating in recent years . This makes many factories start to worry about the cost and profit they can earn .
Most of them feel unsecured because the cost of petrol may lead to low profit or even red deficit .
In the process we can see many firms and companies start to invest in solar energy areas .
It is because of the cost of batteries .
Presently , there is limitation on the amount of energy the batteries can store as we can only " use solar cells to generate up to 240 watts of electrical power in full sunshine .
As long as we can find a way to increase the amount of energy the batteries can store , the cost will not be much a problem anymore .
So I think , although they have to spend much more on research now , they can definitely save more in the long run .
For example , their enemy may cut down the inflow of the petrol .
This will in turn cause many harmful results including acidic rain or global warming .
And as solar energy comes from the sun , it can be regarded as reproducible and we do not need to worry about if it will be depleted one day .
In conclusion , I think we should decrease the use of petrol-related products and slowly switch towards using the products which need new resources .
Only if we show our interests in and demands for these products , researchers can have motivation and more funds to do their projects .
Their achievements influence the development of every industry .
People 's needs are so various that one prime need must be given priority to avoid distractions .
In today 's world , this need should be people 's demand for fresh water .
As is known , water is a resource that humans can not live without .
Its uses range from climate regulation and industry application to food processing and daily drinking .
A hundred years ago , water was never a concern ,
while today it is different .
It is now commonly recognized that fresh water will be the scarcest resource in the following century .
Some people even assume that the next world war will be fought because of limited fresh water on the earth .
In order to ensure humans ' survival and world peace , engineers should respect humans ' need for water most when designing products .
One aspect engineers should work on to meet people 's need of water is to reduce pollution in the engineering process .
To be exact , there is never a lack of water on earth , but pollution damaged most of the available water sources , such as rivers and lakes .
This can stop pollution in water more thoroughly than government 's fine on water pollution .
In addition , engineers can design a device that can save water .
Therefore , if a device can avoid wasting water in the daily life of each person , it will surely save a considerably large amount of water .
Small devices like taps , water coolers , and washing machines , can all be the targets of engineers .
Engineers should give importance to water-efficiency together with other efficiencies regarding designing devices , so that enough water can be conserved to meet people 's needs .
To sum up , engineering should give priority to people 's need of water first , as water is necessary for human survival .
In order to highlight this need , engineers should emphasize environmental friendliness and water saving in designing .
For the next 10 years or more , Singapore have a high percentage of population consisting of the elderly .
There are a few factors leading to an ageing population like low birth rates and increase in the cost of standard of living .
With the increase in the number of elderly , there would be a need for safety areas , thus products or services should be designed to meet this need .
This product is a smart suit that is equipped with an array of microsensors which are able to detect falls suffered by the wearers and to send alerts to their caregivers .
Besides these functions , the engineers have also included an " impact-reduction " system to reduce the damage done on the wearer when he or she falls .
For the product , we have seen that the engineers have made use of engineering design processes to meet the need .
Firstly , they have defined the problem , which is ageing population , and they have seen the need to invent a product which could give extra safety protection to the elderly .
Secondly , they have brainstormed on the preliminary criteria for a better design for the product ( Khandani , 2005 ) ) .
For instance , in the case of a fire , the temperature sensor would be alerted and will send warning alerts to their caregivers or call for Civil Defense Force immediately .
Furthermore , when considering the design of the product , there is a need to make special considerations that are suitable for elderly use .
Those factors that might need to be taken into consideration when designing the product are inflexible movements and slow response time .
Engineers would have to use the engineering design processes to list out multiple solutions the designing of product ( Khandani , S. ( 2005 ) ) .
In order to make sure the product works well , engineers have to test it before they launch the product .
In conclusion , we have seen that the problems of ageing population could get more serious in the next few years , thus there is a need to design a product that could help to reduce the risks and impacts faced by the ageing population .
Through examples of these two products , we could see that both of them have made use of engineering design processes to meet the need .
And thus , they proved that it is really important to go through engineering design processes when inventing a new product .
Human activities on Earth have depleted Earth 's valuable yet limited natural resources , thus damaging the Earth 's environment .
This causes Earth 's natural resources to be depleted and modify its environment so much that it is no longer suitable for human life .
Therefore , humans have to give priorities to conserving Earth 's natural resources and protecting its environment .
This can be achieved by completely setting aside already available engineering processes , modifying and improving these old processes , or correctly identifying the reasons for the rise of that need .
Firstly , engineering processes that are available now and are widely used can be abolished while new ones can be introduced to perform the functions of their precursors and at the same time fulfil the need .
For instance , humans have always depended on one of Earth 's natural resources , fossil fuels , as an important source of energy .
However , due to human s ' overuse of it , fossil fuels are expected to be completely depleted in the year 2050 .
Therefore , engineering processes of technologies that extract energy from fossil fuels must be superseded and new ones must be introduced to ensure a constant supply of energy for humans .
For example , western powers like countries in Europe and the United States are planning to construct large scale solar energy farms in areas in Africa like the Sahara desert to replace generating energy from fossil fuels .
Therefore , we can see how setting aside old engineering processes and embracing new ones can satisfy that need .
Secondly , instead of removing available engineering processes , they can also be modified so that their original functions are still available but at the same time satisfy the need to preserve natural resources and protect the environment .
For example , transportation systems like cars require fuels like fossil fuels which are processed from a depleting natural resource , fossil fuels .
Furthermore , greenhouse gases like carbon dioxide are produced from these cars which contribute to the notorious greenhouse effect .
For instance , electric cars by General Motors use electricity to power the car 's engine instead of fossil fuels .
This satisfies the need as electricity can be generated from renewable sources of energy like solar and wind energy .
Furthermore , greenhouse gases like carbon dioxide will also not be emitted .
Thirdly , the need can be fulfilled by correctly identifying and analyzing the reason for the rise of that need , so that correct decisions can be made through engineering processes .
For example , CFC gases in the past are a by-product of many of our industries .
These gases caused the destruction of the Earth 's ozone layer in the atmosphere which caused more harmful ultraviolet , UV rays to penetrate the atmosphere , and consequently health problems like skin cancer to humans due to these UV rays .
Therefore , a worldwide policy was implemented to ban the emission of CFC gases into the atmosphere by industries .
Thus , we can see how making correct decisions to prevent pollution to the environment can fulfill the need .
In conclusion , to ensure a sufficient supply of natural resources and a healthy environment for us and our future generations to live in , engineering processes can meet our needs by removing and introducing or modifying available engineering processes and making correct decisions through these processes .
Out of all the human needs in the world , clean water should be given priority compared with others .
In addition , due to global warming , the sea level rises .
Therefore , some precious sources of drinking water , like underground water , are polluted and not drinkable any more , which makes the situation even worse .
In some regions in the world , such as the Middle East and Africa , the shortage of clean drinking water is very serious , which sometimes causes wars .
Water we daily use can be divided into two categories , for drinking and not for drinking .
For example , water we use to flush toilets , to irrigate farmland and to wash cars is not necessary to reach the same hygienic level as the drinking water .
Hence , we may use recycled water to do these jobs so that we can save more clean drinking water for people .
However , this method may not be suitable for developing and undeveloped countries because it costs a lot of money , and the technology required is also very high .
The other way to get drinking water is through desalination of sea water .
Another limitation of this method is that it can only be applied in seaside countries , like Singapore , which means that it is not the first choice of many inland countries .
Therefore , since the two methods mentioned above are both costly and difficult to apply , they can be restricted by the economic and the market and thus , they may be not able to solve the shortage of water in a short period .
It is this kind of hope that motivates humans to develop , to improve , to pursue our dreams , and finally to have such a beautiful world today .
Hope is the most significant contribution which engineers have contributed to the world .
The environment-friendly car is a current human need which should be given priority .
The current car 's technology , the fuel injection , has satisfied that need , but has not satisfied the environment 's need .
Humans need a car which is not only able to transport them easily but also is friendly to the environment .
It is the doctors ' job to apply their creative energies in designing a solution which meets humans ' needs .
First of all , the current car 's technology , the fuel injection , has satisfied humans ' need to travel .
For example , the time taken to travel from one place to another with a distance of a few hundred kilometres has been reduced from 2-3 days to 2-3 hours ; as a result , humans are able to travel instantly .
This indeed makes human s ' means of transportation rising to another level .
Second , in contrast with the benefit fuel injection has contributed to human life , it has , in fact , polluted the environment .
This is due to fuel processing in the car .
For example , fuel injection is exhausting Carbon Dioxide ( CO2 ) as a result of incomplete burning of fuels .
Third , humans not only need to travel but also need a pollution -free environment to live in .
In view of this issue , engineers are needed to design a solution .
According to Khandani ( 2005 ) , products or systems are designed by engineers to meet human needs .
For years , engineers have experimented on designing a solution to this issue .
This eco-car has no fuel tank , therefore , it produces no emissions at all .
Lastly , Japan 's engineers had followed engineering design processes Khandani ( 2005 ) to design their first eco-car .
They argued that the fuel injection system 's problem lies in the fuel it uses .
They gathered information in order to arrive successfully at the right fuel source ; subsequently , they decided to use electricity as the fuel .
The road to success is not smooth ; likewise , Japan 's engineers had gone through a lot of challenges and tests before they arrived at the final prototype of Japan 's first eco-car .
Humans need to care about the environment 's condition in order to preserve it for the new generation .
To conclude , by using engineering design processes , engineers can design products that meet human needs .
For instance in Singapore and Japan , healthcare is emphasized on the elderly due to their aging populations but both execute their policies in different ways .
With a replacement rate of 1.5 children to 2 adults and an estimation that by 2030 , 18.4 % of the population will be made up by the elderly , it is no wonder why Singapore government is promoting reproduction in young couples .
As the population ages , the main users of hospital services will be the elderly .
According to a survey in 2004 , Singapore is one of the unfriendliest countries towards the wheel chair bounded .
Hence , there is a need for us to impove the healthcare services of our older citizens .
In Japan , nearly one quarter of the population is made up of the elderly .
The fast paced society forces citizens to place work as priority over family resulting in a declining population .
Since the number of elderly is increasing , it is important to cater to their needs in terms of healthcare .
The first concern is the living condition of the elderly .
Home care facilities such as hospices , day care centres and nursing homes are built to look after the elderly especially when their family members are unable to do so .
For example , in Singapore , one room apartment with specially installed emergency buttons and lifts is catered to the elderly .
Shopping malls and other common places should be equipped with more ramps and handicapped -friendly escalators .
They should be offered free medical check-ups and treatment if necessary .
In conclusion , healthcare services should not be neglected especially in countries which face an aging population .
Consequently , after years of research and design to alleviate this problem , the NEWater technology was invented .
This is an example of a particular human need which has been satisfied by an engineering design system .
Global warming , as a result , is becoming more and more an issue of rising concern as little has been done to eliminate or substantially reduce pollution .
Time is running out and to protect the sustainability of life on Earth , necessary actions have to be taken immediately , and if not , as soon as possible , and the help of engineering design processes should not be left out .
Subsequently , engineering design processes have made possible the invention of catalytic converters which convert the harmful gases emitted by vehicles into non-harmful gases .
On the flip side , although the problem of emission of harmful gases has been , vehicles today are releasing carbon dioxide , which is a greenhouse gas , instead .
After years of research , then comes the idea of inventing an environmentally-friendly car , also known as an ecocar .
Throughout the years , there has always been a debate on whether technology shapes society , a technologically determinist perspective , or society shapes technology , a socially determinist view .
One such technology that is closely related to this debate is the invention of the automobile .
Due to the influence of these factors , gasoline-powered cars have won over electric cars for years .
Firstly , societal factors like the expansion of cities favor gasoline cars over electric cars .
For example , gasoline-powered cars can travel an average of about 300km on a full tank of petrol as compared to a maximum distance of 150km for a full charge on an electric battery .
Everyone now wants to own a car for convenience and for individualism 's sake .
Take Dubai for instance . They now have an average ratio of 571 cars to every 1000 people .
Therefore , this affects automobiles as people purchase more gasoline powered cars .
The reason is that car manufacturers , in order to retain their market share of gasoline powered cars , will invest time and money to promote gasoline-powered vehicles over the unproven market of electric cars .
A social stigma that electric cars are only meant to be golf carts or less is hence created , and this leads to people purchasing gasoline-powered cars .
Next , technological factors like currently available technology and limitation of resources have also helped shaped automobiles .
Hybrid cars involve either part gasoline and part electric or part gasoline and part compressed natural gas ( CNG ) .
The gasoline-powered car has finally seen a worthy competitor .
However , technological restraints like limited resources have been a set back for hybrid users .
This constraint makes consumers think twice before purchasing a hybrid vehicle .
Imagine if there are no technological restraints and that we could create a self replenishing battery .
Technology and society co-exist and affect one another .
Even until now , we are shaping many other technological inventions .
Who knows , hybrid cars might actually manage to successfully dethrone gasoline-powered cars in the near future .
Electronics such as lights and cars have become essential to human beings over the past years .
However , these electronics though wonderful , consume a huge amount of energy .
One current human need that should be given priority for engineering design is to have cos-saving electronics .
The challenge in having a motion sensor light to automatically turn on and off the lights with the presence of a human being was how to accurately identify the presence of a human being in the area monitored by the sensor .
To overcome the challenge , the motion sensors use infrared energy to detect human beings .
These natural gases are widely available on earth as compared to petrol fuel which is getting limited as oil reserves get depleted .
In order for a car to be powered using CNG , there are certain modifications that needed to be done .
For example , new fuel storage was introduced , and took the name of Integrated Storage System .
In Singapore , public transports such as taxis and buses have converted to CNG .
In addition , according to Channel NewsAsia , there is an increasing number of private cars owners converting their conventional petrol fuel-powered cars to CNG cars .
To sum up , with the depletion of natural resources and high electricity and fuel cost , engineering designing should be given priority cost saving electronics .
Usually , engineers face difficulty in designing a product or coming out with ideas demanded by the public .
An engineer needs to define the problem , gather pertinent information , generate and analyse multiple solutions and finally , test and implement the solution .
However , the two most disturbing problems that may hamper engineering design processes for innovations are the inability of engineers to generate multiple solutions to convince their superior to implement their products or ideas and the failure of constantly creating a product that is in demand .
Firstly , in the aspect of generating multiple solutions , engineers often face the problems of lack of funds and inability to convince their superior that their idea is feasible .
Their idea or product is a totally new concept which people may find hard to accept because of a traditional idea or product that may have been etched in their mind .
For example , in the Singapore National Service , military officers , using their portion of dominant influence , typically make most of the important decisions about innovation .
In addition , low ranking cadets usually fail to convince high ranking officers that their innovative products or ideas may improve the military .
This unmanned combat air vehicle might have been potent enough to replace the ubiquitous manned fighter in the near future .
However , due to the higher officer not having enough trust over the air vehicle being piloted by a human , this unmanned combat vehicle project did not succeed in being implemented .
As engineers , if their ideas or products face constant rejection by their superior , they will stop coming up with new ideas or products as they see no purpose in coming up with new ideas or products and constantly opposing their superiors .
Thus , superiority in companies will significantly hamper engineers ' morale and their design .
Secondly , the other problem that restricts engineering design is the lack of confidence to implement ideas or products that are in demand .
Although in the initial stage response to their products may be good , when it comes to implementing their ideas or products , the response may be different .
Engineers spend a lot of effort in developing these products , but the final products that they design may not be of popular demand .
This type of phone faced rejection because it was expensive and users found it infringing on their privacy .
As a result , sales of these phones were low , affecting the morale of the engineer who designed it .
Facing multiple failures may cause engineers to be disheartened and put them on high alert as they will be more careful when they want to design a product .
They will tend to feel disappointed because they need to solicit a lot of funds , putting in their utmost efforts when developing the products , but only to find out that their products face rejection by the public .
The " best " design solution is always hard to develop because it is one that most completely fulfils a client 's requirements .
Therefore , engineers may just stop at gathering pertinent information , and not go into generating multiple solutions as they worry that their products may not be in demand as expected , which again may hamper their design processes for innovation .
In conclusion , it is usually the lack of ability to convince their superiors and the constant rejection by the public that significantly hamper engineering design for innovations .
Traditional mindsets should be changed and let engineers have a chance to develop their ideas .
Furthermore , engineers should do their research and marketing of their products effectively , such that products that they develop will be of market value .
Meanwhile , many new kinds of innovative inventions come out almost every day , thus changing the way people live .
It is a remarkable fact that technical innovation is viewed differently by different groups of people .
A wonderful invention to a group of people may be disliked others .
In general , the justification of the utility of a specific technology or invention depends on the specific opinions of different group of people .
Space technology is a good example to explain the existence of different views .
Space technology is a kind of highly innovative , highly composite and also highly costly technology .
Its aim is to find out unknown scientific questions and for military use .
The beginning of space technology was in America and Russia .
Then it quickly spread out all over the world .
Nowadays European countries , China , Japan and India all have advanced development in space technology .
Toward this new technique , two opposite opinions exist nowadays .
Governments and scientists think it is worth to spend money and people working on this because it will benefit the whole country .
However , many people think that it is a waste of resources which can be used to improve people 's living conditions .
If we look a little deeper into the causes that lead to the opposite solution , we will find that the focus that specific groups of people pay attention to is , obviously , quite different from each other .
From the governments ' and scientists ' point-of-view , space technology is essential because it is the fundamental thing we need to do to protect our countries and fulfill future needs .
They pay much attention to keep technological developdevelopment moving and concentrate more on huge issues , like military demand , and the future .
That is also the reason why every country tries its best to improve space technology .
Former President of America Reagan even announced the star wars program , although it was given up at the end .
They focus more on current living conditions and the environment .
They simply pay their attention to the surroundings that need improvement to make better living conditions .
With the high cost of space technology development , they will think government focus on this is a kind of waste .
In their opinion , government should spend these money and resources on places which can benefit us .
So , it is not surprising that not all people were satisfied when Chinese Government proudly announced the success of the launching of the Shenzhou-5 spacesuit into the universe .
In conclusion , judgments of technical innovation or development always differ because they are made by different groups of people .
All in all , the differences do really derive from different thinking perspectives .
Because people tend to think about things associated with their own experience and life , different opinions emerge .
Hundreds of years ago , people used to go out riding horses , illuminate the house by candles and start fire using firewood .
And we now go out by buses , light the house by electric lights , start fire using lightersand so on . Nowadays , people live in a very convenient world .
But few may notice that we are facing a serious problem behind all these inventions we are using .
And the shortage of petroleum is the most important issue that we must address .
Why is petroleum very important ?
Without these extracted products from petroleum , cars can not run , planes can not fly , and ships can not be launched .
What What is more , petroleum is a liquid mixture of hydrocarbons which is present in suitable rock strata and is not reproducible for now .
One way is to conserve and save petroleum .
Engineers have come up with some solutions to saving petroleum .
One of the engineer 's solutions is to mix alcohol and petrol together to provide energy .
This solution is now being tested and implemented .
In Wuhan , one of the biggest cities in China , all taxies are operating using this mixed fuel .
When the vehicle starts , it consumes electric power .
That is why we can smell strong petrol when the car starts .
The concept of power system is to let fuel fully used in order to save it .
Hydrogen fuel cell , solar power and nuclear power are the three hottest topics that have interested engineers most .
Research on fuel cell on vehicles was started in early 1960s and it has continuously developed until now .
Most car makers have come out with their own hydrogen fuel cell-powered vehicles .
But hydrogen fuel cell vehicles are still in the testing and implementation phase .
But for the finalized product , the cost should be reduced and the efficiency of the cell should be increased .
The key point in increasing the efficiency of solar power is how to isolate the sunshine .
If this challenge can be solved , the potential of solar power is prodigious .
For nuclear power , it is using the power generated by nuclear fusion .
Nuclear fusion is the same way as the sun in generating its power .
Research on nuclear fusion has been going on for decades , but the progress is not very obvious .
In brief , the energy problem is one of our most serious problems now .
So we need to work on it step by step and follow the right rules to arrive at the best solution to this urgent problem .
However , the above only holds through for those who are not stricken with poverty .
The needs of poor people , most of whom are based in developing countries , are endless .
This is because basic infrastructure is the basis for any country to develop essential facilities like transport , housing and education to help the poor .
The word 'need ' refers to a man 's desire for a certain product or system .
This need is usually identified by the society and may vary from society to society .
Thus , needs which are considered a necessity to some might actually be a luxury to others .
The nomads would prefer to conserve the forests and wildlife so as to be able to carry on with their nomadic lifestyle .
So it is vital for engineers to collect as much information as possible so as to not repeat the mistakes and go down the same slippery slope of their predecessors .
The most logical step after coming up with a few solutions is to pick the best one .
This is actually the decision-making process , after studying the various solutions .
For instance , if a school is being built , based on the land available , few designs would have already been thought off .
Certain schools might be able to hold more students while not proving to be as stable as others that hold fewer students but are very much stronger .
Ironically , this step is one that is followed by most . However , they do not bother to pick out flaws , thus in the end the consumer uses a flawed product .
Possible flaws should be identified so that the product can be improved on later .
In conclusion , I would like to recommend the engineering design process because it is very complete in its steps to provide a solution to those in need .
The establishment of basic infrastructure in developing countries through engineering design will give the poor an avenue to successfully escape from the vicious cycle of poverty .
The world today is experiencing global warming which is caused by the burning of fossil fuels and deforestation .
The first step in the design process is problem definition .
Tapping kinetic energy in wind is a good solution as wind is abundant due to the frequent changes in the atmospheric pressure .
This step announces to engineers that the Earth is in grave danger , thus giving them more motivation to think of a solution .
For example , by defining the problem as the fast decreasing quantity of fossil fuels , engineers gain insight into creating a product which can be used to tap kinetic energy in wind .
Referring to the earlier models of windmills like those built in Sistan , Iran , from the seventh century , which were used to grind rice grains , engineers used the same concept to create wind turbine which converts kinetic energy in wind into electrical energy .
The credibility of the problem needs to be addressed after it has been defined .
The last step in the design process is the testing and implementation of solutions .
The testing and implementation of solutions is closely related to the analysis of the design solution .
Lastly , the testing and implementation of solutions consists of marketability , ergonomics and safety which serve as a check on whether the product is deemed suitable to solve the problem .
Nowadays , engineering design products are everywhere .
Engineering systems play important roles in all fields , for example , entertainment , healthcare as well as education .
Although they are essential for all fields , engineering products and systems in healthcare and medical fields should be given the highest priority since health is the most important thing for all human beings .
Designing of medical products which can make all human beings healthier is obviously important .
On the other hand , people normally spend much more time for entertainment than healthcare .
As a result , there are mass products for entertainment because of high demand .
There are many healthcare products which are available in research organizations but not widely available in the current market .
For example , " Fall Detection System " can detect the fall of persons , especially elder people , and can send instant messages via sms to relatives so that they can get immediate help in critical situations .
As mentioned in the " Global action on aging " website , the number of senior citizens is rising taking care of them imperative .
It is also mentioned that since the number of elderly people is increasing , the burden of caring is also increasing for young people .
Hence , engineering should consider this situation and come out with solutions which will help the elderly and make youth work without worry .
Although there are R&Ds for healthcare products for monitoring and taking care of the elderly , these devices are not widely used in the market .
So , in order to address this situation , engineers should think about ways that can make the design process meet the needs of the market .
One example of a medical system is " Posture Monitoring System " which can monitor body posture all the time and continuously warning the user to maintain the best posture .
Recently in 2009 , Nanyang Polytechnic won a merit prize in the Tan Kah Kee Young Inventors ' Award competition in Singapore through its posture monitoring system . There are also research papers and prototypes of posture monitoring system by R&D from other countries but are not widely available in the current market .
One example of engineering products for the disabled which is mentioned in The Straits Times by Grace Chua is a chair that turns sound into vibrations , invented by NUS PhD student Suranga Nanayakkara This help deaf people experience music and even aid them in speech therapy .
In order to make engineering design products meet needs , first of all , a clear and unambiguous definition of the problem should be defined .
Problems should be widely and clearly defined by engineers , the elderly as well as adults so that more innovative products and ideas come out .
Once alternative solutions come out , engineers need to analyze and decide on the best suited solution to implement .Governments and organizations are also responsible in supporting the R&D process in order to gather information needed , generate multiple solutions , analyze solutions and test as well as implement solutions which are the necessary steps for the design process .
In conclusion , engineers should try to identify ideal situation in the market for their products , for example , the " Fall Detection System " which can take care of the elderly and the " Posture monitoring system " which can help people of all ages to maintain best posture with the help of government and organizations as well as consumers .
And the goal can also be achieved by developing suitable design engineering process for healthcare systems and products .
A human need is a necessity that humans need in order to survive .
According to the World Food Program 's 2008 report , 25000 people are dying every day due to famine and related issues .
A large portion of the deaths comes from Third World Countries like Africa and India .
By using the Engineering Design Process introduced by Seyyed Khandani , a professor at Diablo Valley College , we can reduce famine .
Some factors that contribute to famine famine include political , technological and environmental issues .
The World Food Program ( WFP ) has been providing food and aid to areas affected by famine .
The definition of the problem is straightforward in the beginning : the people are starving , so they must be provided food .
However , for Malawi , the WFP and the World Bank figured out a solution and found out that it is better to donate cash to them ; based on their research , they found out that the country has food resources , but the poor can not afford them .
In the 1990s , the WFP introduced donation of cash and vouchers , and one of the pioneer countries that received this is Malawi .
Thus , providing cash did not only help to solve the famine , it also improved the financial situation of the farmers .
Furthermore , the WFP saved time and cost collecting food and delivering it to the affected areas .
In 1970s , the WFP provided food to India to temporarily solve famine .
During this period , they analyzed the situation to generate other solutions to permanently solve the famine .
According to the design process , the second step is to gather related information , then generate possible solutions .
The first possible solution was to provide genetically modified seeds and fertilizers to farmers , so that they would obtain higher yield .
Before this solution was implemented , they did a further study , and realized that the solution would not work as the farmers were using traditional farming methods which are not yield efficient .
These aids improved the famine situation as it dropped by about 20 % in a WFP 1990s report ; On the other hand , these solutions not applicable to all lands in India as different areas have different types of lands .
For the dry lands , the WFP had to do further researchresearch on water irrigation methods .
One of the solutions was to construct a drainage system from the Indira Ghandi canal to irrigate the dry lands in the region .
Some events like drought , flood and earthquakes cause famine .
Nevertheless , events like deforestation and overgrazing have also affected fertile lands and caused yields to go down .
Governments spend millions and billions of dollars on entertainment and military expenditure yearly , but ththis large amount of money could have been put to good use in helping their own people .
India has increased military spending by 50 % in 2008 , bringing the amount to 40 billion dollars , although 35 % of its people are still affected by famine .
The large amount of money could be invested in the agriculture sector , like using technology to plant seeds that will grow on dry land which will greatly solve the famine .
In conclusion , the WFP can do more research and analysis , like creating genetic modified seeds that can survive in dry or wet land , or an indoor farming center that will shelter the crops from natural disasters , to resolve the famine issue .
In addition , governments can try to allocate more budget to agriculture and research centers than to the entertainment sector , which is not right when people in their own country are suffering .
The last step in the design process is to test and implement the solution .
Taking a small step forward will reduce famine .
Thus , we should do more to help the people are suffering from famine .
Communication is an important part of human development . It allows ideas and information to be disseminated effectively .
Two main driving factors that shaped the innovation of radio are economic and military demands , leading to the usage of radio beyond pure communication .
The first radio set was able to transmit only simple signals , but still it was valuable enough to be used by in maritime work .
An example would be the sending of by the Titanic to the nearest ship requesting assistance before it sank . It illustrated the usefulness of radio as a tool for communication in situations where line communication not possible .
Sending of Morse code via radio set was further popularised by telegraphy which transformed the use of radio into a service much like the postal service .
Telegraphy flourished as it was relatively reliable and much faster than postal service , encouraging more resources to be channelled into the development and research of radio technology .
As the average cost of production declined steadily , the radio set was mass produced leading to the birth of radio broadcasting .
Warnings and announcements regarding weather or disaster evacuation made via broadcasting will greatly help in minimising the casualty rate in a disaster as the masses can receive vital and timely information and instruction even when the cable lines are damaged .
The other factors that have influenced the development of radio will be military demands .
Besides improving on communication , military demands had also led to the invention of radar which uses radio wave in detecting distant objects and getting information such as their location and movement .
From its communication values to other discovered usages , economic and military factors have played a positive role in its overall development .
The invention and development of radio have bettered the society in numerous ways .
Overpopulation is one of the current human needs or challenges that should be given priority .
Size or density of the population affects overpopulation .
In the world where human populations are growing , we should focus on solving the problem of insufficient land to maintain life on earth .
Houses today are stronger , and some of them can withstand natural disaster .
For example in Japan , a country where earthquakes happen often , their engineers try to solve the problem of constructing buildings that can withstand earthquakes .
By using the Khandani Principle , engineers gather pertinent information about earthquakes and manage to implement a solution after several tests have been conducted , called Seismic retrofitting method , where Seismic retrofitting is the changing of an existing building to a structure that is more resistant to ground motion and soil failure due to earthquakes or seismic activity .
Engineers try to solve overpopulation by combining many houses into one building , thus building multi-unit housing , or also known as attached dwellings , has been initiated .
Apartments , barracks , tenements and terrace houses are good examples of multi-unit housing .
Engineers applied the Khandani principle that time ; they defined the problem and gathered enough information to make sure the buildings would not collapse .
For example , in Singapore , where land is very small , engineers built a lot of condominiums and apartments to solve the problem of insufficient houses and managed to save some of the land for other purposes .
However , in the future , the population will further increase , and building more multi-unit housing can not solve the problem effectively .
In my opinion , engineeengineers should focus on upgrading the buildings .
They should build multiple level basements for multi-unit housing and building since we do not really use a lot of the underground space .
Building multiple level basements may cause some other potential problems and engineers should try to solve these .
Engineers have to analyze every possible problem that may occur like water seepage , internal condensation , underground virus and bad acoustics when building more underground levels .
That is why in building more underground level , we need to use the Khandani principle ( 2005 ) that requires engineers to gather a lot of pertinent information from any sources available before implementing it .
In addition , engineers can also improve the stability of buildings so that more levels can be built above them .
The stability depends on the wideness of the base level , the material of the structure and the method of building the structure .
Engineers can increase the width of the base of the structure to support an extra level of building built on it .
Engineers can improve the structures by using stronger material like diamonds , gold , etc. and finding more suitable methods for building a structure .
Engineers need to test the solution before they start to use it .
Hidden problems can be found out by testing them under real conditions
( Khandani , 2005 ) .
If we compare the house 10000 BC to the modern house today , the engineering design process is apparent .
If in the world we do not have such process , engineers may generate solutions that are ineffective or may cause harm to other life forms .
The issue of the depletion of earth 's natural resources has been raised repeatedly throughout recent times .
Singapore , due to its small land size area , also faces the problem of the lack of natural resources .
In order for Singapore to be self-reliant on water , there is a need for Singapore to create portable water resources for its people .
Singapore had tried a number of ways in its bid to shift towards self-reliance on water .
However , these methods are still short of providing for the growing need of water by its people .
The product is called New water .
New water is treated waste water that has undergone stringent purification processes using advanced dual membrane and ultraviolet technology .
The product can be bottled for consumption , or be mixed with reservoir water and will then go through the usual water treatment to produce drinkable water .
This is indeed a product of a system which is engineered to meet the human need for natural resources .
Singapore has been buying water from Malaysia , its neighbouring country , in order to supplement its own water supply .
Secondly , they gathered pertinent information on the technologies and usage of water that is purified from waste water .
They eventually built its first plant after the technology of dual membrane purification matured and the production cost came down .
Thirdly , prior to the implementation of the New Water technology , there were also multiple solutions to the problem of lack of water resources in Singapore .
Solutions included desalination of sea water and damping up more rivers to increase the water catchment area .
The desalination of seawater would require large amount of fossil fuel to run which is another natural resource that Singapore does not have .
Furthermore , the desalination plants would also leave a larger carbon footprint .
Despite these , a desalination plant was still built because of the growing demand .
The damping up of rivers to form water catchment areas was in fact being implemented .
Marina barrage , the newest kid on the block , was formed by damping the marina channel to form a large water catchment area capable of meeting 10 % of Singapore 's need .
However , as Singapore has limited land , we could not go on forever creating water catchment areas from our land .
Therefore , New Water was decided as a solution needed to meet the need for water of the nation .
Finally , in May 2000 , the first New Water plant was completed .
Currently there are 4 New Water plant in Singapore with a fifth on its way .
Bottled New Water was also given out during National events , promoting its use in our daily life .
In conclusion , New Water has been an engineering design which was designed to meet the human need for water particularly in Singapore .
Throughout human history , there are a lot of successful products which have great effect on human life , like television , the cell and so on .
It is not only their high level technology that makes them so successful , but also the fact that they meet the needs of the people .
The electric car , which was first invented by General Motors Company ( GM ) , is such an interesting case .
The invention of electric cars is both a success and failure .
We can analyse it in both social and technological aspects .
The electric car is the product of social reasons .
As we know , an ordinary car 's fuel is gas which has been used since the first car was been produced .
While there exists a problem that the burning of gas gives off poisonous gases and a large amount of carbon dioxide which causes serious air pollution .
Furthermore , as it is mineral resource , the supply of gas is becoming less and less which directly leads to the rise of the price .
Another direct social reason is that in the early 1990s , the California and Arizona state governments had raised a policy which said at least 10 percent of the cars produced in the automobile companies should be environmental friendly , in other words , nonpolluting .
This promoted the research into electric cars .
In the mean time , GM also wanted to use this opportunity to restore their position in the automobile world .
These are the social reasons that did favor to electric car .
With the development of technology , people have more comfortable and beautiful clothes to wear , more enjoyable entertainment to participate in , more delicious food to eat and more convenient transportation .
Nowadays , as our Mother Earth r becomes hotter , human beings ' living condition is greatly threatened by global warming , the issue which is discussed fiercely among scientists .
As engineers we must also take this responsibility to protect our Earth Mother .
It is commonly known that global warming is caused by recent industrial activities years . To be precise it is due to the emission of green house gases ( GHG ) .
In recent years , due to much more frequent industrial activities , the curve of emission of CO2 consequently jumps to a very high point . So does the curve of temperature .
Nowadays , the rising temperature has received much more attention because of some sudden , striking events , for instance , the melting ice in Antarctica , the rising sea level .
As mentioned above , the rising temperature is due to higher emissions of green house gases , so the key to global warming will focus of this issue .
Firstly , we can make use of natural energy instead of fuel.As we all know , burning fuel will emit a lot of green house gases , including CO2 .
However , if we use natural energy , we can not only reduce the emission of green house gas , but also save our resources .
Water energy is also a kind of natural energy which can be exploited by human beings , such as in China .
The Kyoto Protocol signed in Japan is the best example .
In this protocol , the member countries have to reduce a certain amount of green house gas according to the amount of green house gas they produced and the most acceptable way is just reduce industrial activities .
Thirdly , increasing planting areas is also an efficient way to reach our goal , as plants absorb CO2 .
In conclusion , the threat of global warming has come . We engineers need to face it bravely and design products against the climate change .
We have only one Earth Earth . We must never lose her .
As our society progresses human beings get stuck in a dilemma of energy .
On one hand , the energy resources we use now , which are mainly fossil fuels , will be exhausted soon if we continue to consume at the current rate while the use of fossil fuels triggers a series of environmental problems .
On the other hand , the development of society calls for larger and larger amounts of energy , which makes us in desperate need of energy .
In order to develop our society without exhausting all the fossil fuels or sacrificing our environment , we have to find new energy resources to take the place of traditional fossil fuels .
In this case , solar energy stands out as our first choice .
Engineering design plays a significant role in the use of solar energy , especially in solar heating .
In fact , humans had begun to utilize solar energy to heat water as early as 3000 years ago .
The question of how to make an efficient and effective solar heating system is addressed by engineers .
In order to find the solution , engineers spend large amount of time to collect the relevant information , from which they can generate iinspiration , while drawing lessons from the previous work .
Though this preliminary stage appears simple , actually it not only takes a lot of time and calls for patience , but also is the crucial fundamental stage of the solution .
Then engineers come in at core step , that is , the generation of solutions .
First , engineers will decide to make a solar collector which can effectively collect solar energy from the surroundings
Because of the efficient heat conductibility of metal , engineers use a huge piece of metal which is painted black to collect the solar energy .
After that , they build the circulation equipment to make water flow below the metal so that the metal can transmit the heat to water and then people can use the heated water .
Using this solar heating system , engineers also designed certain products widely used in our daily life , such as the solar water heater .
What engineers will do next is test the system and make possible improvements .
It is not stable enough , so people may not be able to use solar energy to heat water whenever they need .
To improve the solar heating system , engineers have added accessorial energy equipment to it such as an heater .
To make an efficient and effective solar heating system , engineers carefully define the problem and collect important information about this issue . Then they generate all the possible solutions . Finally they test the solutions and make changes to improve the solution .
Besides the solar heating system , engineering design is also used in other fields .
Currently , people depend more and more on technology to improve their lives , which stimulates the development of science and technology in reverse .
In my opinion , we should pay most attention to the development of clean energy such as solar energy .
The reason why we should focus on the research of solar energy is that the atmospheric pollution caused by the consumption of fossil fuels is severe , and there is enough solar energy to be used on Earth , , and the diffusion and adoption of solar energy product is satisfying .
In fact , the research of solar energy can be traced back to 1900 .
Although at that time they only focused on solar power plants .
Later , because of the decrease in petroleum and natural gas , scientists paid attention to solar energy again .
today , the process of solar energy research is still quite difficult .
Because of the severe pollution problem , we have to focus on the development of solar energy .
Nowadays , there are already various kinds of solar energy products in the market .
For example , people use solar energy converters to heat up water , which will save an amazing amount of energy acquired through other ways .
Besides , the usage of solar panels should become more and more important in the future .
It is said that if we can cover a place of 40,000 square miles with solar panels , the demand for electricity of the whole world will be satisfied .
Also , solar energy is inexhaustible and we can use it without worrying about polluting the atmosphere , which really solves the problem caused by the consumption of fossil fuels .
In some places of the world , people are accepting solar energy products such as solar energy converters as they think that they are fashionable and pollution-free .
But in cities such as GuangDong and ShangDong provinces in China , people are not so willing to install solar energy converters though the government has forced some buildings to install the converters to save energy and reduce carbon emission .
Some residents in America covered their roofs with solar energy panels and those panels will provide 50 to 80 percent of power consumption in their houses .
Moreover , since the price of solar energy panel is decreasing recently , more and more consumers will think about the usage of solar energy panels .
In the 1980s and 1990s , the research of solar energy fell into the low tide because the price of petroleum fell and solar energy products were too expensive and there was no important breakthrough in the development of solar energy products .
However , since environmental pollution has become one of the most important topics in the world nowadays , we also should pay more attention to clean energy such as solar energy .
The usage of solar energy product will not only save large amounts of energy and solve the problem of energy crisis but also give us a clean world with little pollution .
With the development of the society , our demand for the various commodities keeps increasing .
However , without enough energy to manufacture the products , how can our desire be satisfied ?
Therefore , the current human need to find endless energy source is becoming more and more urgent , so it should be given priority .
To satisfy the current human need , we should use Roger 's Engineering design process to work out a solution .
As we know , most of the energy we are consuming is fossil energy such as coal and oil , which is limited .
If we just depend on fossil energy , how can we live on after hundreds of years years ?
Just a few years ago , America declared war against Iraq with the justification that there were bio-chemical weapons in Iraq .
This war warns us that if we do not solve the energy problems , more wars may be declared in the future .
However , there are many other kinds of energy sources on the earth such as nuclear power , water power and solar power .
Now the problem is how to use these power sources as substitutes for the fossil energy , which means how to convert these power into the energy that can be used by us such as electrical power .
To solve this problem , building electrical powerhouses may be the best choice .
The reason is that electrical power is clean , easily transported and easily stored .
Although making use of nuclear power , water power and solar power seems feasible , there are some reasons that make solar power the most appropriate .
Nevertheless , it can generate such huge power that it is very unsafe .
The strong radiation of the explosion even influenced all of the North Hemisphere .
What a tragedy it was !
We can not guarantee there will be no such kind of explosion any longer if we rely on nuclear power .
Undeniably , the technology of solar power conversion today is still not perfect .
Many improvements should be made to increase the conversion rate and lower the cost of the equipment so it can be utilised .
Compared to other sources , solar power has three big advantages .
Actually , the sunlight is electramagnetic waves .
we already have built some solar powerhouses but we have never heard anything unfortunate happen .
Therefore , for the three advantages above , we can find it really meaningful to develop the solar power technology
Furthermore , during the development of solar power technology , .
Lowering the cost of the application is also very important , otherwise nobody will be willing to adopt this technology .
In conclusion , to maintain the sustainable development of our society , we should give priority to the current human need to develop more energy from various of human society .
Among the diverse energy sources , solar power has the brightest prospect for its non-pollution , safety and infinitude .
From a luxurious entertaining appliance in the early stage of development , television has become an indispensable and ubiquitous thing within every household nowadays .
For instance , a character may be driving a particular type of automobile , wearing a certain kind of clothes , or eating at a particular restaurant chain .
A brand or trademark is sometimes used .
I strongly believe that the benefits television brings to our society are undeniable .
Nowadays virtually all the broadcasters have at least an educational program of their own .
That 's because of the high demand from parents , institutions and educationists .
However , television also has more negative influences on our society than positive ones .
Children addicted to television are associated with obesity , passiveness , health problems and sometimes bad grades .
Inappropriate contents are deemed as another type of danger to the youth .
Violence , sex , drugs abuse , nonsense comics , etc. cause a lot of controversies over the right age of watching them ; and the youth are subject to parental television control , especially when it influences their self-esteem and body image .
With concerned parents , a child can greatly benefit from television programs programs , whereas the child may encounter inappropriate contents if the parents let him or her freely use television .
Adults who spend too much time on TV viewing seem to be dissatisfied people because they try to look for happiness in those programs after a hard struggling day .
However it is usually short lived happiness .
It is disputable whether television has been changing the norms of society .
In conclusion , television has obviously contributed a lot to determine and shape our society , owing to the strong links between its development history and the human 's .
However , well-trained ones are hard to find and they are not always available at times when you need them immediately .
Moreover , some people feel that their privacy is not safeguarded with a translator involved .
In the following paragraphs , the design process of our product will be illustrated to show how we fulfill people 's need to communicate with others speaking different languages .
For the after-sale services , we would establish an official website for the customers to acquire necessary information and post their feedback
We will keep upgrading and modifying our software until our customers are satisfied .
As batteries are not environmental friendly , we have made use of the DC chargers instead .
In addition , we have made the device more portable by minimizing the size and weight .
For example , our device has many components consisting of a scanner , speaker , printer and recorder .
