Since China adopted the reform and opening-up policy in 1978 , countless promising students have gone abroad for further study .
Unfortunately , lots of these talents are unwilling to return to their motherland because of the much superior conditions in developed countries , which causes the brain drain problem .
Such a brain drain makes China fall into a severe shortage of talents who are necessary for the implementation of any stage of the process .
As a result , more educated people will go abroad , which aggravates the brain drain problem in turn and exerts a greater negative effect on the process .
Therefore , unlike US and developed European countries , not much capital can be spared for engineering design processes for innovations , which causes the capital problem .
Thus in the course of engineering design , one usually needs much money for getting pertinent information and testing and implementing the solution .
" From his perspective , since every natural event happens as a result of a cause or collective causes , I am not sure if it is proper to refer to the discovery of LSD , short term of Lysergic acid diethylamide , as an accident .
In 1993 , risperidone was approved by the United States Food and Drug Administration , for the treatment of schizophrenia , and bipolar disorder in 2007 .
On another hand , LSD was once widely used for treatments of mental disorder as well before , which would be illustrated in the second paragraph .
However , LSD affects people in alcoholism in a positive way which is unachievable for risperidone .
Secondly , the controllability of both the short term and long term effects of LSD and risperidone vary greatly .
But for LSD , the physical and psychological effect vary greatly from one to the other , and is highly dependent on the amount of dosage , consumer 's personality , mood , the surrounding environment and other variable factors .
Most importantly , the social issues arising from consumption of LSD are unexpected .
Apart from physical and psychological effects , LSD also triggers intense spiritual experience which leads consumers to illusory images and feelings .
There is a great number of people who believe that LSD serve as a divine vehicle which transports the consumers to the outer-space where the gods live .
There were several cases of suicide before the United States government banned LSD in 1966 .
However for LSD , it was mainly regarded as a means to get high by the American hippies .
Even the poets , painters and musicians tried to seek inspiration by consuming LSD .
As a result , the consuming group of LSD is more complicated than that of risperidone .
According to the above , even though riperidone and LSD share some similarities in their pharmaceutical effects to a certain extent , they are different from each other in terms of controlability of side effects and their consuming groups .
sport is one of the most important things in human life .
Among the various knee injuries , the anterior cruciate ligament ( ACL ) injury happens most often .
If the injured do not recover completely , it is likely for him to get injured again at the same place .
It could even affect his daily life .
So ,the treatment of the ACL injury is considered a very important matter in sports medicine .
It is almost impossible for ligaments to regrow if they have been ruptured .
The classic method to solve the problem ( ACL injury ) is to remove a ligament from the patient himself such as patellar tendons .
Second , it has been shown that this method could cause pains and patellar tendonitis .
So , to meet the human need , scientists are looking for a new method .
First , the artificial ligaments should not cause rejection reaction .Second , it should be very strong ,flexible and anti abrasive ,so that it can ensure that the patient can play sports at the normal level .
Third ,it should have the ability to grow and combine with the ruptured ligament .
The result has shown that the LARS ligament is extremely resistant to flexion , traction , torsion , and residual stretching .
Also , the design has biocompatible properties to human tissues , because the intra-articular longitudinal fibers allow for tissue growth .
Futhermore , if we use LARS ligaments in the reconstruction of cruciate ligament , the time of recovery can be reduced a lot .
At the same time , there is also a pitfall about the artificial ligament .
.
I think as it improves a lot in the future , it can the classic method finally .
Among thousands of technologies , the laptop , one of the most important innovations in the twentieth century , is a good example of socially determined technology .
The laptop , first manufactured by Toshiba in 1985 ( Rogers , 2003 ) , ten years after the birth of the desktop computer , has again brought about a tremendous revolution in our lives .
Problems arose as the workers had to stay in the company to finish the work that can not be done without a computer .
Under such conditions , the idea of the laptop was inspired .
Secondly , the main power that provides technological support plays an essential role in the innovation of the laptop .
The idea of designing a laptop was first not approved by Toshiba , but Mizoguchi , the chief designer of the laptop did not give up .
The support of technical staff brought a successful step towards the final goal of promoting and producing laptops .
Last but not least , the source of funding made the production and sales of laptops possible .
Though the research team had made the idea of the laptop came true , the laptop would not be finally put into production without a large amount of money .
To their disappointment , the plan of producing the laptops had again been rejected due to the small potential market estimated by the company .
To sum up , the innovation of laptop can not be separated from the three main factors .
The demand of customers inspired the designers , the support of technical staff put the idea into practice , and finally , the source of funding ensured the sales .
Without any of these three factors , the dream of owning a laptop would be still a dream now .
Fortunately , Thomas Edison created the lightbulb in 1879 and Percy LeBaron Spencer discovered microwave energy after World War two .
It is amazing that Edison picked up a fifty-year-old idea and made it come true , while Percy brought the microwave oven to light by an accident , indeed .
These two wonderful discoveries have many similarities and differences .
Moreover , the idea of a microwave oven was totally new , while someone had worked on the lightbulb before Edison .
Edison achieved this unbelievable task by thousands of different experiments .
To choose the suitable filament for the lightbulb , Edison tried more than 1600 kinds of materials with different heat-resistance .
After many setbacks , Edison decided to use carbon to make the filament .
On the other hand , Percy chanced on microwave energy by pure coincidence .
When he did some experiment focusing on radar waves , the melt of a candy bar in his pocket surprised him .
In addition , Edison did not 'invent ' the lightbulb actually , while Percy is the first person who discovered the microwave energy and invented the microwave oven .
Since he was interested in electric appliances , he picked up this idea and made several improvements to it through various experiments .
In contrast , there was nobody who discovered the energy of microwave before Percy .
After he found out this big secret and went through careful trials , Percy developed the microwave oven into .
Thus , he is definitely the inventor of the microwave oven .
Last but not least , the lightbulb helps us say goodbye to darkness and the microwave oven provides us a very convenient way to heat food .
Because of the lightbulb , the big world becomes brighter and more colorful .
Also , we can read , write and do many things in the night .
The lightbulb has brought us easier and more convenient life .
In the same manner , the microwave oven has become one of the many modern conveniences .
Not only can it save time but it can also be operated in a safer manner .
In conclusion , the lightbulb and microwave oven are both great discoveries .
Moreover , Edison just made improvements to the lightbulb while Percy invented the microwave oven .
Anyway , we must thank Edison Thomas and Percy LeBaron Spencer who made these two extraordinary inventions .
15th August , known as " Victory in the Pacific Day " , is celebrated by people all around the world to commemorate the surrender of Japan in 1945 .
What we need to emphasize here is that the atomic bomb explosion in Hiroshima and Nagasaki on 6th and 9th August respectively definitely hastened the surrender of Japan .
In the history of warfare , these are the only two nuclear weapons used in the offensive .
Now , more than sixty years later , nuclear weapons are still the most destructive weapons invented by human beings .
Surprisingly , when the nuclear technology was firstly discovered by scientists , it was seen as a method to satisfy human 's needs of energy .
After Einstein 's General Relativity Theory and the famous equation E = mc2 , scientists thought more about how to get energy more efficiently and effectively .
In early 1939 , two German scientists first published their essay about nuclear fission and also stated that this new energy source could bring tremendous profits for human beings .
Unfortunately , against the background of World War Two , military demands had priority over anything else .
Obviously , Allies finally won the battle on the invention of nuclear weapons .
Otherwise , the result of World War Two might be different and it is hard to imagine what our life would be today .
The U.S. used more than six hundred thousand people and invested more than two billion dollars to start the " Manhattan Project " .
Japan tragically became the first and only target of nuclear weapons in history .
Even till now , whether the invention of nuclear weapons was for peace or war is still discussed all over the world .
However , the catastrophe it caused for the Japanese was really serious .
Even today , the nuclear crisis in North Korea and Iran still threatens the stabilization of world .
If there was no E = mc2 or World War Two , nuclear weapons may never have been invented .
Maybe for the nuclear technology itself , utilizing it to make weapons is unfair , but we must agree that it is the social needs , or specifically the military demands , and government priorities at that time that determined the direction of this innovation .
Just like every year people celebrate the " Victory in the Pacific Day " , there should be some others remembering the nuclear weapons .
The military also uses GPS in various methods from missile guidance to enemy tracking .
Numerous factors have brought about the development of the GPS : mainly the government , military and public demands .
In 1983 , the U.S. President Ronald Reagan decided that the GPS will be made available for civilian use after the Soviet Union shot down a commercial airliner which had navigational difficulty , bringing about the death of more than 200 passengers .
Currently , the GPS is widely used in the aviation and maritime industry so that similar incidents can be prevented .
Next , the public demands have pushed the benefits of the GPS further when gadgets are integrated with GPS to provide constant relative motion and time coordination .
As such , even the user 's estimated time of arrival can be calculated .
The development of technology has benefited human beings in both scientific research and daily life of human beings .
With the invention of the microscope , scientists are able to observe molecules which form all matter .
Besides scientific research , inventions and new technologies have indeed brought convenience to human beings .
( Rogers , 2003 ) One important technology which was socially determined is the invention of the laptop in Toshiba , a Japanese electronics company .
The invention of the laptop was originally designed to fit crowded offices and small homes which were typical in Japan .
At that time , dozens of workers shared one desk and desktop computers were too large in size .
( Rogers , 2003 ) The laptop was then invented by an engineer in Toshiba Company called Mizoguchi , whose braveness and wisdom have been recognized in the process of inventing the laptop .
However , because of lacking resources and unpromising market , the innovation of the laptop in Toshiba was nearly aborted .
Fortunately , the designers of the laptop were determined so people nowadays are able to access the Internet anywhere with laptops that were first invented by them .
In the process of inventing a laptop , the design team was lacking in human resource and money .
At first , the idea of designing laptop was disapproved by the Toshiba Company , which at that time had just suffered from a huge loss in the business of personal computers .
Although the team survived due to the insistence of Mizogushi and finally came up with the first laptop in the world , lack of resources had had an impact on the design team , which made the team 'stressful ' ( Rogers , 2003 ) in the designing process .
To wrap up , the invention of the laptop was affected by the lack of resources and unpromising market which ultimately came from opinion of the authority in Toshiba Company which turned out to be incorrect .
Actually many major discoveries made by excellent scientists are unexpected gifts from good luck .
In particular , pharmacology is perhaps the most common field where serendipity occurs .
When he served in the army , he noticed that many soldiers died from simple infections caused by small wounds .
Every day hospitals were filled with patients who only got infections from a small cut or a scratch and more seriously those who contracted pneumonia or tuberculosis .
After the discovery of the new substance , he came to the problem of how to cultivate the mould and how to isolate and purify the antibiotic agent .
It saved many soldiers ' lives in the war .
What would have happened if Fleming had never been concerned about the search for the cure or he had had no interest in this area at all ?
It is just because Fleming was intrigued by his research that he could notice the mould contamination on the bacteria culture and stretch out further reflection on it , while others could not .
Hard work finally paid off .
Serendipity only favours those with high aspirations and determination who whole-heartedly dedicate themselves to their beloved career .
Perhaps some people will say that it is reasonable that the society is now in a relatively stable stage since the modern scene was marked by tremendously and ever-accelerating change in the past few years .
In this way , companies may not dare to pump money into the development of new products .
Once the process is lacking in funds , there is little hope for the process to continue .
Statistics suggest that the R&D teams in companies tend to decrease in number .
Worse still , there are many companies which even do not have an R&D team yet .
Besides , the not-so-high salary can hardly attract high-quality talents to join the research team , which is also due to the lack of funds which I have mentioned before .
All these make it even more difficult for the innovation to bear fruit .
People always tend to do things that will benefit themselves .
However , some obstacles still hamper the process of technological innovation in China , as the technological development is in its infancy .
In my opinion , there are mainly two big problems for us to overcome in the next few years , which are the decentralization and shortage of resources and the lagging of technology transfer .
Resource refers to human capital and financial support .
Actually , decentralization of human capital and delayed financial support hamper the stage of research and development to quite a large extent .
Compared to other developing countries , China does not have a standard innovation centre where many talented scientists and engineers can discuss and develop a creative project .
Take Silicon Valley as an example . Many new technological products are developed and promising companies are founded there every year , which is a result of the cooperation of many talents .
How to call them back and work out some big projects is a tough task for our government .
However , if the financial support is divided into small parts , these departments will not receive enough money to do a large scale research .
Furthermore , some research projects must wait several months for financial support , during which time scientists may lose heart and give up .
As a result , research and development , which are the first steps of innovation , become more and more difficult .
China should try hard to solve the problem of resource .
Some new technologies may be born as well as die in laboratories as a result of lag in technology transfer .
Perhaps it takes about a few years to generate a new generation .
Besides , as China does not have a system to link these new techniques with manufacturing departments , I think most manufacturing factories can not make full use of these innovations .
Therefore , we had better build a sound system to do the technology transfer .
Firstly , we had better develop some technical centre to bring talents together and do research .
If we can overcome these problems , I believe the design process of innovation in China will develop farther more .
However , in my home country , many problems exist as huge barriers for engineers to apply their innovative ideas to practice .
Chinese students are very diligent , but sometimes they focus too much on theoretical knowledge and the exams , while overlooking the importance of cultivating their own innovative ability .
So when they become engineers , what they can do is only follow others ' steps and they can not put forward new ideas .
Besides the cognition problem , some universities do not give much attention to students ' hands-on abilities .
Experiment classes , which aim to help students develop their application and innovative ability , are often deleted from the schedule or are conducted without experimental materials .
For technology , personal experience is the best way to learn .
Furthermore , we know it is hard for a person to come up with new ideas continuously but this process becomes much easier when several people exchange their thoughts about this issue .
If there is no project , no lab report , no design assignments , how can students learn to work with others ?
Hence , some engineers can not communicate ; they do not know how to allocate workload , and they do not know how to deal with difficulties and conflicts .
Another obstacle is the unsatisfactory social conditions for engineers to develop their knowledge and thoughts .
When I compare my hometown university engineering graduates with their peers in NUS , I find those from NUS have more opportunities to have internships in institutes , to do experiments in teams , to communicate with researchers and professors .
Apart from this , China does not give as much attention to technology innovations as many other countries .
Besides the above two problems , lack of communication in engineering society also discourages the generation of innovative ideas .
There are not many conferences on engineering topics which can allow engineers and scientists to exchange ideas and learn from each other .
After all the above , we can see the improper model and the unsatisfactory social conditions really act as obstacles to innovative engineering designs .
As China is carrying out education reform in a large scale and putting more emphasis on technology innovations , we can predict China 's technology has a good prospect .
In the olden days , taking photos was a complicated process performed solely by professional technicians .
A photographer had to adjust all the settings manually and develop the films with chemicals called film developer in a darkroom .
However , the recent two decades have witnessed an astonishing innovation in photography . The development of digital cameras ( DC ) has made taking photos accessible to the non-specialists .
Consumers ' desire for more convenient usagof the camera and better photo quality shapes the development of the DC technology .
Consumers ' desire for the convenient usage of the camera includethe simplicity of camera functions and the accessibility of photo sharing .
Both of these requests stimulate the DC technology development .
Innovations like the face detection technology by Sony Company , was developed in response to the increasing popularity of portrait taking ( Cheung , K. M. , 2007 ) .
Other technologies like the anti-blink function and the Smile Shutter function , which automatically capture the best facial expressions , are also developed in the need for simpler photo taking ( Sony Unveils World 's First Wi-Fi Digital Camera with Web Browser , 2009 ) .
Users can upload photos onto the Internet and share the photos with more people .
A case in point is the Wi-Fi cameras .
With a web browser installed within it , this camera can get access to any hotspot , allowing users to upload their photos immediately after shooting ( Sony Unveils World 's First Wi-Fi Digital Camera with Web Browser , 2009 ) .
Another development that improved the convenience of taking photos is portability .
Thus , they can be put inside pockets and easily carried around .
The improvement in portability has also resulted from people 's increasing demand for easy casual shootings .
Consumers ' pursuit of better photo quality has also driven the innovation of advanced DC technology .
To improve resolution , a company needs to conduct a considerable amount of research which included the generation of new ideas , technology breakthroughs and repetitive experiments .
The process is hard , but companies are willing to sacrifice their time and labor for the development . This is because the better the resolution , the more customers will be attracted , and the more profit the companies will make .
Such remarkable improvement shows the strong impact of consumers ' requirement in pushing forward the DC technology .
The innovation and development of the DC technology are shaped by the needs of the market .
At the same time , the technological developments have greatly changed our lives at the same time , making our lives more convenient and colourful .
After the telephone was invented in the late 1800s , people were thinking about ways to improve the communication technology to extend the range of social network .
The original idea of the mobile phone came from combining telecommunication with radio technology , which was considerably improved during the World War 2 period ( Special History Issue , 1990 ) .
Until the 1980s , due to the cellular idea , the portability and the quality of communication of mobile phone were improved and mobile telephony started to play a part in the mass market ( Farley , 2007 ) .
And with the advancement in internet technology , the third generation mobiles phones are digitized ( Wei , 2005 ) .
This essay will examine three major factors in the development of the mobile telecommunication in different stages .
First of all , the post-war economic recovery demanded a better way of communication in order to expand the network of free trade among different countries .
In 1946 soviet engineers Shapiro and Zaharchenko ( Special History Issue , 1990 ) launched the first radio telephone , which was equipped inside a car and could connect to local telephone network within the range of 20 kilometers .
Besides , as water transportation was developed rapidly during that period , radiotelephony service was introduced to harbor and coastal vessels ( Special History Issue , 1990 ) .
In the past , radio telephony was the only way to connect to the telephone service when people were mobile .
Hence , the demands for economic growth pushed mobile technology forward in the early days .
Donald H. Ring came up with the idea of cellular network in 1947 ( Farley , 2007 ) .
With the advance in computing technology in 1980s , a cellular network on mobile phones called Groupe Special Mobile was developed and this made mobile communication start to boom ( Farley , 2007 ) .
Similarly , the development of necessary technologies such as semi-conductors , transistors and microelectronic chips have also contributed to the development of mobile telecommunications .
Therefore , progress in other fields can promote the innovations of the mobile technology .
After the birth of GSM , mobile phones started to more attract private users .
Unlike business usage , private users demand a user-friendly environment to communicate with friends and family , as well as some additional entertainment features .
Such demands by the public encouraged mobile developers to create new functions for cell phones such as delivering ring tones , SMS and voice mail ( Wei , 2005 ) .
Besides , mobile phones became digitized at the beginning of this century , which brought on a revolution in mobile telecommunication .
Mobile phone today is no longer a phone that is mobile ; it can be an MP3 player , a game player and even a personal computer .
Within the context of a society , mobile telecommunication is shaped by economic factors , inventions and consumers ' demands .
The technology of nanorobotics ( nanobots ) is a modern invention that deals with the making of robots at atomic level .
Nanobots would be helpful in making materials that are efficient in storing energy and converting energy sources .
They can be used to create a system that is affordable , fast , and compact .
According to an article , $ 20 million was granted to Stanford - one of 46 Energy Frontier Research Centres - to help the engineers to find energy at the nano-scale .
In Conclusion , the technology of nanobots is a modern innovation that allows human to process tasks that are beyond what our beareye can see .
With continuous development , nanobots would improve the lives of millions in the near future .
The main problem , however , is time constraint and this problem can be seen to significantly hamper engineering design processes for innovations in companies , such as Creative Technology .
This time constraint is caused by competition from other companies which sell similar products and they may also be in the midst of designing similar new products as Creative Technology .
Mr Sim Wong Hoo , chairman and CEO of Creative Technology , commented that being awarded the ZEN Patent to Creative Technology had helped it to protect its invention in portable media players .
He then further commented that in order to be awarded the ZEN Patent , it had taken a major investment of time and effort by a group of its research and development engineers
( Creative Technology , 2005 ) . It can be seen that because of time constraint , the research and development engineers from Creative Technology had to sacrifice most of their time just to focus on the engineering design processes for their new product , ZEN , so that it can be completed as soon as possible .
Furthermore , because of time constraints , certain processes in the engineering design processes may be compromised .
Another problem is that the designing process must keep up with the rapid developments in technology , for otherwise by the time it is completed , it may already been rendered as obsolete .
According to St. James Press ( 2004 ) , Creative Technology began manufacturing its own CD-ROM drives when it could not keep up with the rapid developments in drive technology ; however , it was forced to abandon the effort , dumping its inventory and taking a loss of more than $ 30 million in 1995 .
From here , we can see that the Engineering design processes must be constantly updated , for otherwise more problems may occur that may significantly hamper engineering design process for innovations .
In conclusion , the two problems discussed may significantly hamper engineering design processes for innovations .
However , there are many people who overcame the difficulties and successfully completed the engineering design processes for innovations , and I hope more people can learn from their experiences .
Since the 1970 s , communication technology has made great advances , offering capabilities that are unthinkable a decade earlier .
The last decade of the 20th century saw a flood of new communication technologies entering the market for both the office and home , according to the Central Statistical office .
This is the result of a better understanding of people 's needs and what technology they really want to use .
One of such technology is the mobile phone .
In the past , communication was slow and unreliable .
In most cases , information would not even reach the desired destination .
As a result , people wanted a form of communication that was fast and reliable .
This changed dramatically with the introduction of the telephone .
Firstly , it took away the necessity of having a communication medium , which made it more reliable .
Secondly , the telephone used electricity , which was literally accessible to every household and this helped messages to be passed around more quickly .
The society wanted to be able to communicate at anywhere and anytime and with anyone it wished .
The introduction of the mobile phone allowed people the ability to pass messages to one another quickly and accurately whenever they wished .
This meant that office workers were able to speed up communication and circulate information faster to allow new ideas to be spread quickly .
Being able to do this would benefit the company and have a positive impact on the economy .
Furthermore , even the military has benefited from this wireless telephony .
Through the use of wireless communication , soldiers were able to communicate with one another swiftly and with 100 % accuracy when information was being passed around .
Due to the convenience of having a mobile phone , the number of mobile phone users has increased drastically over the years .
By 2002 , Japan had 55 million mobile phone users ( out of 122 million ) , China had over 200 million mobile phone users ( out of 1.3 billion ) and about 90 % of Finland 's population had a mobile phone , according to the BBC in 2003 .
The mobile phone underwent further developments to enhance its features to suit its consumers .
As a result , by 2003 , the mobile phone was presented as more than just a tool for calling someone .
It will also take on the roles of being digital navigator and a lifestyle accessory that will help individuals control and enrich their lives ( Nokia , 2002 ) .
Looking back at the evolution of communication , the mobile phone is one that has been shaped by social factors .
Recently , there was an outbreak of a pandemic flu that started in Mexico and spread rampantly around the world , instilling fear in people .
Experts estimate that more than 2 billion people worldwide will contact the flu ( Scheirer Micheal and Harrell Eben .
As such , the health ministers of various countries are very concerned .
Thus , this leads to the development of the vaccine for H1N1 . Besides the governments , H1N1 patients and the general public are also very concerned with the development of the vaccine for H1N1 .
The virus is very contagious , and thus this leads to its spread in society .
There is a large demand for the vaccine by various government bodies .
This could be seen when the governments of France , Belgium and Finland intended to purchase 50 million , 12.6 million and 5.3 million doses respectively ( Cormac Sheridan , 2009 ) .
Another reason for the government bodies to be concerned with the development of the new vaccine is the fear of mutation .
As many more are going to contract the diseases , there is a higher chance that the virus will mutate into a stronger strain .
The health ministers around the world are developing a vaccine for the virus before it spreads too widely or mutates .
The public and the H1N1 patients are the other groups that shaped the development of the vaccine for the H1N1 virus .
Although figures from the WHO ( World Health Organisation ) have shown that out of the 160,000 cases only 1.200 cases are fatal , people continued to be in fear .
This is due to a previous outbreak of another flu virus which has taken many lives .
Due to fear , there is a high demand for the vaccine , and as a result the pharmaceutical companies are given plenty of business opportunitties .
Besides the large demand , any new development would also bring about a rise in the pharmaceutical companies ' share prices .
For example , on April 30 2009 , when Lipoxen pharmaceutical company announced the positive preclinical results for an enhanced influenza vaccine and added that the technology should also work against the new swine flu strain , Lipoxen 's share price went up from Â£ 6.62 ( $ 10.11 ) to Â£ 21.75 ( $ 33.23 ) ( Brady Huggett , 2009 ) .
Health ministries of the world , patients , as well as the public have shaped the development of the H1N1 vaccine in various ways .
The government needed the vaccine to help control the spread of H1N1 and also to cure the disease before it mutates into a more deadly virus .
As for the patients and the public , their concern is that they need the vaccine .
Many people have already got used to using cell phone to take pictures and transfer the images to their friends .
However , camera phones have changed a lot since 2000 ( Daisuke , 2003 ) , and when compared to the first camera phone , camera phones nowadays are quite different .
During the nine-year development of the camera phone technology , we can see that market demand , customer requirement , and government regulations have affected this technology a lot .
The first factor that accelerated the development of the camera phone is market demand .
Before the camera phone appeared in the market , the digital camera and videophone have existed for many years .
Actually , a camera phone is a combination of the digital camera and the videophone , and it can take pictures and save the pictures in digital form . It can transfer the pictures or videos to other videophones .
Digital camera and videophone have already become part of everyday 's life , and people want a tool which can let people take pictures freely and transfer them wirelessly .
The need for the combination of the two technologies eventually lead to the development of the camera phone .
Thus , at 2000 , Sharp launched the world 's first camera phone J-SH04 , which has a 110,000-pixel CMOS image sensor for taking digital photos
This innovation has helped Sharp to achieve great success .
We can easily see that the great sales have ensured the development of this technology .
More and more companies have begun to realize this great market demand and started researching on camera phones .
After integrating the image sensor into the mobile phone , the quality of pictures taken by the camera phones , which have only hundreds of thousands of pixel sensor , can not satisfy the need of the consumers .
The pictures taken by the camera phone are very indistinct at that time .
Those pictures can not be developed because of their low quality .
People might need a substitute for the digital camera .
This need will greatly boost the development of the camera phone technology .
Most camera phone companies tried to produce the camera phones with better sensors .
In the year 2003 , Sharp launched the world 's first 1 megapixel camera phone ( Long , 2005 ) , which can provide much better quality pictures .
Since then , the camera phone has become a really useful tool .
Different companies applied the same strategy and released their 1 megapixel camera phone in the same year , and sales surged 200 % , as compared to last year .
From this , we can draw the conclusion that customer requirements have greatly shaped the camera phone technology .
The worries of sneak shot have caused much concern during the last few years , with the increase of such incidents .
For example , on December 30 2006 , a short film of the execution of former Iraqi dictator Saddam Hussein leaked into the internet and led to some serious detrimental effect .
The film was obviously taken by a camera phone .
Different countries have since promulgated different regulations to limit the use of the camera phone .
Different companies also try to find new methods to prevent sneak shots .
We can see that market demand has helped in the development of the camera phone . , and customer needs have led to the improvement of its functions . Government regulations have also affected the usage of the camera phone .
All these factors make the camera phone more and more popular in our daily lives .
The Hawk-eye is a computer system used in cricket , tennis and other sports to visually track the path of the ball and display a record of its actual path in graphic image .
In tennis and cricket , the Hawk-eye system has become an important reference for judgment when there is dispute about the games .
When the Hawk-eye system was invented , it won some prizes , such as the Science and Technology Innovation Award presented by The Royal Television Society .
However , it is not very popular .
Hawk-eye 's development is limited due to its high cost , some errors it made and some opposing voices from the public .
The first limitation for the development of Hawk-eye is its high cost .
The above-mentioned equipment need to be of high quality .
These reasons , as well as the monopolised market of Hawk-eye have led to the high cost of using the Hawk-eye system .
In the 2009 snooker China open , the sponsor spent 400 thousand yuan per week , which is equivalent to almost 60 thousand US dollars
( 2009,http : //sports.sina.com.cn/o/2009-04-08/03264312295.shtml ) . Not many organisers can afford to spend so much money on such referencing aids .
We can say that its high cost has prevented the Hawk-eye to develop further .
The second limitation is the shortcoming of the Hawk-eye itself .
Although the Hawk-eye company has declared that the Hawk-eye is precise and accurate , it makes mistakes occasionally .
In 2009 Indian Wells Tennis Masters , the Hawk-eye system made a mistake in the quarter-final .
When Andrew Murray knocked the ball out of the bounds , the Hawk-eye did not recognize it and Murray got into the semifinal .
We use the Hawk-eye to prevent errors in judgment ; however , if it does not offer us the accuracy , we may not choose to use it .
The errors caused by Hawk-eye are sure to prevent potential users from using it and thus , limited its development .
In addition , not all the Sportsmen value the Hawk-eye system .
Even in tennis , which is one of the sports that the Hawk-eye is widely used , the system is not well accepted by some of the world 's most popular players .
Roger Federer and Lindsay Davenport think that the Hawk-eye system forgets the true meaning of tennis and makes tennis uninteresting .
As it is widely known , these world-famous players have a great influence on the development of the sport .
If they do not accept the Hawk-eye system , it may be very difficult for it to develop further .
In conclusion , the reasons why the Hawk-eye system does not develop further are the high cost , the weakness of the system itself and the opposing voices from some influential world-famous players .
Since the introduction of Iphone on June 29 2007 , it has become the best- selling smart phone in the world1 .
After a series of hardware and software development , we can now enjoy the latest 3GS Iphone with a lot of improvements that include Internet , 3G , music , video and photos .
In the Iphone 's development process , we can not deny that the user 's demands for new functions have a great influence in changing the Iphone .
First of all , users ' demand for the Iphone , which has more features and utilities to combine everything in a phone , forces Apple to continue developing Iphone .
Compared to the 1st generation of Iphone , the latest one ( 3GS ) is very different .
Initially , the Iphone only supported the EDGE network , 802.11b wireless standard , and 4GB internal storage .
Now the Iphone 3GS supports 3G network , video call , 802.11n wireless standard , and up to 32GB internal storage .
To satisfy users ' demand for new applications , themes , software and utilities , Apple finally released the Iphone SDK on March 6 2008 ( Apple , 2008 ) . The Iphone SDK provides a platform in which the programmer can build and develop software , from the simple to the very complicated .
The second factor that affects the Iphone is the user 's budget during the economic crisis .
During the crisis , the sale of the smart phone in general decreases because people do not want to spend money on unnecessary things .
Worldwide sales of hi-tech " smartphones " grew at their slowest pace in the fourth quarter of 2008 as the financial crisis hit demand , according to a research firm2 .
There is no way for Apple to encourage people to buy their products except to make them more valuable .
In 2009 summer , Apple introduces the new version of Iphone , the 3GS , at the same price as the older version .
The new one has higher core speed and bigger RAM , which allows the Iphone to run faster , and it can even display a high definition movie .
Apple also reduces the price of the 3G version to make it affordable to more users .
The result is " California-based Apple was the third-biggest player with iPhone sales of 11.42 million units , more than triple the 3.3 million sold when it launched the device in 2007 " ( citation ) .
Therefore , the user 's demand for advanced technology has contributed to the development of the Iphone through several years .
the Iphone can serve many functions , such as entertainment and video conference .
Although the Iphone is the best smart phone in the market at the moment , it have to be developed further and be offered at a lower price to satisfy the customers .
Both the military and civil demand for precise navigation promote the development of the Global Positioning System
Nowadays , almost everybody knows about GPS ( Global Positioning System ) , and it has made a significant difference in our daily lives , from guiding family hiking to airline navigation .
However , a lot of people may not know that it is a seemingly new and advanced technology that has already existed for more than forty years
( Lowry , 2006 ) . It is the military and civil demand for precise navigation that stimulates the development of the GPS technology to what it is today .
After the WW ( full name ) , the US military realized the weakness of navigating by the stars and the radio signals and started to seek for a more precise positioning system to guide their fighters and warships globally
( Lowry , 2006 ) . In the late nineteen fifties , the scientists in USA realized the possibility of accurate positioning by satellites and finally in 1960 , a satellite navigation system called " Transit " was tested in the USA navy . This is to meet its intense requirement for precise navigation to avoid unnecessary shipwreck .
Since then , in order to grasp the information of the precise positions of its armed forces all over the world , the United States Department of Defense allotted millions of dollars in the GPS R&D , which eventually resulted in a complete Global Positioning System with the operation of two dozen of polar orbiting satellites
( Yogendra , 2002 ) .
Besides military demand , public appeal for a safe civil navigation has also promoted the development of the GPS .
In 1983 , a US civilian airliner KAL 007 was shot down by the Soviet Union Air Force by mistake when it lost its way and flew into the airspace of the Soviet Union without authorization . Thus , the US civilians blamed the government for its ignorance in the safety of civil navigation .
In order to calm the masses and avoid such disasters in future , the then president Ronald Regan promised to apply GPS to civilian users as well as military once it was completed
( Lawry , 2006 ) . And due to the immense pressure of the public , the US government turned off the SA ( Selective Available ) in May 2000 . This leads the the GPS to develop from a critically military supplied technology to a system for both civilian and military use
( Gibbon Media& Research LLC , 2007 ) .
The idea of GPS is first put forward in the nineteen forties .
Since then , both the military and the public have demanded for precise navigation , which promoted the further development of GPS and make it into what we see today -a precise dual-use global positioning system for both the civilians and the military forces .
Technology is the practical application of knowledge , especially in a specific area .
This essay will compare and contrast the discovery of penicillin and the development of embryonic stem cells , in terms of impetus of the invention , involvement of the researchers in the innovation development and the of the inventions on society .
The impetus of these technologies comes from the needs of society .
The embryonic stem cells technology has developed rapidly during a short period because society needs a new way of transplantation .
Similarly , because the society needed a new medicine to treat some diseases like pneumonia , penicillin was discovered .
The discovery of penicillin is by accident and after a long time , it was used as medicine .
The impetus of these technologies is society needs .
However , there are slight differences between these two technologies in terms of the researchers involved .
For technology that is developed via research , like the stem cells , it tends to involve a large group of researchers and even researchers from different countries .
However , for the serendipitous discovery , it seems to involve a smaller group of people , and sometimes only individual .
Researchers involved in these two kinds of technologies are almost the same , with slight differences between them .
Last but not least , their effects on society also have similarities and differences .
Both promote social development .
If doctors use organs which are obtained by stem cells , many technical problems can be solved , like rejection reaction and organ shortage .
The differences lie in the length of time taken for it to be widely used by the majority of people .
Technology developed via research will take a shorter time to be accepted by majority of the people , while technology developed via serendipitous discovery may be rejected by people .
There are similarities and differences between technologies developed via research and serendipitous discovery .
In future , more and more useful technologies will be developed and they can give us a lot of benefits .
The world has become much richer and more complete with inventions or innovations .
Putting these ideas into actions and facing obstacles that come along the way leads to technological innovation .
During this process , technological innovation is affected by economical and social factors which shaped the innovation .
One of the many innovations that help to make our lives convenient is " Refrigeration " .
This is a technology that is shaped by a society in the past which was desperate to preserve its food .
Ice from mountains or snowy areas were transported to warmer regions where they were wrapped in cloth and placed in cellas .
The ice box was made of a metal linked box insulated with cork or snow dust with one compartment to put the ice and another to store the perishables .
The civil war in the US interrupted the ice trade .
The idea of refrigeration is built based on the principle that when liquid changes to gas , it absorbs heat as it expands in a self contained cycle , and air or other fluid surrounding the device can be reduced in temperature .
Using this principle , the gas refrigerator and the electric refrigerator were built .
Gas refrigerators use ammonia or the compression refrigerant .
The gas refrigerator did not comprise any moving parts and therefore it would not break down easily .
Electric refrigerators use an electric motor to pump the coolant or the refrigerant around the enclosed system .
Unlike gas refrigerators , electric refrigerators are noisy and a disruption in the supply of electricity would mean that the refrigerator would stop working .
When gas refrigerations develop a leak , the gas released is irritating and slightly corrosive .
Since the gases used in a gas refrigerators are usually poisonous and flammable , people are not very comfortable with having such gases in their houses .
Therefore , safety concerns outweigh the advantages of gas refrigerators and make the situation favourable for electric refrigators .
Economic factors have also contributed to the success of electric refrigerators .
Since greater economic profits could be gained from manufacturing electric refrigerators as compared to gas refrigerators , large firms started to invest huge amount of research ad development ( R&D ) funding into producing the electric refrigerators , as well as to promote it aggressively .
Therefore , small firms producing gas refrigerators could not compete with the strong competition . With insufficient resources for R & D , further developments of the refrigerator were not possible and it was also difficult to keep the prices of gas refrigerators competitive . The gas refrigerators were forced to go out of sales and the sales of the electric refrigerator continued to boom .
Therefore , economic profit gained from the product would also affect technological innovation .
In conclusion , the path of technological innovation is shaped by many factors .
In the case of refrigeration , gas refrigeration was invented first but due to corporate profitability , R &D fundings were provided for the electric refrigerations . It was then developed further to meet the various demands of people and brought into use widely around the world .
The production of gas refrigerations on the other hand , was forced to close down due to the lack of R & D funding .
Safety has also been a main concern in this technological innovation .
As the gases used in the gas refrigerator were not safe , it was not popular among the consumers .
Therefore , factors such as safety concerns and corporate profitability have played a part in shaping the technological innovation of refrigeration .
The length of the tank 's history is almost one hundred year since 1916 when it was first used as a secret weapon of the British .
If we trace its history further , we can see that Leonardo de Vinci had drawn a similar picture of tank in the 15th century .
Although we are not sure what kind of materials and technologies Vinci had tried to use when constructing his " tank " , we are still astonished by his ingenious imagination .
However , the tank is not a common vehicle for many people .
Most people do not have a chance to operate a tank , but they are interested in it .
The tank is tightly related to war since the first day it was born .
Inevitably , government and military demand for the tank play a vital role in its development .
Both the Triple Entente and Triple Alliance encountered problems with the trench warfare while fighting each other during World War I ( WWI ) .
The British government was very worried about the situation .
After a while , the British government not only took his advice but also organized a professional group to design and produce the tank .
Since the technologies used in tanks and common vehicles are quite the same , the vehicle industry quickly became the pillar industry of many industrialized countries .
It provided many job opportunities as well as markets .
However , after WWI , the leader of the Nazi Party in Germany , Hitler , became very enthusiastic about the mass production of the automobile , because he wanted to use the technology to produce more tanks for World War II ( WWII ) .
Germany was not allowed to have tanks because of the Treaty of Versailles. .
In 1933 , Hitler met Ferdinan Porsche , the founder of the Porsche , and talked about " Volkswagen " .
With the government investment in the research , a cheap automobile called the " beetle " was born in 1936 .
After WWII , the development of tanks has never stopped .
The most common type is the main battle tank ( MBT ) .
Compared to the original tank , the modern tank has a navigation system , infrared night-vision scope , composite armor , etc .
It seems that all the powerful countries are involved in this technological competition .
Russia has T-72 and
the U.S. has M1A1 .
However , no matter how well they have developed their tanks , casualties are inevitable in the war .
Maybe more people will die in wars after new tanks are being introduced .
In conclusion , tank is a great engineering product which government , global politics and military industry have shaped together .
.
Its quick development and adaptability in the battle field is incomparable .
It plays the main role in land battle in modern warfare .
The success of a technology not only depends on how well it resolves the targeted need but also the social considerations it incurs when being introduced to the consumer market .
" The network of power " , a book by Thomas Hughes , addresses one pertinent problem on the way we view technology .
We tend to be blinded by the benefits of a technology and overlook the importance of understanding it as an entire system .
By looking at the development of automobiles , from electric vehicles to gasoline-powered cars , we are able to understand how economic factors have influenced oil magnates , car manufacturers and the government , which ultimately shaped this technological innovation .
With the rise of an alternate fuel source , oil companies may suffer a loss in profits and the possibility of being put out of business .
They may even resort to underhanded means like spreading false information about the new technology .
For instance , doubts were cast on the ability of batteries delivering 100km per charge .
Even if there is a more environmentally friendly fuel , they would resist to develop it .
Car manufacturers are the next immediate culprit culpable for the continued devlopment of gasoline-powered vehicles , rather than focusing on the environmentally friendly electric car .
They know that their core group of customers are a group of non-risk takers who are still uncertain about the new technology .
From a consumer point of view , it does not offer good value for the money spent .
The road users would not pay more for an underpowered vehicle or to be environmenenvironmentally friendly .
Furthermore , carmakers have tried to promote cars using the hydrogen technology , which may still require years of development .
This smokescreen failed to hide the truth that they are afraid to lose the customers .
The government is another deciding factor in shaping the automobile technology .
For example , in 1998 the Carlifornia Air Resource Board mandated that any car company capable of producing electric cars must ensure that 2 percent of their sales are emission-free cars .
However , despite 5000 electric cars being manufactured , 4000 were scraped after major car dealers pressured the government to cancel the mandate .
In other words , the governemnt takes into account the collapse of the automobile and oil industries and the consequences that will ensue , such as the loss of jobs and the increase in unemployment .
To sum up , oil companies , car manufacturers and the government have considered issues from the economic point of view and realised that the consequences of making electric cars are too drastic .
The oil and automobile industries are too lucrative and at the same time crucial to the overall economy , so much so that issues regarding pollution and environment are secondary to it .
Hence , the automobile technology is ultimately shaped by oil magnates , car companies and the government .
The two problems are attitude and funding , which have severe impact on the local engineering process for innovations .
The engineering design process for innovations can be broken down into 3 stages : creativity , process and materialization .
The two problems will be elaborated on how they impact the engineering process for innovations .
This could be due to personal and social attitude towards innovation .
We shall begin with the individual attitude and examine it hampers the local engineering process for innovations .
Singaporeans tend to be prudent and stable .
Being prudent , Singaporeans tend to be less adventurous when compared to their western counterparts .
One common scenario would be for parents to advise their children , especially those with tertiary education , to get a decent job and contribute to the family 's expenditure .
If their children want to go into the research and development profession , such as to become a researcher in a university , they will be discouraged .
Children who later grow up into adults do not do not utilize their creativity , which may be helpful in the engineering design process .
The second part would be the society 's attitude in seeking to hamper the engineering process for innovations . An example would be Paddy Tan , the creator who came up with the unique service that allows owners who have lost their mobile phones to track them down .
When he initially launched his software , the response was lukewarm .
He had to bring his product overseas before his product became popular .
The local society does not have a positive attitude in accepting new engineering innovations and this could affect the materialization stage of the engineering process for innovation .
If no one wants to accept a new product , it will be hard for it to exist in the market and this will also deter people from participating in the engineering design process for innovations .
A good example is the formula racing car of the National University Of Singapore ( NUS ) . The initial stages required the professor and his students to each come up with three hundred dollars to purchase the necessary parts .
However not all inventors have the luck of achieving initial success and thus receiving funding .
Failure to secure funding will turn away inventors with engineering flair
Serendipity is the accidental discovery of a new idea , and the 3M post-it pad is one of such example .
On 4 July 2009 , The Straits Times reported the development of a new product to help the deaf experience sound , the Haptic Chair , by researchers from the National University of Singapore ( NUS ) .
Both innovations bring benefit to the lives of people .
A case of serendipity occurred a few decades ago when researchers from 3M laboratories discovered a new bonding agent .
Next , he distributed pads of the post-it notes to 3M 's president 's executive secretary , who also found them useful .
Eventually , the post-it pads were further distributed to different companies , leading up to its big marketing success today
( Rogers , 2003 ) .
The product is made with the understanding that sound waves , apart from travelling through air , can also travel through solid matter
( Grace , 2009 ) .
The difference between serendipitous discoveries and researched technologies are the types of resources invested in their development .
A serendipitous discovery happens by chance , and has no pre-allocated funds or project timeframe to adhere to .
The post-it pads came about because the 3M researcher happened to have some non-permanent adhesive , and he decided to come out with a new product on his own .
Before he gave the post-it pads to others , no funds or expertise were assigned to him for the post-it 's development .
In the case of The Haptic Chair , a team of researchers had worked together with Suranga Nanayakkara .
A lot of time and effort were put in by the team before it could actually come out with the product .
The post-it pads were only found to be successful after they were given to the 3M president 's executive secretary , who found them useful and mass-distributed them to various companies .
The general public is required to see the item as something useful before it was deemed to be successful .
In The Straits Times article , it was reported that partially deaf musicians like teen piano prodigy Azariah Tan found various aspects of the invention intriguing
( Rogers , 2003 and Grace , 2009 )
For the 3M researcher , he has identified the need to stick notes on paper without leaving adhesive stains to damage original documents ; for the NUS student , he has identified the need to create a product to aid those with hearing problems .
Both technologies benefit the lives of people , and have potentials for profit .
In conclusion , we have come to learn that new technologies can come about via research and via serendipitous discoveries .
What we do need to bear in mind is this : technologies of both natures serve different groups of people in different ways , and they ultimately bring benefits to the lives of people .
Innovation occurs when there is a need for a new product or service . When someone faces a problem and motivates people to find ways to solve it , new ideas are generated .
As we need equipment to solve problems .
Many technological innovations are made via scientific research or the interaction of scientific investigations and applying them on practical needs and problems .
A new idea is created from the rigorous process of research .
Others may be serendipitously invented .
Serendipity means unexpected discoveries or inventions .
These findings are often unpredictable .
Serendipitous discovery can happen to anyone as well as in any field .
This stimulates development and research to create something in order to solve the problem or fulfill a need .
For example , General Motor 's electric car was developed because of the need to meet the requirements of environmentally friendly cars . .
Besides that , General Motor wishes to reposition itself as an innovative company .
These are the two factors that drive it to initiate the research and develop the electric car .
When asked to investigate the death of a farmer 's cow , a professor
found that an anticoagulation agent called coumarin was the cause when the hay stem punctured the cow 's stomach .
Years later he experimented it as a rat killer , and found that it was a very effective rodenticide .
The main contrast between technology created via research and technology created serendipitously is that the former has a clear direction and the latter is created while in the process of researching something which is totally unrelated .
With the use of findings through basic research and investigations , they are able to discover and develop new tools to solve problems .
However , the latter does not have a specific objective , the discovery is purely unpredictable .
In conclusion , innovation occurs at anywhere and anytime .
Through constant exchanges of information about problems , human needs and wants , we can come up with better ideas to solve problems and make our world a better place to live in .
Rogers ( 2003 ) defines technology as a design for instrumental action that reduces the uncertainty in the cause-effect relationships involved in achieving a desired outcome .
However , some unpredicted technologies were invented by accident .
Both the stove and the microwave oven are used to cook our daily meal at home but they were discovered in two different ways .
We will use these stages to compare and contrast the two different technologies .
In the past , people used fire , coal , or heat from the sun to cook .
the stove was invented because people need to cook by applying heat to the food .
Dr. Percy Spencer discovered the microwave technology by serendipity when he found that the candy bar in his pouch melted when he was experimenting with his new magnetron .
The history of the stove and microwave shows that serendipity and researched technology have come from very different beginnings .
Serendipity comes from a branch of a problem or need , while research technology comes straight from the problem or needs .
Subsequently , technology on basic application needs to be researched further .
The stove has undergone a very long history and it has been tested and improved over the centuries .
Similarly , the basic application of the microwave oven is progressively being improvised from the technology of the microwave radio signal radar .
Thus , we can see that both technologies refer to their basic applications for further research .
Next , when the basic and application research are established , the development of the product will begin .
The first known stove was built on the ground with sticks forming a tripod to hold the cooking pot above the heat source .
Today , it has become very compact and light , and features like the automatic functions allow users to cook with just pressing a button .
In conclusion , we have compared and contrasted the serendipitous and research technology using the three stages of innovation-development process .
The results show that both technologies were developed in two very different ways --- research technology is created via recognition of problems and need , while serendipitous technology is discovered by pure accident and has no purpose at the beginning .
However , the two technologies are similar in the stages on basic application and development .
It can be sub-divided into two categories of being developed through research and serendipitous discovery .
The two categories aim at improving the quality of people 's lives and numerous trials are needed for its success . The technologies differ in how they came about and they are being accepted by other people .
One similarity between both categories is achieving the aim of improving the quality of life for people .
The Bionic eyes are being developed as engineers thought of ways to improve visual displays in various fields , such as gaming and the aviation industry .
They hope to develop lenses that will allow players to be entirely immersed in the game , and to move without any constraints .
For the aviation industry , it is hope that through the new technology , pilots will be able to know the speed of the plane almost immediately .
The 3M 's Post-its come in very handy when people want to remind themselves of various events or when people want to comment on essays without writing on them .
It is convenient to use as it can stick to almost any surfaces and be peeled off easily without leaving any marks .
In addition , both technologies have gone through numerous trials before they become what they are now .
In the case of the Bionic eyes , the challenges were to choose materials that are harmless to the body and to put circuit boards in contact lenses which are tiny in size .
They also had to consider how to create slim layers of circuit boards to be placed inside the contact lenses .
As for the invention of Post-its , the researchers were initially looking for a bonding agent that allows paper to bond . But along the way , another type of bonding agent was discovered , and it was deemed useless at first because it did not achieve its original aim .
One of the differences is how the technologies came about .
For the Bionic eyes , it was done via research after it was seen in a movie called 'Terminator ' , where a woman is able to zoom into places that are far away .
This gave the engineers the idea of turning what they see in movies into realities .
Post-its was discovered accidentally by researches who were trying to find bonding agents that can be used to bind papers firmly to a surface .
It was a by-product of what the researchers were trying to achieve .
It was once deemed " worthless " until people found uses for it and it has become one of the most commonly used products in our daily life and one of the products that make the most revenue for 3M .
For the Bionic eyes , it is easier for the public to accept it as this was done with the aim of developing lenses that will help improve the quality of life .
It will also be easier to find people to help market this product .
Post-its was initially seen as a 'failure product ' .
It is only accepted and marketed by the company after someone started sending samples out to the Fortune 500 companies to test the product .
It may have been abandoned and 3M may not be making such so much revenue out of it each year .
In conclusion , both technologies , be it developed via research or from a serendipitous discovery , have achieved the aim of improving the lives of people .
Initial acceptance of the two technologies may be different , which in turn depends on the mindset of the public .
One of the earliest inventions was the wheel .
Over the past decade , a new term " skunkworks " has surfaced .
This term describes the existence of a small groups of researchers who are not bound by corporate rules and politics .
There are several similarities and differences between the technologies generated by " skunkworks " and conventionally generated technologies .
Products generated by each environment may appear similar , but they actually differ in many ways . The environment plays an important part in shaping their distinctive features .
The first similarity that conventionally generated technologies and " skunkworks " generated technologies share is the ability to produce cutting-edge technology .
For example , the IMPACT car developed by General Motors ( GM ) and the Toshiba laptop .
The IMPACT car was conventionally generated by GM to change the fate of automobiles .
The second similarity is that for both environments , generally large amount of money and support has to be put in by the head company .
Hence , long hours are required before any results are visible .
A few examples include GM developing the first electric car named IMPACT , Apple developing their first Macintosh computer and Xerox 's attempt at developing the world 's first personal computer .
Thus , it is evident that huge amount of financing and support is generally required in both environments .
However
there are instances where " skunkworks " environments have little financing and support from the head company .
As a result , the Toshiba laptop has received very little marketing as compared to the IMPACT car by GM .
This has resulted in very different products being developed in each environment .
The " skunkworks " environment has been able to provide the developers with the flexibility and freedom required to break traditional barriers and develop cutting-edge technologies .
Furthermore , " skunkworks " environment is very stressful as compared to the traditional corporate environment due to the lack of financing and hence , the room for error becomes much smaller .
The last and perhaps the most significant difference in the environments has to be the difference in the features of technologies developed by each environment .
An example of such a difference is again present in the IMPACT car and the Toshiba laptop .
Under the stressful skunkworks environment , the researchers from Toshiba are able to think critically and design a product to meet the needs of the society .
On the other hand , the researchers from GM have failed to realize that the public and society were not ready for their invention .
In conclusion , it is clear that the technology churned out by a " skunkworks " environment differs greatly from that of a conventionally generated technology .
The features and characteristics of the " skunkworks " technology set it apart from conventionally generated technology .
.
Innovations can emerge though research or it may be from some serendipitous discoveries .
A certain type of technology may be developed and polished through numerous research and experiment .
On the other hand , another may be discovered purely by chance .
Two typical examples are the electric cars and the Warfarin .
The electric car is invented by some hardworking engineers , while the Warfarin is being discovered serendipitously .
Although they are initialized differently , there are several similarities in the developing process .
Generally , technologies that are developed through research often begin with the need for practical uses or the recognition of a social problem .
The electric car is not an exception .
As the situation of the environment on earth becomes worse and the energy resources are depleting quickly , the need for inventing pollution-free and energy- saving cars is urgent .
Some governments encourage automobile companies to produce environmentally friendly cars .
The motivation of engineers to design electric cars is obvious .
Nobody knew that the chemical in spoiled sweet clover that caused cattle hemorrhage could actually be used as a rat poison until Link , the scientist , accidentally found it .
Even he was surprised when he found the chemical to be highly lethal to rats .
Despite the huge difference that exists in identifying and initializing the innovations developed through research and via serendipitous discovery , there are similarities in some aspects of development .
Serendipitous discoveries can not be put into use straightaway .
Innovations and technologies are for the public use , and they are not completed without confirmations from lab work and data. .
Technologies that are developed via research and from serendipitous discovery are similar in the way that they benefit the society .
Both technologies are globally adopted by the public , and they bring benefits to the whole society .
To sum up , technologies developed via research and from serendipitous discovery are differently initialized .
However , they are similar in the sense that they have to undergo the same process of experiments and research , and both can be very successful and bring benefits to the whole society .
During the process of developing innovations , it is important to consider every detail seriously and the possibility of making serendipitous discoveries .
There are numerous problems that are faced by the world today .
Governments of different countries may have different agenda lists ; however , aging population is definitely an issue present in the list .
Engineers play a huge role in assisting the government to achieve the aim of creating a better and safer environment for the elderly to live in .
With a safer environment , the welfare of the elderly will be improved and less social problems will occur .
Some examplesxamples of such engineering design are the building of ramps at the main entrance of the flats , handrails at the side of the stairs and providing buses for the wheelchair bound .
For example , the Housing Development Board ( HDB ) had implemented several designs to improve the convenience of the elderly , such as installing lifts on every storey and building wider internal corridors and hallways .
The designs had proven to be useful for the flat holders when the HDB first implemented them .
According to Khandani ( 2005 ) , after each solution is generated , it must be tested and implemented to see the effects brought on by the solution .
In this case , there are positive effects associated with the engineering designs made for the HDB flats , and thus the government had implemented the solution throughout Singapore .
Many different countries have come up with many different innovative designs to facilitate the objective .
One of such designs is the wheelchair bound bus provided by the Singapore SMRT Corporation Ltd ( SMRT )
This wheelchair bound bus was first implemented in the European countries , and people have found that the design is innovative , and it benefits the elderly and the handicap .
There is an engineering design process mentioned by Khandani ( 2005 ) which states that when engineers are thinking of the solution to the problem , they should actually research for more information on the relevant issue and observe how the others approach the problem .
Hence , in this case , SMRT has observed the good response from the other countries that had implemented this form of transport , and has decided to try out the transport in Singapore .
Generally , the engineering design process consists mainly of the five procedures mentioned by Khandani ( 2005 ) which includes defining the problem , gathering the relevant information , thinking of solutions to the problem , analyzing and selecting one solution , and testing it out by implementing it .
Although all the steps mentioned by Khandani ( 2005 ) are crucial for designing a good engineering product , the most important step is to test the solution and see the public would response to it .
This is because every engineering product is designed to serve the people and to bring a greater convenience to their lives .
In conclusion , engineering design is a never ending process , and it is the duty of the engineers to keep coming up with solutions to solve the pressing issue of creating better products for the aging population .
An increasing death rate due to traffic accidents has become a major problem in many countries .
The World Health Organisation ( WHO ) states that traffic accidents are in the ninth position among the reasons which lead to death .
When considering the European Union , 1.3 million road traffic accidents occur each year , resulting in 1.7 million injuries and over 40000 death annually ( International Journal of Health Geographic ) .
Even Singapore which implements strong traffic laws and regulations has also been affected by this traffic accident problem .
The accident rate per 10,000 vehicles has increased from 2.34 in 2006 to 2.60 in 2007 in Singapore ( Singapore Police Force ) .
The three important features in the engineering design process will cater to the need to form a new traffic system .
Firstly , a feature in the design process is the identification of the problem and to gather pertinent information .
This step will allow us to identify the reasons for traffic accidents from different angles .
It will help us to identify problems in the current system by doing various studies of the current traffic system .
The studies include the gathering of relevant information to analyse the situation .
For example , doing traffic counts , area-wide surveys and parking surveys , as well as identifying the speed of moving vehicles could help to gain a better understanding of the problem .
For instance , the Times of India states that there was a survey taken in India to measure the percentage of vehicles on the road and the percentage of people taking public transports ( citation ) . This survey has really helped people to understand which cities have high rates of traffic jams and the reasons for them .
Another important feature is the idea generation process .
This is a very important process as it is the point where we will be able to come up with solutions to the problems .
In the process , we will be able to analyse the statistics/surveys that we have obtained and generate new ideas to solve the problem .
These solutions may include devices to identify speeding vehicles and to make sure that there is sufficient spacing between vehicles .
The Netherlands was the first country to implement such road safety devices and they prove to be helpful as road accident rates dropped by 25 % in 2000 as compared to accident rates in 1985 ( citation ) .
From this we can understand that it is essential to come up with a system which is useful in various ways .
So it is important to come up with ideas which will be useful and economical .
It is the point where we will select the solution which best suits the current situation .
To conclude , it is very clear that engineering design process will be a useful method in solving the current traffic problem .
The three important features mentioned are problem identification , solution analysis and selection . They are the key features of the design process which will be really useful in solving the problem .
There are many pressing issues that need to be addressed in the current world .
They are problems like global warming and aging population .
We need to solve these problems as soon as possible .
The need for better health care should be the given priority since it affects us directly .
Hence , many health care products are created and modelled by engineers to meet this need .
In recent years , there were two viral outbreaks that affected us badly and they are caused by the Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome ( SARS ) and the Influenza A ( H1N1 ) virus .
These viruses are very contagious and their victims show a common symptom --- fever .
The engineers have come up with new thermometers that can help to contain the spread .
In the process of developing them , engineers can follow the engineering design processes described by Khandani ( 2005 ) .
Firstly , by understanding what they need , , or " designing the problem " , engineers will know that the new thermometer has to minimise contact between users to prevent the spreading of virus .
Other than that , engineers will also need to go through the process of " analysing and selecting a solution " to make sure that the new product is fairly safe before releasing it into the market and it will not cause any health problem to the user .
As a result , the ear thermometer was introduced , which is safe and fast to use .
It also minimises with the ear by using a plastic cover on the detector that will be disposed after use .
From the original design that requires manual operation to being moved with the touch of single button , the wheelchair has undergone many changes .
Every change is made possible not by chance , but by following a set of engineering design processes , like the set mentioned in Khandani ( 2005 ) .
Ever since the first wheelchair is being made , it has benefitted many people .
However , engineers were not satisfied because they felt that it can be improved further , after looking at how the users used it .
They started the process of creating an automated wheelchair by " defining the problem " that some users do not have enough strength to push the wheelchair .
After that , engineers have to " gather pertinent information " to make sure that this problem is real by doing a survey on the users , so that they will not waste time designing something that the market does not need .
And when they have the ideas on how to solve this problem , they need to ensure that they select the idea that is achievable with the current technology by " analysing the solutions " .
Some wheelchair users will try it and find if it has met criteria like user-friendliness , before it is released into the market .
In conclusion , the two examples we mentioned have shown that engineering processes can play a big part in the designing phrase of a product .
