Both Tamiflu and Penicillin benefit the human population though they work on different micro-organisms .
Most bacteria have rigid cell walls , which prevent them from bursting when they are placed in solutions of lower salt concentration .
However , viruses do not have cell walls and thus Penicillin has no effect on them .
Tamiflu is a neuraminidase inhibitor , and thus the virus is unable to exit the host cell and dies ( Roche , 2006 ) .
Due to the distinct difference in the structures of virus and bacteria , Tamiflu and Penicillin perform differently with them .
Penicillin has the ability to cure people who are from the once-fatal bacterial diseases .
Similarly , Tamiflu has also proven to be effective in the treatment and prevention of influenza in adults and in children .
Regardless of whether the technology is developed via research or discovered serendipitously , it has contributed significantly to mankind .
