Now credit cards are very popular in the world .
For example the circulation of credit cards in China jumped from 3 million in 2003 to 50 million in 2006 to 122 million in 2008
How was the magical card created ?
Which factors led to its production ?
I think there are three factors which contributed to the production of credit card .
Moreover , computer technology and network technology broadened the range of credit card plural and made a strong link between the card and our daily lives .
Secondly , from an economical perspective , it can be summarized in two points : one is the consumption concept implied in the credit , that 'is ' consumption before payment .
Also to some extent 'it ' increases the value of goods .
For example , one has to spend twenty days saving money before he affords to buy a nice coat .
So one earns the extra twenty-day usage of the , thanks to the credit card .
There are several simple methods of payment by using credit card such as punching the card on POS and RFID machines . , network payment and telephone payment .
This character of credit card makes it adaptable to the pace of modern life .
In summary , the concept that should be made before payment is the main reason for credit cards ' production .
