Research shows that , the World Health Organization assumes that about 80 % of all disabled people worldwide live in developing countries .
It is also estimated that there are 600 million disabled people worldwide , which is about 10 % of the world population .
Among these disabled people , the World Health Organization estimates that 27-35 million people are blind in the world , of which about 20 % live Africa and 65 % live in Asia .
The number of blind is rising . Firstly because of rapid increase in population size in developing countries ; and second despite of increased longevity , ageing is related to visual loss from cataract , glaucoma and macular degeneration .
Hence , the first solution is to invent and innovate equipments that help combat blindness .
Building eye treatment centres is another way to reduce blindness .
First of all , engineers have to fabricate products which combat blindness , that are user- friendly and low cost .
We will introduce not only new paradigms of instructions but also new approaches to deliver this up to date equipments .
Secondly , it is important to build eye treatment centers where patients can get treatment and buy the optical equipment .
Additionally , an attempt will be made to work with private initiators in order to build treatment centers which is run only by people who are blind visually damaged. .
Though the special treatment for blind and visually damaged people is a once- only expense , it is very expensive .
So to finance these expenses , we have to set up community service activities such as fund raising .
It is getting even lower : from 33 % blind working people in 1995 to 29 % in 1998 ( Harris , 1998 ) .Therefore , in order them to make progress , new possibilities and new occupational areas are needed .
In conclusion , blind people should also have same opportunities as everyone . This to get freedom from extreme limitation , to accomplish and to be able to have confidence
so that other people give respect to them .
Moreover , their passions are the same as others .
They too have same dreams and assurance that they can reach their targets .
The rapid increase of cars exhausts more carbon dioxide which is actually worsening the Green House effect .
Although countries like the US have already spent more than 10 years to do research and development on electric cars ( e-car conversions ) , there are still two main problems that significantly affect its growth in the market of China .
The government support is one of the main difficulties that prohibit the development of electric cars .
First of all , the running duration of the electric cars is what the government is concerned about .
By using the most advanced batteries , a fully charged electric car can run about 160km ( ) .
However , compared to gasoline cars which can last for 500 to 600 km , the distance travelled by the electric cars is still considered as too limited .
The government worries that the electric cars will restrict the development and expansion of the big big cities due to its short running duration .
Second , the cost for building the infrastructure of electric cars is really a big amount of money .
There are about 600 cities in China . Imagine how much it costs if the battery charging facilities are built in every car park .
Besides that , the development of the electric car industry will definitely affect traditional gasoline car industries
Thousands of petrol stations will have to close petrol related service industries will also be severely affected .
As a result , many people working in these areas will lose their jobs .
The government is reluctant to see such kinds of bad influence to the economy .
Many people suggest building electric cars is eco friendly .
Although there are wasted gas treatment processes in those factories , carbon dioxide emission is still unavoidable .
The only advantage is that the factories have high efficiency resources resulting in less pollution .
Besides that , making use of batteries will also have negative influence on the earth .
Normally , batteries are not biodegradable and there are toxic substances , such as mercury , inside the batteries ) .
