Engineering design process is usually a cyclic process where decision making is required .
Often , engineering sciences , basic sciences and mathematics are applied to convert the available information optimally to achieve the desired deeds .
Basically , this process can be divided into various steps including identifying objectives , defining problems , conducting research , analyzing solutions , making decisions , presenting the products and finally , selling the products .
These are the universal steps in the process which is followed by most engineers .
In Malaysia , corruption within the political system has led to slow development in design processes .
Besides , the education system introduced leads to a lack of creativity and innovation by engineers .
Undeniably , political systems in a country plays an essential role in the development of the country .
statistics have shown that Malaysia ranked 47th out of 180 nations on Transparency International 's 2008 Corruption Perception Index .
Under most circumstances , one needs to bribe in order to accomplish his or her objective .
For example , bribing is necessary and people usually need to pay money under the table to establish an engineering company , or to conduct a project .
One of the examples is the defects in Middle Ring Road 2 ( MRR2 ) fiasco , which happened in October 2004 .
The British engineering consultancy firm , Halcrow Consultancy Ltd , had found that there were structural defects of piers on the MRR2 highway due to design flaw .
Then , the Work Ministry and the Cabinet decided to replace the British with a German consultant , which costs RM40 million and at last , the Work ministry admitted that the repair cost was RM70 million .
Therefore , .
It is painful to hear that the repair works had to be deferred as the Anti-corruption Agency ( ACA ) stepped into the investigation .
Indirectly , these corruptions have hampered the engineering design process at the stage of analyzing solutions to get the repair work done as fast as possible .
In addition , the lack of creativity and innovation have been identified to be the main problems hampering the engineering design process , which might be due to the current education system in Malaysia .
Most of the students are so used to being spoon fed .
s , they expect that every solution will be provided .
They were overindulged by teachers as knowledge or information was provided to them in an oversimplified way , causing students to be too reliant on teachers .
Students have been treated in a way that discouraged independent thought and learning processes , thus indirectly hindering their ability to analyze and interpret problems due to a lack of creativity .
Consequently , these two reasons have caused a lack of development in engineering design process .
The corruption in the politicalystem and the abuse of power by the higher authorities hinders one 's motive to design a product as the steps to run a project is so tedious
As a result , there will be less and less engineering products being developed as a result people might not have opportunities to enjoy the conveniences and leisure that is brought about by the products .
On the other hand , a lack of creativity and innovation by engineers leads to a lack of knowledgeable engineers to design a product .
An engineer might have difficulties in interpreting solutions and making decisions during the design process if he or she lacks creativity .
Indirectly , insufficient human resources in engineering field might llead to a poor economy , due to a lack of progression in the engineering field .
In conclusion , corruption in the political system and the lack of creativity by engineers , , significantly hampers the engineering design process .
Therefore , action should be taken to prevent further corruption in the political system so that the engineering design process would not be hindered .
Hence , governments should encourage independent learning so that students will be more creative and innovative to facilitate engineering design process .
Before 1870 , people could communicate with one another from a distance only by writing .
But in 1876 , Alexander Graham Bell invented a device that changed the world .
He invented the telephone - a device that allows two remotely located users to communicate by voice with each other ( Mary Bellis , n.d ) .
Similarly , Konrad Zuse invented the first computer , which satisfies our need for a systematic and efficient method of data management ( Mary Bellis , n.d ) .
Therefore , they play a crucial role in the society by never failing to improve our standard of living .
