From 1840 to 1949 , The Chinese people were suffering from World War II and The Chinese civil war .
After these battles and wars , The Chinese people finally stepped in to a new era , a peaceful but impoverished era .
The Chinese people did not have time to develop their economy and technology .
Therefore , the Chinese economy and technology was far behind that of developed countries .
However , the Chinese people did not give up ; Chinese leaders put forward a series of policies .
Moreover , The Chinese people wanted to contribute towards establishing a new China .
This is why the Chinese economic situation was much better than before .
With regard to technology , a group of Chinese scientists and engineers sacrificed their holiday and worked day and night in order to improve the technology of China .
Therefore , many excellent and well designed technological outcomes appeared during that period of time .
But now , there are two factors hampering the innovative design process .
One is that students lack innovative thinking .
Learning means to learn and use the knowledge which has been taught by the teachers .
Thinking means students consider how these theorems are derived and how to find the simplest way to solve the problem .
For example , when students ask their teachers a question , , they usually would say they can not solve a particular problem , and question why this formula does not work ? .
However , we need to hear students say that they have tried a new method to solve a problem .
their query is to ask if the teacher can help to check if their method could be used or not .
The main reason for the present lack is the Chinese situation .
China has the largest population , and they use the college examination to select the talented people .
Furthermore , the method of testing is to provide many questions and to have students solve them quickly rather than give students a single question and have them solve it in many different ways. .
There is also limited time for a teacher to grade the exam paper .
So if the solution is not the standard solution which is given by the ministry of education , the solution is incorrect .
Therefore , students are satisfied in using one way to solve a problem .
For instance , when there is a finding which is interesting and can contribute to society ,
scientists and engineers will do their research individually and if someone were to invent a machine by this finding first .
However , one person takes a whole year to make one invention .
What if a group of engineers invents this machine ?
The time would be much shorter than one year and the quality of this invention would be much better .
Hence , if Chinese scientists and engineers work as a team , the efficiency of work will be improved and the period of work time will be less .
There will be more innovative outcomes appearing in the Chinese market and the technology of China will be raised to a new level .
However , coming up with new ideas and innovations are more often than not , easier said than done .
As a matter of fact , statistically speaking , the number of failed attempts at innovation far exceed the ones which made it into the books .
For instance , the proposed plan to use nuclear energy in Malaysia never came to pass due to the enormous funds that is required to carry out research in the technology and even if the necessary funds are secured , there is always the uncertainty if the research will yield any significant results .
In the case of a nuclear power plant in Malaysia , the idea is not viable as the country has an abundance of forest reserves which needs to be kept untarnished and preserved .
Besides that , the innovations that engineers come up with needs to be safe for the public to use .
With small but useful engineering design ideas being introduced daily , serving as a basis for many bigger innovations , it 's only a matter of time before the many obstacles which are holding engineers back are removed .
