as human needs are carefully observed to make necessary adjustments , the need for medical things and the curing of diseases is presently the top priority
Disease has been a great concern for humans from a very long time ago , but medical system seems not to be enough in the fight with countless threats that steals many human lives .There are many limitations that can only be surpassed by the magic of engineers ' technology .
For instance , many doctors are having trouble in predicting human symptoms .
There are many diseases like cancerwhich can not be cured using only normal medicine .
This is the moment engineers start their innovations .
They realize the first problem is that we need a revolution in medical procedures .
The normal methods like injecting medicine , predicting a threatening symptom using common equipment does not bring optimal results or worse , it is useless especially with the dangerous diseases .
We need a great change and the most possible plan now is to apply nanotechnology .
Using the latest knowledge , engineers can design various types of micro-robots which have the size of a bacterium .
With this size , the normal physical limitation is now removed and we can easily discover every corner of the human body .
It not only reduces the material cost , makes a more accurate diagnosis , but also is less painful for the patient and gives scientists a great chance to study deeper about the human body .
These micro-robots can have many useful functions .
It can bring a camera and help doctors observe the inner world of the human body with their own eyes .
It can be attached with a tiny medicine package and put directly into the damaged spot .
This micro-robot is very promising and now is developed by many professional engineers all over the word and will soon be released , making it one of the greatest achievement of engineers
The long and tedious journey in finding the key to save mankind now lies in a tiny microscopic life , that is extracted from a mammals embryos , called stem cells .
They are believed to have the ability to create brand new organs , curing an array of serious diseases and even perhaps solving human ageing problems , .
Although after 30 years of research , scientists are still unable to solve the mystery of these cells , but there has been fruitful development where these stems are now being used to repair important tissues in the human body
But due to the nature of these cells , scientists now face both technological and scientific problems which hinders them from unleashing the full potential of these cells .
Technology played an important role , to aid researchers on in their work .
We need the right tools for the right kind of job , we ca n't possibly use a screwdriver to do a hammer 's work ,
wee need better technology to increase scientist 's capability to understand this cell better , like how it changes ( Transform ) into specialized cells which will later transform into an organ .
With current DNA technology , it has proven insufficient to proceed any faster .
This is a serious factor that scientists are now looking into , and once they succeed , imagine the amount of life that would be saved .
Meeting the demand in the market and reducing the cost of medical treatments bringing an infinite possibility to the medical-industry .
One of the fascinating problems faced , is the human body itself .
Firstly the human body has an extraordinary capability to identify foreign objects and purge them out from the system ( Rejection ) .
This has led to serious complications to patients who are receiving this life-saving treatment .
Without this , it would result in an uncontrollable and misdirected growth of unwanted cells , etc tumor , or even cancerous cells .
This is a major obstacle that scientists are now facing .
I believe this would be a most valuable scientific breakthrough .
The world food crisis would be solved by merging these cells with the current cloning technology to create fast and range of food supplies .
Take the aspect of electric devices as an example , The refrigerator was studied for a long time in the laboratory after people had the desire of preserving things in a cold temperature longer .
On the other hand , the theory of the microwave oven was discovered by Percy Spencer by chance .
He noticed that candy in his pocket melted while he was doing another experiment and by using this technology the microwave oven was invented .
As technologies of modern society , both The refrigerator and the microwave oven have practical meaning .
Refrigerators helps to keep food fresh and microwave ovens helps to heat food quickly .
They are used in a way to make our lives better and more convenient .
Actually , they both have become essentials of daily life .
In this way , the standard and quality of life has improved to a large degree .
Firstly , refrigeration was a concept before it was invented .
As a result , the product will sell well because the aim of the technology was a common desire to meet the demand of the public .
The microwave oven , on the contrary , was not known before the theory was discovered and the equipment invented .
Thus , sometimes there will be a risk in producing a large amount of equipment applying the serendipitously discovered technology because the market for this product might not be large .Since before it was invented , other ways may have already existed .
Secondly , developing the technology for the refrigerator in the laboratory needs a long time .
Since the idea was introduced , generations of people have used various methods to improve the machine and make the technology perfect .
Do you know that the global worldwide energy consumption was 500 exajoules which is astounding 5 Ã 1020 J ?
Next , the electrons with higher energy levels in the panels will be separated from their atoms and allowed to flow in a single direction due to the special composition of the cells .
( " Photovoltaics " ) However , in most third world countries , the governments or private industries may not have the funds to set up photovoltaic plants due to the high initial capital
Therefore , solar energy being a clean and renewable source of energy will definitely build up its popularity as a popular source that can be used to produce electricity .
Since there is life on the earth,all living things depend on the sun.Photosynthesis is the process whereby green plants turn carbon dioxide and water into carbohydrate.The energy we humans need is directly or indirectly received through photosynthesis .
petroleum,coal and gas are an outcome of photosynthesis . that nature gives to us .
Because of the rapid development of the world,the energy that nature passes over to us are less and less.This even causes countries to begin an energy war.Energy plays a more and more important role.what we desperately need is a kind of resource that can give out high energy and does not do harm to the nature .
Hydrogen energy is this kind of energy.There is only water after it burns and hydrogen contains a lot of heat.So we need to try hard to invent a machine to make hydrogen energy .
To achieve this we use plates that are made of semiconductors which can absorb the sun light . Simulated by the sun 's light , the semiconductor can emit electrons . The whole plate forms a battery.So the solar energy will be successfully converted into electrical energy .
After doing this , we will artificially simulate the process of photosynthesis.In this step,we need to find a highly efficient catalyst to speed up the electrolyzation and make the process to be complete.Finally , we can get the hydrogen gas .
Hydrogen gas has been produced,but the transmission is still hard work.We need a high-pressure and low-temperature surroundings to let the hydrogen remain in liquid form.But it is very hard to make that kind of surroundings in normal life.We need a kind of catalyst to make the hydrogen be liquid at normal temperature and pressure .
We will no longer be afraid of atmospheric pollution and greenhouse effect.What 's more,the energy we use is renewable.We will not be short of energy resource .
With this kind of hydrogen energy,a lot of problems that obsess us today will be solved.No wars for energy will break .
In the process of developing a new idea into a product , all kinds of expected or unforeseeable troubles will occur , making the path to be filled with struggles and disappointments .
Although the knowledge and technological breakthroughs we accumulated through ages have provided humans with aolid foundation for putting our ideas into practice , there still exists many inevitable factors due to the advancing capitalism which deter the process of innovation .
Among all these socially determined resistance to the way of innovation , one fatally significant phenomenon is the unfair competition between monopolies and other less competent companies .
It can be perceived as good in the sense of market selection , but on the other hand , such type of rivalship can easily be abused and transformed into one-sided violation if monopolies use these advantages as weapons against their opponents instead of raising the standard of living for mankind .
One vivid example is when Microsoft forced Netscape to go into bankruptcy by packing its inferior web browser IE with its dominant windows system for free .
It is also common for monopolies to lower the price to a large extent to annihilate their opponents .
compared with this , however , the time for design and development seem too long to wait .
This can be extremely significant to industries like the pharmaceutical industry .
Before a new drug reaches its commercialization stage , it must undergo a long period of time for testing to prove its effectiveness and safety .
Meanwhile , people 's intention to buy branded goods helps exacerbate this problem .
In short , companies may have enough funds for innovation , but that does not mean they can survive the loss of market share .
With so many things to consider , managers do have reasons to hesitate before they risk the future of a company for the unguaranteed profit .
In an age of accelerated obsolescence of information and technology , lots of new inventions and design concepts are generated from the human mind every second. .
In the meantime the demands rising from an endless pursuit for higherstandard breakthroughs have boosted and inspired the human brain to increase its potential .
During this new innovation-development revolution in science and technology , engineers no doubt play a vital role in beautifying and simplifying the whole world
In addition , numerous breakthroughs are derived from the audacious imagination .
However , with the discovery of oil , Dubai has undergone a sequence of earth-shaking changes overnight .
While happy days do not last long , the exhaustion of oil is already around the corner .
In order to find a way out , Dubai has made a crucial decision to shifts its economic center from oil to tourism .
Subsequently , a series of unbelievable plans have emerged .
For example , The Burj Al-Arab hotel , is one of the most luxurious hotels in the world since its completion in December 1999 , , it has become one of the most dazzling architectural buildings of our time
During the entire design and construction , not only were some of the latest technologies applied into this magnificent project , more impressive is that most of the designs had never been used before and every engineer could freely come up with all kinds of brand new ideas .
One of its innovative technologies was the first use of hollow concrete blocks , which can decrease the effect of the sea wave .
The first stage of the whole project was to construct an artificial island which is about 300m away from the shoreline , while the most challenging problem was the bad weather , engineers need to take all potential risks into account before figuring out a perfect plan .
Therefore , after a series of trial and error , the hollow concrete block stood out .
The hollow concrete blocks are like sponge which can absorb the energy of the sea waves , the principle is that when the seawater flowed into the block , the water would rotate automatically and finally most of its kinetic energy dissolved .
For the quality of life , , people require higher and higher criterions .
The reason why this situation is can be seen from the need of the market , the process of research & development , and the product features .
As the first step of innovation-development , the need of the market is significantly considered in two ways .
Usually , the need of the market is defined as technologically determined and socially determined .
However , as its name infers , skunkworks is being developed in a shabby environment due to the scarcity of capital .
On the other hand , convention gets enough things to support , which makes it much easier and more stable to finish the innovation .
However ; because of its large scale and many other factors involved , it will take more time and more cost to finish the whole innovation .
At last , the products of the two , convention and skunkworks , will appeal to different kinds of consumers .
The products of skunkworks are more practical , and people are in need of those products .
For example , the invention of the laptop helped Japanese employees have more space to work .
These make it operate smoothly .
However , by taking every point into consideration , both of them can work well in innovation-development , depending on different situations .
Engineers are trained to solve problems and design products to fulfill human needs .
Overcoming a problem requires time and repeated trialsl to make sure that the product is safe to use and works efficiently .
One of the current human needs is to find an environmentally friendly vehicle as a substitute for the gasoline vehicle .
Thus , an environmentallyl friendly vehicle needs to be created and should be given priority for this creation to save our earth from pollution and to lessen the impact of the air pollution .
Electrically generated vehicles can be designed to overcome the air pollution problem .
electrically generated vehicle will not exhaust gases when it is being driven .
It is because mining and refining processes of petroleum which emit fumes that will pollute the air .
To build an electrically generated vehicle that can have longer lasting battery power and powerful pickup , it should have a special battery , light weight material and well designed shape .
The battery of the vehicle must be able to recharge within a few hours .
It should also be able to store higher amounts of energy in order to last for longer periods of time .
Furthermore , having an aerodynamically styled shape , the vehicle can move faster and have a powerful pickup .
The electrically generated vehicle should be fully tested and examined .
Test drive and open the electrically generated vehicle to the public and ask for feedback from them and make improvements for it .
After that the electrically generated vehicle can be introduced to the market throughout the world .
In conclusion , the creation of an electrically generated vehicle can reduce air pollution problems that is becoming more and more serious nowadays .
Engineers can make the world different by their expertise and knowledge .
E-commerce : the Socially Determined Technology
Picture a scenario : a man sitting in front of a computer is busy using email , eBay , online banking , and teleconferencing .
This is e-commerce , which consists of the buying and selling of products or services over electronic systems such as the Internet and other computer networks .
Thanks to this burgeoning technology , people can almost fulfill all their needs without moving a step .
With the goal to achieve a more convenient human life , ecommerce is considered to be socially determined rather than technologically determined .
Basically , the origin of e-commerce is due to public 's desire to facilitate their life and work .
( Kenneth , 2008 ) These were the very first types of ecommerce .
Later on , with the rapid spread of internet , the utility of this technology quickly varied and extended to global scope .
This concern soon resulted in the appearance of online stores .
( Julie , 2008 ) Till now , people can nearly do whatever they want simply by clicking the web browser .
During the speedy development of e-commerce , corporations realized the potential to gain huge interest and participation to shape the direction of e-commerce 's growth .
Comparing with the traditional selling styles , e-commerce manages to broaden the market as well as obtain a cheaper but more efficient forms of publicity .
Thanks to the technology of e-commerce , these shops can now advertise to a much larger target group .
At the same time , the online banking system also facilitates the procedure to make deals .
In the 1990s , as a result of the rising development of e-commerce , the usage of this technology gradually went out of control .
Directed by public requirement , enterprises ' intention , and government regulation , ecommerce is now still developing .
with continued efforts in these three aspects , we have confidence this technology will sooner or later develop to a certain stage which satisfies the whole society .
Singaporeans live in the comfort of their own homes believing that all the things that can be invented have already been made .
These are a few traits that are often seen amongst the Singaporeans .
Therefore , only by overcoming the two major problems , will Singaporeans then be able to create and innovate .
The republic 's physical landmass of approximated seven hundred and five square kilometers is ranked one hundred and eighty- seventh internationally .
In addition , even if there were potential solutions , it would be a tough task to carry out experimentation or trials , either as a means to gather data or to implement a solution , simply because a local test group might not exist .
This deficiency in raw materials and useable land as well as to a lesser extent , wealth and labour , limits the magnitude of the engineering solutions to be pursued .
Such an enormous amount would be several years of Singapore 's gross domestic product in the current economic climate .
In conclusion , Singapore 's unique size and state of available resources are obstacles in the engineering design process .
The educational system is based more towards theory and not practicel .
The amount of time spent in labs for practicals is minimal .
Since the birth of cars at the end of the last century , its development has gone through ups and downs over the last one hundred years .
Zaochu Benz at that time only had a speed of 18Km per hour , but now , a sports car can accelerate from zero speed to 100Km per hour within 3 seconds .
The car industry ' development can not be separated from the adoption of cars by the people .
So again , what are the factors influencing the adoption of cars ?
Actually , after Henry Ford 's Model T automobile was invented , cars just gradually became a vehicle that can be adopted by people .
The { Model T } was introduced on October 1 , 1908 .
Because the Model T was so cheap by the 1920s a majority of American drivers learned to drive on the Model T. Apart from this , in order to make the Model T more universal , Henry Ford also created a massive publicity machine in Detroit to ensure every newspaper carried stories and ads about the new product .
He also created a network of local dealers , which provided a good marketing channel for his company .
If we analyse from a broader view , we can see that there were also other economical factors influence the cars ' adoption .
One of the most important factors was the declining cost of oil at that time .
The daily output of this site was more than 1 million barrels of oil , which was even more than the sum of output of other sites in the United States .
This made the price of oil in the United States decrease very fast at that time .
But the Model T was just the beginning of the adoption of cars , another factor which made the technology of producing cars became more mature was the military demand .
During the wars , vehicles and armored transportation became essential for every country .
For example , a very popular hydraulic actuator which is still used today was developed in the early part of World War 2 .
All these inventions not only increased the usefulness of the engine , but also improved the overall situation of the car industry .
Government policies and priorities also play an important role in the development of the car industry .
After the United States won the war , many ordnance factories became civil factories ; this made the expansion of the car industry faster .
Especially during the Cold War , in order to demonstrate America 's superiority and wealth , the government encouraged the car industry .
In conclusion , the adoption of cars and this technological innovation was not only technological determined , but also shaped by economic factors , military demands , and government policies and priorities .
An engineering design process , which includes mainly five stages-defining the problem , gathering pertinent information , generating multiple solutions , analyzing and selecting a solution and testing and implementing the solution , plays a very important role in improving the quality of people 's lives .
Take China for instance , the culture for innovation in engineering design is severely lacking .
Even if they have the motivation , their ideas are unlikely to come true due to the lack of funding from the government .
When a student finds out an alternative method of solving a problem , there is usually no reward for him and he still has to answer the question in the standard way to avoid losing marks at examinations .
Another problem that poses obstacles to innovation in engineering in China may be the lack of funds from the government for research and development ( R&D ) , thus engineers are hardly attracted to the R&D industry and the lack of funds to implement their new ideas .
Mr. Yuan Long Ping , who is known as the " Father of Hybrid Rice " , had contributed to tremendous increase in the level of world 's rice output through cultivating species of hybrid rice during the 1970 's .
However , the Chinese government only awarded him the State Preeminent Science and Technology Award of China in 2000 which was valued at merely 5 million yuan .
This was very little if it was meant to reward him for his more than twenty years ' of hard work .
This lack of government support means , engineers will not be able to get resources , raw materials , precise equipment for research during engineering design process .
Thus the stage of testing and implementing solutions during the engineering design process is greatly hampered
In conclusion , the rigid education system and the governments limited incentives for innovations limit the number of innovative engineers and hinder the realization of innovative ideas if any .
These are hence two prominent obstacles that hamper the engineering design processes for innovations in China .
Skunk works projects do not have access to the full resources of the company , have their own rules and have to maintain confidentiality about their projects .
The research funds and human resources are not made available to them .
Hence the rules of the company need not be enforced in their secret working environment .
There have been extreme examples of rules set by project managers where both emerged successful in their innovations .
Personnel will have to maintain a double life for this project .
Personnel often have to stay back late after office hours to work on their secret projects and no claim of overtime is allowed .
There will also be media coverage and time to time updates on their projects .
However they face equal stress on their projects .
Singapore 's education system has been structured in such a way that it is rigid and text based and does not teach students to apply what is being taught .
Another portion of the design process involves commercialization .
Sadly , society as a whole is generally not that receptive tof new ideas and innovative products .
In sum , a society which is less receptive to new ideas and innovative products could lead to the hampering of engineering processes for innovation .
Two problems have been identified which might hamper creativeness in engineers .
However , several decades earlier , few people dared to declare that they were sure these innovations would surely be popular around the world someday
Despite the poor environment , tough stress , and high risk , skunkworks indeed value more than conventional technology .
To some extent , conventionally generated technology usually improves our life , but innovation in skunkworks often changes our lives .
Skunkworks - defined to pioneer the development of a technological innovation , normally has tougher working conditions .
Usually skunkworks can not get enough support to create a satisfying working environment .
Due to uncertainty , R&D groups in skunkworks often can not find enough people to conduct the innovation .
Just like the design team at Macintosh , they worked day and night under the aggressive leadership of Steven Jobs .
The starting point of innovation in skunkworks and conventional technology are different .
However , Conventional technologies is made for solving the existing problems or needs .
When NOKIA upgraded its N series hand phone annually , iPhone of the Apple company surprised the world , because it give a different definition to the touch phone .
Skunkworks takes a high risk in the innovation process , but it is rewarding .
Just like " Post-its " of 3M , was initially considered as a failure , but was finally proved to be a great success in other fields .
on the contrary , it is more stable and reliable for conventional technology .
Furthermore , it is often at a high risk to invest in skunkworks .
The Compressed Natural Gas ( CNG ) vehicle is an alternative fuel vehicle .
By 2008 , there are roughly 7 million CNG vehicles on the roads worldwide .
Unlike the normal gasoline vehicle which emits greenhouse and harmful gases , the power of the CNG vehicle can emit 70 % lesser CO2 and little harmful gas .
Therefore CNG vehicles are more environmentally friendly than gasoline vehicles .
In the context of global warming becoming a more serious problem , the development of such environmentally friendly vehicles becomes a must .
Apart from reducing the air pollution , The natural gas vehicle also produces lower noise levels than gasoline vehicles .
This is another positive feature of CNG vehicles .
Moreover , the intention of reducing the fuel cost also shaped the development of the CNG vehicle .
The oil embargo resulted in an energy crisis in the U.S. during the 1980 's .
Such situations motivated the discovery of alternative fuels that could reduce our dependence on foreign imports .
From 2000 , the oil price grew tremendously , but the price of natural gas was much less .
More owners of private cars wanted to convert their petrol-driven vehicles to also run on CNG .
Lastly , the development of CNG vehicle is also influenced by government policies .
Due to the increase of the oil price and the necessity of improvement of the urban environment , many countries ' governments support the development of CNG vehicles .
Many countries which have an abundance of natural gas introduce CNG cars and buses to their public transportations .
Some other governments provide tax rebate for the owners of CNG vehicles , so as to encourage the using of eco-friendly vehicles .
For instance , the Singapore government provided 40 % discount on the Open Market Value ( OMV ) cost of newly-registered green passenger vehicles from 2001 in order to build up the intensity of CNG vehicles ( wikipedia,2009 ) .
With the help of the favorable policies and sponsorship from the government , more talented people are attracted to researching the CNG vehicle .
As a result CNG vehicle technology is shaped by government policies .
Without the requirements of cheaper and cleaner vehicle and governmental support , it might not be as well-developed as now .
In recent years , with its growing prosperity and affluence , China is investing more on science and technology development .
In the so-called cramming method of teaching , teachers pay particular attention to memorization , even at the cost of comprehension .
During the examination , the students are evaluated by how much they memorize , and not on how they think .
In conclusion , the lack of research funding and an exam-oriented education system are the two most significant factors which have hampered engineering design process in China .
For example , in the 1970 's , a new tomato variety was launched by a research team in California .
This tomato variety could be harvested by machines , which was a big success .
After about ten years ' of research , he discovered Warfarin one day in an unrelated experiment , which turned out to be the most impressive progress in the whole research .
Not only should the scientists figure out how to breed the variety , but they also needed to do other non-research works in order to successfully put the variety into practice .
Finally , they came up with their research results after many years of research , in due time according to their plan .
Besides , although both these two technologies were successful , the keys to their success were different .
In conclusion , the mechanized tomato program and the discovery of Warfarin had a different start , process and reasons for success
Technology is progressing every day , and different products are created using new technologies .
Life has become more convenient with these technological products and companies can benefit from producing these products .
However , not all technological products can bring profit to their companies .
Before manufacturing a product , companies have to evaluate its profitability and reject products with an uncertain future .
Engineers who are enthusiastic about these " no future " products form a group , and these groups are called " Skunk works " .
Conventionally generated technologies and technologies in " Skunk works " are while they still have features in common .
Technology in " Skunk works " is like a double-side sword , which not only can become a great success but also can be a super failure in the future .
Working in a " Skunk works " environment is much tougher than in a conventional environment , as engineers working in " Skunk works " are not rewarded unless their work turns out to be a success .
Nevertheless , both " Skunk works " technology and conventional technology make a contribution to technology development .
Compared to conventionally generated technology , " Skunk works " has great potential to become a big failure , while it also has the potential to be successful .
and to optimize a design under given conditions .
Whereas , a well optimized design is worthless if it can not meet the desires , or at least the needs of the customers .
Whereas on the other hand , can also be a success in market .
As E.M. Rogers mentioned in his article - " the Birth of the Laptop Computer at Toshiba " , the laptop is a good example of successful " Skunk works " .
The environment of " Skunk works " and the conventional one are very different .
Though engineers in " Skunk works " are enthusiastic about their project , it is very hard for them to find financial support , and other experts may criticize their work .
" Skunk works " and conventional projects are different , but both of them are making a contribution to the development of technology .
Conventionally generated technologies are closely connected to our life .
By doing sufficient market research , technologies provide things that can fulfill our desires and make our life become more and more convenient .
Therefore , " Skunk works " can promote technological innovation and also provide a platform for creative engineers .
In summary , A " Skunk works " environment is much tougher than a conventional environment , and " Skunk works " is more like a gamble for a company for it may either be a big success or be an absolute failure .
Conventionally generated technology plays an important role in fulfilling people 's need and generating profit for companies , .
Therefore , both of them are indispensable for technological development .
Two problems of innovation in China
However , nowadays new technology is playing a more and more important role in society and replacing the importance of resources .
One of them is that intellectual property rights in China are not protected well and there are many illegal copiesa in China .
The other problem is that normal employees in many companies are not valued much by their employers .
The phenomena of illegal copies block the innovation of technology in China .
One of the reasons is that the popularity rate of computers has increased much faster than the rate of consumption levels in China , which means that the price of software is relatively higher than normal people can accept .
Subsequently , the inventor of the software can only get a little profit , which will not impel him or her to continue paying much attention to innovation .
When we compare the software area and the space flight area , we can easily find that space flight in China develops extremely fast because of innovation while software develops slowly with little innovation .
Therefore , the illegal copy phenomena restricts the development of technology in China .
There is no doubt that China has developed fast since the foundation of the country .
However , when the focus on the enterprises in China is changed , it can be found that most of the huge enterprises are public and rely on resources and monopoly .
Huge enterprises which rely on high technology are very few .
One of the reasons is that normal employees are not to take part in the innovation .
In many companies , only certain research staff take part in the innovation of technology while normal employees just do their routine work .
Compared to professional research staff , normal employees have more experience about certain .
As the employers do not show much respect to normal employees , few employees will try their best to provide their experience to research staff .
It is well known that IBM employers value every employee in the company .
Many employees have a chance to make a suggestion to the company .
With the large , research staff can achieve new production relatively more easily .
Therefore , that normal employees are not inspired restricts the innovation of technology in China .
Therefore , China should pay more attention to intellectual property rights to encourage people to innovate .
Uniting everyone can maximize the ability of the whole unity .
China needs to solve these two problems to clear the way for innovation .
Another major problem that engineers might face in Singapore is that people are less receptive to innovations and ideas as compared to Western countries .
For example , the education system has now definitely improved in terms of its rigidity .
Since 2005 , the Ministry of Education ( MOE ) has introduced Project Work ( PW ) to junior colleges in order to improve communicative skills of students , as well as to encourage building of teamwork among students .
Hopefully in the near future , more effort will be put in to encourage society to be more accepting of new innovations that would greatly change their way of life for the better , and also to encourage in not just aspiring engineers but in students in general , skills that they are able to use and apply in handling problems in the real world .
Since the 1960s , there has been a paradigm shift from low end industrialization to high end industrialization thus resulting in a rapid depletion of the already scarce resources .
Engineering design processes are therefore created to meet the above mentioned human needs .
One such engineering design processes is gathering pertinent information .
According to Khandani , " Efforts spent searching for information about your problem...reveal facts about the problem...discover mistakes and false starts . " Researching land scarcity problems can help one to prioritize by deciding on the more important infrastructure to build to strike a balance between social and economic needs .
For example , high rise flats are built to help prevent overcrowding and to sustain the population while mega infrastructures like the Integrated Resort are for economic purposes .
According to Khandani , " Creative abilities can be developed if one is willing to take risks and is not afraid to tackle problems . " The lack of land is a challenging problem to the leaders of Singapore thus engineers have to come up with innovative solutions to tackle land scarcity .
Some of these solutions are land reclamation , condensed structural landscapes and the construction of sky scrapers .
Construction of sky scrapers is relatively safe despite their height due to deep analytical insights in the construction of these buildings .
One is via research and the other is the result of some serendipitous discovery .
But history shows that that sometimes the fate of the two kinds of technologies are also not the same .
The " designs " are thought highly of by people at the beginning , though the importance of the " accidents " is realized much later .
Actually the majority of engineering inventions coincide with the " design " way .
Though it may just be a matter of few seconds for the final success of a new technology development , the process from its infancy to maturity can be very long and tough .
With the coming out of a technology people will , of course , , because it already cost a lot .
Take the atomic weapon test as an example , decades years ago the military of the USA tried to make use of atomic power . They employed a lot of human and non-human sources to complete numerous experiments and tests , and plenty of money was spent on inviting talented scientists and engineers to come to help them make the most powerful weapon in human history
According to Wikipedia " The Manhattan Project cost 2 billion dollars , this included the cost of the two bombs used as well as the test bomb .
Therefore , the US treated this new technology as their most precious weapon .
In many cases , technology which was created via research will be thought highly of at the beginning .
Because of the formal research process , like the atomic bomb , many other technologies which were developed via research will draw people 's attention .
As we can see during the process , people know its property , figure out its purpose , understand its advantages and disadvantages , and at last master the way to make full use of it . .
is that some human and non-human sources have already been expended , and governments do n't want to see these sources turn into nothing .
So technology which is designed purposefully will draw more attention .
Sometimes people will get unexpected outcomes from their experiment or research .
Even some of the greatest discoveries come from accidents without any indication , for example , the discovery of penicillin and the invention of gunpowder .
Gunpowder was invented by an ancient Chinese alchemist accidently .
One day the alchemist wanted to find some medicine called the elixir of immortality aimed at giving people immortality. .
What he encountered was not the magic drug , but an explosion and the birth of gunpowder .
However , the alchemist did n't set enough value on this great power , nor did other Chinese people .
Gunpowder did n't have a chance to step onto the stage of history until the famous adventurer and merchant Marco Polo introduced it to Europe from China .
Only after that did the world gradually began to pay enough attention to this powerful chemical medicine .
Compared to the development of the atomic bomb , the discovery of gunpowder was just an accident or something unexpected that no one planned to make .
This is very crucial in explaining why nobody attaches importance to new technology at first .
That 's to say , though technologies like that may somehow change the world , it is not in time is needed for people to realize the existence of them and to learn more about them .
The world always improves along with the progress of technology step by step .
No matter whether their existence is a design or an accident , as long as it benefits people , that 's what society wants to see .
In 2005 , news revealed that the Al Burquan Oil Field in Kuwait , which is the second largest oil field in the world will be depleted before the middle of this century ( AME Info , Inc. 2005 ) .
Meanwhile , the increasing oil price also indicates that society is facing a tough challenge , the energy crisis .
According to the Oxford English Dictionary ( 2006 ) , engineering is defined as the " science , discipline , art and profession of acquiring and applying technical , scientific and mathematical knowledge to design and implement materials , structures , machines , devices , systems , and { processes } that safely realize a desired objective or inventions .
" Overwhelmed by the demand for energy , increasing energy efficiency should be viewed as the priority or desired objective of inventions or engineering design .
Primarily , energy is the fundamental base for all human activities which exploit nature to meet our needs .
For example , if there was not sufficient fuel for automobiles , then we would go back to the era of antiquity when walking and riding were the only means for transportation .
On the other hand , it is very irresponsible to squander energy otherwise our would face the consequences of our behaviours .
Hence , maximising energy efficiency should be taken given priority in technology development so that human beings and the whole of society will develop and move forward sustainably .
Moreover , to give energy efficiency priority will enrich the engineering design process resulting from .
It is defined that there are five stages to solving an engineering design problem , " to define the problem , to gather pertinent information , to generate multiple solutions , to analyze and select a solution and to test and implement the solution " ( Khandani , 2005 ) .
If all the engineers are trying to design the technology with higher energy efficiency then they probably will gather more information , generate more efficient solutions and select the solution which is more efficient .
At the time when engineers take energy usage into consideration , the design process is upgraded to a higher standard which meets our needs and fulfills the vital objective of engineering design for technology .
If all the solutions are capable of solving the problem , then the one which is the most efficient should be chosen .
The real example is that people now are pro hybrid gas-and-electric-powered automobiles instead of the conventional ones .
In one word , energy efficiency should be a priority concern for all engineers due to its positive impact on the design process .
Equipped with high efficiency , all the innovations of engineering technology will be more dynamic and practical to meet the country 's ever-increasing needs .
Toshiba 's laptop and Microsoft 's operating systems are two technologies that were created under different conditions and environments .
Toshiba 's laptop is often known as a skunk work innovation whereas Microsoft 's is known as a conventionally created product .
According to Rogers , due to the fact that Toshiba 's laptop creator Tetsuya Mizoguchi failed to convince his superiors in Toshiba to support his laptop project , he was not able to receive any research and development funding .
It would be useless if there was no hardware for Gates ' program to work on .
According to the article ( 2 ) , Gates actually wrote to computer hobbyists demanding that they pay for the usage of his program so as to allow him to continue to write quality programs .
In May 1998 , Microsoft was accused of abusing its monopoly power to keep rivals out of the market .
On the other hand , Mizuguchi 's idea was to create a laptop that was compatible with IBM 's platform despite the fact that they were competing for the same market share .
He recognised that IBM was dominant at the time and that it would be fair to consumers to allow them to use an IBM compatible peripheral Toshiba laptop .
If Mizoguchi had done otherwise , people would probably only buy Toshiba 's laptop for its convenience .
Similarly for Microsoft , Gates rode on the success of IBM 's personal computer by becoming the full owner of a program that was written especially for IBM 's personal computer .
This allowed them to have a monopoly in the industry .
In conclusion , despite the fact that both skunk work and conventionally created technologies differ in the environment where they are being produced , they will still be successful if their creators have the determination and are full of ideas .
The birth of new technologies and inventions come about in different forms and through different processes .
Although the innovations may be comparably similar , the conditions where they were created may be totally different .
An example would be the case of conventionally invented electric cars by General Motors and the first laptop that was invented in a skunk works environment by an engineer from Toshiba .
Differences like , risks involved , working environments , marketing strategies and similarities like the visions and goals of both innovations .
The first difference between the two types of innovation is risks involvement and work stress .
For skunk works created technology , the person who suggested the innovation has to take very big risks because it is their own project , they are not supported by companies , only their own team .
As mentioned in Rogers ' article on the 'Birth of laptops ' , Tetstiya Mizoguchi , a Japanese technologist , disobeyed orders and risked his career for the sake of innovation-development which in the end was successful .
Secondly , the processes in which the new technology are designed and carried out are totally different between the two types of innovations .
Therefore , people who are working in a skunk works environment have to gather their own team and a substantial amount of money before they can actually start on their project .
As such , because of limited funds the team or individual have in skunk works , they have more stress because they can not afford to fail .
Because of disapproval from companies , the working space for skunk works innovation is usually smaller and limited as compared to those who work under companies to create new technology .
As mentioned in Rogers ' article , Tetstiya Mizoguchi and his team went 'underground ' and worked at a factory which was far away from Toshiba 's headquarters .
In the case study of the creation of electric motor cars by General Motors written by Rogers , General Motors went to the extent of putting advertisements in newspapers and came out with marketing campaigns to publicise their new product .
On the contrary , products or technology created from a skunk works environment do not have the capabilities to roll out massive campaigns to advertise due to the lack of funds .
They have to depend on their own network to publicise their product and introduce their prototypes to the public .
Comparing the two articles written by Rogers , the target group for skunk works prototypes testing usually started small , and then eventually became bigger as more people accepted the product ; whereas in the case of conventionally created products , the target group is very large in the beginning due to large scale marketing campaigns .
The similarity between the innovations created under different environments is that both wanted to come out with solutions to solve problems that were present .
In the case of Toshiba 's first laptop invention , Tetstiya Mizoguchi wanted to solve the problem which most Japanese companies faced , crowded offices which prevented the usage of more desktops due to the lack of space ; while , electric motor cars were created to lessen pollution .
In conclusion , there are various differences and similarities between conventional or skunk works innovations , but at the end of the day , both have produced products that have helped to solve problems and bring benefits to the people of the world .
In 1943 , Abraham Maslow published a theory on the hierarchy of needs of people .
In his study , he defined five stages of needs ; they are , in descending order of importance , physiological , safety , love and belonging , esteem and finally self-actualization . In view of the world today , engineers should tackle the most important human need .
This is of course one of our basic physiological needs , water , which is imperative in sustaining life . .
The five stage engineering design process , as proposed by Khandani , will guide engineers in making solutions to solve this problem .
Potable water , the source of life , has become in third world countries .
Drinking water that has not been treated can lead to life threatening diseases .
According to the World Health Organization report in the year 2000 , Africa , home to a population of 784 million people , faces dire shortages of clean and disease free drinking water .
Furthermore , it is the continent with the least supply of potable water .
It is important that engineers realize the true root of the problem , so as not to waste resources on a solution that does not work .
For instance , one may think of solving the water shortage by building desalination plants throughout the coast of Africa , only to realize that he or she did not address the problem at all .
Because the water shortage may not lie in the quantity of water , but rather in the ease of access to potable water in Africa .
The second step is to research the shortage of potable water .
Engineers have to understand why current technology has failed to solve the water shortage , and the oversights of engineers of the previous technology .
For example , a company has produced " LifeStraw " , a portable device that processes safe drinkable water by removing microscopic bacteria through its filters .
Something like this may seem like a godsend to the people of Africa , but its downfall is its cost and the problem of transportation of filtered water .
Therefore , a thorough understanding of the limitations of technology can guide engineers to invent a product that fulfills all the criteria .
Subsequently , in the fourth step , they would have to rate and outweigh all of their ideas and determine the best one to implement .
This ensures the product meets expectations .
In a nutshell , the five stages of engineering design introduced by Khandani can help engineers plan and develop solutions to solving the water shortage in Africa , thereby saving countless lives in dire need of safe drinking water .
Back in 1943 , while working on the secret project P-80 Shooting Star jet fighter , one of the team engineers in Lockheed Martin Corporation , Irv Curler answered a call by saying " Skonk Works , inside man Culver speaking . "
The name was soon adopted for usage in engineering , business and technical field to describe a small group of people working on secret projects .
( How Skunkworks Got Its Name , par.2 ) Skunkworks have been a huge contributor for invention for many decades .
Therefore , skunkworks drive innovation to conventionally generated technology .
Therefore they are often used to roll out product research before it is developed according to usual business processes .
With minimal management constraints , inventors are given freedom to research the area they want .
Facebook was started off as a small networking site for college students , which slowly extended to be the most popular global networking site
With the help of a few roommates , Mark created Facebook with limited resources .
With no management pressure , Mark could add on any application on Facebook , which soon turned out to be the main ingredient in fueling its success .
As mentioned , skunkworks always lack resources , .
As a start-up , Facebook did n't have the funding which its competitor , Myspace had .
As the history suggests , Myspace had everything when they first launched , including funding .
Thus , they got instant popularity in the beginning .
However , Facebook trounced Myspace recently , setting its user numbers to a record high .
It can clearly be seen that , skunkworks are no loser to conventional technology despite funding problems .
While conventionally generated technology are opened to the public , skunkworks undertake secret projects .
Before Facebook was created , Mark hacked into the Harvard School system to get the information of all the students .
Instead , he scarified his sleeping time to program another program to replace Facemash , which is the Facebook we all are using today .
Myspace took a different approach to show the public what they were doing .
The underlying reason could be the confidence Myspace had over their program because of the size of their resources which Facebook did n't have .
Despite the fact that the approaches they take are obviously different , they share the same goal , which is to innovate future products .
Either Facebook or Myspace can be used share information without borders .
They are competing with each other by introducing new features .
One of the few positive impacts that arose from the Iraq War is that governments as well as individuals became aware of how people 's dependence on oil , gas and other petrol products can trap people into a serious situation once the supply of petrol is limited .
Moreover , people are now aware of the importance of finding new , sustainable and eco-friendly energy sources . .
Indeed , the utmost purpose for the existence of engineers is to improve living standards and to satisfy the higher requirements of human beings by creating or improving the products used in daily life .
In daily life , the energy supply is so important because almost all human activities , like cooking , working , heating and even water supply can not work normally without electricity , and the emerging energy shortage is impossible to solve without the development of new energy sources
Thus , the government should give priority to research in economics and environmental-friendly and sustainable energy .
The basic steps for engineers to find new energy is shown below .
For engineers to discover f energy , firstly , it is essential to have a clear definition and criteria of the problem and to gather enough relevant information .
A clear definition instructs engineers as to the direction in which their research is going ( Khandani , p6 , 2005 ) .
And knowing more information makes our design process more effective ( Khandani , p10 , 2005 ) .
In this case , New energy sources can be defined as energy sources excluding fossil fuels that have a reasonable price , are sustainable and belong to green energy .
The criteria are : the new energy should be safe ; the energy should be sustainable ; the energy should not create pollution ; and the price of the energy should be acceptable .
Then , engineers have to list all the solutions and select the ones that satisfy the criteria .
When judging a new energy , engineers have to think about questions , such as , " Is the energy able to replace petrol ?
" and " Does it have any potential problems ? "
The energy crisis appears to be increasingly serious as human consumption keeps increasing while the increase in energy supply is slow .
Since engineers are important in discovering new energy sources and the aim of their work is to meet people 's needs , they should give priority to the development of new energy .
On one hand , much effort and funding has been put into our education system to prepare our people for the Knowledge-based Economy .
On the other hand , Singapore has always encouraged companies , regardless of their size , to do more in Research and Development ( R&D ) .
The reason for doing is that the government has realised the importance of R&D in Singapore 's progress as a nation .
Although much effort and funding has been spent on R&D , some problems still exist to significantly hinder engineering design processes for innovations .
The first problem that hinders engineering design processes for innovations is the influence of monetary profit .
Around 1930 , there were two prototype refrigerators .
The other one was the gas refrigeratorr .
Gas refrigerators did not produce the humming sound and had overwhelming advantages over electric refrigerators .
But the electric refrigerator was selected over the gas refrigerator because General Electric believed that larger profit could be made from the electric refrigerator .
Because such influence affects the commercial , diffusion and adoption stages of the engineering design process .
Thus , many great innovations have been destroyed prematurely because of their lack of promotion to the public .
The second problem that hinders engineering design processes for innovations is that Singaporeans , are not as creative as our counterparts , for example the Americans , Japanese and Taiwanese .
It is because , in the past , our education system was more exam-oriented and theoretical. .
Thus , knowledge was only applied in examinations , without applying it in real-life situations .
However , in recent years , the government has been actively promoting creative thinking .
Although the plans that promote creative thinking were started years ago , it is still in its initial stage .
In addition , in this imperfect world , engineers are always solving problems that arise to make a better world .
Over the last couples of years , with the development of China , all industries , especially the manufacturing industry , are developing on a large scale .
However , it is strange that not so many big companies like Lenovo and Haier exist with such a large-scale industry and such a large home market .
Instead , millions of small companies are operating their small business everywhere , and large transnational corporations are enjoying their profit in the Chinese market .
Many companies , especially the small ones , are following each other 's steps to design and manufacture their products , expecting that some profits in the market are still left for them .
Then , another question arises , what hampers innovations in engineering design ?
I think there are two primary reasons , high costs in engineering design with relatively low rewards and an unsatisfying engineering education system .
As I mentioned , many manufacturing companies in China are running their business on a small-scale .
What they manage to do is to make their designs slightly different from other similar ones , which makes their products quite elastic in the market .
In most cases , the circle continues until they shut down .
In the emerging Chinese market , not all investments in innovation are rewarding .
Instead , just following others has proved to be more profitable sometimes .
Secondly , engineering education is not focusing so much on innovation but memorizing .
Other steps are unfortunately neglected. .
Behind prosperity of the products " made in China " during the last few years , is the lack of innovation in products of Chinese local manufacturing companies .
The mains reasons why they lack innovation are , high costs , the low rewards of innovation in China and an unsatisfying engineering education system .
The common challenges faced by developed and developing countries are the daily demands for improvement in various areas , be it economy , infrastructure or even society .
Engineers plying their trades in Singapore , however , will face two major problems which are potentially critical in the future development of the city-state .
Singapore , besides being famous for its airport and most recently named as the best place for business by the World Bank , is also famous because of its size .
Hence , local engineers encounter their first major test in their quest : limited land space .
Despite ongoing plans to build a third plant , Singapore is still rather reliant on Malaysia for the sale of water .
Reclamation of land from the ocean was also limited due to sensitivity of border issues , thus hindering any designs that require huge spaces .
Past engineering miracles in housing now require an upgrade in innovation and design due to the cultural shift in our society , as the younger generation now demands quality unlike the past , when the more crucial task was providing a roof for every citizen .
There is another common global issue , much worse in Japan , and that is the ageing population crisis .
Entry into the 21st century provides the world with a whole new set of problems : pandemic flu , terrorism and the emergence of a group of senior citizens .
( The Straits Times , June 28 , 2008 ) Adding to this problem , Singapore , being a small country , has always faced a talent crisis .
Low birth rates coupled with the outflow of local talent forces the government to resort to adopting a foreign talent scheme in order to increase the talent pool in the city .
However , what Singapore 's short history has shown is that it has faced countless daunting tasks and has proven to be up to the mark . Therefore , there is no doubt our engineers will strive and succeed in their tasks ahead .
The problems that affect engineering design
Nowadays we are living in a fast developing world which provides not only abundant goods but also convenient and functional production .
Now focus on the things in China , there are two main factors : the overflow of copying and lack of money .
When a famous company releases a new product , some small companies or workshops will soon copy the design of the product and sell " their products " at a much lower price .
Moreover , the customers may view both products as the same and the " fake " ones are more attractive with an incredible price .
A company will spend a lot of money and a lot of time designing and producing a new product. .
The engineers keep working and working , trial and error , wishing to invent a best seller and to generate a lot of profit .
Workshops which simply copy the design just do the procedure directly with low prime costs .
Usually customers will not discriminate between the products and they consider the price as the main point .
After all their effort , the company will not receive the profit they wish , which will definitely cool down their desire to innovate .
Thus , the overflow of copying really hampers the processes for innovation .
For most companies in China , they are still on the path of development .
They badly need to focus on mature products to accumulate wealth .
It seems too extravagant to pay for the designing of the product. .
Yet innovation is full of risk which may push the company to the edge .
Just like gambling , the company bet all they have on the future .
In this way , the lack of money actually affects the stage of process for innovation .
If everyone is afraid of losing money on innovation , then no new designs will come out and our world will not develop .
The government can do little about the copying incidents .
The poor quality of products hamper the interests of customers and affect the reputation of the famous company .
Hopefully the government will invest money in projects with good prospects .
Since the USSR 's Obninsk Nuclear Power Plant was established on June 27th 1954 , nuclear power has become one of the most important energy resources in the world .
By 2007 , an estimated 14 % of global electricity came from nuclear reactions according to the International Atomic Energy Agency .
Due to the ever increasing consumption of oil and its limited reserves , it is predicted that there will be a further surge for nuclear energy .
Nuclear power was first discovered by scientists in the 19th Century .
As a result , it is perceived as being an alternative of energy resources .
Recently , Iran and North Korea have been facinghave faced sanctions from various countries because of their nuclear development .
This case clearly presents how political factors have structured the advancement of important technology like nuclear power .
In North Korea 's case , they started the development of nuclear technology because of the increased tension with South Korea .
Hence , they regarded nuclear development as a way to sort out disputes over policies .
At the same time , Iran makes use of nuclear power to resist American policies and its influence in the region .
For nations like Iran and North Korea , the development of nuclear power is mainly determined by political forces .
Despite the political impact on nuclear technologies in the less developed world , military forces are likely to exert a similar impact on the development of nuclear power in those more developed countries .
For instance , the US military force considers nuclear power as a viable source to provide energy for military use .
Due to logistic reasons combined with the unstoppable depletion rate , scientists in the United State are diverting most of their funding into research on how to make nuclear power a readily mobile and less dangerous energy source for military use .
In conclusion , recent innovation and development have showed the impact of political , military and other social factors .
Similar to the development of technology , innovation has become more and more important all over the world .
In order to survive and develop in the competitive world , it is crucial for not only many countries , but also individuals to fully develop the process for innovations .
According to Rogers ( 2003 ) , there are six main stages of this process , namely the needs and problems , research , development , commercialization , diffusion and adoption and the stage of consequences .
Take China as an example , there are two main problems hampering the development of innovation .
First of all , the education system has a big effect on the process of recognizing the problems or needs which is the fundamental stage of the innovation-development process .
It is true that the Chinese education system excels in laying the solid foundations of knowledge and skills which are also very important in doing research and studies , but the lack of flexibility and creativeness of the Chinese education system is still a big problem .
As a result , many students get used to accepting information without thinking and investigating by themselves .
Consequently , it becomes quite difficult for them to discover potential problems even when they try to .
However , Innovation requires students to develop the ability of discovering problems instead of being easily satisfied with the current situation or just following the rules .
In fact , most famous inventions or significant scientific discoveries are based on the ability of questioning .
If Watt did not realize the shortcomings of the traditional streamer , the age of stream maybe would not have been invented so fast .
If Galileo did not challenge and had simply accepted the statements presented by Aristotle thousands of years ago , people may not have realized the nature of free fall motion for a long time .
Without the awareness of recognizing or discovering problems , the innovation process can not proceed smoothly .
In addition to the education problems , economic development is also one of the important limitations for China .
General speaking , the success of innovation needs a lot of prerequisites .
Not only human resources , but also financial resources have an impact on the development of innovation .
The implementation of many big projects or innovations requires large amounts of economic support .
Indeed , the economy of China is accelerating at high speed .
However , it is really hard to meet all the needs of the rapid innovation-development .
Compared with some developed countries , China still can not provide large amounts of financial aid to encourage and support scientists and engineers in doing the process of research and in putting these innovations into practice .
In a nutshell , for the importance of developing the processes of innovation , it is necessary to solve these existing problems .
Only if China tries to minimize these potential limitations , will the innovation-development processes succeed and flourish .
It was a serendipitous discovery made by Alexander Fleming from a petri-dish with bacteria left behind from his experiments when he went on a holiday .
In-vitro fertilization is the process of fertilizing eggs with sperm outside the womb of the mother . The technique was invented through research .
Many may think that serendipitous discoveries are just by luck , but through the comparison of penicillin and in-vitro fertilization , it can be seen that serendipitous discoveries are just as complex and impactful as technologies created through research .
Rogers ( 2003 ) suggested that research with the objective of providing solutions for one problem might result in solutions that are useful for another problem .
Indeed , for the case of penicillin , Fleming did not anticipate the discovery of penicillin , a type of antibiotic , when he was doing research on the characteristics of bacteria .
On the other hand , in-vitro fertilization was researched and invented with the primarily objective of conceiving babies outside the wombs of mothers .
After the discovery of an anti-bacterial substance , Fleming did his research to improve on the results just like what the researchers for in-vitro fertilization did .
Both the technologies had to go through laboratory testing and many other processes before the final formula is derived .
Hence , both the technologies were developed in a laboratory environment with sufficient equipment for their testing and both required extra steps even after discovering the correct method of making the technology .
In addition , both the technologies were developed not just by the person who founded the technology .
( " Alexander Fleming " , Wikipedia ) In addition , in-vitro fertilization would not be successful if it were not for other researchers such as John Rock , Patrick Steptoe and Robert Edwards besides Carl Wood .
Furthermore , both penicillin and in-vitro fertilization have a similar impact on mankind .
They have both brought benefits to people in the medical field .
Thus , in terms of the effects they brought for people , they are similar in enhancing the life of mankind .
In conclusion , even though penicillin 's discovery was accidental , from the comparison of the two technologies it can be seen that the invention is actually comparable to those developed by research .
The development of both technologies are similar in terms of the complexity of the processes and the impact of the technologies are equivalent .
Many countries are faced with the problem of an aging population .
As the elder population grows larger and larger , the burden on the younger generation and the government becomes greater and greater .
I think the government can implement positive policies to limit the money spent on the elderly indirectly .
Encouraging the later retirement and giving out subsidies based on the financial need are efficient ways to reduce the amount of money spent on the growing population of the aged .
The government has to limit the money given to the elderly because the expanded population of the elderly can lead to serious problems in economy , society and productivity .
( { http : //bbs.chinadaily.com.cn/redirect.php ? gid = 2&fid = 6&tid = 58116 } [ HYPERLINK : http : //bbs.chinadaily.com.cn/redirect.php ? gid = 2&fid = 6&tid = 58116 ] &goto = nextoldset ) Encouraging a later retirement is a effective method to solve this problem .
As the aging population becomes larger , more people retire than usual .
It can be predicted that more people will leave their work and fewer people can enter the work force .
On the other hand , the amount of the tax will go up as productivity increases .
For some people , they had saved enough money when they were young or they can still make their living when they are old or they are supported by their children .
Giving everyone a pension means that some people 's living standard will be affected but giving out money based on the fanatical need means everyone can live in a good condition .
The pension is not important to the people who are able to live a good life in their twilight years .
Although more and more countries are faced with the aging problem , the government can make some policies like encouraging later retirement and giving out money based on financial needs .
Throughout the process of aging , people will face certain problems relating to health , finance , and socialization ; and many of these problems are usually interrelated .
With the help of these technologies , many possibilities have emerged .
All these have helped to make the process of aging easier , as the aged can lead better lives with fewer health problems .
Also through research and development , many lifestyle guides that help promote healthy lifestyle become available .
It is known that by having a healthy lifestyle , one will have fewer health problems and thus will need to spend less on healthcare .
As these new technologies involve the usage of newer , and more advanced equipments , the costs of using such technologies tend to be higher than in the past .
Prolonging the life of the victim can be financially draining on the family , and cause financial and social tension within the family .
Financial aids can be made available to these families and help relieve the financial stress .
With these , the aged can have longer working life , and thus accumulate more wealth to support themselves through their old age .
Also , the government helps relieve financial stress by subsidizing healthcare costs , and providing financial aids to the elderly .
New technologies have been created to help eliminate many age-related health problems .
However , not every elderly in the society can get to enjoy these perks , especially those who are bound by financial problems .
Therefore through current research and development and policies , the aging process has been made easier , but only to a large extent .
Until recently , the problems of an aging population have become a major concern among all the nations throughout the world .
Governments of many countries have come up with policies and solutions to decrease elder dependency and slow down the process of a fast aging population .
Aging statistics taken from the United States of America administration of aging show people above the age of 65 represented 12.4 % of the population in the year 2000 but are expected to grow to be 20 % of the population by 2030 .
The statistics have shown that in time to come , the problems of a fast aging population will be too overwhelming for the society to handle ; therefore , we have to slow down the aging process .
The country 's economy will also suffer as a small number of young working population will have to support a bigger umbrella of elder generation .
A lot of resources will also have to be spent on the elderly people .
In this way , the working population will not be stressed too much by the elderly population .
This will help the elderly to be more in touch with the society and keep their physical health in good shape , which will in turn reduce diseases .
Singapore has also helped working adults to save money when they are working so that when they retire , they will still have money for living expenses .
To meet healthcare needs , Medisave is introduced to allow CPF members to use their CPF savings for hospitalization .
In this way , most problems of the aging population are taken care of .
Singapore has also emphasized and instilled filial piety to the children of the aging population to support their parents through meeting their financial needs and emotional needs .
The children of the future should provide for their parents as much as they can even though their financial status looks bleak so that the aging population will not have to rely too much on government help .
Singapore has encouraged people to buy an HDB flat near their parents by subsidizing a substantial amount of money .
This will definitely reduce the fiscal cost of elder dependency .
No matter how much we encourage young people to care for their parents , it 's still their personal choice ; the society or the government can not force them to do their part .
This is because what the aging population needs are their children 's provisions and their care and concern .
In conclusion , I think that many developments and policies have helped to reduce the aging process and also solve the problem of a fast aging population .
Although this problem can not be solved in a short period of time , theses policies and developments will help to curb the problems of an aging population .
Many pessimistic predictions were made by people about this problem .
However , with the assistance of Information and Communication technology ( ICT ) , the situation could be fundamentally shifted through mainly three ways .
This change effectively eliminates their disadvantages in terms of mobility compared to the young people .
Nowadays , fewer and fewer jobs require certain level of performance .
Those repetitive and tedious jobs are now performed by machine and jobs become more of managing people and resources , especially with Information Technology as the medium .
This change of job nature makes a huge difference to the aged people 's constraints for physical conditions are no longer employers ' top concern .
Besides changing the workspace , ICT also brings good news to the aged by changing employment relationships .
9 out of 10 employers would be reluctant to hire old people because they are afraid that they can not work as efficiently ( which is always not the case ) .
However , with the introduction of ICT , many more new jobs are created , a large percentage of which are self-employed jobs .
So for the elderly , a new choice is offered to them : after their retirement , instead of heading into the job market and competing with people probably half their age for a post , they can start up their own business .
What matters is their , not their age .
The previous two points are mainly about ICT 's impact on the jobs for the elderly .
Thus , being re- educated becomes a priority for them .
Important as it is , very few old people will get back to school and receive education again .
There are two main reasons for that . Firstly they may feel embarrassed studying together with young students who are at their early twenties .
Secondly they may not have sufficient money or time for their re-education .
Opponents may probably argue that ICT is a privilege that only benefits the young people .
Although young people have an advantage for they have been exposed to the technology from early ages , the aged people still stand a high chance to succeed , as long as they can adapt to new features quickly .
After all , the internet is a common property of which every one can enjoy a share .
Current research and development in the field of ICT has largely shaped the society .
Since people have longer life expectancy , the number of elderly people increases .
This leads to the issue of the aging population .
The aging population causes a lot of problems , since a lot of money will be used to support the elderly .
Consider if an elderly person has been sick for a long time and his/her spending has already reached the limit ; are we going to tell him to die because we will not provide him with anymore money ?
Secondly , the elderly have the right to be protected because they have worked for the country before .
Would we like to be treated as a burden ?
It is really selfish if we treat the elderly badly but still want to be treated nicely when we grow old .
It may be argued that the elderly might misuse this service and fully rely on the public funding rather than trying to cope on their own .
There are a lot of people who could only rely on this service to survive .
We should remember their deeds and we should also remember that we will become old one day .
In other words , the government should spend more on creating jobs and educating the population .
It might be true to some extent , but we should also consider that the government will only limit the public spending on the elderly , but will not eliminate it .
The government will still take care of those who can not take care of themselves .
Friedland and Summer ( 2005 ) stated that the meaning of " retirement " and " old age " nowadays is different from what it was in the past , as future groups of older people are likely to be even better off .
Furthermore , the country will also lack trained labor force .
For instance , Indonesia , the world 's 4th most populous country , has 109,900,900 labor force , but the rate of the unemployed was very high ( 9.10 % ) in 2008 ( CIA , 2008 ) , due to low literacy rates .
The current situation is worrying as when this generation ages , the government will need to provide a certain care for them .
Hence , it is again the government 's role to subsidize the education so that everybody at least can get the standard level of education .
Education alone is not enough because even if the society is better-educated there may not be adequate jobs available and the unemployment problem still exists .
The government should create and maintain new jobs .
Besides increasing the number of new jobs , the government can try to invent a new type of job , which can be done by people regardless of their age , including the elderly .
For instance , telecommuting part-time jobs , which do not require the workers to be in the workplace , are good to be implemented nowadays , by means of our advanced technology .
Governments and policy makers will take the main role to formulate the best policies to deal with the long-term economic and social challenge of global aging , so that we are fully prepared to face this issue .
Aging is becoming a hot issue when the percentage of the elderly in the society is continuously increasing .
Certainly , when the number of aged people rises , public spending on this group will have to be raised as well to take care of this group .
However , I think there should be a limit on how much shall be spent for the elderly , because the government needs to use more money on country development .
Actually , the problem of more population getting aged does not lie in the demographic change , but in the fact that the productivity of the nation will decline .
When the government tries to spend more and more on the aged , it will lead to a lack in money for development , then a slower economic growth , which will finally leave the government with less choice to spend for the elderly people .
Secondly , imposing a limit on public spending for the aged can make people spend money more responsibly .
For most people , if they know they will have to take care of themselves more when they are old , they will be forced to save money for the future .
They therefore will have to think more when spending money , and will try to reduce wasting extra money on unimportant things .
Moreover , nowadays , with better living condition for the whole life of a person , many old people may not be in poor health. .
Hence , extra care for additional health care may not be necessary for many elderly people .
.
Many opponents may argue that the aged are the most vulnerable group in the society and thus need more and more attention .
However , to help these people become less vulnerable , it is not so good when they are already aged .
Thus , focusing on social development as a whole , and improving living condition throughout the life of people is actually a better way to help people gain a better health and become less vulnerable when they are aged .
The productivity of the country will therefore be increased , and again , with more wealth earned , public spending in general , and on the aged , in particular , will be increased as a result .
In conclusion , although the population of the earth in general is getting aged , which could lead to certain consequences , the government should not be panicked to address that problem in a temporary way by increasing public spending for the aged as much as possible .
Rather , the government should focus on developing the nation as a whole , especially maintaining the economic growth , because this is the long term and most effective way to solve the aging problem .
In my opinion , I agree to a large extent that current research , development and policies have helped ease the aging process .
In the course of my essay , I will first show how economics , medicine , architectural and technological inventions and social policies have helped ease the aging process while financial constraint can limit the effectiveness of easing the aging process .
Firstly , economics have helped ease the aging process .
The various products available have helped to minimize the impact of unforeseen events so that an individual can save resources to meet aging needs .
In addition , as education opportunities increase , economies around the world have transformed from labour intensive to knowledge-based .
Secondly , architecture has also helped ease the aging process .
With the increasing prevalence of obstruction free buildings , the mobility of the senior population is significantly increased .
The safety features in household appliances have enabled the elderly to take care of their own needs safely .
Overall , technology has allowed the elderly to reduce their dependency on others , and has improved the quality of their lives .
In this way , the elderly will have a sum of money available to support themselves in their golden age when they retire .
In conclusion , economics , medicine , architecture , technological inventions and social policies have helped to ease the aging process but they require financial resources to achieve .
The problems of an ageing population have led to these countries coming up with measures to counteract the problems .
One of these measures is to increase public spending so as to ensure that the aged are taken care of .
We have to prepare more healthcare teams to specialize in treating illnesses related to the old as it is commonly known that the old are more prone to illness .
Thus , by increasing the amount of healthcare workers focusing on treating elderly illnesses prevent the situation of the lack of healthcare workers for the elderly in the near future .
Some of the elderly may not have saved enough to last them till death or their children are not willing to take care of them .
Nevertheless , if the government leaves the elderly who are fighting old age alone without care , it would be too cruel of the government .
These unfair treatments that the elderly face may pose a psychological problem to them .
For example , the aged may face discrimination when looking for jobs as compared to the young and also , the old age may receive less all-rounded treatment in the healthcare sector based on the stereotype that they are in the natural process of aging and that they are less likely to recover .
The government then has to interfere to educate the public to be less prejudiced against the aged .
If the economy improves , people would earn more money and thus the burden on the children taking care of their old-aged parents would be relatively less as they could better afford the costs of taking care of the elderly .
Those elderly who are unfortunate or those who have no children may face problems as they would have no one to take care of them and would be worse off without any help from the government .
As a result , public spending on the aged should not be limited as it is needed to help these elderly people .
To sum up , the government has to assume responsibilities in taking care of the elderly and to ensure that the country is adequately prepared to accept an ageing population ; thus , spending on the aged should not be limited and money should not be diverted into other areas of the country 's development .
I agree to a large extent that current research and development/policies have helped to ease the aging process .
Technology plays a significant role in providing aid for and improving the lives of the elderly .
It is also important that ageing related problems are highlighted so that corresponding policies can be implemented , for example the introduction of the pension system and late retirement to reduce elder dependency .
Firstly , the goal of personal health technologies will be to change from a centralized model where the elderly would go to the hospital where healthcare is provided , to a distributed model whereby healthcare services are delivered to where the elderly live .
Information technology applications have enabled the elderly to initiate communication , keep track of their personal health record and also make follow-up appointments which can be conducted through Telemedicine .
Telemedicine was introduced to provide care for the patient from any location with the help of transferring electronic information through various technology applications and equipments such as the web camera .
This technology delivers care directly to the homes of the elderly at an affordable rate and provide right information at the right time which benefits decision making of the medical officers involved .
It allows the elderly to be more active in taking care of themselves at the comfort of their own home .
It may be argued that telemedicine might not be as effective as contact monitoring and hands on attention .
Nevertheless , such applications have helped to reduce the time spent in hospitals and medical costs , improve record tracking practices and speed of communication .
Next , national policies such as pension systems are arranged to provide the retired elders income .
The fund may be set up by a corporation , the government , or any other organization to pay the retired workers .
Critics of this position point out that the cost of providing pensions leads to the increased taxes on the workforce .
However with the help of the pension system , it has provided the elderly with a retirement fund , thus reducing the elder dependency on the children of the elderly .
Opponents of this position argue that there would be an increase in the wage base with a lower retirement age , because people will save less as they need less wealth and lower savings .
Moreover , lifelong learning empowers the elderly to lead a better lifestyle through social interaction and contribution to the community .
In conclusion , technology and national development and policies have helped ease the aging process .
Technology applications such as Telemedicine which aids the tracking and handling of medical reports and appointments encourage the elderly to keep track of their personal health through a cost and time effective system .
In recent years , an aging population has become a serious demographic challenge to many countries around the world .
Many governments are concerned about an aging population as it leads to problems such as a shrinking workforce , decrease in economic growth due to a drop in productivity , increase in societal costs and many more .
an increase in the number of elderly persons can potentially lead to an increase in healthcare costs .
higher demands and costs for healthcare spending will pose a great challenge to the distribution of family and public resources .
Government spending on healthcare in countries around the world has always taken up one of the biggest fractions of the government budget .
However , what if there was a decrease in the amount of government spending on healthcare costs , where could the money be better used ?
Money can then be diverted to other areas of the country 's development which may be of greater use to the future generations . This will also make members of the society more independent in after their own health . In addition ,
Firstly , with a higher budget to spend in other areas such as education and defense , a country may develop even more rapidly .
With little economic growth , a society may be faced with fewer options on how to take care of people who are least able to take care of themselves .
However , with sufficient economic growth , this would not be the case as there would be more options and fewer persons in need of the help .
With more educated youths , the size of the economy and the tax base would be bigger and the cost burden of an aging population may be spread over a larger and more productive future generation .
Such is the case in Scandinavian countries where generous public funding for prenatal incentives and investments in children , for example in education , has helped curb the problem of an aging and declining population .
Furthermore , in a more educated society , more people are equipped with the knowledge to better take care of themselves and hence help lessen the amount of healthcare spending .
Elderly dependency can be reduced when they are forced or encouraged to plan and provide in advance for their own old-age livelihood .
When enforced by law or encouraged to save and invest more of their income while still in the work force , people will then save a sufficient amount of money to take care of their health when necessary rather than depend on government spending to support their health in their old age .
Dependence on the government can also be reduced by encouraging later retirement ages , longer working lives and lower requirements to elder employment , which can be achieved alone with an increase on the eligibility of age for pensions and government incentives for the elderly .
In Singapore , the government has tried using schemes such as CPF ( Central Provident Fund ) , Medisave and Medishield and even scrapped the pension scheme in order to encourage more Singaporeans to take greater responsibility for their own health .
Lastly , limited public spending on healthcare will encourage more working adults to take better care of their elderly parents .
With the elderly to look after , there will be more stress on filial obligations thereby increasing the willingness of adults in the future to take care of their elderly parents by all means .
In an increasingly society , working adults often have no time , attention , care and even finance to take care of their elderly parents and thus eventually abandon them in homes .
However , depending on the support and care from the family may be a better and cheaper alternative to take care of the elderly than depending on the nursing home 's nurse to take care of one 's parents .
However , detractors may disagree with the stand that public spending on healthcare should be limited and the money should be diverted to other areas of the country 's development .
The society may face a wide range of social issues on education , housing and many more which may not be solved by setting limits on healthcare expenditure on the government 's part as this may instead create even more problems .
Yet , in the first place , spending on healthcare may not be a good way to solve societal issues such as the lack of filial piety amongst the youths and over dependence on the government to solve every problem one might face .
In a nut shell , government spending on the aged in healthcare should be capped at a certain limit to take care of people who may really be in need while the rest of the budget should be shifted to other areas of the country 's growth .
With a limit on healthcare expenditure in the government 's budget , there may be a better investment in the area where the government 's budget goes to , people would be more self reliant and lastly it will instill a stronger sense of filial obligation in the youths .
If the government decides to cut its expenditure on the aged population , the elderly will be struggling for their survival as many welfare benefits will be limited .
This increases burdens on the younger workforce as they have to bear the cost of healthcare services required by the elderly .
This is because the older generation contributed to the workforce during their younger days .
It is their hard labour that has paved the road for us today .
As a result , the younger people and the government should reciprocate the hard work by helping the elderly .
Even if the elderly is able to support themselves , the government should continue to assist through other policies .
However , priority should be given to the needy elderly , especially for older people with a lower education background and less savings .
A handful of old people have been left stranded on the streets without shelter .
Some have been abandoned by their families while others can not afford a house because of their financial difficulties .
Therefore , the government should not limit public spending on the aged population .
As they age , their body constitution becomes weaker .
They have to make occasional visits to the doctor for diagnosis and remedy .
The cost is high , especially nowadays when new technologies and treatments are expensive .
The government can subsidize part of the healthcare expenses incurred by the elderly .
This will lighten the burden of the aged population as well as the younger workforce .
Certainly , if the government diverts its spending to other areas of the country 's development , the country would enjoy greater economic growth .
Because of that , the government would be able to collect more taxes , which can be used to aid the aging population .
Clearly , the consequences of cutting expenditure on the aged outweigh the alternative in many aspects .
A sizeable segment of the aged would suffer through the process of achieving economic growth .
Consequently , they would be struggling for survival with the limited welfare policies available to them .
In other words , if welfare programs for the aged are reduced due to limited spending , many problems would arise .
Subsequently , the government would have to spend more resources to solve the problems that arise .
Therefore , it is better to give equal if not more spending to the aged , while keeping existing welfare benefits in place .
Current psychology researchers claim that there are several pillars to being a healthy individual .
Therefore , to have pillars such as having sufficient social support and having an active engagement in life helps the elderly to cope with the inevitable stress of elderly life .
Care at home is often the preferred choice of the elderly and is generally more affordable for care providers than putting them into an institution for the elderly .
The elderly need some form of monitoring technology to help improve their safety when no one is able to be around to look after them all the time .
Remote health monitoring solutions such as to keep tabs on their blood pressure , body temperature and their heart-rate can raise alerts for medical attention quickly .
Technologies have also been designed to help the elderly maintain their own independence .
One invented device uses optical sensors to monitor how these elderly pick things up and how they use them .
It can tell if a person does something wrong such as mistake a bottle of vinegar for drinking water ; or if they are doing certain things in the wrong order .
This technological invention can also be extended to monitor how the elderly interact with other devices such as a television , a DVD player or a washing machine .
Another invention uses Radio Frequency Identification ( RFID ) technology to track which medications are taken and when .
In addition , adding a motion sensor system to provide a daily update of the elderly can help bring peace of mind to distant relatives who are concerned about the safety of their elderly family members who might be injured or ill and , worse of all , unable to call for help .
We have seen how technologies are able to replace human supervision and to monitor the condition of an elderly person round the clock , which is less possible with human care providers .
One may argue that these technologies could potentially isolate the elderly further from their families and keep them indoors even more .
This is no longer true because advanced technologies have managed to put a face to high tech devices .
A technology called the Digital Family Portrait enables the elderly and their relatives to hang up a special digital frame on their walls to receive updates of what 's going on in .
This technology can also be used to receive video phone calls from neighbors within the neighbourhood an elderly person lives in .
Furthermore , the elderly who have difficulties getting out of their homes can tap on various video technologies to draw themselves closer to their neighbors and faraway relatives through activities such as playing chess with them or engaging in a simple conversation .
Instead , it is meant to be a life enabler to increase the quality of life , like helping the elderly stay indoors safely and providing maximum possible social interaction and social support from their neighbors and relatives .
Therefore , current research on technology targeted towards the elderly not only helps ease the aging process , but it also increases the quality of life significantly for these elderly folks .
As Singapore 's population ages , there are many questions on how to help the elderly cope with the aging process .
with the government 's emphasis on tackling the rising problems of an ageing population , current research and development have helped to ease the aging process through introducing policies , upgrading facilities and providing quality healthcare services .
These improvements can be seen in various contexts and we will be looking at the benefits they have provided to the elderly .
They introduced laws and encouraged people to save and invest more of their income earned while they are active in the work force .
The government created public awareness of early planning and proper saving strategies which are necessary to ensure that we have enough money to last us through our old-age after retirement .
The government has also set up a mandatory saving scheme for all working Singaporeans .
However , some people , especially the younger ones , disagree with such a scheme .
They believe that they should have control over their earned income instead of being 'forced ' to contribute a portion of their income to such a scheme .
Thus , with the public awareness of saving for old age and the CPF , one will have sufficient savings for their old-age dependency .
Therefore , the development of an elderly-friendly environment helps to ease the aging process .
An elderly person is not afraid to walk around the housing estates or travel in public transport as these facilities have become more accessible to them .
One of the infrastructural developments that we can see is the building of lifts to serve all levels of new and existing HDB flats .
This eliminates the need for an elderly person to climb the stairs in order to get to the level that the lift does not stop at .
The elderly will have an easier time walking up and slopes than stairs to get to their destination .
Public transportation such as the MRT and buses have implemented a similar concept in the building of their facilities .
MRT stations have built lifts to allow the elderly to travel up to and down from the platform with ease .
Public buses have steps-free entrances and exits for easier mobility of the elderly .
However , some people question if the spending on all these upgrades to increase accessibility for the elderly is necessary .
But if we do not maintain a good infrastructure that caters to the elderly , no matter how good the economy is , the elderly will not be able to enjoy accessible and user-friendly facilities that make their life more convenient. .
However , now we will be able to get the proper care and rehabilitation due to improvements to healthcare facilities such as public hospitals , nursing homes and polyclinics .
We have a team of well-trained doctors and nurses who are committed to taking care of the elderly who need special attention .
We also have groups of medical specialists who are always finding ways to improve the healthcare of the elderly through better medication and rehabilitation .
As a result , more day rehabilitation centres and nursing homes have been built to handle the demands for increasing healthcare .
In my opinion , the elderly do not need to worry about getting good healthcare services as it is easily found anywhere in Singapore .
government policies are involved to ensure that proper saving for the future is in place , the upgrading of public facilities have helped create an elderly-friendly environment and better healthcare services have been made available .
Firstly , encouraging later retirement for the elderly can drastically change individuals ' attitude towards work .
This in turn will provide a positive mentality to better prepare them for their old age .
For example , when the government announces measures to encourage later retirements , the citizens would be prepared for what is to come and be more ready to accept it , thus reducing elder dependency in the long term .
Secondly , extending individuals ' working life will often result in the accumulation of more wealth which can be used to support them in their old age .
This acts as a safety net to dramatically reduce the need for elder dependency .
For example , an elderly person who has worked for 50 years compared to one that has worked for 40 years should have considerably more savings .
With the ability to work and also a sustainable income , the elderly will find themselves less dependent on others .
Moreover , their gained experience can prove valuable to the economy .
For example , with increased measures by the government fto put the elderly into the workforce , the elderly will be able to depend on themselves .
All in all , the strategy of reducing elder dependency through the 3 methods can prove to be valuable for an aging society .
Once you are on board , there is nothing you can do " , said Golda Meir .
Indeed , perhaps everyone is afraid of aging because it not only marks deterioration in physical health and significant psychological changes , but also places more financial burdens on the government and the society , because obviously , the elderly need fiscal support , better health care and facilities specialized for their age-related problems .
One example of necessary financial support is the investment on developing and upgrading the current facilities used in education , including information technology equipment , laboratories and library systems .
This is particularly important to the education in developing and less developed countries , like Vietnam , China , the Philippines and Malaysia , where teaching and learning still utilise traditional methods with little IT support and the use of old textbooks , as well as using laboratories with obsolete devices .
With improvements in educational facilities , students will be able to access up-to-date knowledge more easily , as well as experiment with and apply what they have learned in reality .
By providing tuition grants ( of 80 % ) and financial aid for living costs of foreign students along with a career bond , Singapore will have a greater workforce serving them for at least 3 years after graduation .
Another area that the government needs to be concerned about is the environment as hundreds of environmental projects ( such as reducing the level of green house gases and noxious fumes in the atmosphere or promoting the use of non-plastic carrying bags ) are waiting for capital and fiscal support .
In such small nations ( in terms of geographical area ) like Singapore , this issue is particularly important because every climatic change or pollution problem is likely to negatively affect the whole country , especially the physical health of the people , including the aged .
Moreover , the environment is a global concern ; it influences everybody in the world .
Thus , protecting it means we are protecting not only the young but also the elderly ; not only the current generation , but also the future ones .
Besides the concerns surrounding environmental protection and education , public spending on the aged should be partly transferred to public infrastructure development projects such as public transportation , schools and hospitals because such developments are directly related to the improvement in the living standards of senior citizens .
Firstly , a modern infrastructure will bring about s , effectiveness and efficiency .
One example of this is the extension of access to most public places and even on public transport vehicles for people with physical disabilities , through designing paths or elevators specialized for wheel chairs , or placing special directional signs for the elderly with sight or hearing problems .
Secondly , due to its higher efficiency , such facilities will help reduce operational costs and subsequently decrease the cost of living for citizens .
For instance , a well organized public transportation system will help minimize the use of private vehicles , which is costly , and reduce traffic congestion and accidents .
And therefore , to some extent , the elderly will indirectly benefit from this policy .
In conclusion , people may be upset with the idea of limiting public spending on the elderly because they may think that the aged increasingly lack care from the society .
However , considering the positive impacts it brings about to the entire society , obviously the advantages will outweigh the disadvantages .
Singapore is no different .
As the population continues to age , government spending on the aged will probably increase as more and more people would rely on the government for their needs .
I do not agree with this .
In the past , the literacy rate of the people was low .
Many elders of the current generation have little to no education so in their economically active years , they were n't able to save a lot .
Moreover , most of the money they earned was spent on their children to make sure that they received proper education .
This act of placing the younger generation 's interest before theirs and making sure that they got proper education increased the literacy rate of the country and contributed to the country 's development .
In other words , the old have contributed a lot to shaping our country into what she is today .
Therefore , now that the country has prospered , the government should look after the people who helped made it possible .
some may argue that since the elderly spent their money on their children , it 's now the responsibility of the children to look after their needs , and not the government 's .
However , if that were to happen , would increase and the younger generation may find it harder to start a family .
According to the Singapore Ministry of Finance , in FY2009 , 41.5 % of government expenditure would be placed on the economic and social development of the country .
Looking at the numbers , we can tell that sufficient funds have already been allocated for the country 's development so no additional funds are required .
Even if there is a need for additional funds for economic and social development , instead of limiting or cutting expenditure on the aged , the government should look at other areas to cut .
A reason for the stand that the government should limit spending on the aged is that the aged is not of much use to the society so the government should not concentrate so much on them .
Most of the aged have proved that they can continue to work and contribute to the society in one way or another and thus their welfare should be looked at as well .
In conclusion , spending on the aged should not be limited or diverted as , for a developed country like Singapore , many successes have been brought about by them and they have helped shaped the country into what it is today .
If there was ever a need for more funds to be injected into the development of the country , other areas and not the spending on the aged should be looked at .
I agree that the implemented policies have eased the aging process .
To control the population , the government introduce the 'stop at two ' policy that was so successful that it resulted in a decline of the overall population even till today .
The drop of population has given rise to an aging population .
To tackle the issue of an aging population , the government has implemented some measures that are helping the elderly to age comfortably .
Some of the measures are the Medisave scheme , Lift Improvement and Facilities Enhancement for the elderly ( LIFE ) and the Eldershield scheme .
The Medisave scheme covers a range of health expenses which includes surgical operations,psychiatric treatment and many more .
Such measures of saving for the rainy days will help Singaporeans to cover part of their medical expenses as they retire into old age .
Although this scheme does not provide 100 % coverage on their medical bills , patients will have a smaller burden when the majority of the medical bills are heavily subsidised by the government and supported by Medisave .
The services include upgrading of lifts to access every floor , installation of support handbars in washrooms and setting up a Senior Activity Centre in the neighbourhood .
According to General Housing Survey 2005 , there are around 22,000 elderly people living alone .
More attention should be given to this group of elderly as they have no one to turn to if they require help in their home .
By installing handbars and improving the accessibility of lifts , the elderly are now able to move around safely and in greater comfort .
The Senior Activity Centre also provides a place for the lonely old individuals to mingle around and to participate in recreational activities .
The upgrading process might cause inconveniences to the residents but this is a trade off that they have to bear with for a better tomorrow .
Thirdly , the Eldershield scheme was introduced in 2007 .
The scheme automatically covers Singaporeans that are aged 40 and above with an insurance plan .
According to the Census of Population 2000 , about 3 % of the elderly are non-ambulant .
However , one will have to pay a minimum of $ 176.96 annual premium in order to enjoy the benefits of the scheme .
To make the plan affordable , the government provides premium subsidies and constantly reviews the plan .
In conclusion , the elderly are now more protected and are aging more comfortably with the implementation of the policies .
There are two sides to a coin ; although the measures do not solve the problem entirely and may cause inconvenience in some cases , the benefits will eventually outweigh the cons .
The government will have to constantly review and improve the measures to be prepared for the aging population .
There have been many controversial debates on whether the government should limit public spending on the elderly so that money can be diverted to other areas of the country 's development .
While the latter is important and inevitable , our government is being challenged to cope with the need to increase allocation of public funds for the elderly with a graying population .
If a limit is not in place , the government might soon face difficulties in funding other key sectors of the country 's development such as education and defense .
Smaller side effects include the over reliance on the government to support the aged .
This will turn the regime of supporting the elderly into a nightmare and burden to the society .
Firstly , with a graying population , the government is expected to spend more public funds each year on areas like healthcare for the elderly and elderly friendly public facilities such as slopes in housing estates .
This section of public expenditure soaks up a large portion of the government 's annual allocated budget each year .
In Singapore 's 2009 budget allocation , a total of $ 66 million ( up from a total of $ 55.6 million in the year 2008 ) was allocated from the pool of $ 18.1 billion allocated for social development .
This expenditure is expected to rise further with the increase of life expectancy and the increase in the proportion of the elderly ( from 8.6 % in 2008 to 18.7 % in 2030 ) .
To quote a statistic from Singapore 's 2008 budget day report , in 2007 , 21 % of the Government Healthcare Expenditure ( GHE ) , or 0.2 % of the country 's GDP was dedicated to elderly care .
Many people might however , disagree that government should limit the public spending on aged .
The economic growth of a country relies on many areas such as education , the welfare of the public , defense , transportation , and many more .
All these aspects work together to make a great impact on the country and make the country grow .
Therefore , the government should not direct their money specifically into certain areas while neglecting the rest .
Education is one of the very important a country should develop .
The government should invest a substantial amount of effort in this area .
The school is a place where every single young person receives education .
The government should also focus on developing this area to make the learning process more interactive and exciting .
Education and knowledge are important tools that help them to survive int the working world .
Lack of education leads to lack of knowledge .
If a country does not develop well in the area of education , the economy of the country will definitely not grow well .
This is because most graduates do not meet prerequisites required by the industy .
Thus , the government should also focus on and put in more effort to help these people .
The government should create more job opportunities for them .
For example , the government can run some job training programs to help the graduates exploit their talent and better equip them for the industry .
Investing in the young is more worthwhile than in the aged because they are well-educated and have the potential to make more contributions to the country .
Over time , the population of the elderly is gradually growing .
If expenditure on the aged is not controlled , the government would be putting more and more money into something which would not really have any impact on the country 's economic growth .
The government can limit the expenditure because the burden of healthcare can be borne by the family members of the aged through schemes like MediSave .
Working adults have to pay for high living expenses such as their children 's tuition and enrichment classes .
To those with low incomes , these are already a burden for them .
Most elderly have a lot of health problems and they also need medical care , the majority of which involves high cost .
Therefore , cutting down on welfare programs will burden the working adult with greater financial problems .
They will then have to work even harder to earn a living .
For example , they might take up 2 or more jobs working day and night .
As a result , they end up with poor health and reduced productivity in their work .
In conclusion , limiting public spending on the aged does not mean ceasing expenditure on them .
Instead , it achieves a balance where the government can set a limit and provide adequate funding for them while focusing on other more important aspects like education .
Public spending refers to money expended by a government to pay for areas such as defense , development projects , education , health , infrastructure , and law & order maintenance , and such spending is supported by taxation .
With an increasing number of elderly in society , it is rather strenuous for the non-elderly to contribute to the tax base .
And it is in no doubt that the aged require additional spending on public pensions and health care .
One argument that suggests money should be diverted to the education area is that higher education would help to cut down the sizeable segment of the population who needs government aid during old age in the future .
This is because according to Robert B. Friedland and Laura Summer , people with better education are more likely to have higher incomes and better health .
However , they should take into consideration the fact that there are elderly from the past generations without good education who have not been able to save in their younger days .
Since they are old , retired and do not have much savings , large health and long-term care expenses will significantly deplete their resources .
Some think that spending money on the aged is like throwing money down the drain since it is part and parcel of life for them to grow old , age and die .
Thus making it possible for people to live comfortably now .
Whereas , an elderly who has children whose income is relatively stable , will receive less help .
In this way , public spending will not be misused and children are forced to be filial and therefore , the government does not have to set a limitation on public spending since the amount spent on the aged will be less .
In order for those elderly to live reasonably well , but not to the extent of " luxuriously well " , government should assess the living condition of these elderly and provide them with the necessary aid they need .
In recent years , public spending on the aged has gradually increased , sparking countless discussions about whether public spending on the aged should be limited , so that the money can be diverted to other areas of the country 's development .
In countries where the population is not aging , public spending on the aged should be decreased and the funds should be channelled into other more important policies and schemes .
One of the reasons why the government should not be the one that supports the elderly is the simple concept of filial piety .
Filial piety is one of the virtues that have been around society for ages . It emphasises respect for parents .
Therefore , the costs of spending for the should be borne by their respective offspring .
Their children should be the one to support them through their old age as " repayment " for all that their parents have done .
It is not easy to bring up children ; parents have to scrimp and save just to give their children the best .
Parents also try to give their children the best education they can afford .
So , should it not be only fair that their children support them through their old age , especially when they have no one else to rely on ?
Therefore , public spending on the aged should be cut down because the younger generation should be the one supporting their parents ; it is their own duty and should not be left to the government .
Nevertheless , there will be special cases when such aged folk do not have children to rely on , either because they do not have kids , or due to some misfortune have lost their children .
In these cases , it would only be right for the government to help them .
Hence , public spending on the aged should be limited , but not completely ignored .
Also , in every society where exist , there will be a group of people who tend to " abuse " the system .
In reality , there are a number of those who try to leech off as much government funding as they can , despite their ability to support themselves .
After the aged retire , there are a large group of them who actually are still fit to work and are able to do minor jobs to support themselves .
However , this is rarely brought up due to the fact that most of them do not wish to continue working into old age ; they believe that they deserve to rest .
Although I believe that people who retire definitely deserve their freedom , I completely disagree that most of them should be doing it at the expense of the government .
If their children are unable to support them through their old age for whatever reason , they should try to find minor jobs to support themselves , especially if they are still physically fit .
Therefore , spending on the aged should be minimized , and funds that are allocated to it should be given out more wisely and strictly .
Some people disagree that public spending on aged should be cut down , arguing that the cost of supporting an old person may be too much of a burden for young adults nowadays .
However , I feel that if there are increased funds in the other areas of development , the burden would actually be lesser than it already is .
If public spending on the aged is decreased or minimized and the funds are diverted to other channels to boost economic growth , the country would be a richer society .
There would be a rise in wealth and the working population would actually have more monetary assets to support the aged .
Also , funds could be diverted into other sources which would result in an improvement in a country 's cleanliness .
This can be accomplished through increased technology , or investment into machinery that cleans up polluted air .
The cost of supporting an old person is no doubt largely due to increased medical costs that come with old age .
However , if the country is able to find a way to improve cleanliness , this will no doubt lead to a healthier population , which in turn means lower medical costs .
Therefore , it is a wiser choice to lower public spending on the elderly because the net benefit from such an action would be much greater than if we were to leave the spending untouched .
However , such a policy would only work in countries that do not face an ageing population .
Countries that face the problem are unable to carry out such a plan .
This is due to the fact that it is almost impossible for the younger generation to support the aged , considering number of aged in society greatly outweighs the generation that supports them .
Therefore , it would be wiser for the governments of such countries to craft other policies that would suit their own needs .
This would in turn benefit the countries more than if they were to leave the policies untouched .
This essay argues to a large extent that current research and developmentpolicies have helped to ease the aging process because of the innovative that Singapore 's government and other organizations have provided .
These solutions are mostly in the area of medicine , technology and society which are essential in slowing the and eradicating this problem in the future .
For instance , in United Kingdom , a research done by Deloitte and summarized by Dr Michael Harris ( Nesta , April 2009 ) showed that more than a quarter of fifty- to sixty-year-old elderly people have been diagnosed with medical conditions and the numbers are expected to increase in the future .
It is possible for people to have this view because this medicine is not widely used in the market as further research is still ongoing to further improve its effectiveness .
Most of them will have trouble adjusting to new technology if they are already comfortable with the level of technological background that they are equipped in .
Moreover , health conditions such as deteriorating eye sight or poorer hearing can be a problem as well .
However , Microsoft has come up with technological innovation that helps the elderly deal with these situations due to their health concerns .
Nevertheless , despite this solution , the elderly are still struggling to cope with the latest technology .
But they should be willing to adapt to technological changes as these are there to help humans cope with their daily activities ; there are also alternatives provided to these changes so that society would not to neglect the elderly .
In fact , one of the measures includes the " Maintenance of Parents Act " ( Statutes , " Maintenance of Parents Act " , Chapter 167B , June 1996 ) in which parents can demand rights from their children who neglected them .
This helps to prevent grown up children from running away from their responsibilities towards their parents .
Moreover , companies are also encouraged to employ older workers even after these workers are past their retirement age ( Channel NewsAsia , September 2009 ) .
To further attract the interest of companies to do so , recognition such as the " AARP International Innovative Employer Awards " is given out to companies which demonstrate innovation in inclusion of elderly in their companies ( AARP International , January 2008 ) .
Yet , despite such incentives being given out , many companies still choose to retrench those who fall under the older age group during the retrenchment period claiming that the elderly are less productive and effective .
While this may be true , it is possible to keep the elderly from being retrenched as they can take up courses to improve their skills .
In conclusion , although such research and policies have yet to fully solve the problem of an aging population , they still provide alternatives for the aged and society to cope with the problem .
Thus , it is up to the individuals themselves to determine whether they want to oblige to the policies implemented or try out those new alternatives .
Aging population is becoming a more and more serious problem , consuming a great amount of money from public programs .
One solution is limiting the money spent on programs for the aged and diverting that money to other areas of a country 's development .
Some critics say implementing this solution might imply that the government does not want to support the elderly ; however , it is a practical solution to the current aging population problem .
Some people say this solution might cause financial difficulty to many elderly and their family , especially some critical segments of the elderly population , such as those who have particularly low income like older single women , or those who have attained little education ( Friedland and Summer , 2005 ) .
However , this policy will only use up a part of the money used for the aged .
Those who can support themselves , either by their own savings or by support of family , should help reduce financial stress exerted on programs for the elderly .
In fact , there are more and more people who do not have to rely on government help .
Friedland and Summer ( 2005 ) also agree that " the population aged 65 to 75 is healthier , wealthier and better educated than persons in this age group in past generations " .
In fact , several countries have already implemented means testing systems that reflect the above idea .
In Australia , there is means testing for age pension based on income test and assets test to assess compensation payments ( http : //www.fahcsia.gov.au ) .
Starting from 1 January 2009 , Singapore has run a means testing system in its public hospitals : a certain group of citizens with a certain range of income will have a different subsidy scheme .
For example , citizens who have average income lower than $ 3200 per month will have their hospital fees subsidized by 80 % while those who earn more than $ 5200 monthly will only have their hospital fees subsidized by 50 % ( source : http : //www.hospitals.sg ) .
Most importantly , limiting public money spending on the aged will save a great amount of money for the government .
This money can be diverted to other needier and more important programs , such as educational , environmental and other economic development related programs .
Friedland and Summer ( 2005 ) state that the key word in fighting against aging population is economic growth .
As the economy develops , the country will generate more money and thus be able to spend a greater amount of money on programs such as health care support for the elderly .
In conclusion , a country which faces an aging population problem should consider limiting public money spent on the aged and instead use more of it for its development .
Such money can be considered as an investment for the country 's economy .
Besides , a country could also support programs that make this policy run more effectively , such as promoting children 's willingness to support their elderly parents and implementing means testing programs .
Firstly , it is user-friendly .
IT is user-friendly .
It overcomes the two main problems that the elderly have when using IT .
IT , on the other hand , will never grow impatient with the old .
Some people may argue that although IT would not grow impatient with the old , the old may , in contrast , grow impatient with IT .
However , I believe that IT is user-friendly , and therefore easy to pick up .
The elderly , if given a chance at IT , will never tire of it .
IT ( as cited in Helsinki , 8 April , 2003 ) could improve the operative ability of the elderly and may even enhance their well-being .
The aged could even prevent being sent to an old folk 's home , be able to live alone at home , and increase individual management of their personal issues .
IT not only brings great convenience to the livelihood of the aged , but is also user-friendly .
This makes it easy for the elderly , who would be slow at learning , to pick up IT and get familiarized with it at their own time .
It is also clear that with all the above reasons , the elderly would most definitely find it rather undemanding for them to embrace IT in their lives .
Many problems usually start to arise when one reaches old age .
For instance , one will have lower productivity in work as well as will need to face the issue of rising social and healthcare cost
( Peterson , 2001 ) . Also , the effects of having little education , not being able to save during one 's economically active years as well as deteriorating health among the elderly suggest that government should not limit public spending on them ( Friedland and Summer , 2005 ) . Although there are many benefits if money is diverted to other areas of a country 's development , such as education and generation of a more productive workforce , public spending on the aged should not be limited to allow elderly people to age with dignity .
First of all , public spending on the aged can be diverted to help those people who have lower income but have the potential of pursuing a higher education to get better qualification .
The government could offer scholarships or offer subsidized school fees based on their income level in order to help to generate more highly educated people so that the effects of having little education and not being able to save during one 's economically active years could be minimized .
Although there are benefits , this will result in a large number of people having high qualifications and it will end up becoming something that is common among everybody .
Therefore , diverting money to education would not help to minimize the effect of having little education and not being able to save during one 's economically active years .
Thus , this suggests that public spending on the aged should not be limited .
Secondly , public spending on the aged can be diverted to increase salaries and bonuses of people who are more hardworking and productive so that it will help to generate a more productive workforce .
With an increase in salary and bonus , it will allow one to save during their economically active years and also help them to slow down deteriorating health that will continue into old age . one will have the ability to pay for their healthcare cost in order to cure any illnesses before it continues into old age .
On the other hand , with an increase in salaries and bonuses of people who are more hardworking and productive , it will result in everybody fighting for such increases and therefore , one will become an enemy of the other person .
This also suggests that public spending on on the aged not be limited .
In conclusion , public spending should not be diverted to other areas such as education and generation of a more productive workforce .
Instead , the government should support the aged by providing work that are suitable for them as well as providing support for their medical and social spending in order to help them cope with the rising issue of social and healthcare cost .
Moreover , when the government provides support for medical and social spending , it will allow the elderly to have enough money to spend for their other leisure activities .
Therefore , public spending on the aged should not be limited in order to allow the elderly to age with dignity .
Yes , I agree that public spending on the aged should be limited so that money can be used for other areas of development .
There are several reasons why public spending should be limited .
One reason is that the government can still provide benefits to the elderly by developing programmes that will benefit all age groups .
By limiting public spending on the aged , the government can focus on other areas of development such as the economy .
Government could use public funds to invest in job markets to increase the economic growth of the country .
This does bring some benefits to the elderly .
With an increase in economic growth , the number of working population will rise as more people will be able to find jobs .
This will encourage working adults to take responsibility in looking after their elderly parents and thus , promoting filial obligation .
On top of that , with a better economy , the elderly will be able earn more income if they decide to continue to work until retirement age .
Firstly , business depends on a reliable network of transportation , as time saved will be money saved .
In addition , the transportation network is a key determinant of how businesses are which in turn will affect the flow of investments and the country 's economy .
For example , with more MRT stations and buses , the working population will find travelling to their workspaces become more convenient .
As for the elderly , they will be able to save time travelling to places such as hospitals , community centers , etc .
The elderly would also be able to travel in a more comfortable way .
Therefore , the government should use public funds to improve transportation .
Funds could be used to build more MRT stations and increase the frequency and quality of buses which , in turn , will benefit everyone .
There are other reasons why public spending on the aged should be limited .
One reason is the rising cost of care for the aged .
This is because the number of people aged 60 and above is expected to triple by year 2050 .
Also , with the rising cost of living , the amount of funds needed to care for the elderly will rise tremendously .
This will mean higher tax is required .
Therefore , if the government does not limit the spending , more taxpayer 's money will be needed to care for the elderly .
If this trend continues , the country 's financial reserves will be depleted .
As a result , there is a need to balance public spending .
In conclusion , public spending on the elderly should be limited so that funds could be used in other areas of development .
" Public spending on the aged should be limited so that money can be diverted to other areas of the country 's development " .
I disagree with this statement .
The idea of reducing public spending for the aged would eventually generate more problems in the country and thus slow down the country 's development instead .
The scope of this essay focuses on the area of public spending in healthcare of the elderly .
The country could consider adjusting the budget to improve the economy .
Indeed , this may seem to be a wise move as the country will be richer in its next budget planning .
However , as the economy grows , wages increase and the cost of living also increases , it would be inevitable that prices of products , medication , services , and hospitalization bills , would also be on the rise .
As subsidy is reduced , the family will have to pay more .
Therefore , the positive effect of an increase in wages could be offset by or even be insufficient to keep up with the cost of living for the middle and lower income groups .
Thus , this would lead to the rich getting richer , and the poor getting poorer .
Can we consider a country with high GDP , tall and flashy buildings , but with an increasing number of its citizens living in slum conditions , a country with good economy ?
In order to reduce public spending on the aged , policy makers argue that children who take responsibility for their elderly parents ' medical expenses because it is a form of filial piety .
Despite this wonderfully painted deception , reality proves otherwise , as people to work around the system .
For example , the existence of schemes such as Do-Not-Resuscitate ( DNR ) and Euthanasia , though only in certain countries , could tell a different story as these voluntary schemes may possibly not be so voluntary after all . Children could force their parents to die earlier allegedly to relieve their pain so as to lighten the children 's financial burden .
The movie " Money No Enough 2 " , directed by Jack Neo , shows a scene in the hospital where a mother 's three children burn a talisman hoping for their mother 's death during the economic downturn .
In addition , according to { http : //www.euthanasia.com/deaths2003.html } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.euthanasia.com/deaths2003.html ] , an increased in the number of people in Oregon died through euthanasia , of whom 37 % of the patients had indicated being concerned about the financial burden of their families { http : //www.euthanasia.com/reasons2003.html } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.euthanasia.com/reasons2003.html ] .
Although these statistics did not specifically target the aged , they indicate that being a financial burden played a part in their decision to terminate their lives , be they instigated or not .
Money could also be invested in many other areas of the country 's development for further growth or better benefits to the country , rather than waste on healthcare benefits for the elderly .
On the other hand , it is the aged population that had brought the country to what it is right now with their sweat and blood .
Their ailments and conditions could have resulted from their work , be it directly or indirectly caused , while contributing to the nation 's progress , thus they should not be ignored .
Because of this , it is only reasonable that the country should look after these past contributors and not to overlook their achievements just because they are no longer as capable of contributing to the .
This latter move will reflect badly on how the country regards its citizens ; it may even discourage its citizens from performing their best , or even and work in other countries , as they know that the state will not take care of them in their later life .
To sum up , without a doubt diverting public spending from supporting the aged population to the other areas of development in the country may at first seem to be the best option , but eventually , it could result in more harm than good , either by upsetting the balance of wealth in the country , imparting wrong moral values or conveying the wrong message to its citizens .
With the development of societies , governments and policy makers pay more attention to the phenomenon of aging populations , especially in developed countries .
According to incomplete figures , in the European countries , spending on pensions , health , and related issues is currently 15 % of GDP ( gross domestic product ) .
However , although spending on the aged is high , it should not be limited .
Some argue that public spending on the aged should be limited so that money can be diverted to other areas of the country 's development .
For instance , government should cut down the spending on the aged , and use more money to attract talented immigrants .
However , the result may be that many immigrants who have different cultural backgrounds will enter the country .
One country with a great influx of immigrants may become unstable , since cultures are different and cultural fusion needs a long period of time .
Hence , it is not necessary to limit public spending on the aged to attract talented immigrants .
