This essay is going to elaborate the effects that scientific discoveries , technological inventions and social policies have on easing the aging process .
Firstly , new scientific research and discoveries are regularly annouced and the elderly can follow the suggestions given by the researches .
" Strength training stimulates the growth or muscles and people feel more energetic ; also , the elderly with strong muscles are less likely to fall and suffer bad consequences .
In fact , we keep hearing health tips from the news broadcast or feeds such as healthy recipes , aerobic exercise and Yoga .
These are the practical summaries of scientific research and discovery
Secondly , uesful technological inventions have also been convenient to the elderly .
It is not unsual that the elderly have problems with their body like loss of senses .
Technologies like The Hearing Aid may be old news to us ; however , a new invention enables the blind to see .
( ' ) " They can not necessarily read a book but they can read a sign " , said the development company .
The blind are able to gain a rough perception of their surroundings with the " eye " and be independent from their families ' care .
Thirdly , social policies like CPF ( Central Provident Fund ) have helped alleviate the financial support of the elderly .
CPF is a policy to help people save a portion of their salaries while they are economically active .
With CPF , the eldly have money for life after retirement without extra financial help from the government , thus the implementation of CPF alleviates the government 's financial problem , and it is also favored by the rest of the society since they do not have to pay for the expenditures of the eldly after retirement .
Critics of science , technolological and social policies ' for an aging population argue that the elderly could live a satisfatory life in terms of the material ; however , it is hard for them to be happy since the society does not favor old people who do not fit its fast pace .
It is because there are communities which welcome the retirees who are healthy , independent and rich . In time , they will become more popular and be 'recruited ' by the communities since traditionally , women have provided much of the voluntary work but now more of them have joined the work force .
