In conclusion , scientific discoveries ease the aging process by educating the elderly on what is healthy ; technological inventions do this in ways to heal the sick , injured and even the disabled ; finally , social policies help the elderly in finance to secure a peaceful life .
These diseases often decrease the quality of life of the elderly because they cause the elderly to lose their ability to live a normal life as they used to live .
This fact is quite worrying since fingers are the most frequently used part of a human hand .
[ 6 ] Heart disease makes up more than 30 % of deaths in American adults aged 65 and above caused by chronic disease , making it the disease which kills most elderly .
In the past , these dead cells caused by a heart attack could not be replaced .
But today , thanks to a new heart treatment called " Heart Myoblast Cell Injection " , heart attack victims can get their healthy heart muscle cells back .
[ 7 ] In this new treatment method , myoblast cells are extracted from the heart patient 's own thigh muscles .
Research show that new tissue formation and improvement in the heart function of the patients were found after this treatment .
The lead researcher of this treatment at the Arizona Heart Institute , Nabil Dib , says , " Through this heart treatment we can regenerate a scar tissue caused by a heart attack , which is the opposite of what we learnt in medical school .
[ 8 ] While heart disease is still the leading cause of death in the elderly , cancer comes second .
[ 9 ] In the United States , Lung cancer kills more people than other cancers .
The traditional method to cure lung cancer in a patient is by surgery or radiotherapy which is given five days a week for six to seven weeks .
Another advantage of SBRT is it can double the survival rates of early stage patients .
The survival rates of SBRT are as high as surgical methods , which some patients can not have because of their conditions or refuse to have .
[ 12 ] Colorectal cancer is the second cancer-related killer in the United States after lung cancer .
Most colorectal cancer patients are elderly because the possibility of having colorectal cancer increases with age .
Nevertheless , some scientists from The United Kingdom have found a vaccine called TroVax which is able to cure kidney and bowel cancer .
The research on the vaccine showed that " [ 13 ] One patient who was given the vaccine has seen his tumour disappear totally .
Unlike chemotherapy which can cause depression of the bodies immune system because it kills not only bad cancer cells but also good cells which contribute to the body 's immunity , this vaccine works in a totally different way .
The vaccine improves the body 's immune system to fight a particular disease which in this case is colorectal cancer
These inventions help the elderly to live a healthier life .
By living a healthier life , the elderly people can live their days more normally and hence this will help them in the aging process .
First of all , the layout of the home is extremely important for old people to manage their living .
Firstly , by making sure that the house has single level living space , with no steps in main entry points , no obstruction in the hall way and bedrooms opening into the sitting room can reduce the accidents at home for the elderly .
It finds that 71 home accidents are reported by 607 elder people in four weeks and 70 % of the accidents are caused by falling .
Psychologists from the university of Texas indicates that being positive delays aging .
Equally important , is lighting another concern with regard to the health of the elderly especially the eyes .
Such as room lighting with controlling senses is also necessary to increase the illumination for eye protection , and the glare should be avoided by choosing the material of the wall , ceiling and mirror to fight against cataracts .
On the other hand , getting enough exposure to daylight can help fight against osteoporosis and insomnia .
And a study by Gloth ( 1995 ) suggests that half of the elderly have deficient vitamin D levels .
Furthermore , since old people stay at home most of the time , adequate sunlight would help them to form the cycle of day and night and thus prevent them from having sleep disorders .
Although some people still insist that it is better to let someone take care of the old or provide asylums for them , and therefore there is no need to redesign their homes , they fail to consider the fees for their care and the feelings of the elderly
Since most of them do save their pension for health care and do not want to burden their children .
and , since old people have already developed a strong sentiment for their house , and do not want to move .
Furthermore , home care can be done by providing welfare and consultation by government agencies at a lower cost to alleviate the solitude and physical burden of the dependent elderly , which is suggested by Claude ( 1993 ) in " Home based care " .
In conclusion , redesigning homes such as ordering the layout and adjusting the light for the old can ease the aging process in terms of reducing home accidents , facilitating those who have physical problems and protecting the eyes and bones .
