As the result , many people are afraid of nuclear power even until today .
Although there are a lot of opposition to the reborn of nuclear power ; there is some evidence which show that the potential benefits of molten salt reactor ( MSR ) far outweigh its dangers .
According to the former director of that plant , it was pure luck that the plant had no meltdown ; otherwise , it could be another disaster ( Greenpeace , Jan2009 ,
Firstly , the molten salts have low chemical activity at sea-level pressure .
Besides that , there is a passive cooling system which includes passively cooled dump tanks that will perform emergency cooling and shutdown in any emergency conditions ( Forsberg , C.F , June2006 , ) .
Moreover , in a MSR , the mobile fission products are removed continuously and reused .
Since the beginning of nuclear power , radioactive waste has remained a major problem .
However , according to a study published in 2001 , there was a significant increment of leukaemia among under-25 year olds who were living within 10 km of La Hague nuclear reprocessing plants , in northwest France ( Greenpeace , Jan2009 , ) .
Yet , reprocessing the radioactive waste and recycling the salts seem to be possible in MSR .
Some of the radionuclide is still left out in this recycling process .
Still , a molten salt reactor is worth its price .
Moreover , the system of circulating molten salt fuel mixture can reduce the operation cost considerably which provide MSR another advantage
( . Besides that , MSR has a lower construction cost as it is smaller compared to other types of nuclear reactors .
This is because MSR system offers an integrated fuel cycle and embodies a breeder reactor concept .
In conclusion , though many people are still opposing the concept of reactor generation IV , I believe that MSR could bring the nuclear power to another new age .
MSR has many advantages such being cost-effective , minimize the danger of disposal and it has a nearly perfect safety precaution which reduce accident rates greatly .
However , safety precautions and corrective actions are not fail-proof .
Furthermore , it is essential to note that the most damaging errors made by the engineering team is not regarding the technical aspect of the engineering process but with regard to ethic issues which often jeopardize safety .
Hence analysis of the mind and behavior of man may potentially help rule out the possibilities of such occurrences .
In the case of the Hyatt Regency walkway collapse , human error was undeniably one of the most influencing factors underlying the failure of the structure .
Even though the collapse of the walkway was due to the failure of components of the structure , it would not have been fatal if the errors were identified and corrected in time .
Not only do engineers have to communicate within their team , but also with representatives from various other levels .
In times , the breakdown of the communication system can lead to disastrous consequences
In the case of the Regency accident , the miscommunication between the engineering team and Havens Steel Company , the contractor responsible for manufacturing the rods , is very much accountable for the fatal accident .
The manufacturers were not informed of the possible effects of the change in material .
In the case of the Hyatt Regency accident , the failure to foresee the large crowd and hence larger workload is one great mistake made by the engineers .
Hence , it will be of importance to verify the maximum load that the walkway is able to withstand .
In the case of the Hyatt Regency accident , the application of psychology would possibly have prevented the accident .
Since the first use of nuclear reactor as electricity generator in 1957 , the public has been very concerned about its safe operation ( { Matthew } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.nytimes.com/info/nuclear-energy/ ] , n.d. ) .
Public opposition is even more intense after the accidents at Three Mile Island [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.pddoc.com/tmi2/kemeny/ ] and Chernobyl .
But recently , vast amounts of supporters have surfaced , mainly due to the urgent need in reducing carbon dioxide emissions .
As a result , six generation 4 reactor concepts were proposed by the Generation 4 International Forum ( GIF ) , offering substantial advancement in safety and reliability , sustainability , cost and physical protection (
Opponents of VHTR might claim that Lead-Cooled Fast Reactor ( LFR ) exhibit better safety features for its selection of molten lead as relatively inert coolant ( Generation IV Technology , n.d. ) .
However , the VHTR offers higher degree of passive safety ; for instance , it is built underground and uses the earth to sink most of the heat produced .
Since reprocessing of nuclear waste can eminently reduces raw fuel input and conserves the world 's uranium supplies ( ) , opponents might argue that the Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.gen-4.org/Technology/systems/gfr.htm ] ( GFR ) , { Molten Salt Reactor } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.gen-4.org/Technology/systems/msr.htm ] ( MSR ) , { Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.gen-4.org/Technology/systems/sfr.htm ] ( SFR ) , and LFR offer better performance with the adoption of reprocessing ( Butler , 2004 ) .
On the other hand , reprocessing is extremely expensive , costing more than uranium fuel itself ( ) .
On the contrary , the VHTR does not have this issue , for it operates in a once-through uranium cycle .
Since plutonium - the main substance in manufacturing nuclear weapon - is not separated with the nuclear waste , it can not be easily extracted to build nuclear weapons ( ) .
The VHTR is equipped with superior passive safety features with its underground construction , which also greatly increases its security and physical protection .
Furthermore , the VHTR offers high thermal efficiency , while retaining the capability of hydrogen production and utilization in heat process applications .
Finally , the VHTR also provides high proliferation resistance , which prevents the production of new nuclear weapons , maintaining peace in the world .
However , many controversies have emerged over the development of nuclear reactors because of fear of nuclear leakage and accident .
Considering the fact that global warming has becoming an increasingly serious problem nowadays , the development of nuclear power is quite necessary .
But if it is to figure in the energy equation , it will need to be cheaper , cleaner and safer " , .
However , compared with VHTR , the sodium-cooled fast reactor ( SFR ) has more advantages and should be chosen as a main type of reactor in the future .
Furthermore , the closed fuel of SFR can utilize almost all the energy provided by the fuels and the recovery and recycle of the actinides in SFR can reach about 99.9 % , which indicate the high efficiency of SFR .
Although the sodium is radioactive and easily has chemical reaction with water and air , the self-activated shutdown system of SFR has largely reduced the possibilities of the leakage of sodium .
More importantly , an extra loop which is called secondary system acts as a buffer in case of reactions between the sodium and water ( Roglans , Allen & Line , 2002 ) .
Another argument advanced by opponents of SFR is that it can only produce electricity and it has shown little promise of becoming an economical reactor so far ( ) .
It is true that the VHTR can produce not only electricity but also hydrogen ; however , the electricity is more widely used than hydrogen nowadays .
Actually , the hydrogen energy system is not very matured because of the limited technology .
All of these facts show that the SFR is more economical and flexible than VHTR .
On the contrary , the SFR system has more advantages over VHTR on its safety , efficiency and costs , which make the SFR a promising reactor .
The accident resulted in a total of 101 deaths and caused 88 injuries .
The cause of the accident was due to a broken wheel that led to the derailment of the entire train ( 1998 ) .
Further probing into the accident revealed that although the wheels were not fully tested and commissioned , the wheels were already in service .
Furthermore , in-depth investigations revealed that before the night of the accident , the maintenance crew did not carry out their maintenance jobs properly .
Therefore , if a psychologist had been in place during the designing , testing and maintenance phase , the chance of the accident happening would have been minimal .
From the feedback they received from customers , the company said that passengers could hear loud vibrations and dinnerware and glasses were moving across the table when the train was moving at cruising speed ( ) .Thus , the engineers were tasked to come up with a new design to solve problem .
The engineers claimed that they have superior technical knowledge and by following the specifications on the datasheets closely , there would unlikely be any mistakes in the design . Hence , minimal testing was required .
During the testing phase , the psychologist would have proposed that the engineers further test the wheel at a much higher speed , observe problems the wheels might develop under wear and tear conditions .
He would also have said that since there were no testing facilities present , the engineers could have brought the wheel out to other countries to run the required tests .
Furthermore , Fraunhofer Institute told the company that it is possible that the wheels would fail earlier than expected ( 09 ) .
Yet , no actions were taken by the company to replace the failing wheels .
To ensure that the wheels were replaced , the psychologist , in this case , would have constantly reminded the engineers to correct the errors present on the wheels .
The company claimed that the maintenance crew had many years of experience in inspection and repairing of wheels . Therefore , they were the " experts " in that area and whatever they said could be fully trusted .
Yet , the maintenance crew did not bother to repair or replace the wheel , assuming that it would only cause discomfort throughout the journey ( ) .
Just imagine that there may have been relatives or friends of the crew seating in the train that the crew assumed to be safe . In the end , an accident happened , and the lives of those they knew were gone .
Thus , if a psychologist was included during the designing , testing and maintenance phase , the chance of the accident occurring would have been very minimal as the psychologist would have helped ensure that the design and testing of the wheels complied to the standards set by the organization .
During the maintenance phase , the psychologist would have advised the maintenance crew to be more serious in their . The safety of many lives depended on . They should not have been complacent just because they had many years of experience .
To end , I can say that with the inclusion of a psychologist , the chance of the accident happening would have been very minimal .
