In order to overcome the energy shortage situation today , human beings have tried many ways to explore new kinds of energy , for instance , natural energy which includes wind energy and water energy .
Therefore , scientists and publics have suggested that we can develop one kind of energy which can produce high energy efficiently , and that kind of energy is known as nuclear energy .
In my point of view , using nuclear energy is the right way to meet today 's increasing energy demand , due to its high efficiency and environmental emission .
There are several disadvantages of using nuclear energy : The funds paid on developing this technology is high , the time taking to explore the technology is long and there exists dangers which can actually be solved .
Secondly , if we do not use nuclear energy , it will cause a serious shortage of fuel , which will lead to the increase the price of electricity .
Thirdly , if we keep using normal fuel energy instead of nuclear energy , it will weaken the quality of the gas , since it will emit green house gases . In order to deal with global warming , governments will pay a lot of money .
Here it is suitable to make an assumption . If the time used to explore this technology is fixed , according to the conclusion reached in the previous paragraph , it is easy to know that if we explore the nuclear energy earlier , we can save more money and save more resources .
Moreover , human beings now can not find a kind of ideal energy to replace nuclear energy .
It is true that dangers still exist , however , with the development of the technology , it is desirable that those dangers could be overcome .
To sum up , the Generation IV reactors is a trend of the 21st century . It will make a great improvement and progress for our life .
with the increasing demand of energy , only nuclear energy is the correct choice as it has so many advantages as compared with other kinds of energies .
Its high efficiency is the most attractive . The environmental emission makes it better for human beings .
Even though there are shortages that still exist , it is believed that with the development of the technology , all the problems will be solved and all the difficulties can be overcome .
There is a relationship between psychology and design process which can prevent accidents from happening .
Here is an example of a real major industrial accident . The world 's deadliest high-speed train accident , which occurred on 3rd June 1998 , in Eschede , Germany .
The steel tire on the wheel broke and peeled away from the wheel , penetrating into the floor of the train .
The train was totally damaged after hitting a bridge support .
The proximate causes were the disintegration of the wheel rim and the failure to stop the train after the wheel had delaminated .
If the wheel did not crack , no metal would have been embedded into the train and the derailment of the train would not have happened .
Other than that , if the train had been stopped immediately when the wheel had disintegrated , the disaster might not have occurred and countless lives would have been saved .
Unfortunately , no one pulled the emergency brake during the emergency condition .
All these show that decision-making and human action played an important part in the cause of the accident besides component failure .
Design errors in socio-technical system have really made a significant difference in their reliability and safe operation .
However , it is better to use the path of feed-forward control of , , to do a correct original system design right from the beginning .
To improve design safety , a scientist is needed .
Apart from this , a scientist may also be called upon to help evaluate the prototype by using simulation techniques .
" The reasonable person adapts himself to the world : the unreasonable one persists in trying to adapt the world to himself .
" ( ) .
The conception of engineering psychology was first brought out during the First World War , when people found that the efficiency of machines was reduced sharply when they were operated by women instead of men ( these machines were designed for men and not women ) .
However it is hard to say whether we can solve the engineering problems by simply improving the psychological problems , since for many engineering incidences the technical problems had occupied an overwhelming part .
Hence in this essay I will argue about the proportion of psychological problems and technological problems during engineering incidences and give a conclusion from my own view .
Based on the report provided by Reason ( 1990 ) , 92 % of all nuclear utility accidents between 1983-1984 were caused by people and only 8 % of them were cause by control room operators .
For instance , there were two serious incidences which are cited frequently in technical literature .
They happened in Three Mile Island and Chernobyl .
The failure for the first one included operators who were unprepared to handle serious accident due to the lack of training . Complex and confusing operating procedures led to the operators ' incorrect action . There were problem within the Nuclear Regulatory Commission .
The first factor relates to people 's misunderstanding of effects of their actions on the whole system . The second factor is a kind of persistent action which is made by a small and cohesive group in the process of pursuing an unsuitable aim .
What is the most important evidence for his theories is that after realizing these engineering psychology problems , quite a lot of America 's nuclear institutes began to train their staff in a psychology-related way , which indeed prevented the nuclear accidents from happening again till now .
Although there is nuclear incidences have not happened in recent years , it is too biased to say that the engineering psychology can solve the problems by itself .
One saying about the cause of Chernobyl disaster is the problem in peculiarities of physics and the construction of the reactor ( ) .
These problems definitely can not be solved from psychological view since even we had solved all human-related problems , these defects of system are still vital .
However , the human-factor has again been considered as the main cause to the reactor design by IAEA 's 1986 analysis ( ) .
To simply solve one of them will contribute nothing to the problem .
