( Bernhard , 2006 . If people do not like using the product , the product is a failure .
Design engineers always overestimate the ability of users ; the design may not give sufficient help to operators
( Bernhard , 2006 . Three Mile Island 's tragic consequence was caused by inadequate structure design .
When the radioactive gas and coolant leaked , the valve should have been closed immediately in order to prevent radioactive materials draining away .
The operator thought that the valve has been closed , but there was no instrument showing the position of the valve
( . Then this accident happened .
If designers had designed an instrument to show the process of cooling circuit , then operators would have known that the valve had not been closed , and this disaster would have been prevented .
