People hardly link engineering problems with psychology since the previous one belongs to pure technology problems while the latter one is a branch of social science .
However , with time , psychology is gradually applied in various fields , including law , medicine , architecture , design and so on .
People nowadays have fierce controversy over the use of nuclear power due to the appalling nuclear accidents which occurred at Three Mile island and Chernobyl , or even the recent nuclear accident at Sellafield , England .
These accidents destroy cities , take people 's lives and leave many deadly post-effects for future decades .
Therefore , safety becomes the main concern when people choose to continue using nuclear power .
Even though SCWR has not been tested yet , it is proved to have less possibility of causing nuclear accidents as has happened before ; it is easier to implement compared to other generation VI reactors , and it has a relatively high thermal efficiency which makes its long-term cost relatively low .
The nuclear accident at Chernobyl was mainly because the nuclear plant utilized positive void coefficient of reactivity , causing it impossible to stop the working process when things went wrong .
( Bodansky , 2004 ) On the contrary , SCWR uses negative void coefficient instead , which could effectively reduce the possibility of this kind of fatal accident ( U.S DOE 2002 ) .
The other is supercritical fossil fuel fired boilers , which is also in use now ( Idaho National Laboratory , 2007 ) .
To sum up , although there exists disagreement of the use of SCWR due to its issue of reliability and safety , SCWR is worthy for further research because it is based on two current technologies , which increases its reliability , and its design principle improves its thermal efficiency compared to LWR and reduce the possibility of causing nuclear accidents .
Hopefully , SCWR could be better improved on current problems in future development .
Given the memories of the two accidents which happened in 1979 at Three Mile Island in Pennsylvania and in 1986 at Chernobyl of Ukraine , some people may still have not recovered from the great horror when they hear nuclear power .
On the one hand , people are facing the challenge of energy shortage because fossil fuels are nonrenewable .
On the other hand , burning fossil fuels produces the " green gases " such as carbon dioxide that have resulted in serious problems like global warming .
One is that the reactor and the gas turbine system are separated from the hydrogen production plant , which is aimed at isolating the hydrogen plant from the reactor system during the abnormal events of the hydrogen production plant .
To conclude , it should be evident that the arguments against the safety and cost of VHTR are invalid .
Since VHTR uses helium as a coolant , the research of the materials for VHTR is also ongoing , and also there are unique designs for VHTR , the safety of VHTR would be enhanced a lot .
Furthermore , VHTR produces hydrogen as future fuel , which is environmentally-friendly and can effectively solve the energy shortage as well .
Therefore , VHTR is a promising and practical form of power .
Firstly , the VHTR has a core outlet temperature of about 1000 degrees Celsius this high temperature increases the efficiency of the reactor and also enables us to use it for applications such as hydrogen production ( VHTR , Generation IV technology forum ) .
The hydrogen produced can be used in automobiles , which in turn help decrease the carbon emissions by 30 % when compared to modern day diesel engines ( Ewing Jack,September 2009
This is the same material which is being used in the Japanese , South African and Chinese high temperature test reactors ( Corwin Bill,2003 . ) and has proven to be very successful .
The VHTR is designed to operate on a pebble bed core in which the fuel is coated with silicon carbide which ensures that the radioactive fissile material never leaves fuel spheres or pebbles ( Kadak.C.Andrew ) ) .
The reactor is helium cooled and uses graphite moderated core , which takes advantage of the fact that the helium coolant is inert and has no reactivity effects and that graphite has a high thermal inertia and is stable at high temperatures ( VHTR , Idaho National Laboratory ) .Also , any waste produced goes directly to the repository and this means an additional waste recycling process can be avoided ( Butler , , 2004 ) .Thus , in case of any failure the damage does not spread to the surrounding regions but is contained within the plant itself .
Lastly , most of the technology involved in the VHTR is already in its development phase and the reactor can be shelled out as early as 2020 ( Butler , , 2004 ) .
There was a train disaster which occurred on the 3rd of June 1998 near a small town in Lower Saxony , Germany .
Such a super fast , state-of-the-art Inter Express trains of German Railways rolled out of the tracks and split in two , due to a bridge falling onto the train .
It resulted in 101 dying and 88 being injured .
Although there were many causes to be pointed out for this train accident , I think the biggest cause is that no one was aware of the importance of the use of psychology during the design process .
It was reported that the direct cause was a wheel with a composite construction which is relatively common on light railway transit vehicles , but are unique to ICE 884 in high speed trains which replaced the original wheel .
It can not be denied that this is a human mistake which can be avoided by applying psychology .
Psychology can make engineers aware that they are not only normal persons , but are also professionals .
If they understand that , I believe that the engineers would not have used those composite construction wheels and used wheels which had not been checked properly and approved .
Observing the pictures which recorded the scene of accident , there was at least one car was detached from its underframe .
If designers considered more about that for the high-speed trains must take into account the forces to be absorbed in the event of the vehicle being in a collision , there would not be so many people who were thrown through the air
Considering only the construction of trains is not enough , the environmental element can affect the result as well .
The designers never anticipated that a bridge which was expected for lightly use , demanded a less substantial structure than if it were to carry a major truck load . .
They completely ignored environmental elements which was the speed and weight of the train passing under the bridge which resulted in such a horrible disaster .
To sum up , any design process can minimize a probability of danger , even can be avoided by applying psychology .
Because all design processes are to fulfill needs of human ; and all products are produced by humans .
Therefore , anything as long as it is people-oriented will get the biggest benefits .
Of course , avoiding an accident is the biggest benefit to people .
The Chernobyl accident that happened on 26 April 1986 , has led everyone to realize the damages and consequences that we might face when we build a nuclear power plant .
The six nuclear reactors are not only sustainable and economically viable solutions ; they are also a safe and reliable source of energy .
Among the six concepts of nuclear reactors , the Very High Temperature Reactor , ( VHTR ) and the Gas Cooled Fast Reactor , ( GCFR ) are quite similar , but the Gas Cooled Fast Reactor has more benefits than VHTR in terms of performance , sustainability and cost .
[ GCFR is a concept which uses the reference design of VHTR , thus it is also a reactor of high performance .
Since GCFR operates at 850 degrees Celsius , there are more choices of materials that can be used in the construction of GCFR .
[ Idaho National Laboratory , 2002 ] Because GCFR operates at a lower temperature as compared to the VTHR , therefore the materials used for construction is cheaper and there are more choices of material available .
[ , 2009 ] The reduction of radioactive waste uses processes called pryo-chemical or hydrometallurgical .
[ Commissariat Ã  l'energie atomique , 2007 ] With this there is a great reduction of nuclear waste , and money can be saved to build a storage site for nuclear waste .
Therefore , GCFR not only can have efficient energy conversion with the current design but also has an economically beneficial outcome .
In conclusion , although the there are several advantages of the VHTR however there are factors that makes it difficult to implement it as it is more expensive and limited by choices of construction materials as compared with the GCFR .
Nonetheless , the decision to implement the reactors still falls in the hands of the countries that are highly interested as the budget for every country is different .
Nowadays , since fossil fuel is running out at a very high rate , people are seeking another alternative energy resource to replace the traditional fossil fuel resources , which have been used by humans for hundreds of years .
However , the public is very concerned about the safe operation of nuclear reactors .
This is because once a nuclear reactor accident happens , it would be a huge disaster to both the creatures and the environment within that area .
A very famous accident , which is also used by the public to oppose building nuclear reactors , is the accident at Chernobyl which happened on 26 April 1986 .
Moreover , according to the estimation , there would be thousands of people dying from cancer in the next forty years .
Another famous example is the accident which happened at the nuclear power station at Three Mile Island in Pennsylvania on 28 March 1979 .
Furthermore , as the technology has improved so much , even if an accident happens , the damage is probably not that big .
For example , in the Three Mile Island accident , nobody was killed or injured .
Besides safety , the economy is also a very important aspect which people should take into consideration .
However , since we can eliminate the need for an intermediate heat transport circuit in lead-cooled fast reactors , and lead is relatively cheap when compared with other materials used in other fast reactors , a large part of cost would be saved through this .
The Chernobyl explosion is one example showing the seriousness of those dangers .
The Chernobyl accident , which happened in 1986 , was a nuclear reactor accident .
Because of that , the safety of engineering design is very important .
at present , most design teams use the safety laws and rules as their gatekeeper and thinks that it is enough .
However , some psychologists argue that those rules are not enough as all the procedures are carried out by humans , there is the possibillity that a human error may occur .
Therefore psychologists are necessary , to be involved in the design process to detect the human error and to be the new gate keeper of engineering design .
The Chernobyl accident can be a good example to see how the use of psychology helps to prevent the accident .
However , though with such rules , accidents still happen
This of course implies some imperfections in terms of safety .
( Wilpert , 2006 ) Those human factors mainly include the irresponsibility of operators and human error during the design process .
Chances are this accident may not have happened .
To follow up , some designers may also consider that a team member without strong technical background may become a disturbance during work or decrease the efficiency of the team .
Therefore they may cause more problems than they can solve .
However , in present engineering groups , team members are always from different specialities .
This is because today 's design requires consideration from all aspects .
A team with single specialities can not satisfy such requirements and therefore will lose the ability to compete with others .
Considering all those facts , a psychologist can never be a disturbance in the team .
Rather , the presence of a psychologist in a team can help the members work at their optimum and avoid the chance of having human error in the design process .
By doing this , hopefully there will be chances to prevent accidents because of misuse caused by the misunderstanding of instructions , like the operator in the Chernobyl accident .
However , considering the serious results of Chernobyl accidents and other engineering accidents , such wondering is of no use .
In conclusion , psychologists may become new gatekeepers of engineering design process by helping correct the human error in design process and increase team efficiency .
And the increase in safety will make people enjoy the benefits of engineering design products much better .
Some insist that insights can be gained when analyzing design process using psychological approaches .
No matter what the designers are to work on , complex systems or everyday products , psychology is helpful to gain insights of problems that may be encountered or to prevent undesirable accidents .
For everyday products design , it is quite understandable that if the technical configurations are similar for all , psychology could help designers make a difference by considering making improvements that are more user-friendly in design .
More impactful consequences of not applying psychology in design are that serious failures can happen in complex projects and systems hence causing loss of life .
For instance , the collapse of Nicoll Highway , two stretches of highway road linked by Merdeka Bridge , located in the Central Region of Singapore ( Vernon , 2000 ) , could have been prevented if psychological approaches had been adopted in the design and construction process .
For the Nicoll Highway incident , some argue that it was merely constrained by technology and the only cause was an engineering problem .
While it is true that the restrictions set by technology limitations are a direct cause for the engineering failure , the application of psychology could help to overcome the negative effects of technology difficulties .
Numerous journals written by engineers and professionals analyzing this disaster were all very absorbed by civil engineering details and theories after the Nicoll Highway collapsed , but the disaster was concluded to be unexpected as technology should have been sufficient for this construction project ( Thansnanipan & Aung , 2005 ) .
This means that it is not a shortcoming in technology that necessarily led to engineering failure , but a lack of psychological analysis .
When some were arguing for objective difficulties in technology , it was admitted by the main contractor that the major cause is the overload of temporary works and their low quality ( New Civil Engineer , 2005 ) .
The contractor admitted that they had foreseen the potential problems that might arise due to overloading , but they somehow still did not pay enough attention and continued with it .
The primary goals being to improve nuclear safety , efficient thermal performance and reduce cost .
Many reactor designs are being considered to meet the generation IV goals of today .
Two of the generation IV reactors called Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor and Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor are highly appreciated and accepted in modern nuclear power plant systems .
In terms of performance , security and cost cost , both reactors are well designed .
( M.J. Lineberry & T.R. Allen , 2002 ) compared to the Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor , Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor has the thermal efficiency about 48 % , which is generally higher than sodium-cooled fast reactor .
van Rooijen , 2009 ) In addition , under the high performance , both reactors need to work under high temperature .
In thermal performance , both reactors have good features especially for energy conversion however , the Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor may have additional advantages .
Then , it is a primary system that operates near atmospheric pressure .
Meanwhile , the Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor is based on safety countermeasures for self-controlled shutdown function and controlling function .
( M.J. Lineberry & T.R. Allen , 2002 ) The Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor , not only includes a basic self safety control functions but also has many safety approaches applied to the system to make it work safely under high temperature with additional safety devices being added to the equipment .
Recent research and development with in depth studies for safety shows that , , the Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor system has through experiment demonstrated its security aspect .
Newton & P.J. Smith , 2007 ) Hence , it is safer when it works properly .
Furthermore , in terms of cost , the Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor was economical with the use of high burn-up fuels .
It uses advanced materials and innovative design options to reduce power plant capital cost and lower operating cost .
However , the Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor is also well designed especially for waste recycling ; GFR tries to minimize the release of gaseous and liquid effluents to the environment .
GFR systems are designed to allow for self-treatment by applying fuel manufacturing operations .
In conclusion , both the Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor and the Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor achieve generation IV primary goal to satisfy the requirement of energy .
The Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor works with good thermal efficiency under a lower temperature when compared to the Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor .
Moreover , it is designed well in terms of safety and cost .
Similarly , the GFR system offers significant potential to advance generation IV sustainability goals through its thermal efficiency , direct energy conversion , safety arrangement and proper cost .
Over all , the Gas-Cooled Fast Reactor has advantages over The Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor with respect to thermal efficiency , security and cost .
According to The Cambridge Advanced Learner 's Dictionary , the word " accident " means something bad which happens that is not expected or intended , and which often damages something or injures someone .
Let us have a quick scan through one of the world 's deadliest high-speed train accidents- the Eschede train disaster , which had a death toll of 101 .
Post accident investigation has shown that the main factors that contributed to this severe train accident was the wheel design of the train , maintenance of the train , and failure to stop the train .
Could this accident have probably been prevented with the usage of psychology as proposed by Bernhard Wilpert in " Psychology and design processes " ?
Psychology is the study of the behavior of the human mind .
In most accidents , the main causes are errors in human judgments or simply known as a human problem .
For example , the faulty design of the " wheel-tire " in the Eschede incident .
As Wilpert mentioned in his article , humans can make mistakes .
Psychologists might make mistakes but at least they can lower the probability of errors caused by human 's irresponsible acts or carelessness .
Besides this , it has been found that accidents are usually caused by chain reactions of a series of factors according to Heinrich Domino theory .
In the case of the Eschede train accident for instance , if the wheel of the train was designed in a better way or well maintained , or if the train could be stopped at the right moment before the crash , the accident could probably have been avoided .
But on the other hand , not all factors are within the control of human capability .
Bad weather conditions , earthquake , are all hard to predict .
It is quite true that these factors are beyond human control and we can not prevent them from happening .
All we have to do is take all the necessary steps and precautionary methods to prevent these " uncontrollable " factors from triggering an accident .
As mentioned in the very first paragraph , accident are usually unexpected .
Moments before the accident of Eschede , one of the passengers on the train had noticed that the tire on a wheel broke and peeled away from the wheel and punctured the floor of the train .
He informed the conductor about what he saw but the conductor insisted on further investigating the incident and thus refused to pull the emergency brake .
Psychologically , the conductor did not want to get into trouble as pulling the emergency brake would definitely have caused much hassle .
If he chose to give safety the most priority , he would have pulled the emergency brake and the accident could probably have been prevented .
However , when it come to an emergency , the most important thing is often an individuals ability to react rationally to resolve the problem .
The more one gets trained , the more readily he is able to face an emergency .
Finally , the approach of psychological knowledge can prevent or at least reduce the probability of accidents occurring .
Studies of human behavior , stages of an accident , investigation into industrial accident , together with some necessary and suitable psychological approaches would definitely help in minimizing the occurring of severe accidents , especially those that are due to errors in human judgement .
The drastic industrial development and advancement in science and technology has led to the rising energy demand .
The invention of Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) is one of the latest Generation VI nuclear reactors that have high potential to replace coal and fuel as an energy source .
Nonetheless , debate on the using of this nuclear reactor has become a hot issue today due to the negative effects that would be brought to humans as well as other living organisms on the earth .
First and foremost , The Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) has a good security system and is safe to be used . Much has been said about the danger of using nuclear reactors as power generators such as emission and leakage of radioactive waste and explosion of nuclear reactor , where Chernobyl and Three Mile Island emerge to be famous for that reason .
Furthermore , this reactor 's pressure vessel is incorporated a core arrangement with three passes to avoid the overheating effect and thus , minimizing the probability of the explosion of SWCR .
Moreover , the cost of construction of The Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) and cost of its power output are cheap and reasonable . It is undeniable that uranium oxide , the main input for SWCR , and the construction materials used are expensive .
Although uranium oxide is expensive , it has a very long life , about 24000 years .
Last but not least , The Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) has high efficiency in term of electricity and power generation . According to Nuclear Engineering and Design ( 2007 ) , The Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) promises to have high thermal efficiencies of approximately 45 % , which can generate about 1,700 MW of thermal energy per hour .
Further researches have shown that The Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) can achieve great safety by its design modification , lower and reasonable cost of its construction and power generation and has high efficiency in terms of electricity and power generation .
Therefore , further research and development funding for the Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) should be provided as it stands in good stead to become the future 's power generator in the near future .
Most scientists have agreed that we have to reduce the emission of green house gases as the impact of global warming becomes more serious .
Nuclear power will not produce the green house gases and it will provide vast amounts of energy .
However , The U.S gave up building reactors since 1979 because of the defects of nuclear power and as the cost of a reactor was high , since there was no appropriate coolant for reactors and as the waste recycling system was not perfect .
Therefore , it sparked a significant controversy of whether the nuclear power should be reconsidered .
Firstly , SCWR is still facing a financial problem .
If the government uses this money to build more fossil reactors , the increasing fossil reactor plants will help the situation of lack of energy .
It is true that the initial cost of building a fossil plant is low , but the long-term costs which keeping it working are high says PBMR Company international marketing manager Gert Claassen .
Furthermore , the SCWR reactor 's efficiency and relatively simple design , would be cheaper to build and run than normal reactors .
Secondly , it is too difficult to find an appropriate coolant for nuclear reactor .
Thirdly , people are worrying about the waste of nuclear power , because the waste of reactor is normally radioactive .
Therefore , this waste are not radioactive and it is much safer compared with the wastes of previous of reactors .
Moreover , SCWR has built a system for water purification through supercritical oxidation .
Therefore , the SCWR is feasible and reliable .
For the public , the problem of global warming and other environmental problems caused by emissions of fossil fuel will be eliminated .
Politically , the nuclear power will maintain their energy source independence and reduce the conflicts of energy possessing .
To engineers and scientists , the applications of nuclear reactors would encourage them to find more efficient way to generate energy from reactors and the improve the safety of reactors in case of any accidents .
The question of whether we should have nuclear power plants as an energy resource is controversial .
People stand against it as they have little knowledge about the nuclear power plant .
Cost , safety and performance are three major aspects of opposition to this technology ; nevertheless , there is still an unyielding need to support further research and development funding for VHTR .
Still , in point of fact , nuclear power plants can reduce the expenditure in producing more energy in the long run .
compared to conventional plants , VHTR can bring out 50 % more electricity from the same amount of fuel .
Since that VHTR uses a lower amount of fuel to produce higher amounts of energy , it is much more economic than other power plants regardless of the start up cost , as the start-up cost can be compensated in the long run .
Therefore , when sources of conventional plants are severely depleted , its cost will soar up and become uneconomical ; on the other hand , VHTR uses half the amount of fuel to produce an equal amount of energy , hence it can last longer .
Safety of a nuclear plant is the issue that concerns the public the most .
It raised public 's uncertainty about the safety of developing new nuclear power plants .
VHTR is coated with a layer of graphite which can be used to slow down neutrons in order to control the nuclear chain reaction and it is covered with an ultra hard ceramic layer .
Furthermore , it uses helium , an inert gas as a coolant .
Therefore it can avoid any radioactive material from escaping if an accident happens .
Moreover , a back-up emergency core cooling system ( ECCS ) has been designed .
ECCS can remove excess heat and avoid damage to power plants in emergency situations , such as terrorism .
In addition , VHTR would be able to function without the need to reprocess plutonium waste .
This would be able to prevent the creation of nuclear power weapons as plutonium is an ingredient to produce advanced nuclear weapons .
People assume that VHTR has lower performance when compared to other kinds of Generation IV power sources .
This gives people a wrong assumption that VHTR .
Furthermore , VHTR is designed to efficiently produce both electricity and hydrogen at the same time .
Likewise , VHTR is being designed with adequate safety precautions to prevent a tragedy from happening .
It has better performance as well since it has high efficiency and both electricity and hydrogen as its reactive product .
Consequently , more research and development funding should be given to VHTR .
As society develops rapidly , the demand for energy also increases in tandem .
SFR is basically the use of sodium as a coolant to produce nuclear energy .
cost wise , building a SFR is estimated at US $ 610 million , while the VHTR would cost US $ 610 millionU.S .
Therefore , in the long run , the VHTR is more economical in producing a large amount of energy .
Some people also say that the efficiency of the SFR is about fifty percent at a temperature of 500 centigrade degrees .
It is higher than the VHTR which is about forty percent at 500 centigrade degrees ( , 2009 ) .
For the SFR 500 centigrade degrees is the suitable working temperature , which means the maximum efficiency for it is fifty percent .
However , for VHTR , the suitable working temperature is about 1500 centigrade degrees .
At such a temperature , the efficiency of the VHTR is about 65 percent , which is much higher than the SFR ( ) .
Under the same standard , we can clearly see that the efficiency of the VHTR is better .
What we should do is to plan what we should do when bad things happen .
Besides that , it can also harm human beings .
Even though the coolant leaks out , it will not do any harm to the environment and human beings .
To conclude , the initial cost of VHTR is higher , but in the long run its cost is much lower .
By considering the cost , efficiency and safety factors , we can judge that a very high temperature is the better choice in theong run .
With the speedy development throughout the whole world , the rise in energy needs becomes an unavoidable problem .
In order to satisfy the needs , the generation IV reactor concept has been brought forward for further research and the utilization of nuclear power , and the Very High Temperature Reactor [ VHTR ] , which uses a graphite-moderated nuclear reactor with a once-through uranium fuel cycle under an outlet temperature of 1000 Â° C , is one such concept .
However , even before VHTR has been made use of , the public has begun to debate whether this concept can do more good than harm .
Although quite a number of people have no faith in the concept and provide some reasons , there exist solid evidences to show that the VHTR is worth developing and can benefit the society .
As they state , in order to generate as much electricity as it expels in the U.S. every day , almost 400 nuclear power plants should be constructed and utilized .
The great discrepancy threatens VHTR 's development .
In fact , this analysis is due to a mis-illustration .
One fact that needs to be clarified is that the opponents misuse the capacity of the conventional plants rather than that of VHTR .
Scientists suggest that the new generation reactor can squeeze 50 % more electricity from the same amount of fuel when compared with the conventional plants .
Instead , it should always be a combination of complex methods .
In that case , whether VHTR can fulfil one country or even the global needs of electricity is not of concerned .
As long as the concept is feasible and is better than the old ones , VHTR deserves further research and thus can bring more advantage to the society .
In addition , opponents are also concerned about the safety of the reactor especially when they recall the Chernobyl nuclear accident .
The great graphite and the single-phase , inert helium coolant can not react .
This can to a great extent ensure its safety during its reaction .
On the other hand , the corresponding design of the constructions of the nuclear power plants can prevent nuclear leaks even when disasters occur .
Simultaneously , the system will also bring about a safe environment .
In that case , we can safely draw the conclusion that VHTR is worth further research and development .
July 17 , 1981 in Kansas City , Missouri , United States , while dozens of people were gathering on the walkway in Hyatt Regency Crown Centre and seeing a dance contest , the walkway collapsed and caused 114 people to die and 200 to be injured .
After the accident was investigated into , the main cause of the accident was a significant change in the design of the walkway .
The original design by Jack D. Gillum was using a set of steel tie rods to suspend the two walkways to the ceiling , but the contractor proposed to use two separate tie rods : one connected one walkway to the ceiling , and the other connected the two walkways .
Jack D. Gillum and associates did not calculate the alternate plan before they designed it on paper .
( )
In order to prevent such accidents from happening , psychology should be introduced to the design process .
For example , cognitive psychology focuses on ways to improve memory and how to increase decision-making accuracy and social psychology is interested in the impact that social environment and interaction has on attitudes and behaviors ( Kendra , V.W .
For instance , if we introduce psychology to the case above , then the designer and the contractor would have communicated well ; so that the accidents would not happen .
The new generation reactors are planning to run at very high temperatures or high pressures ( Butler , D. ( 2004 , ) .
The more complex the process is , the more difficult to predict the problems .
Sometimes only after the process is implemented , will the problems be known. .
For example , the " Prestige " oil spill was mainly caused by the rainstorm .
Prestige carried 77,000 tons of heavy fuel oil and was traveling on the sea near Spain when it met rainstorm .
Finally the tanker sank and caused an oil spill ( ] ) .
Psychology only can deal with human error , not the other factors .
It can not prevent all the accidents , as accidents are not only caused by human errors and as for some new designs , they must attempt to assess where problems are likely to occur .
On the 28th of January , 1986 , the US Space Shuttle Challenger exploded 73 seconds after launch , killing the entire crew .
In other words , not only the technical factors , but also the human factors caused this disaster to occur
Actually , from the time it was first scheduled to lift off on January 22nd , to when it was finally launched on the 28th of January , liftoff was delayed several times for various reasons .
Well , it is true that the errors can not be prevented completely ; nevertheless , we should try our best to reduce the risk to the least level one that we can accept .
Apparently , the condition of The Challenger was not what we can accept as safe .
Secondly , had the decision-making system been better , the tragedy could have been avoided .
Furthermore , they also had policy failure in terms of competitive bidding for manufacturing companies and defects in the supervision system .
Although NASA have had to face the pressure from the public and from politicians , they should have been aware of the consequences of the failure , .
The NASA officials seemed neither to have been warned adequately of the danger of a launch in cold weather , nor be told emphatically enough the need of redesigning the O-rings .
Besides , the warning of an air blast from a Boeing 757 aircraft was also ignored before the liftoff .
Communication did not flow effectively , which indirectly led to the tragedy happening .
As discussed above , the Challenger disaster 's causes lies not only in the technical factors , but also on the human factors .
Though it was an indirect cause , its influence is so large that it was more important than the technical factor .
Psychology in design processes , whose significance has been showed in this accident , should be paid more attention to in future engineering design .
Only in this way , can the safety of projects be improved efficiently and be guaranteed .
There has been a debate between two Generation Four reactors , the Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) and the Supercritical Water Reactor ( SCWR ) , as to which reactor has superior performance .
On the one hand , engineers use the most advanced technology and concept to design the VHTR .
On the other hand , the technology applied on the SCWR is developed from conventional technology of an older type of nuclear reactor , Light Water Reactor ( LWR ) .
The supporters of VHTR attack SCWR for its " obsolete " technology and its incapability of generating Hydrogen as a co-product of electrcity .
When people compare the two types of reactors , they tend to focus on the temperature at which reactors operates .
As a result , a misleading conception arises , which is that the VHTR works much more efficiently than the SCWR .
These two energy states of neutrons are closely related the fusion of two fuels , U235 and Np237 .
For people who are obssesed with the VHTR , one main reason would be it allows an easy way to generate a clean natural energy , Hydrogen .
Furthermore , using Hydrogen , which has just begun developing and is far from matured , electricity has been with human beings for over a hundred years .
The technology of electricity can be found everywhere and big automobile manufacturers have started to discuss the possibility of replacing fossil-fuel-powered cars with electricity-powered ones .
The SCWR is built of low-cost electricity .
In addition , the two technologies needed to build the SCWR are already at hand , which are widely-employed by current Generatioon Three LWRs .
Unlike the VHTR which uses rare gas Helium as a coolant , the SCWR simply uses water to cool down the system .
As a result , the SCWR costs much less to build and greatly simplifies the nuclear plant .
In conclusion , the most advanced technologies may not be suitable in a certain condition .
The SCWR has proven itself to be more capable at both high performance and low cost .
In this sense , the SCWR is a better nuclear reactor compared to the VHTR for our future .
Competitive costs and financial risks of nuclear energy systems are constantly being compared .
The current race to develop the best reactor for use is still questionable as all the reactors have their own strengths and weaknesses .
At the turn of the millennium , the rising of Asian countries such as China and India intensified the competition for energy .
In 2007 , China consumed a third as much oil as the United States , which burns a quarter of the world 's oil every day .
New York Times ) By 2030 , China and India together will import as much oil as the United States and Japan today .
( Pachauri , 2007 ) Hence , fossil fuels are not a viable means to meet the increasing demand of energy .
Acknowledging the need of nuclear power to meet the world 's energy appetite , several countries have formed the Generation IV International Forum ( GIF ) to research the possible nuclear technologies and to mitigate the risks posed by them .
Better heat transfer also allows the coolant to have a slower flow rate of the coolant , thus saving cost by using smaller pumps and piping .
Compared to the SCWR , the sodium can be kept at normal atmospheric pressure .
Also , the reactor core is at a lower temperature , and thus relatively easier to manage .
Moving on to the cost , SCWR does offer much savings .
Consequently , the research could be focused towards developing irradiation resistant materials to be used for the reactor .
Research into fuel cycle and physically stronger and more radiation resistant structural materials would minimise the operating costs with improved operations and performance .
Also , with the support of countries such as Japan , France , and Russia , the cost of research is shared .
Finally , keeping nuclear-enriched materials at a high temperature would prevent them from being stolen and used as weapons by terrorists .
Though the deployment cost is high at present , the burden will be shared by the many countries supporting the technology .
Facing the issues of rising oil prices and the long term availability of fossil fuels , governments are now rethinking their national energy strategies .
In recent years , despite the contentious debate of using nuclear power to meet our ever-increasing energy needs , the world has started to consider nuclear energy as a future fuel source which is believed to more environmentally friendly compared to fossil fuels .
Hence , late in 2002 , Generation IV International Forum ( GIF ) announced the selection of six reactor technologies which they believe represented the future shape of nuclear energy .
These were selected on the basis of being a clean , safe and cost-effective means of meeting increased energy demands on a sustainable basis , while being resistant to usage of materials for weapons proliferation and secure from terrorist attacks ( US Department of Energy , 2009 ) .
However , this may be an unfounded concern in years to come when we consider the fact that the Korean and the US governments have worked for the past three years on developing and validating advanced computational methods for simulating LOCA in a VHTR , in an attempt to prevent such an accident from happening ( Chang , 2006 ) .
The fuel pebbles used in VHTR are also very 'durable ' in the sense that it is very difficult to extract the trapped fission products inside which render it a less favorable choice as a nuclear weapon .
VHTR also adopts a passive safety feature in which in the event of an emergency , does not require operator 's action to shutdown the plant safely .
The concern of graphite being an easily-combustible material is also addressed by experimental results that have shown that graphite can be heated to 'white-hot ' temperatures ( ~ 1650 Â° C ) without incurring ignition or self-sustained combustion ( Lee , 2009 ) .
Firstly , in terms of burn-up rate of the fuel , for VHTR , it is possible to burn up to 65 % ( US Department of Energy , 2008 ) of its initial fuel as compared to SCWR which is capable of only burning up to 45 % of the initial fuel ( Buongiorno , 2003 ) .
This is unlike SCWR , which can only produce electricity .
Hydrogen production , an energy--intensive process , is important as hydrogen holds enormous promise as a power source for the future generation .
Hence , the plant can be operated at high temperatures without having to worry about corrosion of the plant pipes .
This is different from SCWR , which uses water as the coolant and hence there is a possibility of the pipe 's corrosion by water .
Lastly , proponents of SCWR claim that the construction cost of VHTR plant is much higher than SCWR due to its high operating temperature .
However , after the concept of Generation IV reactors was raised by GIF in 2001 ( Butler , 2004 ) , whether governments should solely focus on current nuclear reactors or split the funding for the new generation became a controversy .
Despite the accident in Chernobly , Ukraine , which was mainly caused by man-made operating errors ( Chernobly accident , 2009 ) , no major accident has occurred in the past two decades .
Rather than fund the Gen IV reactors , they think that governments should use the money to reinforce the safety of currently operating reactors .
These wastes take thousands of years to lose their activity . Thus they are not environmentally friendly in the long term ( Radioactive wastes , 2001 ) .
On the other hand , the cost of generating electricity from current nuclear reactors is already quite low ( 2.3 pence per kilowatt ) , which is comparable with other major sources ( The cost of generating electricity , 2004 ) .
But with the technology of Gen IV reactors , the efficiency can be improved 45 % to 50 % due to extremely high operating temperature ( 1000 degrees Celsius ) ( Daniels , 2007 ) .
Moreover , the heat produced by the Gen IV reactors can be used to produce hydrogen from water or supplied to the petrochemical industry ( The very-high-temperature reactor , n.d. ) .
The cogeneration and applications make the total efficiency even higher , thus further reducing the operating costs .
In order to optimize its power to meet the increasing demand of electricity as well as to maintain long term sustainability , governments should fund the Generation IV reactors instead of the old generation ones .
Fossil fuels , being non-renewable , are being exhausted at a rate faster than they can be replenished .
Hence , in order to solve the energy crisis , we need to look for other sources of energy .
Nuclear power is an important source of energy for the future . Hence more funding should be provided for research and development of nuclear reactors .
The public is worried that nuclear waste or nuclear materials could be stolen or sabotaged by terrorists during transportation or storage .
Nuclear waste or nuclear materials meant for energy production is not suitable to be used in nuclear weapons ( European Physical Society , 2007 ) .
Furthermore , the newer generation of reactors , like the VHTR , produces much less nuclear waste at terror-proof facilities ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Therefore , with these improvements in technology , we are able to minimize or even eliminate these security issues concerning nuclear generators .
Hence more research and development should be put into nuclear reactors .
People are worried about radiation leaks from nuclear facilities or nuclear waste .
All the factors mentioned above maybe true , and hence put nuclear power plants in a bad light .
Hence , problems such as nuclear waste is harder to process , can be solved with sufficient funding for research and development of nuclear power plants .
It is a known fact that nuclear power plants require high-start up costs .
Funds have to be inserted so as to support the high technology machinery and also create a safe environment with proper safety guidelines for the reactors .
In addition , operating licenses have to be bought from the government , to ensure safe operation of the nuclear power plants .
However , once the basic infrastructure has been laid down , nuclear power turns into a readily accessible and cheaply recoverable source of energy ( European Physical Society , 2007 ) .
Furthermore , with 4 of the 6 Generators-IV reactors being able to use reprocessed radioactive waste ( Butler , 2004 ) , it would be no surprise if nuclear power is able to last much longer than we expect .
It is a widely known fact that nuclear power is able to produce much more energy compared to traditional fossil fuels .
Furthermore , comparing the Generation-IV reactors with older nuclear reactors , the new reactors are much more efficient . Some of them , like the VHTR , produce hydrogen at the same time ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Nuclear power will make an important contribution to our future energy needs together with other alternatives ( European Physical Society,2007 ) . Hence , in order to produce nuclear energy more effectively and cleanly we must put in more support and funding for the research and development of nuclear reactors .
They were very much surprised by the unique design and amazed by the stunning price .
Although it was a surprising package , both positive and negative arguments about the car were presented at the Auto Expo 2008 .
The main issue discussed was safety .
The big question raised was whether Tata 's Nano was safe to drive on normal roads .
They prove that it is able to withstand a crash on a solid steel bar at a speed of 48 km/h .
Besides that , Hichman , designer of Nano , explains that their target was to construct a modular body where structure was added to the base of the vehicle so that Nano will be able to meet the European safety regulations ( Schedel , 2009 ) .
Moreover , a test was even done at Motor Industry Research Association ( MIRA ) in the UK to prove their claim .
Although much supporting evidence was given by Tata , it is said that Tata made critical modifications specifically to meet the European and Indian test norms .
Besides that , Americans feel that the test was not sufficient as it was only done at a speed of 48km/h . Many vehicles travel at much higher speeds especially on highways ( Jenks , 2009 ) .
Tata provides warranty for a period of only 18 months , which is much less compared to the other cars .
It is a big surprise that Tata has just neglected some of the most important features like the airbag , parking sensors , fog lamps and traction controls in its design .
Many who bought the car are complaining especially about the safety aspects of the car .
For example , a citizen of India stated that there are not enough safety features and that the Nano is a very bad design ( Gangadharan , 2008 ) .
