So , if other countries are not willing to purchase the car because it lacks safety features , then it will be a big loss for Tata .
Drivers will definitely have difficulties spotting the vehicles which are coming from behind and this may even lead to accidents .
Besides that , the wheels look small .
So , while travelling on slopes or heavy traffic , it could be dangerous .
The more comfortable the driver feels , the more easy he will find it to drive the car .
So , clearly it seems that there are some features that need to be changed .
It would be better if tougher materials could be used , more safety features added and some required changes done to the current design .
But I strongly feel that those who want to purchase the car will not mind paying a little more if it is going to provide a safer ride on the roads .
The reactor was invented because of the increasing demand for an alternative source of energy that could substitute crude oil .
Nuclear reactors can produce cleaner and higher energy than crude oil .
However , there is always an intention of the public to reject the idea of using nuclear reactors .
The disaster that happened at Chernobyl , Ukraine , in 1986 is one reason for the public 's anxiety .
Nonetheless , a VHTR ( Very-High- Temperature Reactor ) , which is one of the generation IV reactor concepts , has the technology to prevent disaster by using helium as its coolant and by producing waste with low radioactivity .
The VHTR can also produce both electricity and hydrogen through a very efficient process , so the cost of running a VHTR will not be as high as other reactors in the long run .
This argument may arise because of the lack of knowledge about helium .
This is indeed true . However , the ongoing HTTR ( High-Temperature Engineering Test Reactor ) project in Japan gives us a clue that it is not impossible to develop a new strong material in the future .
In addition , the operation of the VHTR does not depend on plutonium reprocessing , which is a controversial issue ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Thus , the VHTR waste is much safer than that of the existing nuclear reactors .
They say that the money that the government spends on building the reactor can be used for other purchases .
This is indeed true . However , , the cost of building a VHTR is in fact not as high as the other generation IV reactors .
Therefore , in the long run , it is profitable to build the VHTR because it can produce both electricity and hydrogen through a very efficient process .
To conclude , in spite of claims that nuclear reactors are dangerous and costly , the VHTR with its improved design , can overcome these issues .
Mention nuclear power and the general consensus are fear and rejection , and Chernobyl comes to mind .
These reactors , still in the designing and testing phase , excel in areas of sustainability , safety , economics and proliferation resistance ( Bouchard and Bennett,2008 ) , all which are specially intended to address all issues and challenges that nuclear power faces in a world combating the production of greenhouse gases , but in the safest possible way .
Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) emerges from the six as one of the most promising and is currently being heavily researched on . But is it worth the funds and efforts when safety concerns are still present and worse , unaddressed ?
For its performance level , the operating core temperatures of the reactor is capable of reaching an almighty peak of 1000 ( Chapin , et al 2004 ) , figures that will not only raise questions about its viability as well as the safety measures in place for such a high amount of energy , since temperature is directly proportional to the energy level of a closed system .
And because of the heights in the Celsius scale , the materials used in the reactor can not be of regular quality , much less inferior .
The use of high temperature creates an extremely volatile and sensitive situation which , on the one hand raises output efficiency ( OECD Nuclear Energy Agency , 2000 ) , but also requires a precise state-of-the-art monitoring system that further increases the production prices .
The six new reactors mainly differ only in their choice of coolant used in the system .
Helium gas is abundant on the Sun 's atmosphere but only at trace levels on the Earth 's surface ( AIR LIQUIDE , 2009 ) .
In addition , helium is not the only coolant that is chemically inert with the fuel ; molten lead is another viable option and is plentiful on the Earth 's crust .
Last but not least , gaseous coolants have low thermal transfer properties , hence requiring an intermediate heat exchange with a larger surface area ( Chapin , et al 2004 ) .
LFR on the other hand , is more suitable . The relatively smaller scale of operation and hence energy output , may be inferior compared to VHTR , but it is not feasible and unsafe for a large nuclear plant in a developing country where security and social unrest are issues .
LFR is a more portable option , thus more resistant against terrorism and weapon conversion since it is too stable to become a destructive tool .
Maintenance costs for VHTR will also be a tight spot for a growing nation , an area of concern which can be resolved by the use of LFR , which requires refueling once every 20 years .
The system core temperatures of LFR can reach up to 500 ( Idaho National Laboratory , 2005 ) , almost 50 % lower than that of VHTR and present significant differences in the operations of the plants .
Molten lead , compared to helium , is a superior and cheaper heat transfer medium , hence increasing the portability of the power plant by reducing the need for a large intermediate heat exchanger .
In conclusion , LFR may not be as proficient in energy production when compared to VHTR , but it addresses critical issues that VHTR fails to
As the population 's reliance on technology advances and grows , a greater need for electricity energy to power these computer gadgets has since sparked an inevitable concern as many worry that fossil fuels , being used over the years to generate electricity , are not sufficient enough to accommodate all the needs .
Moreover , global warming has been growing at an alarming rate , thanks partly to the excessive air pollution generated by fossil fuels .
Therefore , a search for higher efficient and safe energy supply is desperately needed and it is already on the agenda of all countries .
Nuclear power has since expanded to replace conventional fuels because of the higher efficiency it can provide to the world .
Many concepts are reviewed to improve the already competent nuclear reactors and so far , generation IV reactor concepts are among those which have stood up among the crowd that are worth developing
Safety factor is heavily considered because if an accident occurs at nuclear reactor sites , it can result in massive releases of radioactivity .
And it includes the development of passive heat removal systems , low power density and easily cool-able geometry .
However some have argued that VHTR is unsafe as it is operating at a higher temperature and it would easily be the target of terrorist attacks
And some have also put doubts on the ability of a passive heat removal system because if it fails to remove heat in the reactor , leakage of radioactive components will occur .
Certainly , disasters which happened in Three Mile Island , Tokaimura and Chernobyl should never be repeated .
But , according to Forrest J. Remick , professor emeritus of nuclear engineering and a former associate vice president for research at Penn State , VHTR is safe and this concept has been demonstrated in several test reactors in the United States , Germany , China and South Africa .
However , some experts have pointed out that if such high temperature is stimulated within a reactor , a new hardy alloy may be necessary to protect the inside layer of the reactor .
To get those alloys would already cost millions .
How about the construction cost of the entire power plant which is still unknown ?
When the cost is reduced , cheaper electricity can be provided to the public .
But in terms of performance , VHTR is a more efficient concept compared to others in generation four nuclear reactor concepts .
Even though it might prove costly at the beginning it pays off well as it produces both electricity and hydrogen fuel instead of electricity only .
High temperature processed in the reactor can be used as a condition to yield hydrogen from sulphur-iodine cycle , which is a series of thermo-chemical processes that will fail without a sufficient source of heat .
Hydrogen fuel produced can be used in vehicles as its onboard fuel .
Currently , VHTR development is in the early stages .
There are enormous items left to do in order for this concept to succeed in future .
Therefore , more research and development should be carried out so that in future this concept can become the energy supply for everyone on this earth .
However , as global warming is becoming a more pressing issue , we have now turned to nuclear reactors to provide us clean energy .
Which generation IV nuclear reactor we should choose ?
One of the main reasons for LFR being safer is LFR , which operates at around 550 degree Celsius , has a lower outlet temperature than VHTR , which operates at around 1000 degree Celsius ( Butler .
In short , operating at 1000 degree Celsius is not much of a safety issue since VHTR is safe and reliable at high temperatures .
In terms of the coolant used by the two reactors , VHTR is safer than LFR .
Given the presence of the radioactive polonium and the corrosiveness of lead , it is not safe to use lead as a coolant .
In terms of cost to build the reactor , LFR costs around US $ 700 million ( Neil W. Brown .
2006 ) while VHTR costs around US $ 1.1 billion ( Butler .
In addition , in terms of the cost of coolant , lead costs around US $ 0.24 per 100 grams ( MetalPrice.com ) while helium costs around US $ 5.20 per 100 grams .
However , there are other factors that will also affect the cost of operating the reactor , such as maintenance costs .
The economic production of hydrogen ( H2 ) by thermochemical cycles , can reduce the maintenance cost for operating the VHTR .
The final argument advanced by the supporters of LFR is LFR performs much better than VHTR .
However , recycling of nuclear waste will result in the production of plutonium , which can be used for nuclear weapons ( Butler .
Hence , recycling of nuclear waste is not safe in terms of security .
It is because the higher the outlet temperature , the greater the efficiency of electrical generation .
VHTR generates electrical energy in two ways , from the nuclear reactant directly and from hydrogen fuel .
In conclusion , VHTR is safe because it is designed to attain thermal stability and it uses an inert coolant , which is helium .
Hence , it should be evident that VHTR works better than LFR in terms of security , cost and performance .
Since VHTR is one of the better options among the generation IV nuclear reactors and it is feasible , we should invest in and support further research and development on VHTR .
Nowadays , we use fossil fuel in most cases , because it is convenient and has low cost of production .
But as the environment issues become high-profile problems and under the situation that this kind of non-renewable resource run out in the near future , people are beginning to seek some other methods that can support the world .
Nuclear power is now widely used in many countries and plays a more and more important role in the 21th century .
According to a survey , nuclear power produces around 11 % of the world 's energy needs and could take a greater proportion in the future .
This new reactors operating at high temperatures are safer and more efficient
That 's why US , France and China have already planed to build the plant in order to occupy the dominant position in this new area .
However , among the six types of new reactors,s the Very High Temperature Reactor is the most appropriate for us to realize .
It may become the next major energy producer
The VHTR , just as its name implies , needs temperatures as high as 1000 Â° C .
VHTR can provide some outstanding features which the rest can not , or VHTR is an extremely high efficiency reactor with a good security guarantee .
The VHTR system is highly ranked in efficiency not just because of its high nuclear production but also the large hydrogen production , and such a by product can also be used in many other industries .
Actually , according to the report from DISCOVERY : VHTR plants could even produce hydrogen for fuel using high-temperature steam electrolysis , which breaks apart the bonds of water molecules . This process is 50 percent more energy-efficient than existing hydrogen production methods .
The electricity , of course , will be used as electric power . .
Based on the information from DISCOVER : The VHTR should produce electricity about 40 percent more efficiently than most reactors in the United States ( New Tech Could Make Nuclear the Best Weapon Against Climate Change , Elizabeth Svoboda ) .
In terms of safety , firstly , the design takes advantage of the inherent safety characteristics of a
Helium should be very stable and inert even under high temperature condition , so this kind of inert gas can protect the system during the refrigeration process .
Numerous tests and calculations have shown that it is virtually impossible for the this kind of graphite to become unstable . Self-sustained combustion or incurring ignition will not happen during the process .
That means low system pressure and low thermal energy will be stored in the core with low power density and , then decay heat will be dissipated passively by conduction and radiation even under the most severe accident conditions. ( ...................... .
) So the damage of the decay heat will be less serious .
The security of VHTR can be guaranteed , because of these three features that protect the system from collapsing .
But things are not always perfect . The cost of this reactor is very high and we still notice some technology gaps for the VHTR , for example , chemical process and the nuclear heat source to each other with regard to temperatures , power levels , and operational pressure. ( .......... .
After more than 20 years of evolution , medical robots have becomee one of the great inventions in this technology driven world .
In the past , medical robots helped the surgeons to diagnose the patients ' internal organs and perform minor surgerys .
But in recent years , due to the technology advancement on the medical robots , prototypes of these robots surgery systems are now able to perform more precise , accurate and complicated surgery , such as reaching for untouchable tissue on the patients with the surgeons controlling them remotely .
However , there are many issues revolving around the use of the robotics surgery system compared to traditional human operated surgery
The first issue is that the public is concerned that robotic surgery will be expensive. .
However , this is true for medical fees , especially surgery , and it is even more expensive when compared with traditional methods .
This may be the only disadvantage that the patients are going to have but there are lots of advantages for them if they are willing to use medical robots to perform surgery .
" This is quoted from one article by Debra S. from Reuters .
Another article from Newsweek , reported by Jennifer B. mentioned , " Forbes was walking within hours of his surgery and was discharged the next day .
" From these , we can see that patients are definitely benefiting in many ways especially when the they are able to go back to their normal daily life within a shorter recovery time .
The public is also concerned about the safety and reliability of the robotic surgery system , for example , the system breaking down in the process of surgery .
They are worried if this would have happen to them during surgery .
However , the public can rest assured on this matter because the hospitals have always been doing maintenance of the robotic systems .
As a matter of fact , this is the biggest downside for having a robotic system in the hospitals .
An article in The American College of Obstetricians and Gynecologists mentioned " The system costs hospitals about $ 1.6 million and requires an annual $ 100,000 maintenance contract , according to Dr .
The last issue of public concern is that the surgeons are not well trained in controlling the robotic surgery systems .
This is a valid concern as the patients are placing their lives in the surgeons ' hands .
However , the public , especially the patients , do not need to worry about this issue , as there is a robotic surgery training center in Singapore to train the surgeons .
The surgeons are responsible for proper training and follow training standards for using the equipment .
The surgeons are encouraged to have more practices before operating on the patients .
" The more you do , the better you 're going to get , said Dr Kevin Zorn "
In brief , with the advancement of medical technologies , the robotic surgery systems definitely benefit both the patients and the surgeons .
While the patients are able to recover quickly and return to their normal lifestyle , the surgeons are able to perform more surgery as they spend less time on each patient and require less manpower in the operating theater .
In my opinion , robotic surgery systems help to extend the lifespan of one human being .
Therefore , the public should not fear the robotic surgery and should have confidencet and trust the surgeons and the technologies they are using .
The nuclear power industry is reviving in the 21st century .
However , the accidents of reactor meltdown and explosion that happened in the past made the public worried about the safe operation of the nuclear reactors .
Whether it is necessary for the further research and development funding for VHTR therefore has becomes a big issue that is being widely discussed .
A number of oppositions were raised to stop the funding for the six generation IV reactor concepts because of not only the security risk but the inefficiency and the great cost as well .
Despite such concerns and queries , however , the new concept of VHTR does meet the public 's requirement in terms of safety , efficiency and cost , and the further research and development funding for it is definitely needed for resolving the energy crisis and also developing new materials and techniques .
The helium , which is used for cooling , has inherent safety characteristics to enhance the security of the whole reactor system .
Thus , it largely reduces the possibility of explosions or other accidents .
The VHTR system , if successful , will prevent most accidents
Practically , Japan has already put the concept of VHTR through tests and has been successful ( Kazuhiro , 2005 ) .
From this point of view , further research and development funding is also needed .
This may be true , but the value the VHTR system can rise and the benefit obtained can not be ignored .
Firstly , the VHTR system can largely contribute to easing the energy crisis that is widely spread all over the world , .
.
In addition , the VHTR system has a perfect design for waste recycling .
Furthermore , more research is needed to develop the VHTR system , including new materials such as heat resistant ones , and new techniques such as temperature control .
Once this research has been done , not only would the VHTR system benefit , , but also many other industries .
Therefore , the great value and benefit from developing the concept of VHTR are far more than the high cost it requires .
The first generation of nuclear reactors was built in 1950 .
Since then , continuous researches has been done to produce a better generation of nuclear reactors .
Nuclear power plants have been widely deployed in many leading countries in the world such as United States , Japan , and China which use the nuclear power plants as one of their main power sources to propel the energy industry .
The usage of the nuclear power plants is widely recognized and they are being integrated as part of those countries ' promising energy sources .
One kilogram of uranium can release the same amount of energy as that released by 2400 tons of standard coal .
It is a good alternative energy source which not only reduces the greenhouse effect,but also helps solve the problems of limited fossil fuels .
Nuclear power is deemed to be a promising energy source for the future .
However , the nuclear leak incidents which happened in the past few decades in countries such as Three Miles Island , Pennsylvania , Chernobyl in Ukraine , and Bhopal in India have posed doubts on the reliability of the nuclear reactors .
It is an organization formed by 9 leading countries in the world : Canada , China , Euratom , France , Japan , Republic of Korea , South Africa , Switzerland , and United States .
The organization tries to resolve security issues posed by the current nuclear reactors .
100 international experts from GIF and other world leading nuclear power plant research centers have gathered together to find the most promising nuclear systems .
These state-of-the-art nuclear reactors will be able to minimize nuclear wastes and reduce the long-term stewardship burden posed by traditional nuclear reactors .
They have integrated safety design and back-up systems to prevent accidents due to human errors and carelessness , therefore reducing the likelihood and degree of vector core damage .
The physical protection of the new nuclear reactors will also prevent acts of terrorism .
Out of the six proposals in the Generation IV Reactor , Very- High-Temperature Reactors ( VHTR ) stands out for its potential capability to achieve an excellent thermal performance .
The great breakthrough in the research also suggests that the VHTR does not require intermediate refueling , therefore eliminating the likelihood of accidents .
The reactor operates by using a high temperature exchanger and electrical heater to avoid efficiency penalty and enable the generation of electricity and hydrogen at the same time .
It iss also known that the ultra-long life VHTR systems can be developed with the use of minor actinides ( MA ) .
With today 's high demand of energy sources , one can say that nuclear energy is an inevitable energy source of the future .
Nuclear power , for a long time , has been one of the most useful inventions that served the people .
The Generation IV International Forum , which was attended by the ten nations specialising in nuclear power , introduced the six new reactor concepts ( " Nuclear power 's new dawn , " 2004 ) .
One of them , the Molten Salt Reactor , has a prospective application though there are several objections with respect to safety , cost and performance .
Some think that nuclear plants emit radioactive waste into the environment , which may cause both pollution and genetic mutation ; others are afraid of the safety system , meaning the plants might explode easily .
However , nuclear power as well as the new Molten Salt Reactor system , in fact , is safer and useful .
According to Declan Butler ( 2004 ) , the Molten Salt Reactor system mainly uses fluoride salts , which also belong to heat-and corrosion-resistant materials , as coolant , which can operate for a very long time and is also safe and reliable .
Another advantage of nuclear power is its green emission .
In fact , among other Generation IV Reactors as well as electricity generators , the Molten Salt Reactor seems to be the cheapest way to produce electricity .
He compared them in terms of the availability to build , cost to produce power and area of land occupied .
For example , the cost ( in US dollars for fuel used per Megawatt-hour energy is $ 5 for nuclear and $ 11 for coal plants ( " The Virtual Nuclear Tourist , " 2005 ) .
A nuclear plant can be built anywhere , which does not require natural resources .
Solar or wind power need a lot of land to produce the same amount of energy .
Performance is one of the most concerned factors that people
The power , an amount of energy generated in a unit of time , of a nuclear plant is highest among the others' .
As Roger ( 2007 ) stated in his statistical data , the average amount of energy generated per hour varies among kinds of plant : average 4000 MW for nuclear , 1000 MW for coal or oil-fired and 700 MW for hydroelectric generating stations .
From these numbers , it is obvious that the performance of nuclear plants is sufficient to support the consumption of a large population , which helps the nations lacking in natural resources be independent of coal or oil import .
In short , cheap material , additional product ( hydrogen ) and high performance ( property of nuclear power ) make the Molten Salt Reactor system as well as nuclear power most efficient .
In conclusion , nuclear power is safe , clean and effective , which most people seem to forget .
With the cheap , safe , recyclable , low pressure , having-additional-produce and high performance properties of the Molten Salt Reactor system , it is one of the most potential electricity generators for the future .
One of the Achilles ' heels of nuclear power plants is the danger of radioactive radiation leakage to the environment .
Generation IV nuclear reactor plants promise higher redundancy , higher efficiency , and better safety features than its predecessors .
In this essay , I shall discuss the advantage of Lead cooled Fast Reactor ( LFR ) over Sodium cooled Fast Reactor ( SFR ) on the aspects of safety , cost and performance .
The element sodium has a low boiling point of 1156 Kelvin , compared to lead 's higher 2023 Kelvin , which is dangerous because it becomes overheated and starts to boil ( Hejzlar , 2009 ) .
On the other hand , lead can become radioactive and is therefore harmful to life during refueling when the lead is exposed .
While research is being done to control the lead 's radioactivity , it is reassuring that refueling is done every 8 years in large plants and every 15 years in smaller plants .
Cost has become a very important criterion in the world today . In this case , the LFR fits the bill very well .
Considering the economies of scale , the cost of building materials such as steel and concrete will increase significantly , hence the size of a nuclear plant has become a consideration .
On the contrary , research on the use of pure lead instead of a lead-bismuth cooling agent may outweigh the economic benefits of LFR .
Also , the SFR is projected to be launched 10 years earlier than LFR .
For the time being , LFR has the advantage of costing less today .
Also LFR has better fuel efficiency than SFR as LFR has less specific power , 45kW/kgHM compared to 65kW/kgHM of the SFR .
SFR has been the mainstream for nuclear power plants in the past years and is therefore more familiar and accepted .
However research is needed to prove the capability of sodium at high temperatures , as it has a low boiling point , which will result in a complex design .
Hence , to meet the world 's energy needs , scientists are re-addressing the potential benefits of harnessing power through nuclear reaction , in which uranium is split to release energy .
Moreover , the processed heat that the nuclear reactor produces can also be used in other industrial areas such as hydrogen production , water desalination and the treatment of crude oil ( Jacques , 2008 ) .
The fact that uranium is also widely available in ample supply is in contrast to the trend of the rapidly depleting coal and natural gases reserves .
In addition , the leftover waste is radioactive in nature and if not handled properly , creates pollution and poses great threat to the ecosystem of the world .
Firstly , the VHTR does not recycle its leftover from the nuclear reaction . Instead the waste is discarded at the end of the nuclear process .
They are afraid that if terrorists were to sabotage these nuclear plants , their act will lead to a catastrophic disaster which will affect the nation 's economic and social health
To conclude , nuclear energy is relatively cheap , environmentally and socially responsible , and safe to use .
There was a sequence of events that caused the explosion of reactor number 4 that led to the release of radioactive fission products to the atmosphere .
This resulted in many deaths , including those who died from the accident , those firefighters and majority who were exposed to radiation .
There are arguments that the lack of knowledge of the operators and the technical failure of equipment could not be solved with the application of psychology .
However , it seems otherwise since psychology is a study of the human mind or behavior .
This incident occurred during a non-routine operation to test the ability of the turbine , in times of power failure , to produce sufficient power .
The behavior of operators should be anticipated and thus engineers could have reduced the complexity of the task by providing short and efficient procedure guidelines .
The failure to do so showed that the engineers had overestimated the operators ' knowledge of the process .
( Wilpert.B , 2007 ) In other words , it is unfair to blame the operators when accidents happen
Even so , many still think that psychology may not come in handy in preventing accidents , especially when it is due to technical faults .
This characteristic will cause reactors to be unstable at low power levels .
Another fatal technical fault was the chosen design of the control rods .
If they had adopted the use of psychology , they might have reviewed safety records of that type of reactor in the industry before deciding on it .
However , in this process , there may be partial failures in the system which the engineers failed to identify and were thus unable to improve safety of the system .
Therefore , a systematic thinking is recommended , where engineers constantly analyze their own approach and decisions so as to take corrective action to improve the safety of the whole system .
This is preferred to making corrections only after an accident has occurred .
Men have always wanted to fly freely since the realization of the aeroplane . Therefore , being able to travel great distances with freedom of route and comfort has since been the aim of the transportation industry .
" ( Moller , 2008 ) In 2008 , the prototype of Skycar , priced at over US $ 3million , was invented and put on sale via the auction site , eBay ( Techchee , 2007 ) .
Being able to take-off and land vertically with very little noise , it soon attracted the attention of not just the US Army but also rich businessmen who could rely on it to travel to different places with ease ( Yahoo , 2009 ) .
However , should its design safety be compromised to balance out the other factors like performance , cost , environmental and social requirement or needs ?
Although it may be true that redundant safety systems can be removed and the Skycar will still remain safe for usage but when an accident happens , no one can ever be too safe .
Besides , the loss of life and the cost of safety systems which could have prevented the accident can not be compared .
For example , the cars used in Formula One are much more heavily equipped with safety features since the death of driver , Ayrton Senna da Silva in 1994 , though his car was already very much equipped with safety precautions during his accident .
Some enthusiasts have remarked that it is simply too costly to own a Skycar .
The safety of bystanders is also considered where design safety is concerned .
Equipped with a auto-releasing parachute , it allows enough time for bystanders to evacuate when the vehicle fails .
In 2005 , of the 43443 people killed in vehicle accidents in the US , more than 5000 were innocent bystanders ( Stats , nd ) .
Some consumers commented that the structure and shape of the Skycar should be modified as it looks weird and
Although the designers modified the airfoil at the expense of raising it 's cost , if the vehicle were to be less stable , will the consumer still be interested in the product ?
The Skycar has since passed it flight test and awaiting approval from the Federal Aviation Administration to be recognised as a commercial vehicle .
As the market for such vehicle grows , mass production is likely to take place , which will in turn lower its cost price .
The rapid development of countries and expansion of population have created a world that is increasingly unable to meet the demand of energy.Additionally , fossil fuel is criticized as the main contributing factor for green house gas effect .
As such , there is a pressing need to search for alternative renewable forms and energy which is comparatively more eco-friendly and highly effective .
In such a context , nuclear energy created by using the Generation IV ( Gen IV ) reactor is able to replace fossil fuel , which is believed to be the main cause of global warming .
Some may argue , with skepticism , that the safety issues of this reactor are still imminent and hence , nuclear power should not be supported .
Some opponents have raised doubts of the performance of VHTR .
First , VHTR performs under very high temperature , thereby allowing for more efficient conversion of heat to electricity .
Nowadays , there is an increasing demand for energy due to fast economic development . Thus we need a power generation method that would be sustainable in the long term .
Actually , fossil fuel is also possible but with the spike in energy consumption in the past few decades , fossil fuel is predicted to be depleted by 2040 .
Moreover , the fossil fuel 's emission of carbon dioxide , which contributes to soaring green house gas levels would not happen with nuclear power .
In short , I believe that with further research , the efficiency of the nuclear power can be increased , making it a potential energy resource in the future .
Some skeptics feel that the building of VHTR is a risky investment , complaining that VHTR is an expensive source of energy , hence unfeasible .
Due to low maintenance , the fixed cost would be lower in the near future .
The fact that China , one the world largest consumers of energy , is willing to spend high proportion of money for this project shows the long run benefit that nuclear power can bring about , especially since the Chinese government has been always very pragmatic .
Yet , VHTR is actually still safe and reliable to operate , with improved accident management and mitigation and reduced off-side response with little human intervention .
Last but not least , some will question why helium with low thermal conductivity is chosen as its coolant given that some other coolant , for instance molten salt , allows better electric conversion efficiency than a helium-cooled VHTR operating at similar conditions .
However , the selection of coolant is based on many factors .
Although there is certain undenied limitation of VHTR , I am strongly convinced that with the current technology advances , the limitation will be solved .
With more funds channeled into research into this area , the potential of VHTR could be maximized .
The most common method of power generation for close to 150 years the burning of fossil fuels such as oil or coal .
Perhaps a solution to save our planet will be to use a cleaner energy source -- nuclear power , which does not emit any harmful gases .
The world is concerned with the safety of nuclear power plants and the possibility of nuclear arms proliferation . Past incidents at Chernobyl and Three Mile Island ( Bodansky , 2005 ) have left many in doubt about the technology .
Recently , , both North Korea and Iran have been told to step back on their plans of a nuclear power plant for fear that the same radioactive materials used for energy generation will be used in producing nuclear weapons .
Moreover , detractors have argued that the high temperature generated in nuclear reactors is not fully utilized and conventional non-nuclear energy generation methods have better performance in terms of thermal efficiency . Existing nuclear plants have thermal efficiency of approximately 33 % ( Olander , 2009 ) compared to 70 % and above for non-nuclear power plants .
Another objection is raised by the taxpayers . They are not convinced with the heavy investment of building a nuclear plant.TS A nuclear plant costs on average , a billion dollars and is designed with a lifespan of sixty years ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Acid rain had caused deforestation and affected fisheries . The damages amounted to millions per year .
The collision involved two Boeing 747s , KLM and Pan Am . KLM took off while Pan Am was still on the runway .
Many factors such as foggy weather contributed to the accident . However , , the most significant causes are considered to be the ambiguous phraseology in the comment " We are uh taking off " or " We are at takeoff " from KLM and the single channel radio which made the crucial readback for clearance lost in radio squelch ( Kilroy , n.d. ) .
Proponents may argue that with the input of psychology , the designers of the airport should have anticipated such possible dangers and imposed stricter laws to insist on proper phraseology and check for clearance should have been put into use .
For the technical part , the centerline lights were out of operation which prevented the two planes from seeing each other . The single channel radio made the response inaudible and there was no ground radar ( ALPA , n.d. ) .
Besides , the thick fog worsened the situation .
The adoption of psychology in design might have taken a few of the factors into consideration , but it was unlikely to have anticipated all and hence there would still be potential hazards .
To sum up , the use of psychology in design would not be very helpful in the special case of the Tenerife accident due to the human errors and accidental factors that were difficult to anticipate and prevent .
Scientists have put in a lot of effort into the development in nuclear energy which is one of the major modern energy resources .
It is one of the clean and renewable energy sources which can help us solve the emergent problems of energy shortage .
But from my point of view , I believe nuclear energy can bring much more benefits than those lost .
Compared with that , the number of coal mine accidents deaths is much llarger reaching 7530 per year .
So it is easier to guarantee the safety of nuclear power plants because if workers follow the regulations , no accidents will occur .
It is the real hazard .
It can keep the nuclear reactor operating under lower temperature and pressure .
From the above reasons , we can see that nuclear energy is not as dangerous as people expect . Contrarily , , it is one of the safest energy humans can use in modern society .
Secondly , as I mentioned above , scientists are trying to develop the lead-cooled fast reactor . However , , the enormous size of investment has prevented most countries from this kind of research .
Currently 442 nuclear power plants are working all over world , contributing about 19 percent of the world 's electricity supply .
Another case in point is America , " They produce much of the electricity that fuels our economic growth .
Statistics show that , in 1996 , nuclear power produced 674 billion kilowatt-hours of electricity , which was more than the total electricity consumed in the early 1950s ( Nuclear Energy & Society , n.d. ) .
Thus to sum up , nuclear power plants can produce electricity with higher efficiency and in larger amounts compared to fuel or coal burning electricity generating plants .
They can bring great economic benefit .
Lastly , the lack of technology to deal with the disposal of nuclear wastes which are radioactive and highly toxic is the last reason preventing countries from using nuclear energy .
Officers are afraid of terrorists who acquire a substantial amount of nuclear waste and could construct a so-called " dirty bomb " which may affect the country 's safety .
And if the government can reinforce the management of where the nuclear waste goes after using , people do not have to worry about the attack from terrorists .
In conclusion , nuclear energy is not dangerous to human beings so we should make full use of nuclear energy to benefit the whole of mankind .
However , none of these can be the ideal energy to us now due to the technological problems , economic concerns , or potential dangers .
There is no need to spend so much on nuclear energy development .
However , in terms of efficiency and economic value , nuclear energy has great advantages over both solar energy and wind force .
Besides this , in the process of nuclear reaction , a large amount of hydrogen can be generated for the use in petroleum refinement and also as new advanced fuel in transportation ( Vilim , 2007 ) .
It is said that for America , the energy demand of transport alone will cause increase of oil imports by 78 % by the end of 2025 if it does not switch its dependence on oil to hydrogen ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Though solar energy and wind force can also contribute to environment protection , nuclear energy indeed has its unique advantages which they can not rival .
But they will not expect that the meltdown proof in VHTR can cool itself down when accidents happen and minimize the interaction with human beings ( Butler , 2004 ) .
So , nuclear reactor would not be a desirable target for terrorists any more .
To sum up , the Generation reactors have made great improvements compared to the older generation ones in terms of both technology and safety features .
On one hand , nuclear energy has the advantage of high efficiency , non--greenhouse-gas emission and the by-product hydrogen , which is supposed to be another ideal energy .
The electric vehicle ( EV ) is not new on the road . In fact it has been on the road for more than a century .
However , there are safety issues on the newly developed technologies that the electric vehicle carries such as the volatile Lithium ion battery , massive battery weight problem , and the silent electric motor that might cause unnoticeable hazard to the pedestrians .
Despite all the safety issues , steps have been taken to enhance the safety of the EV .
In my opinion EV is safer than a conventional gasoline vehicle .
Although numerous articles claiming that EV is unsafe , there is evidence of improvements made to make EV safe to drive .
An anti-impact cage is added to shield the battery from being crushed .
In order to prevent over charging and discharging , advanced microchips will be used to monitor the batteries ' capacity .
With these improvements , Osamu Masuko , president of Mithubishi Motors says that gasoline is relatively far more dangerous than batteries .
The electric vehicle carries large and heavy battery packs to increase the mileage per charge .
These heavy batteries result in an EV being much heavier compared to an identical gasoline vehicle .
Other than that , in a crash test , the occupants of a lighter vehicle suffered from higher damage compared to a heavy vehicle ( insurance Institute for highway safety , 2009 ) .
In comparison , an accident involving a 1400 Kg vehicle will cause about 50 percent fewer injuries than a 900 Kg vehicle .
Recently , there have been debates on electric vehicles posing a hazard to pedestrians , especially to the blind or visually-impaired road users ( Nuckols , 2007 ) .
EV is propelled by an electric motor in which torque is produced by electromagnetic forces .
Tests have shown that the noise level that the EV produces while operating below 30 km/h is not noticeable for all types of road users .
Beyond that speed , more audible noise is formed by the air displaced by the body of the vehicle and friction on the .
Thus , the European Commission and the US Congress are taking the initiative to set up a minimum level of sound for the EV , and the Japanese may add noise to the quiet vehicle ( AFP , 2009 ) , so that the pedestrians and blind people are able to detect oncoming EV .
This shows that initiatives have been taken to make the electric car safe for the drivers and the pedestrians .
From all the weaknesses of the EV mentioned above , we can actually see that they are no longer a threat to the EV drivers or pedestrians .
EV batteries have been improved to prevent over-heating , controlled charging and discharging . The casing has been fortified to ensure the batteries are not seriously damaged after a car crash .
The weight problems were countered easily by properly aligning the batteries such that the weight will give more stability to the EV .
In conclusion , we can see that manufacturers have greatly improved the EV to a standard that EV is safer than the conventional gasoline vehicle .
Patients with cardiovascular disease usually suffer from heart failure , where the heart ceases to work , leading to a sudden heart attack .
A heart transplant was the only option to save these patients initially .
This proves to be very difficult , and the mortality rate of cardiovascular disease remains high .
Heartmate II is a battery operated electronic pump attached internally to a patient 's heart inside his or her chest cavity .
Battery life is one of the main concerns that needs to be addressed for the Heartmate II .
Essentially , what needs to be achieved is a compact and less bulky battery with a longerr life span .
Furthermore , changes could be made to enable the users to take a proper bath , instead of being restricted to just wiping themselves clean with a wet cloth .
Over the decades , the quality of life has improved tremendously in terms of technologies .
People are now living in a world filled with technology with every edge of the world powered by electricity .
However , the day when people use more electricity than they produce is approaching .
This forces people to resort to producing energy through nuclear reactors which have higher outputs .
Firstly , the public has always held the view that nuclear reactors are unsafe to use as they emit substances which are hazardous to people 's health and the environment .
As MSR has a liquid fuel , the reactor has the unique safety advantage that in the event of an accident , the fuel salt is dumped to critically safe , passively cooled storage tanks .
Moreover , molten salts are effectively incompressible . Consequently , a failure of a heat exchanger in the chemical plant will not pressurize the plant .
Also , the public is afraid that the nuclear reactor will be misused for development of nuclear weapons .
This does not concern MSR , as it is able to operate with non-weapon grade fissile fuel which gives no chance for people to misuse the research to develop nuclear weapons .
Secondly , it has always been a general perception of the public that the cost incurred to build a nuclear reactor is always huge .
This results in not much effort being taken to initiate a nuclear reactor project as they believe the project is not feasible .
Another related concern is the amount of cost incurred for the maintainence of the reactor .
However , MSR is known to be among the cheapest nuclear reactors .
Also , MSR will be using thorium as fuel as thorium is so abundant in the world as compared to current technologies which mostly use coal as fuel where coal is expected to last just for another 146years according to Energy Information Administration ( EIA ) .
These show that MSR is economical and should have cleared any doubts regarding further research on MSR as it is a feasible project in the long run as it makes use of resources which are abundant .
If funding is provided for research on MSR , there is no doubt that MSR can be fully utilised .
Although MSR generally generates less energy as compared to other nuclear reactors , the less space it requires can make up for it .
In conclusion , it is evident that MSR is worth the funding for the research given the attributes it possess .
If further research is done , there is no doubt that MSR will be able to improve its weakness in having higher output as well as further refine its strong points which are economyl and safety .
Due to its huge energy production and no emission of carbon dioxide , many nuclear power plants have been built .
People have been arguingg about the safety problems and the cost brought by these plants for a long time .
Despite the controversy , the nuclear power plants still find their way back onto the table .
During Generation IV International Forum , the concept of Very-high-temperature reactor ( VHTR ) was raised . It is more efficient than the previous ones .
Acoording to scientific measurement , the energy generated by per unit hydrogen is about 2.6 times greater than fossil fuel .
Some opponents will say that a large sum of money may be spent on the research and be pessimistic about the result .
What is more , we should look at the problem over the long term .
They all have dangerous .
Accoding to car crash states in America in 2005 , there were nearly 6,420,000 auto accidents and about 40,000 people were killed .
And because we know very clearly that it is dangerous , we devote very much effort to monitor the whole process in case accidents happen .
In conclusion , energy is the key to keeping our society and economic development sustainable .
Besides , the demand for the energy is soaring , a more efficient ways should be used to generate energy .
However , given the accidents of nuclear meltdown , people are worried about the safety issue of using nuclear power .
Experts have found a new generation of nuclear reactors which are safer and more effective than the old generation .
A good moderator is one that should not absorb too much energy when the neutrons bounce off nor absorb the neutrons before they split .
Graphite is a good one compared with the ordinary moderator which is water , since graphite is heat resistant .
So , using graphite increases the efficiency of the usage of uranium and reduces the loss of energy .
people still wonder if safety is guaranteed after the accident related to the VHTR basic design which has a potential to cause the destruction of the reactor core ( Takeda , 2001 ) .
First is the choice of the coolant .
Therefore with this design , the risk could be lowered .
In addition , new computational methods can be used for simulating air ingress in the VHTR to help prevent the accident ( Kim , 2009 ) .
Apart from safety issues , in order to implement the very high temperature reactor , people also worry about the economic factor .
Obviously it is more expensive to build a nuclear plant , but , after the start-up , the operating cost is cheaper because of high-efficiency , lower-cost high-temperature reactor for electricity and hydrogen production .
The Federal Energy Regulatory Commission reported that the overall operating costs for nuclear power plants is roughly the same as the recent coal-fired plants and below the costs of operating most gas-fired generation units ( Forsberg , Peterson , Zhao , 2006 ) .
Besides , a technoeconomic optimization method has been developed and can be applied to the power conversion system of a very high temperature reactor , taking both investment costs and operating costs into account ( Mansilla , 2008 ) Due to concerns over the energy resource availability , climate change , air quality , and energy security issue , nuclear power may take an important role in future .
The very high temperature reactor , being one of the possible systems of new generation power which aims to achieve improvements in economic competitiveness , nuclear safety , is promising to be implemented in the future .
Under these circumstance , scientists have come up with very high temperature reactor ( VHTR ) to make use of energy in a safer and more efficient way .
People wonder if there exists a suitable material to build this reactor .
They are concerned about the probability of radioactivity leaking .
Firstly , people wonder whether scientists can find a suitable material that can withstand such high temperature , more than 1000 , compared to that of the current nuclear reactor which is less 330 .
It is true that there is a huge jump between these two levels , but that does not necessarily mean it is impossible .
Secondly , some people are concerned about leakage of radioactivity after a period of running although the reactor maybe good enough to hold all radioactivity inside at the beginning .
That is why engineers have set the timeline to replace some certain parts of the reactor that may not be safe after some years .
The other common aspect that may have some influence in the safety area is the reaction between coolant and the crust of the reactor which may directly results in radioactive leakage and even explosions .
With rapid industrialisation , the energy requirements of the world are increasing exponentially.It has increased to a point where the conventional sources of energy are no longer able to meet the demands . There is also the problem of pollution which is becoming graver everyday and threatens to eradicate life altogether on this planet .
The VHTR can not only supply heat to a broad range of high temperature and energy intensive processes but also produce electricity to meet the modern demands.Also in the end , hydrogen is produced , which clearly is a huge benefit as the energy required to produce pure hydrogen is really tremendous .
Helium is an inert gas . Hence exposing it to radiation does not make it radioactive , thus averting a major health hazard.Because of helium being used as the coolant very high temperatures such as 1000C are possible , thus increasing its efficiency manifold .
In fact , the refuelling in this type of reactor can be achieved when it is still running.It is so highly efficient that a single pebble can last upto three years .
With the green house effect threatening to cause severe climatic changes , it is really wise to switch from burning fossil fuels to nuclear fuel.Research still proceeds everyday in perfecting this . Maybe several years from now there will be an even more efficient way to tap the nuclear energy .
