Engineers do face a tremendous pressure every time an engineering accident occurs .
As it is reported in Nuclear Science and Engineering ( 1987 ) , the primary causes of the Chernobyl Nuclear Reactor Plant Explosion were recorded as follows :
Therefore , it is natural for ordinary people who witnessed those tragedies to put all the blame on the engineers
Though engineers have been compelled to be the target of public criticism for a long time , few psychologists really decided to conduct a comprehensive study on human factors to reveal the truth .
Actually , the way to prevent engineering accidents should be innovated by taking psychology into consideration instead of expecting engineers to be perfect .
Normally , the public criticises engineers for their carelessness and strongly suggest raising engineers ' level of responsibility .
Actually , nowadays the rapidly-developing technology and resultant economic effect over-focus on the improvement of the equipment and machines , which strictly requires human 's adaptation .
From a psychologist 's ' point of view , the engineers have to take on more pressure which finally causes all sorts of negative impact on them and certainly does nothing effective to their daily work .
Moreover , in many countries , the governments usually do not pay enough attention to engineers except when one must come out to bear/ face the consequences .
This is unfair to engineers , the most important founders of the modern world .
Therefore , psychologists can play an irreplaceable role in designing workplaces by analyzing the structure of users ' physical and mental systems so as to guarantee that workers can perform in a good condition from start to finish .
Relieving fatigue and restoring vitality should be the best way for engineers to prevent accidents .
Third , the public criticism of engineers needs to be more objective when referring to the theory of possibility .
Just as B.Wilpert has illustrated in Psychology and design processes , engineers are human and it is possible for human to make mistakes , in other words , engineers need more understanding from society .
Theoretically speaking , everything must eventually fail to perform its given function .
That is why accidents are called " accidents " and that is why humans are " human " not " god " .
Excessively high expectations should not be placed on engineers . After all , engineers are also ordinary people and have human limitations as well .
As humans , they need to relax , they need to work in sound conditions and they also need the understanding and recognition of the society as well .
From the development and achievements of this subject in the not-too-distant future , the choice for a better design and the way to prevent accidents can be directly obtained .
