For decades surgery was performed by human force only , which is limited by the size of surgery tools , and causes complicated procedures .
In 1985 , the emergence of a prototype " PUMA 560 " pointed a new way to do surgery , and that is robotic surgery .
Today 's robotic surgery machines are usually equipped with 3D cameras , recording body images more clearly , and enabling more precise operation .
However , controversies over robotic surgery have also raised concerns about safety , high cost and performance .
Opponents of robotic surgery maintain that this surgery is highly dangerous . , Incorrect design and fault of its running program can result in disastrous consequences .
Actually , safety issues are also the major factor for scientists doing research on robotic surgery to consider , since any tiny mistake means a life at risk .
Before a robotic surgery machine is put into use , strict inspection will be done on it to ensure safety .
On the other hand , the outcomes of robotic surgery also reveal that it is a safe surgery method .
In America , with the approval of FDA ( Food and Drug Administration ) Intuitive Surgical ( Mountain View , CA ) has studied the use of its robotic surgery system on 113 patients , and then compared it with those of 132 patients who underwent conventional surgery .
Results showed that robotic surgery was comparable to conventional one in safety and effectiveness , according to FDA .
In addition , training surgeons to operate the equipment is also a large expenditure .
As robotic surgery gains acceptance , increased production of such machines will reduce the cost .
So when an unknown situation happens robots can not cope with it .
In fact , the current robotic surgery system serves to assist in surgery .
The main role is still a human surgeon who will make judgment , and the robot itself can not do anything without human instructions .
Continuous advances in technology on one had will bring down the possibility of error occurring , and the other hand allow the machine to shut down safely if any emergency happens .
The combination of the two will also bring modern surgery up to a new level .
According to surgeons , patients ' feedback on robotic surgery have been very positive ( Tracy , 2001 ) .
