From the above , on the one hand , the worries of opponents of nuclear reactors being built all can be solved by scientists and engineers ; on the other hand , energy needs of the society and the development of the related technologies have made it possible for VHTR to come true .
The Chernobyl accident happened on April 26 , 1986 .
The accident caused a total of 56 fatalities as of 2004 , and some seven million Chernobyl victims suffering from the impact of Chernobyl accident ( World Nuclear Association , 2009 ) .
Design is a human activity , and humans may make mistakes .
In The Truth about Chernobyl , the author , Medvedev ( 1991 ) , notes that one of the reasons which caused Chernobyl accident is the inadequate operators with insufficient knowledge operating the reactor inappropriately .
In the design process , designers should consider the user of devices , components or systems under development , which includes people who maintain and repair the product as well as who operates it ( Ertas & Jones , 1996 ) .
The designers were aware of the defects of the reactors , however , they did not make efforts to correct them .
If the designers knew the severe consequence of the accident , they would have tried their best to prevent it .
In conclusion , Chernobyl is the result of flawed design of reactor and inappropriate operation by inadequate operators .
Nowadays , developed countries and developing countries have invested huge funds to develop nuclear power as nuclear energy is regarded to be the potential energy source for the future ( Butler , 2004 ) .
They will help reduce carbon dioxide and subsequently reduce the effect of global warming ( Jacques & Ralph , 2008 ) .
