Safety issues will be handled with extreme care by all GIF member counties .
Even though the fund is limited and by allocating funds for Generation IV reactors , we have to forgo other possible benefits such as spending the same amount of money to solve poverty or terrorism . I support to explore new and advanced technology , Generation IV reactors , to solve environmental and energy problems .
Current reactors in use around the world are considered 2nd or 3rd generation systems , with the 1st generation systems having been retired a long time ago .
TheSupercritical water reactor ( SCWR ) is one of the generation IV reactors . The concept is that uses { supercritical water } [ HYPERLINK : http : //en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Supercritical_fluid ] as the working fluid .
Supercritical water-cooled reactors ( SCWRS ) are the most advanced nuclear systems . They can generate high thermal efficiency .
( Nuclear power plants , 2009 ) .The proliferation of the new nuclear technology is causing considerable controversy and concern . Opponents say that nuclear reactors may be a serious threat to the world populace as well as the environment .
However , there are two sides to the coin , in my point of view , the generation IV Supercritical water-cooled reactor is worth building in the near future by analysing the pros and cons .
Opponents are apprehensive about the hazards of nuclear reactors .
