It is safe and efficient , so therefore it can produce a lot of energy and is able to replace traditional sources of energy .
Hence , only a few countries have built nuclear reactors to produce electricity .
But now , scientists have developed six new types of nuclear reactors called Nuclear Reactor Generation IV which are said to be safer than previous generations .
Although GFR produces fuel waste that contains plutonium , it reprocesses its fuel waste such that the amount of waste produced can be cut by about 96 percent ( " Fuel Cycles " , page 33 , table 4.3 ) .
For comparison , VHTR can not reprocess its fuel waste , and because of that , the amount of fuel waste that it produces is getting bigger and bigger as the electricity demand increases ( Rohrer , 2007 ) .
Different from VHTR , which can work on 1000 degrees Celsius , GFR can work only on 850 degrees Celsius .
They say GFR produces less energy than VHTR. .
One more important information is thatt there is no need for GFR to be manually moderated because GFR has already used Thorium which can absorb fast neutrons and decay into Uranium-233 ( " Gas-cooled Fast Reactor " ) .
This makes GFR cheaper to maintain and safer than VHTR which needs to be checked every time in order to make it operate safely .
It is also more efficient than other reactors , because it can produce the same energy as VHTR at just 850 degrees
Since then , Nuclear power was often seen as the best alternative energy source as it has no carbon emission and can theoretically produce an unlimited amount of energy since nuclear fuel is inexpensive and abundant on earth .
This stigma against nuclear power has led people such as the general public and environmentalists to favor other alternative energies namely wind energy and solar energy , as they are deemed as better choices .
However , many of these arguments are based on short run expenditure that one would face when building a nuclear power plant .
In the long run , after considering the higher capital cost , financing costs and operating costs of a nuclear reactor , a nuclear reactor would still produce much cheaper electricity when compared with other alternative energy sources such as wind energy .
This is because the Chernobyl accident caused many direct fatalities in the explosion and future fatalities due to the effects of nuclear radiation .
Besides reactor accidents , nuclear reactors may also be easy targets for terrorism as many nuclear reactors appear to be vulnerable to any form of terrorist attacks .
In addition , nuclear wastes are dangerous as well as they contain high levels of radiation and can be used for weapons of mass destruction as tons of plutonium nuclear waste are produced by nuclear reactors each year and are often recycled to make nuclear weapons .
On the other hand , since the Chernobyl accident 23 years ago , there has not been any other major nuclear power plant accident .
Moreover , Generation IV nuclear reactions , such as the sodium-cooled fast reactors , excel in many safety aspects such as having the ability to withstand up to a magnitude of 8.2 on the Richter scale and to shut down safely if any accidents were to happen ( Nuclear Power Plants , 2009 ) .
These new reactors are also more reliable and resistant against proliferation , and are able to use their fuel more efficiently , thus producing less plutonium waste ( Generation IV , 2009 ) .
With the technological advancement in nuclear power in mind , nuclear accidents and disasters would be a thing in the past as nuclear power plants will become safer in their operations .
Environmentalists would often suggest the use of alternative energy such as wind , hydroelectric , thermal and solar energies as these energies are known to have little emissions of any kind of pollutants .
These environmentalists would thus believe that nuclear power 's benefits to the environment are insignificant ( Nuclear power undermining , 2008 ) .. On the contrary , these beliefs are often biased against nuclear power .
In conclusion , more research and development of Generation IV nuclear power plant should be done as the many benefits of nuclear power clearly outweigh the disadvantages in many important factors such as cost efficiency , safety issues and environmental friendliness .
Generation IV nuclear reactor will allow mankind to fully realize the potential of nuclear power , thus encouraging further development on nuclear technology .
As a result of fewer fossil fuel supplies left to be extracted , oil companies will either search for smaller oil fields that will inevitably increase the cost of production of oil or look for unconventional sources of oil such as tar sands that will increase the level of carbon dioxide emission and pollution ( World Oil , National Geographic , June 2008 ) .The increasing demand for oil and the rising level of carbon dioxide emission , which contributes to global warming , have prompted the energy market to search for alternative energy sources .
The public is very concerned about the safety of nuclear power plants , the storage of radioactive waste and the cost it has to pay for nuclear power .
In contrast to public opinion on the adverse effect of building a nuclear power plant , the latest generation IV reactor , Very-High-temperature reactor ( VHTR ) , is designed to overcome these problems faced by the public .
The public is very concerned about the safety of nuclear power plants and fears that any factors that trigger the explosion of a nuclear reactor will have devastating impact on the people living in the region .
Ever since the partial reactor meltdown at Three Mile Island in 1979 and the Chernobyl nuclear accident in 1986 , the public feared that any similar incidents would have grave consequences to the people living around nuclear power plants .
All these measures are implemented to meet the safety expectation of the operation of nuclear power plants .
Any successful terror attacks on these nuclear plants will have disastrous health and psychological impact on surviving victims .
These measures comprise regular 'force-on-force ' exercises to test the plant 's ability to react to attacks made on it , vehicle inspection at greater safety distance away from the plant , improved communication among different government organizations and stricter access to restricted sites ( Source : NRC , February 2005 ) .
Other measures include bullet-proof barriers in important areas , intruding detecting devices , detection zones that are illuminated , well equipped and trained security personnel on daily duty and protection against intrusion of network by outsiders ( Nuclear Energy Institute ( NEI ) , July 2009 ) .
The purpose of these stepped up security measures is to deter any potential terrorist attacks on nuclear power plants and to have a contingency plan in the event of any attacks .
Another reason why the public and environmentalists oppose the building of nuclear power plants is that the radioactive waste produced by nuclear power plants will remain radioactive for hundred over years .
When radioactive waste is not properly stored in location that is of safe distance away from people , the people may be exposed to harmful radiation resulting in serious health effects .
The public does not need to worry about the large amount of radioactive waste produced by VHTR because VTHR spent fuel is contained in a repository that is very resistant to leaching of radioactive materials .
The public is worried that nuclear power tends to have higher operating and maintenance costs which will result in them paying a higher price than that of coal and gas power plants .
According to the World Nuclear Association , the price of nuclear power is actually competitive with other types of power plants .
For instance in 2007 , the cost of electricity generated by a nuclear plant is about 2.87cents per kilo-watt hour in comparison with 17.8 cents per kilo-watt hour in the case of oil power plant in the United States .
The cost of nuclear fuel is as low as 0.5 cents per kilo-watt hour which is one quarter of that of a gas power plant .
As compared to conventional nuclear power plants , there is greater efficiency in generating electricity because VHTR can produce fifty percent more electricity output using the same amount of fuel ( The Economics of Nuclear Power by World Nuclear Association , July 2009 ) .
The process heat can be provided by VHTR to support other industrial activities such as refining and manufacturing of fertilizers and plastics .
Therefore , the high operation cost of VTHR can be offset by extra revenue earned from these services ( Idaho National Laboratory , 2009 ) .
As the future of oil prices continues to rise due to the scarcity of supply and increase in demand by emerging economies , this will inevitably lead to a more competitive price of nuclear power .
However , with the designing of generation IV reactors such as VHTR , the problems of radioactive waste disposal and the high cost of electricity generated by nuclear power plant will be solved .
Moreover , there are many safety measures implemented to minimize potential dangers of operating VHTR .
With the increase in global population , the demand for energy is increasing .
According to the International Energy Agency ( January 2009 ) , worldwide energy consumption on average will increase 2 % per annum and will double by the next 35 years .
With the fuel prices soaring up , fossil fuel reserves dwindling and increased pressure to tackle climate change and global warming , nuclear energy is back in the agenda of many countries .
In 2001 , amidst increasing debates about nuclear energy , the ten founding nations of Generation IV International Forum also known as GIF decided to work together , collaborating on research activities in the field of nuclear energy ( Butler D , 2004 ) .
These collaborative efforts resulted in building up six possible nuclear reactor concepts known as the generation IV reactors . However these concepts at that time were still untested and would require years of further extensive research before they could be used in the industry .
Although six possible concepts were developed I personally believe that the molten salt fast reactor concept is the best solution amongst the six .
Nuclear energy is produced by splitting the nuclei of uranium atoms which in turn produce a large amount of energy that is used to drive turbines which produce electricity .
This procedure is extremely efficient so much so that one pound of uranium produces 20,000 times more energy compared to one pound coal .
However , according the World Energy Council there are only 442 nuclear reactors to date and currently they provide only 11 % to 18 % ( March , 2008 ) of the world electricity requirements .
After the Chernobyl accident in 1986 and Three Miles accident in 1979 ( Think quest , May 2007 ) many people fear the word " nuclear energy " , but if we consider the number of accidents since the commencement of operations of the world 's first nuclear power plant in the year 1954 ( Think quest , May 2007 ) , it is only a handful .
Also , the technology used in the production of nuclear energy has significantly improved in the past few decades and safety factors are analyzed thoroughly when a nuclear plant is designed following the Three Miles Island and Chernobyl accidents .
We should also not forget that accidents do happen in other energy related industries . For example , statistics show that there is one accident taking place in a coal mine somewhere around the world every week ( Mining Industry Today , August 2008 ) .
In contrast to other accidents , nuclear accidents are given more media coverage sparking public disapproval .
The primary cause of many nuclear accidents is overheating of water which is used as the coolant in nuclear fission reactions .
As a result of such overheating under high pressure an immense amount of steam is produced if uncontrolled . This causes the system to explode .
However , in molten salt reactors also known as MSRs fluoride salts are used instead of water as the coolant .
Fluoride salts has boiling temperatures over 1300o Celsius which is about 13 times higher than the boiling temperature of water and they are not flammable ( Forsberg CW , 2007 ) .
This further increases the probability of possible accidents . However , MSRs operate at much lower pressure levels and with Min a relatively low temperature range of 750 o C to 800 o C. ( World nuclear Association , August 2009 ) .
Thus these enhanced features of MSRs further reduce any possibility of any nuclear reactor-based accidents .
One such example is the mixed oxide fuel process ( commonly known as MOX ) used in France where Plutonium is converted to a form stored under very high temperature so that it can not be used to produce nuclear weaponry . Moreover , more than 90 % of the energy in spent fuel can be reprocessed and reused leaving only about 3 to 4 percent as net waste ( Ling K , The New York Times , May 2009 ) .
Furthermore , MSRs being closed fuel cycle nuclear reactors ( World nuclear Association , August 2009 ) reprocessing takes place minimizing nuclear waste .
In addition nuclear waste produced by MSRs is not soluble in water thus reducing chances of possible contamination .
Thus , through advanced research the cost of nuclear waste management can be reduced and the MSR technology can be enhanced to further minimize the harmful effects and to avoid nuclear waste proliferation .
Another challenge faced by the nuclear energy industry against other alternatives of energy is that building of nuclear power plants is very costly and time consuming .
Most nuclear reactors involve the use of the fast breeder technique but the MSRs use a technology known as slow breeder or thorium fuel cycle breeder which has been proven to be less expensive ( Forsberg CW , 2007 ) .
Besides , the operation costs involved in maintaining high temperature and pressure within nuclear reactors during nuclear fission is notably low in MSRs since they operate at a much lower temperature and pressure .
Also the concepts behind the MSRs are not completely New . Several have been already constructed with simple validated designs , thus this will reduce the time required in designing larger nuclear reactors ( Forsberg CW , 2007 ) .
Another important advantage of MSRs is that they can be built in a small scale first and can then be expanded gradually , so the plants could be easily built with several small reactors and from the income they can carry out expansions ( Forsberg CW , 2007 ) .
This further reduces cost and additional financial burden arising from interest expenses .
Therefore , MSRs are highly cost effective and efficient .
Compared to hydro or solar power , nuclear energy does not change the ecology of a certain environment .
Unlike wind turbines , nuclear energy does not require specific environmental conditions and compared to fossil fuels , they do not produce green house gases , However , the future of nuclear energy depends on further research where these generation IV reactors have to be tested , constructed and operated in such a way that they can provide competitive prices while maximizing the usage of natural resources and enhancing nuclear safety .
They also need to address the fears of the public so that people are more aware of the advantages of nuclear energy .
In conclusion , all earlier mentioned objectives can not be achieved without necessary funding .
In an era where global warming is a burning issue , when the effects of extreme climate change are already evident , nuclear energy may be the ultimate solution to greener energy alternative , thus it is indeed time for us to move forward by challenging our fears and supporting funding for research based on nuclear reactors .
Nuclear power -- an evolutionary discovery that is capable of replacing conventional thermal power stations for decades or even centuries .
Nuclear power makes use of a common element on Earth , which is uranium .
The atoms of uranium are shot against each other , processing an incredible amount of gamma radiation and heat .
Nuclear power plants have been around for decades and according to Brain and Lamb ( 2007 ) , 430 operating nuclear plants have been providing power to the world as of July 2008 .
Nuclear plants have come a long way since the early days and the world has witnessed two major accidents , the Chernobyl and Three Mile Island Incident .
According to Butler ( 2004 ) , Generation IV nuclear reactors comprise of six different types of reactors , Gas-cooled fast reactors , Lead-cooled fast reactors , Sodium-cool fast reactors , Supercritical-water-cooled reactors , Very-high-temperature reactors and lastly Molten salt reactors which will be discussed in this article .
Generation IV nuclear reactors including the Molten salt reactors are designed to be safer and preven similar incidents such as the Chernobyl and Three Mile Island from happening again .
Molten-Salt-Reactor technology as one of the six Generation IV nuclear reactors is designed with these factors in mind -- safe , environmentally friendly and cheap in their use of electricity . However , with all the different concerns involved , this might not be the case .
In addition , MSRs use liquid fuel as compared to the other reactors that use solid fuel .
MSRs are high temperature reactors , depending on the choice of salt ; it could range from 320 to 500 degrees Celsius .
In addition , the close helium or nitrogen Brayton power cycles are adopted thus allowing the high temperature generated by the MSRs to be efficiently used .
MSRs handle the situation by having excellent safety measures to handle emergencies .
When the situation calls for it , there is a drainage system to cool the critical safe dump tanks using the liquid fuel .
Firstly , despite the safety of MSRs , one can never forget the devastating Chernobyl incident in April 1986 .
Approximately 200,000 people were involved in the clean up from the accident and these people were exposed to high radiation .
More people were then evacuated from their homes as the radiation spread widely and rapidly .
Currently there are people around the world who are still suffering from the after effects of such an accident , living in pain where some develop cancer from the exposure to radiation .
Even with the new safety precautions which promise excellent safety measures and technology , no one can guarantee that such accidents would not cause more people to suffer .
For example , the Titanic , the largest ship built then , and was equipped with the most advanced technology and safety measures at the time .
A collision with an iceberg during her maiden voyage still sent the enormous ship deep down onto the sea bed .
Secondly , nuclear plants are said to be environmentally friendly due to the fact that they do not produce Carbon Dioxide .
As a result , it helps reduce the greenhouse effect .
On the other hand , the wastes produced by nuclear plants are highly radioactive and can not be easily disposed .
During transportation , there might be leakage from containers , and the effects of burying the waste underground are yet to be confirmed till years to come .
In addition , these waste disposal process might become an open target to terrorists who are constantly keen on destruction .
Lastly , nuclear power might be more cost effective as compared to the conventional thermal power stations . However the cost of constructing the plant is significantly higher , as well as the operational and waste disposal costs .
The construction cost involves research on the material so as to contain radiation in the event of a nuclear meltdown .
Labor costs include labor from various departments in the nuclear plant .
These include maintenance , health , engineering and headquarters .
Thirdly , engineering consists of electrical , chemical , computer , radiological , nuclear and mechanical aspects .
Lastly , headquarters consist of mainly administrative personnel .
The waste disposal cost of a nuclear power plant is higher than a conventional thermal station .
The cost involves transportation of the waste to various storage ponds and dumping grounds , and the running costs of these sites .
In conclusion , Generation IV MSR does provide energy hungry cities with the amount of electricity needed and it reduces greenhouse effect due to the zero carbon dioxide emission , and lastly it is much safer than the previous Generation plants with enhanced meltdown technology .
On the other hand , the danger of nuclear radiation , fear of terrorism and the high initial and running cost of a Generation IV nuclear plant , make us consider if there are any other alternatives .
Nuclear power is not a new concept .
This is due to nuclear power 's close relation with nuclear weapons and the public 's concerns with the safety of nuclear reactors .
Frankly speaking , nuclear reactors and nuclear weapons share the same basic theoretic foundation-the chain reaction of uranium .
Since nuclear power does not generate carbon dioxide , it was once regarded as the best replacement for fossil fuels .
But after the terrible partial reactor meltdown in 1979 at Three Mile Island and the 1986 accident at Chernobyl , nuclear power gradually has gone out of the public 's sight .
The new generation reactors , namely generation IV reactors , have tremendous potential in improving reactors ' efficiency and safety .
This by-product of nuclear power is also a kind of clean energy ; in place of oil the third advantage VHTR has is practical experience .
Nevertheless , in spite of so many advantages VHTR has got , it still faces some technical challenges .
One of the most essential ones is the high cost of a reactor , which will deeply affect the development of the whole nuclear industry .
Based on a report from the U.S. Department of Energy , even a prototype , which is just a sample run of the practical reactor , will require $ 1.25 billion to build ( Korman , 2008 ) .
The high temperature and pressure , which give birth to the advantage of producing hydrogen , on the other hand , mean a high risk of accident .
In terms of high cost of a reactor , significant cost deduction can be achieved by design improvement , standardisation , better construction methods , reduced construction time and improving project management in building a reactor ( OECD ) , 2005 ) .
Meanwhile the high efficiency of fuel utilization in VHTR makes reactors use less fuels which in turn lower the cost of fuels ( OECD ) , 2005 ) .
For finding suitable materials , although the perfect solution has not been found yet , engineers do have some suggested materials that have potential to develop , such as silicon carbide , specific grades of graphite and high chromium steels ( Murty & Charit , 2008 ) .
Lastly , the design of VHTR enhances safety features and excludes sophisticated backup systems or experienced operators so as to minimise human intervention .
The rising sea level , the increase in natural disasters , the proliferation of pandemics , which are the by-products of industrial development , along with the depletion of fossil fuel , demand a new source of energy .
To me , these thoughts on safety - daily danger , accidents and waste , cost and security , can be completely expunged from our minds with the new reactor technology , specifically the lead-cooled fast reactor .
Economically , the price of electricity generated from radioactive fuel would be much lower than that generated from fossil fuel due to the enormous energy churned out from fission reaction .
In addition , as the new nuclear reactor works at high temperature , scientists can utilize it to produce hydrogen from thermochemical reaction of water , which is material for other industries .
About the negative effects , the first argument concerns the impact of radiation on humans due to the routine operation of a nuclear plant .
However , according to the Journal of the American Medical Association published by the National Cancer Institute , a major survey showed that there was no rise in cancer rates in 107 US counties near 62 nuclear plants .
In fact , the amount of radiation that people living in the neighborhood of a nuclear plant are exposed to is really miniscule in comparison with that from natural sources .
According to the Atomic Energy Commission , power plants using coal produce ash that contains 5.2 tons of uranium and 12.8 tons of thorium per year .
Regarding nuclear accidents , it is the modern reactor generation that is invulnerable to the meltdown incident .
Granted , we can not deny their impact , such as the Chernobyl and Three Mile Island accidents , but the new technology can eliminate the possibility of these accidents .
It has double-walled container and a lot of core-cooling emergency systems .
Moreover , since accidents are mainly brought about by the leaking of the cooling tube , lead is chosen to reduce this possibility .
Lead is an inert substance preventing corrosion .
Besides , the effects of accidents in coal and oil industries are noticeable , such as oil spills , mining accidents , let alone the environmental effects of the toxic fumes they produce .
As far as radioactive waste is concerned , a lead-cooled fast reactor is designed best to cut back on the amount of high level waste .
It has a closed cycle and high operating temperature in order to increase the efficiency and lower the radioactive waste .
Furthermore , the high level waste is turned into a rock-like form before it is embedded into a deep rock layer whose lifetime is about one billion years .
On the other hand , the emissions of coal and oil industries are still lingering in our atmosphere , which impact on the number of respiratory disease .
Therefore , in terms of safety , the new lead-cooled fast reactor can really outweigh coal and oil plants .
Another rationale behind protests against nuclear plants is that it takes a huge capital investment to build up a nuclear plant ( from $ 3 to $ 5 billion dollars ) ( Nuclear Energy Information Service , 2004 ) , to research the new reactors ( approximate 1 billion US dollars for each prototype of generation IV reactors ) ( Nature publishing group , 2004 ) .
From the viewpoint of those against , to gain such a sum , the government has to cut off its expenditure on on education , health , etc , and raise taxes .
In my opinion , it is essential to invest in a new nuclear power plant .
First , if the government fosters research and development in the nuclear industry , the cost for building and maintaining the new nuclear power plant will be affordable .
Second , the expenditure can be compensated for by profit since a nuclear plant is competitive in comparison with coal and oil industries in terms of productivity and environment .
Third , fossil resources are shrinking rapidly , so the cost for coal and oil would increase sharply in the future .
Last , if the country continues producing energy without reducing the burning of oil and coal , health and social service expenses will rise .
At any rate , the government has to increase its expenditure .
For the lead-cooled fast reactor , it has new features to increase the longevity of core life , and scientists have come up with the idea of creating a medium size reactor to reduce the cost .
They believe that the development of nuclear states might create opportunities to produce nuclear weapons from plutonium reprocessing and uranium enriching .
Terrorists may also have the chance to magnify the destruction by attacking nuclear plants and freighters that carry radioactive substances .
However , the new lead-cooled fast reactor , as I have mentioned , has many emergency systems that make the reactor " meltdown proof " even in cases of human interference .
In other words , it reduces the amount of foreign energy import , so it can help solve disputes over energy , especially oil .
In conclusion , the new generation IV nuclear reactor , in particular the lead-cooled fast reactor , is an optimal choice for future energy in three fronts - safety , cost and security - though there are still many challenges ahead .
Thus , the government should invest more in nuclear power development to make construction of these reactors a feasible feat .
For the past few decades , the engineering field has developed drastically to a new level .
At the same time , the peril and hazard of engineering installations and systems rise in response to complexity .
The result was a series of engineering accidents : Three Mile Island , Chernobyl , the Challenger and more .
Interestingly , the analysis reports of these accidents invariably described human factors as the major cause of the accidents .
Supporters claim that psychology can help to reduce the probability of accidents and emphasize the value of human lives .
Opponents , mainly composed of engineers and operators , consider costs more and somehow ignore safety measure as it is reasonable for suppliers to produce at a minimum cost .
Although engineers and operators tend to oppose the use of psychology in engineering design process , research results have shown the importance of psychology in preventing accidents by using their professional knowledge .
One of the most famous accidents -- the Chernobyl accident that occurred on 26 April 1986 in the Soviet Ukraine -- is a typical type of engineering accident .
Frot 's ( 2000 ) studies gave two main causes of the explosion of the Chernobyl reactors : design errors and faults of management and errors committed by the operating staff .
While psychology is described as a necessity in improving the safety measures during a design process , opponents are still sceptical about the validity and reliability of psychology research .
Karanian ( 1988 ) showed how engineers think : " The content is considered repetitive and filled with slanted views and reflective of self-interest and personal bias " .
However , their disbelief is mainly due to their lack of knowledge about studies in psychology .
According to the International Ergonomics Association ( 2000 ) , engineering psychology is defined as " the scientific discipline concerned with the understanding of interactions among humans and other elements of a system , and the profession that applies theory , principles , data and methods to design in order to optimize human well-being and overall system performance " .
It does not only reflect on how human thinking solve human errors but it also uses sophisticated theory and principles .
For example , one famous psychology law -- Hick 's Law -- describes the amount of time that a person takes to make a decision , given several possible choices he or she has .
It can be seen that psychology is a professional field that has been accepted by society and the theories and principles are useful in analysing latent designing errors .
Still , opponents argue that accidents are unpredictable as there are too many possible causes .
However , research has shown that causes are basically formed by human errors .
In the Chernobyl accident , six human errors were identified ( Frot , 2000 ) .
During a design process , designers do not focus on human response to the design and there is frequent mismatch between operators and designed machines ( Wilpert , 2007 ) .
However , psychology takes human behaviours into consideration while using the machines and they look into questions like " Are the machines too complex for the operators to deal with ?
A single error will usually not produce an accident but it arises from a number of failures ( Noyes , 1997 ) .
For the Chernobyl accident , there were five major design errors ( Frot , 2000 ) .
Psychology is useful in foreseeing latent errors and thus it is easier to come out with a solution that will reduce the probability of an accident .
It can be done by designing a less complex device , giving more useful information and practice for operators in charge , designing better backup systems and so on .
With the aid of psychology which focuses on safety measures , accidents are more likely to be avoided .
In brief , while engineering has become a much sophisticated field , safety measures have become more and more important at the same time .
Human errors are unavoidable , but psychology is meant to reduce the effect caused by these errors .
In the current world , nuclear technology has evolved significantly and researchers have come out with many prototypes and systems which can benefit the world .
The latest systems are the Generation IV nuclear systems which were introduced in 2002 .
Now , the 6 nuclear energy systems are technologies which include advantages like reduced capital cost , enhanced nuclear safety , minimal generation of nuclear waste , and further reduction of the risk of weapon material proliferation .
Gen IV systems are designed to be highly sustainable because the energy they produce meets the desire for clean air and in the long term , benefits the environment .
( Bouchard,J ) , Each system has its own advantages in terms of performance , cost and security ( Generation IV International Forum GIF and U.S. Nuclear Energy Research Advisory Committee NERAC ) .
It operates at 400 ~ 500 during its operation .
We measure performance by the output of the system and the amount of power it can generate .
Since the lead-cooled fast reactor is not a large scale reactor , its output is not as much if we compare it to reactors like Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) .
The VHTR is a helium-cooled , graphite-moderated , thermal neutron spectrum reactor with a coolant outlet temperature of 1000 Â° C or above .
VHTR outperforms other reactors because of its potential to produce hydrogen .
From this , we can see that VHTR greatly outperforms LFR .
On 26 April 1986 at the Chernobyl Nuclear Power Plant in Ukraine , there was a nuclear reactor accident which resulted in the deaths of many due to radiation poisoning .
To prevent such accidents from happening again , much emphasis has been put into the safety aspect of nuclear reactors being designed .
The publication by MPR further added that these features of VHTR replace the current safety systems in current reactors .
This removes any possible corrosion or irradiation which could occur with the component materials .
In addition , helium does not go through any phase change at or over reactor operating temperature ; this will improve safety because the design and operation are being simplified .
Due to the extremely hard reprocessing of its fuel , it deters any means to misuse them since the process is very complicated .
Although this feature does not really decrease the chance of reprocessing to zero , it does complicate the means to try to reprocess them
( Chapin et al,2004 ) .
On the other hand , lead-cooled fast reactors ( LFRs ) have various safety issues which are of concern when it comes to building a safe reactor .
( Generation IV International Forum GIF and U.S. Nuclear Energy Research Advisory Committee NERAC ) . This will pose as a threat for workers at the reactors due to the corrosion of the materials .
Because the Gen IV 's VHTR systems are built on the older generation of high temperature reactors , therefore many of the safety systems which already existed in the old reactors are further being enhanced . In this way , the safety systems in VHTR do exceed the ones in LFRs .
For the generation IV nuclear reactor systems , the cost of the individual reactors varies and some are far more costly than others .
The estimated cost of building a 100MWE prototype of lead-cooled fast reactor in the U.S. is between $ 400- $ 700 million
) . Compared with this , the cost of building a VHTR reactor is much higher ; it has an estimated cost of about $ 1.1 billion
( Butler , D.2004 , May 20 ) .
This is partially due to the reason that VHTR 's coolant , helium gas , is much more costly than LFRs ' coolant , and because of the strong structure that VHTR consists , it costs more to build .
In conclusion , both Very high temperature and lead-cooled fast reactors have good performance and excellent safety systems , but VHTRs are on a higher end as compared to LFRs due to the greater system performance and system safety it provides .
Hence , VHTRs are , to some extent , better than LFRs .
This kind of energy-producing method did make a big contribution to the industrialization of the world , but it also did a lot of harm to the natural environment .
However , there is no doubt that the energy demand will continue to increase , since human beings can not slow down the pace of technology development .
In this case , we have to consider more new energy .
The recent research and development of generation IV nuclear reactor makes the large scale use of nuclear energy more reliable and feasible because of its sustainability , reliability , economics and proliferation resistance .
Some may say that a nuclear plant is dangerous , after experiencing nuclear accidents in the last few decades .
However , generation IV reactors are quite different from the previous ones .
Here , we are going to discuss two of the generation IV reactors , Gas-cooled Fast Reactor ( GFR ) , which features a fast-neutron-spectrum , helium-cooled reactor and closed fuel cycle , and Supercritical Water-cooled Reactor ( SWCR ) , which is a high-temperature , high-pressure water-cooled reactor that operates above the thermodynamic critical point of water .
I think that GFR does a better job than SWCR in the aspect of efficiency , cost and security .
Yes , they are right , but they are just comparing SWCR with generation III reactors , not the GFR reactor .
According to statistical data provided by Idaho National Laboratory , the thermal efficiency of SWCR is 43.8 % , which is lower than that of GFR , 48 % .
What is more , GFR also gets hydrogen production .
The only production of combusting hydrogen is water and burning the same amount of hydrogen or other fuels , we get much more energy from hydrogen .
After referring to most of the budget reports , which say that building a GFR plant will cost 1 billion while a SWCR plant only takes half a billion , many people believe that GFR is much more expensive than SWCR .
This may be true , note that most of the budget reports are not able to take all the expenditure into consideration , which of course is not convincing .
Although GFR costs more than SWCR according to the reports , the life of GFR is also longer .
In other words , a GFR plant can work a few decades longer than SWCR .
Another factor is that SWCR only can react under very high pressure .
We all know that the higher pressure it is the higher possibility the reactor will break down .
So maintenance cost also should be taken into account .
Moreover , GFR has an effective fission of Pu and minor actinides , ability to operate on a wide range of fuel composition and capacity for breeding excess fissile material ( Frank Carre , 2002 ) .
Last but not the least is the security .
Many people 's main fear of nuclear comes from the several nuclear accidents in the last few decades , such as the Three Mail Island one in 1979 and the Chernobyl one in 1986 .
So now , people are concerned most about the security of any kind of nuclear plants .
Some think that SWCR is safer than GFR because once an accident happens , the pressure of SWCR will decrease immediately , and then the plant will shut down automatically .
Actually , it is not true because the safety issue is not only about pressure inside .
Second , the coolant of GFR is helium , a kind of inert gas , which hardly reacts with other reagent .
In conclusion , Gas-cooled Fast Reactor is better than Supercritical Water-cooled Reactor , in the areas of efficiency , expend and security .
I believe that GFR is one of the most promising generation IV nuclear reactors , and its large scale application is just around the corner .
The accident caused many deaths and resulted in severe health impacts due to the population 's exposure to radiation ( Cleveland , 2009 ) .
On the other hand , the supporters claim that through the use of psychology , the engineers might have has anticipated different scenarios that could happen and designed a safer and more stable plant .
In other words , the Chernobyl accident could have been prevented and if better safety measures were in place , the effects of the accident would have been minimized .
The problem of psychopathology of design refers to a mismatch of the engineers ' and the operators ' theoretical models which happened in this case .
The use of occupational psychology could have aided the engineers in understanding that the operators might not have been equipped with the necessary skills and knowledge to operate the plant .
They could have exercised precaution such that unauthorized personnel could not shut down the emergency safety systems ( World Nuclear Association , 2007 ) .
At the very least , it would have had weakened the severity of the consequences .
The Chernobyl reactor was unstable due to the positive void coefficient which made power exacerbation uncontrollable .
However , this instead posed a challenge to psychology to help modify the plant design through the method of feed-forward safety controls which could be applied in the ( Wilpert , 2007 ) .
The engineers should be aware of the limitations of the reactor and the use of psychology could have led them to use a better reactor or install other measures to counter the weaknesses of the reactor .
Furthermore , when some reactor components fail to work correctly , the operators face more stress ( Stang , 1996 ) .
Such external conditions are not part of design process and hence the use of psychology would not be helpful .
However , occupational threats and individual workplace misfortunes are the focus of psychology as they are influenced by the individual 's motivation , attitude and decision-making ( Wilpert , 2007 ) .
On the contrary , psychology could have helped the engineers foresee possible problems during the operation and more safety precaution could have been incorporated .
The use of psychology might have prevented the Chernobyl accident and the effects of the accident would have been minimized .
Moreover , nuclear energy is environmentally friendly because it has very low emission of green house gases .
However , only " 16 % of the world 's electricity is produced from nuclear energy " ( Nuclear Power Reactors , 2009 ) .
One nuclear accident was the Chernobyl accident in 1986 .
A total of 54 people died in this accident ( Chernobyl Accident , 2009 ) .
Therefore , in recent years , scientists and engineers have developed six Generation VI reactors that are cost effective , safer , and minimize waste ( Misak , 2009 ) .
This essay will focus on sodium-cooled fast reactors ( SFR ) in comparison with supercritical-water-cooled reactors ( SWCR ) based on three aspects : performance , cost , and safety , and show that the SFR is a better concept than the SWCR .
On performance , proponents of the SWCR claim that the thermal efficiency of this reactor is 44 % , compared to the SFR 's 42 % ( Generation IV Nuclear Reactor Comparisons , 2008 ) .
However , the difference is not very much and they fail to consider that SWCR is working in the environment of very high pressure , while SFR is working in low pressure .
On the other hand , SFR is more sustainable because of its closed fuel cycle and excellent potential of actinide management
Compare this to SWCR ; in a word , sodium-cooled fast reactors do well in performance .
In terms of cost , proponents of SWCR claim that SWCR has a longer history of development while SFR is a newer concept that has just been brought up in recent years .
People who are against nuclear reactors even claim that the existing method of generating electricity is good enough and a new method is not necessary .
However , these shortsighted people fail to realize that global shortage of resources is already very serious .
Hence , the invention of generation IV reactors can both generate electricity in a more efficient way and more fuel-saving way .
For SFR , it saves costs through two main methods : the reactor vessel and fuel .
The usage of advanced materials , the loop type cooling system and innovative design options , are all adopted to save plant capital costs .
For SWCR , it does not recycle the waste ; nuclear waste management is also one concern with SWCR in terms of both cost and safety .
The third point to emphase is that SFR has the earliest delivery time which is 10 years earlier than SWCR .
This means that the time and money required to do the research for SFR are much less than that of SWCR .
We can conclude that SFR is also cost-effective .
Taking safety into account , opponents of nuclear reactors state accidents in the past to prove that they is not safe .
For this reason , SFR pays special attention to safety issues .
Its operating temperature is as low as SWCR 's .
SFR also recycles radioactive materials thus decreases the risk of leakage of such dangerous materials .
SWCR does not recycle waste which is not that safe .
Moreover , to protect the workers in the nuclear power station , only low occupational radioactivity ( Corradini , 2005 ) .
Hence , SFR is very safe .
In conclusion , the sodium-cooled fast reactor is rated better in performance , capability to save cost , and safety .
Its research should continue as there is much use of it in the future .
Generation four nuclear reactor plants went into development with the hope of creating a new nuclear reactor plant that can replace the current old generation three reactor plants .
The new nuclear reactor may be high in cost for research but it has better performance , safety and security measures than the old generator plants .
In this new development , experts have looked into 6 new nuclear reactor plant concepts like molten salt reactor ( MSR ) and Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) .
MSR researchers did intensify research to ensure that it has superior safety standards and fuel cycle qualities than VHTR .
Therefore , research in MSR costs about $ 1000 million as compared to VHTR 's research which costs about $ 670 million as quoted from the report on " a technology roadmap for generation IV Nuclear Energy system " .
The latter costs only 20 % less than the former and the difference in money spent is used to build generation 4 reactor 's standards .
From the report , researchers for MSR distributed a lot of funds in areas like safety , reactor system and fuel cycle as compared to fund distribution in these areas of research in VHTR .
Fuel cycle in MSR needs to have more attention as compared to VHTR because there is a need to ensure that molten salt which is mixed with nuclear material will still be functional after many rounds of usage in the system .
The idea of MSR is that it will produce less waste and be able to recycle it .
Therefore , the effort put into this area of research is to make MSR a cleaner nuclear reactor plant that reduces , reuses and recycles its waste .
The molten fluoride salt used in the system helps to lower vapor pressure , thus , reduces stresses on vessel and piping .
A highly pressurized system is dangerous and needs to be consistently monitored to ensure a safe operation as stresses acting on the pipes and vessel can cause the system to explode .
When MSR is operating at high temperature of eight hundred degrees and above , it can produce another good energy source .
Hydrogen can be used to generate power for machines like hydrogen-powered cars which are clean for the environment .
The fuel used in MSR can be recycled as mentioned earlier .
However , in the case of VHTR , the fuel used is one through fuel cycle and therefore , it requires proper disposal .
The Molten Salt reactor is a lot safer in performance and operation than the Very High Temperature Reactor
MSR works based on 3 independent sub stations and is a closed loop that interlink with each other to transfer heat energy to electric energy by turning on the turbine generator .
In case of an industrial accident in one of the systems , operators can easily isolate that particular system and rectify the problem as quickly as possible without worrying that the problem might spread to parts of the other two systems .
MSR 's design works on fail-safe drainage , passive cooling , and low inventory of volatile fission products in fuel .
As for VHTR , it has only one open loop system to produce electricity from heat .
Overall , MSR also operates at lower pressure than VHTR as low temperature results in lower pressure .
One of the reasons for development in Generation 4 nuclear reactor plants is security reason .
The waste products produced by the current old nuclear plants can not be recycled and need to be disposed at wasteland .
If these wastes landed on the wrong hands like terrorists , the world would be in chaos as we live in fear of nuclear attacks by unknown enemies .
Wastes generated by these nuclear plants also bring problems to future generations .
As these wastes take very long to degrade , the land that holds them will become a wasteland which is not suitable for agricultural , residential and commercial usages .
Therefore , Generation 4 nuclear reactor plants like MSR recycle their waste products and do not need to dispose them .
However , in VHTR , as mentioned earlier , it produces wastes and researchers are trying to find solutions to it .
In conclusion , even though MSR costs more due to research than VHTR , its benefits outshine VHTR .
Its performance in low pressure quality can help to reduce stresses on equipment and less chances of industrial accidents than a high pressure system which induces high stress to the equipment .
It is safer than VHTR as it has better safety standards .
Lastly , in the area of security , MSR will not create chances of producing waste that will land on the wrong hands like the terrorists as compared to VHTR which has to deal with secured and proper waste disposal .
In recent years , we have seen that nuclear power is one of the main sources for generating electrical energy .
As of September 2009 , there have been 436 nuclear reactors worldwide and another 53 nuclear reactors under construction .
An undeniable fact is that a total of 14 percent of the world 's energy was produced by nuclear reactors in 2008 ( Nuclear Energy Institute , 2009 ) . Another shocking fact is that 76.2 percent of electrical energy is generated by nuclear reactors in France ( Nuclear Energy Institute , 2009 ) .
There are always concerns about the safe operations of nuclear reactors , opponents of the supporters of nuclear reactors note that the public 's irrational fears towards radiation .
I have chosen the Supercritical water-cooled reactor to support the argument for further research and development funding for generation IV reactors .
The public often have doubts when it comes to security and safety issues concerning nuclear reactors .
However , the Supercritical water-cooled reactor is one of the safest reactors compared to current generation II and III reactors .
events that lead to the occurrence of such possibilities would probably not reach the nuclear vessel ( Carl & Mark , 2005 ) .
Ever since the Three Miles Island incident , many new safety regulations have been implemented ; also in SCWR , emergency plans have been set up to prevent such things from happening again .
Such plans are to assist in protecting people within the 10-mile radius .
Normally , the economics of nuclear reactors are basic construction costs , operating costs , the life-time of the plant and the rate of return on capital ( Solar Energy Systems ) .
Critics often said that the overall cost for using nuclear energy has increased over the years and was relatively high ( Jack & Nicolas , 2008 ) .
In contrast , with the new SCWR , it is possible to decrease its cost since it is cheaper to build than existing nuclear reactors in the United States which consist of the Pressurized Water Reactors and Boiled Water Reactors .
Performance is measured through the efficient production of electricity , the production and recycle of waste disposal , and the method and characteristics of the nuclear reactor .
Critics often said that nuclear reactors are unsafe , impractical and low in performance .
The Generation-IV International Forum ( GIF ) has been formed in order to improve the current generation reactors , thus also improving the performance of the Generation IV reactors .
It should be evident that the arguments against supporting further research and development funding for Generation IV reactors are not valid .
Furthermore , the cost of the SCWR which is lower compared to existing LWR reactors also plays an important role in further research on Generation IV reactors .
Nonetheless , the formation of the GIF and the increase in performance SCWR are also another reason for further research and development of the nuclear reactor .
Therefore , the development of the Generation IV reactors will surely benefit mankind and help with energy demands of the future .
Comparing this with open human surgeries , patients can only return to their daily activities after 4 to 6 weeks .
However , as surgical robots are still not widely used , there are some constraints which patients are concerned about .
When it comes to patients ' safety , some questions such as the reliability of surgical robots are raised by the public .
Every movement of the robot 's arms is controlled by the surgeon ( Morristown Memorial Hospital , 2009 ) .
Some patients chose robotic surgery solely because of the shorter recovery time ( U.S. news , 2009 ) .
A research carried out by Detroit 's Henry Ford Hospital ( 2003 ) states that 100 patients who undergo robotic surgery lost less blood than 100 who had traditional open surgery .
Robotic surgery is useful in some ways such as microscopic precision ; it saves manpower and ergonomics .
The surgical robot has keyhole techniques to reach previously untouchable tissues during surgery as compared to traditional open surgery ( Bonsor , 2008 ) .
With the robot , surgeons can now sit comfortably controlling the robots , hands positioned in a natural forward position , relieving stress as unlike in traditional open surgery ( Morristown Memorial Hospital , 2009 ) .
The government will also subsidize for the cost of the system and also for people who are in need of financial help .
Actual precision such as keyhole techniques produces less scarring and less blood loss .
This will enhance safety of patients .
Although the cost of the surgery is high , given the high quality provided from the robots such as shorter hospital stays , faster recovery and safe operation , surgical robots should therefore be encouraged worldwide .
What we are facing for the next few hundred , or even tens of , years is .
Also , it helps ease global warming .
Nevertheless , , there are still some concerns about using nuclear energy : The most important one is about the safety of nuclear power plants , especially its potential for radioactive pollution .
Another problem is the performance of nuclear power plants with respect to their cost .
Since it is much more expensive than the usually used firepower plant , whether nuclear power plants can provide electricity efficiently with a reasonable cost became a rather essential problem .
Considering the above three concerns -- safety , cost and performance , the Generation IV International Forum , formed by ten countries , puts forward six outstanding protocols into Research and Development .
In this essay , I will only compare two of the six reacting systems -- Sodium-Cooled Fast Reactor ( SFR ) and Very-High-Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) based on safety , cost and performance considerations to illustrate that SFR is more superior to the other .
However , according to the design , SFR is an entirely closed system containing nuclear fuel and Sodium that can only reach the inner surface of the reactor .
Moreover , a secondary sodium system is designed as a Passive safety confirmation in case of emergency .
Another issue is about the performance , or economic evaluation , of these two reactors .
Because of the temperature factor , the power supplier SFR can not be as efficient as VHTR , which can achieve efficiency higher than 50 % ( " A Technology Roadmap for Generation IV Nuclear Energy Systems " , 2002 ) .
Yet , SFR is still quite efficient and economical in terms of its recycle of nuclear fuel and flexibility in the plant structure .
Accompanied with its effective recovery and recycle of actinides , SFR can achieve converting 99 % of natural uranium energy into electricity .
More specifically , its power supply can range from a few hundred MW ( e ) for a Mid-Size plant to 1500- 1700 MW ( e ) for a Large Monolithic plant ( " A Technology Roadmap for Generation IV Nuclear Energy Systems " , 2002 ) .
However , VHTR only can be built as a Large Monolithic plant .
That means SFR is able to meet the economic requirements of different situations better than other reactors .
Hence , the SFR still can meet performance and economic requirements in the future .
Thirdly , about cost , it is quite clear that SFR is among those low-cost Generation IV nuclear reactors , whether based on Research and Development or plant features .
Especially with only 610M $ , the cost of Research and Development of SFR is exactly the lowest one compared to the other five protocols ( " A Technology Roadmap for Generation IV Nuclear Energy Systems " , 2002 ) .
A hugeuge amount of nuclear energy will come out during atomic reactions .
Because of its high efficiency and enormous quantity , nuclear power energy has developed rapidly in recent years .
However , many negative aspects of nuclear energy , such as radiation pollution , waste heat , greenhouse gas emission etc , also cause people to question its reliability .
Nowadays people argue about the safety and economic cost of nuclear power generation and they doubt its ability to help ease climate change as well asserted specifically by some scientists .
According to scientific observations of nuclear power generation and the positive effect of nuclear energy , there is no doubt that nuclear power is one of the best ways for energy generation , although there are some negative influences .
One of the most controversial issues is the safety of nuclear power plants .
Everyone knows that nuclear reaction produces a lot of radiation waste which will harm human health .
In the past years , accidents did happen .
One catastrophic example was the Chernobyl accident in 1986 in Russia which caused 28 deaths within 4 months and up to 56 fatalities by 2004 just because of steam explosion and a slight waste release of the radiation of the reactor 's core ( Chernobyl Accident , April 2009 ) .
Nevertheless , scientists found that nuclear power risks are actually tiny and they can also be further reduced through using the updated technological reactors .
Facts also indicated that the record of the operational safety of nuclear plants is much better than any other types of power plants ( debate on nuclear power , n.d ) .
Millions and billions of dollars will have to be spent to build a nuclear power plant .
For example , in May 2008 the congressional budget office reported that the actual cost for the construction of 75 nuclear power plants in the USA is 45.2 billion dollars ; furthermore , they eventually cost 144.6 billion dollars after taking the facilities into account ( { Benjamin K. S. } [ HYPERLINK : http : //scitizen.com/screens/usersPage/userSummary/sw_userDisplay.php ? idUserDisplayed = 899&sign = 08b456d033fcee27acbc8caf208135e8 ] Nov 2008 ) .
But the argument only considers short-term effects while it does not pay attention to long-term impact .
In fact , compared to other forms of electricity generation , nuclear power is ascendant with lower cost .
The results showed that the generation cost is 4.2 c/kWh , which is just the same as coal , eliminating all carbon cost .
The final data suggested that with its 5 % discount rate , nuclear is much cheaper than all the others ( The Economics of Nuclear Power , July 2009 ) .
Another reason why people argue against nuclear power is that people doubt its ability to help ease climate change .
People argue that nuclear is not emission-free at all .
They argue that if we take into account emission in relation to plant construction , uranium mining , transportation radiation and the contamination storage , in the UK for example , its 23 nuclear reactors can only cut less than 8 % emissions .
However , the European Union stated that more achievement with 20 % reduction can be reached at zero net costs by 2020 ( Velloor R , 2009 ) .
But the truth is nuclear power can do more than what has been mentioned .
Take France as example . Its emission of nitrogen oxide and sulphur dioxide has been reduced by 70 % over 20 years .
In India , the government also stated that it will sharply reduce global warming gas to combat climate change ( Velloor R , 2009 ) .
There is no doubt that nuclear power can efficiently help ease climate change with low cost .
Generally speaking , nuclear power is becoming more and more acceptable .
Some countries which did not support nuclear power before , like Australia , have started developing their nuclear power generation .
In an earlier survey , more than half of the Australians support nuclear power now ; even 92 % of them think it is quite an important approach help ease climate change ( Australian attitudes to uranium , 2007 ) .
Although some technological problems still exist , nuclear power energy , as one of the energies of the future , will surely become more and more popular .
It is in time like this that mankind is driven to innovate and churn out alternate solutions , hoping that coupled with existing ones , he can solve or at the very least tackle the problem effectively ; and in this case , an experimented , practical solution would be the further development of nuclear energy .
While there are public concerns about cost , security and safety issues involved , the new generation IV reactors are proposed to address these areas of concern .
One particularly advanced concept is the Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) , which makes use of helium coolant , which is inert and not reactive , and produces electricity and hydrogen , which is in turn used for the formation of hydrogen cell
( GEN IV International Forum , 2003 ) . These advantages , along with other safety precaution in place , will definitely serve to tackle the energy problem of the world .
Nuclear energy has never been a foreign subject to energy scientists .
A vastast amount of resources , manpower and time has been invested in research involving it .
Nuclear energy is most commonly produced by the fission of uranium , which produces 10 million times the energy produced by the combustion of an atom of carbon from coal
The amount of money required for research is initially estimated at 6 billion over the next 15 years for the 6 Generation IV reactors , but one must realize that subsequently the cost of maintaining the nuclear plant as well as the raw materials are far cheaper than coal
The inexpensive fuel cost and the sheer volume of energy produced by a nuclear reactor far outweighs the cost of research and development .
The next key agenda on the minds of the public is nonetheless the safety considerations and implications that these nuclear reactors can have .
This not only serves as a reminder for generations but also for scientists to reflect upon and further enhance their research .
In fact , it is because of these very reasons that the Generation IV reactors were proposed -- to further improve on the safety aspect of existing reactors .
Most thoughts were put into the proposal to ensure the level of safety and security in producing such a powerful reactor .
Security issues tied with nuclear power plants have been a very sensitive topic as political leaders have to account for the internal and international security of their country .
However , the concept of a VHTR , one of the safest reactors proposed , encompassed this consideration and will prove hard to be a security breach due to the high temperature in which the nuclear byproducts are embedded in
( EU and Energy research , 2007 ) .
Indeed , nuclear power development carries with them a social stigma ; being dangerous and harmful to the society even in the modern world as mankind is skeptical about its use and benefits , and instead are more wary of the few incidents whereby lives were lost .
Nuclear energy does not produce greenhouse gases or acid rain , and thus governments abiding by the Kyoto Protocol will definitely be looking at this to cut down on greenhouse emission .
I definitely believe that it is too early to simply brush aside the whole concept of nuclear energy and classify it as being unsafe .
The devastating damage and long-term , " chronic " consequences of the two nuclear disasters at Hiroshima and Nagasaki still remind us about how dangerous this type of weapons is .
Greenpeace and a lot of volunteer groups and organizations around the world are trying their best to ensure that those calamities will never occur again .
Nevertheless , the scenario of no fuel resources left and increasing extreme weather caused by global warming nowadays have pushed us to reconsider nuclear power .
Governments and scientists support the wide use and development of nuclear power .
Obviously , to lessen the world 's thirst for energy in the long term , and to reduce the growing number of disasters , I am in favor of using nuclear power as a main resource of energy in the future .
First of all , we have to ease public worry .
Mistakes are impermissible because they would kill several people and totally destroy a huge area .
There are also a lot of nerve-wracking problems , particularly chronic diseases many years after a disaster .
Discrimination is widespread around the world due to terrorism , racism and religion .
Because of this , any source of .
Typhoon Ketsana , Hurricane Katrina , and tsunamis striking the South- and South-East Asia are some apparent consequences of global warming .
Acidification , famine , and disappearance of permafrost , coastal areas and agricultural lands will threaten our future .
It not only generates 50 % more electricity than conventional plants from the same amount of fuel , but can also split hydrogen from water , which is another fuel for the future .
It is a remarkable benefit of nuclear energy compared to other developing kinds of energy like solar energy and wind power .
Those types just meet the requirements of residential , office and house needs .
Using nuclear power is a long-term solution to human need for energy .
Secondly , this technology has had a long process of development while solar energy and wind power have just been developed recently .
Humans do not need to invest too much on it compared to other kinds of energy .
Thirdly , nuclear energy frees us from fossil fuel dependence .
That means no monopoly of some oil-rich nations like in the present .
It will prevent some countries from abusing fuel as a way of achieving political and economic power to form a new world order .
In contrast with fossil fuel , uranium is evenly deposited around the world .
Thus , there will be enough fuel for all nations and regions .
Lastly , more procedures will help decrease the potential danger of nuclear energy .
Thanks to the rapid pace of technology development nowadays , new materials for reactor construction , ways of observing and controlling process , we can be assured that past accidents like Chernobyl will never happen again .
Without nuclear disasters , no people die due to working inside nuclear power plants .
As global energy demands are predicted to soar relentlessly , nuclear energy is a prominent resource .
It will not only mitigate the consequences of global warming , but also help lessen the world 's thirst for fuel for a long period .
We , human beings , have to adapt to a new age of nuclear power and fully exploit it rather than be uneasy and doubtful about this controversial type of energy .
With increasing concerns over the impact of global warming and oil prices , fossil fuels alone will not be able to meet the world 's increasing energy demand in the future .
Nuclear energy is currently supplying 17 % of the world 's energy demand ; however this number is projected to drop as old plants close more frequently than new ones open .
Unless a new source of sustainable energy is discovered , continuous research and development of nuclear energy should be conducted in order to sustain the economies of the world .
The Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) is one of the nuclear generation IV reactor concepts that should be given priority in research and development .
It uses helium , an unreactive gas , as a coolant and operates at high temperature to achieve high efficiency .
It has one of the earliest delivery dates among the other generation IV reactors .
Many projects incurred high costs due to extended periods of research and development , thus it is economically more sensible to give priority to a project that has an earlier delivery date .
The difference between the cost of nuclear and conventional power plants is perhaps the most important factor in the research and development of the former .
The costs mainly comprise of two components : the investment and generation cost .
On the other hand , for example in the coal-rich regions of China , coal-based electricity is much cheaper .
Many countries depend on the import of oil , gases and coal for generation of electricity , which means that cheaper electricity is only limited to countries with control over fossil fuel .
Since 1990 , oil prices have risen steadily as sources of fossil fuel decrease and demands for fossil fuel increase .
It is apparent that eventually nuclear energy will be significantly cheaper even in regions that are rich in fossil fuel .
The main reason for public opposition to nuclear energy could be the lack of confidence in the safe operation of nuclear power plants .
The Chernobyl ( 1986 ) and Three Mile Island ( 1979 ) accidents are frightening examples of how devastating a nuclear accident can be .
Even until today , people are dying from the effects of radiation caused by the accidents .
The nuclear power industry is still a relatively new one and confidence in the safe running of nuclear reactors comes only with experience over time .
There has been a concern over how the growth of nuclear power will contribute to nuclear proliferation .
Nuclear was first developed under a project codenamed " The Manhattan Project " and it was fueled by competition with the Nazis to develop the world 's first atomic bomb during War World II .
The technology was later used to generate energy , thus it is inevitable that most countries own both nuclear weapons and plants .
In summary , nuclear energy will continue to play an important role in meeting the world 's energy demands .
However , with increasing public opposition to nuclear technology due to the harmful effects of the radiation produced , in recent years more plants have shut down than new ones opening .
The concerns are uncalled for as continuous research and development will bring about cheaper and safer operation of nuclear plants .
As new reactor concepts develop , it is no surprise that nuclear energy is the " next big thing " .
Such disastrous events also happened in Pennsylvania and the Chernobyl nuclear power plant in the Soviet Union .
The serious consequences caused by nuclear leaks make experts consider over and over again before building new nuclear plants .
Nowadays , because of the desperate need of human societies for long term energy sources , experts are forced to explore a safer and more economical reactor to generate nuclear power
( NBF , 2007 ) . Under this scenario , Molten salt reactors ( MSRs ) are the best options for three reasons .
In the first place , Molten salt reactors are much safer due to the properties of the chosen salt mixture and .
Moreover , it is more economical to develop MSRs .
Finally , most of the technology challenges can be overcome .
First of all , according to the table , the MSRs are safer to operate and maintain than most of the other reactors .
{ ( GIF , n.d. ) } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.gen-4.org/Technology/systems/msr.htm ] The chosen salt mixtures do not burn in air or water and the solubility of the fluoride salts with radioactive fission substances in water is zero .
The other reason is that low-pressure molten salts can not cause a steam explosion in the core
( Charles W. F. , 2004 ) . In addition , almost no excess reactivity of the fuel goes on in the reactor , since the fuel is added in as needed and the radioactive substances are removed on-line from the nuclear plant .
Moreover , a Molten salt reactor costs less than other reactors under development which is indicated in the table .
Flourides are favored to be used as coolant because fluorine does not need expensive isotope separation as chlorine does ( Per F. P. & HaiHua Z. , 2004 ) .
What is more , in the core of the reactor , the pressure is relatively low .
ThuThus , there is no need for the quite expensive high-pressure steam vessel .
Instead , low pressure pipes built of thin sheets of metal are used .
Since the metal pipes are thick , they cost less to construct and weld .
In addition , efficiency is raised effectively due to high temperature , which accordingly reduces the use of fuel and the cost of complementary equipment by 50 % or more .
{ ( GIF , 2007 ) } [ HYPERLINK : http : //www.gen-4.org/Technology/systems/msr.htm ] These properties imply that MSRs can work in small sizes , reducing the cost of land and construction .
Furthermore , some experts do not support MSRs for two reasons .
The other is the decay heat produced by noble metals which can damage the heat exchanger
( Paul P. , 2002 ) . Nevertheless , these two limitations can be solved by carbon-carbon heat exchangers .
Therefore , the amount of plated out noble metals is significantly reduced and it is easy for trapping systems to remove those noble metal from the system
( Per F. P. & HaiHua Z. , 2004 ) .
First , MSRs are relatively safe compared to the other reactors under development .
Secondly , MSRs provide countries a much more economical way to develop nuclear plants .
Lastly , the two main challenges of MSRs are solved by the new technology called carbon-carbon heat exchanger .
Thus , under current circumstances , the new dawn of Molten salt reactor will come soon .
Many major engineering accidents have occurred around the world such as the Three Mile Island and Chernobyl accidents .
Some feel that incorporating psychology into the design process can help to avoid such accidents from happening .
This could be one of the reasons why Psychology is now being taught in the design graduate programs of many institutes , such as Chicago 's Institute of Design ; it is also used in some design firms ( Psychology by design , n.d ) .
By understanding psychology one would be able to enhance his or her thinking style and creativity , therefore would be able to come up with better solutions during the design process .
Therefore , the use of psychology in the design process would help to prevent major engineering accidents from happening again .
As stated by Wilpert ( 2007 ) , the train accident in Eschede ( Germany ) , in the year 1998 , was one of the major engineering accidents that had occurred .
It has been documented that the crack in the wheel of the train caused it to derail
They suggest that if there had been a better team of engineers involved in the design process , they would have worked in an effective and productive manner and would have been able to come up with a better piece of design for the wheel , thus preventing the accident .
However , these people are not aware that the use of psychology helps one to understand the people around him as well as know their strengths and weaknesses .
This way , during the design process they would have been able to split themselves up into smaller groups and work on the part of the design process they are strong at .
Khandani ( 2004 ) ) also states that building of a prototype , which is the last step , is very important as it helps us to know if the design is reliable to use .
Therefore , even if a prototype had been built it would not have been possible to test it out with real conditions .
The use of psychology , on the other hand , would have helped to prevent the accident .
The design process places a very high demand on the creativity of the engineers involved , which is closely related to thinking ability .
According to Wanger ( n.d. ) , cognitive psychology focuses on the essence of human thinking .
n.d ) The use of cognitive psychology would enhance style of thinking and creativity in the design process , encouraging engineers to come up with an effective and safe design .
There are a group of people who might strongly feel that if proper research has been done , the engineers at Eschede would have come up with a better design such that any fault in the wheels would have been detected and hence prevented the train from moving .
High technology research on this aspect of design would have been possible and hence would have prevented the accident .
However , the study of psychology focusing on Human Computer Interaction ( HCI ) helps one to use the rapidly advancing telecommunication and research facilities to their advantage .
Therefore , the study of HCI would better enable the engineers to analyse information they gather and would hence to be able to come up with innovative designs which look into the safety of the design .
Therefore , the use of psychology would have helped prevent the accident .
In conclusion , incorporating psychology into the design process would help to enhance the creativity and style of thinking of the engineers and it would also help the engineers to better interact with advanced technologies and modern information .
Psychology also helps teamwork to be effective . Therefore , the use of psychology would have prevented the accident .
The world 's population is predicted to expand from about 6 billion people to 10 billion people by the year 2050 ( A Technology Roadmap for Generation IV Nuclear , 2002 ) .
And global energy demand is expected to double at that time ( Nuclear Power 's New Dawn , 2004 ) .
Today 's energy use has caused adverse environmental problems so energy supply will be far from sufficient for future demands .
Now the whole world works towards sustainable development .
However , the public is very concerned about the safe operation of nuclear reactors , economic costs , technical risks , and waste disposal of the nuclear energy systems .
Compared with the other five concepts , the Molten Salt Reactor ( MSR ) is most advanced in safety , reliability , performance and economics .
In my point of view , people should support more research on MSR technology to fulfill human s ' energy consumption in the future .
Given the memories of previous nuclear reactor accidents , the public is concerned a lot about the safety of nuclear plants .
However , since to ensure safety is the primary goal of MSR , it has good safety measures .
Molten salt reactor systems use liquid salts as a coolant and fuel together .
It has an integrated fuel cycle , taking advantage of the great heat transport properties of molten salt ( Malten Salt Reactor ) . The reaction process keeps low pressure and low chemical reactivity . The mobile fission products are removed continuously .
The cooling is very fast and they can cool down almost automatically when an accident happens ( Forsberg , 2004 ) .
The simplified safety features do not rely on sophisticated backup systems or experienced operators ( Nuclear Power 's New Dawn , 2004 ) .
This can prevent any deliberate accident and minimize damage caused by accidents .
Consequently , we should further develop these techniques , conduct more tests in different situations and carry out enough precautionary measures .
Then safety can be ensured , or even though accident happens , the loss can be eliminated .
Furthermore , another main concern from the public is performance and radiation during the reaction process .
This implies that to build an MSR could be smaller than other reactor concepts and that the efficiency of thermal power output would be higher ( Forsberg , 2004 ) .
At the same time , it can split hydrogen from water , which can be alternative fuel for transport to deal with oil shortage ( Nuclear Power 's New Dawn , 2004 ) .
CITATION Lui09 \ l 1033 ( Echavarri , 2009 ) . As the result , radiation and waste will not be a significant problem anymore .
Opponents argue that the use of nuclear plants would be too expensive to compete with other resources such as coal and gas .
So now we should not only consider economic profit but sustainable development of human society .
The MSR uses thorium as fuel .
Thorium is more abundant than uranium and its price is relatively cheap .
It is a well developed energy source .
Therefore , compared with the other reactors , MSR has economical and social advantages .
Moreover , as new technology develops , costs can be cut down gradually .
In the future , it can compete favorably with other energy sources .
Today , the principal challenges are using green resources and energy to radically reduce CO2 emissions to help ease climate change and to pursue sustainable development .
In recent years , oil has become very important to many people by providing fuel for cars and most importantly , generating electricity .
We are using more tools that require electricity with technological advancement .
At the same time , burning oil to generate electricity also releases a large amount of carbon dioxide into the atmosphere .
However , there are many who oppose this idea because they feel that this choice is expensive , unsafe and can not perform as well as others like renewable energy .
Since the Generation IV Reactor that is expected to have one of the earliest deliveries with the highest power output ( Butler , 2004 ) , research on it should be supported and continued .
Firstly , many people oppose the use of nuclear power as a form of energy because it is expensive to research and build .
However , they do not realise that nuclear power is expensive only at the early stage .
In the long run , nuclear power is still a cheaper alternative fuel as VHTR can generate fifty percent more electricity from the same amount of fuel in the current coal-powered power plants ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Besides this , the rising price of oil will eventually become much more expensive than the radioactive materials used .
Secondly , people may argue that nuclear power is not safe because of the radiation that radioactive materials give out .
The Three Mile Island accident and Chernobyl accident are evidence of their claims .
In the Chernobyl accident alone , there were fifty-six deaths ( World Nuclear Association , 2004 ) .
Yet , according to the World Nuclear Association ( 2008 ) , the most serious case of nuclear reactor accident was the Chernobyl accident with fifty-six deaths while a recent coal mine methane explosion in China has caused seventy-eight deaths .
Furthermore , in the new concept of VHTR , it will be " meltdown proof " so it will still be safe if accidents happen ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Thus , nuclear power is not as dangerous compared to other sources of energy and VHTR can be made safer with modern technology .
The radioactive materials will run out one day like oil and coal , giving us the problems that coal and oil are giving us today .
Thus , even though it can not perform for a long time like other renewable powers , it is the best performing power that we can rely on now for its efficiency per land area and cost .
In conclusion , coal and oil are no longer sources of energy that we should rely on because of their rising costs and environmental impact .
Currently , generating power using the nuclear reactor , VHTR , will be our best choice since it has zero emission , cheap , safe and efficient .
Thus , research on VHTR should be continued and funded to get ourselves ready before the demand for energy increases much more in 2050 as predicted ( Butler , 2004 ) .
However , nuclear energy is more efficient and gives a new future for energy consumption , especially after the use of generation IV nuclear reactors ( Hill , 2008 ) .
In my perspective , it is a good choice to support and fund the development of generation IV nuclear reactors for future energy consumption .
The first reason why it is good to fund and support the development of nuclear energy for future energy consumption is the limitation of energy resources .
The main energy resources human beings consume today are coal , oil , natural gas and some other non-renewable resources .
People may argue that we still have enough resources in the following centuries ; however , according to a survey done by world geographers , oil will be used up 40 years later if human beings continue using it like they do now .
Natural gas will last 60 years and coal can last a little longer time , 160 years .
Nuclear energy now is hot and it will show its great use in the next few centuries ( Gerstner , 2009 ) .
If they build a power plant that can produce 17.8 billion kilowatt-hour of electricity , they need 81 ton uranium , or 4.34 million ton oil , or 6.51 million ton coal
From this it can be seen that the uranium can produce more energy per kilogram and it can partly solve the issue concerning limitation of energy resources .
In this case it will be a good decision to fund the development of nuclear energy , especially the generation IV nuclear reactors .
Besides the advantages mentioned earlier , nuclear energy also does not produce any greenhouse gases , like carbon dioxide .
The generation IV reactors can really reduce the production of green house gases ( Butler , 2004 ) . People may argue that many accidents have happened related to nuclear reactors .
We can not deny it ; for example , on 26th of April , 1986 , the nuclear reactor in Chernobyl , Ukraine leaked and exploded .
Although the possibility of accidents exists , under strict management and better technology , the number of accidents will be reduced and nuclear energy will be a kind of energy that is environmental friendly . The public should fund its development .
A country can also benefit a lot from nuclear energy .
Not because it is a kind of future energy but also because it can enhance the speed of economic development ( Hill , 2008 ) .
People always say that economic development will depend on comprehensive national strength or national power , not the nuclear energy . However , they may not see the importance of nuclear energy in improving .
According to a report made by OPEC , in 2009 , China consumed 8.27 million barrels of oil a day , which is 0.29 million barrels more per day than 2008 .
The generation IV reactors will perform very well in this aspect .
If we can support and fund nuclear energy for future development , it will enhance the speed of economic development .
In conclusion , it will be a good decision to fund the development of generation IV nuclear reactors for future energy consumption .
Nuclear energy has three main advantages -- its high rate of energy production , its being environmental friendly , and its ability to enhance a country 's economic development .
However , some people have lost their confidence in nuclear power development after the occurrence of nuclear disasters in Three Mile Island and Chernobyl .
Of the six generation IV reactors , the Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) has the most potential to be selected for further R&D funding .
Specifically , compared with the Molten Salt Reactor ( MSR ) , the VHTR is safer and incurs low operation and maintenance costs and modular construction costs .
The MSR operates at the temperature of 700-800 Âº C and low pressure .
Thus , the VHTR would incur a higher cost of installing since it needs thicker pipes to sustain the high pressure .
However , the VHTR which operates at a higher temperature is highly efficient in the conversion of heat to electricity compared to the MSR .
Therefore , with economy of scale , the cost of installing and maintaining the VHTR increases less than proportionately with the plants ' generating capacity due to its high efficiency .
Moreover , additional R & D technologies for the VHTR includeing high temperature alloy , fiber reinforced ceramics and composite materials can further improve the efficiency and cut down the costs ( U.S. Department of Energy Nuclear , 2002 ) .
For instance , an optimized approach to dealing with graphite is currently under research .
Thus , the VHTR is much cheaper than the MSR in overall cost .
Some people might have a wrong assumption that the MSR has higher performance than the VHTR since it is a fast reactor that relies on fast neutrons while the latter is a thermal reactor that relies on moderators to slow neutrons first .
However , this is not true because the reactors ' performances also depend on temperature and pressure .
In fact , the overall plant efficiency of the VHTR is more than 50 % compared to MSR 's 44-50 % .
In addition , the VHTR is operating in a midsized plant as compared to the MSR which is large in size .
Thus , the VHTR is neutral in sustainability which means that VHTR spent fuel that could be disposed of in a geological repository or conditioned for optimum waste disposal .
Furthermore , the MSR discards a larger amount of waste compared to the VHTR .
Even though waste from the MSR undergoes recycling , this process is unsecure as this bypasses the stage where plutonium , an active ingredient for nuclear weapons , is produced .
Hence , plants might become targets of terrorist .
In addition , the cost of recycling is very expensive and a lot of fuel still ends up as waste .
On the other hand , the VHTR enhances minimization through fuel recycling .
From the analysis , the VHTR will spend fuel in a symbiotic fuel cycle that can achieve significant reductions in waste quantity and radio toxicity because of its ability to accommodate a wide variety of mixtures of fissile and fertile materials without significantly modifying the core design ( U.S. Department of Energy Nuclear , 2002 ) .
Thus , in terms of safety and security , the VHTR is actually much safer than the MSR .
In conclusion , the VHTR provides an economically competitive nuclear heat source and hydrogen production capability ( Idaho National Laboratory Idaho Falls , 2006 ) .
Therefore , unremitting efforts and funding should be put into its research and development so that it would give a fresh impetus to enhance the development of nuclear power .
Should funding be given to Supercritical Water Cooled Reactor over the other Generation IV reactors ?
This will fulfill the nuclear reactors ' main purpose of generating affordable and reliable electricity ( Buongiorno , 2003 ) .
As the Earth is mostly made up of water , there will be enough water to be used for the coolant of the SCWR .
Unfortunately , the development is not aided by nuclear disasters , such as the Chernobyl disaster in 1986 and the Three Mile Island disaster in 1979 , which are two of the most serious accidents which happened in nuclear power plants .
The current nuclear power plants use generation II reactors , for example , Pressurized Water Reactors and boiling water reactors .
However , the efficiency , security , economics and sustainability of generation II nuclear reactors are not up to the mark .
New nuclear technology is definitely needed to be developed to achieve a broader application in the power industry .
Then we will decide which one will better meet the energy deman of the future .
However , it is not important , as no research has proven that the method of generating hydrogen can achieve a higher efficiency compared with generating electricity .
It is not wrong to assume that under a higher temperature VHPR can achieve a higher efficiency than SFR .
As a result , it is easier for SFR to achieve its intended goal of providing energy to the world . Similarly , it has the potential to achieve a higher efficiency rate .
Lastly , SFR has an obvious advantage over VHTR .
Such reductions would bring benefits in the radioactive waste disposal requirements associated with the system and enhance its non-proliferation attributes "
) Such feature increases sustainability of SFR and makes it easier to ease public anxiety over the security of new nuclear power technology .
Thus , it will be much easier to put nuclear power plants to work .
Nuclear power is a good substitution for fossil fuel .
The utilization of nuclear power is going to change the world and people 's way of living in the future .
At present , it is necessary for people to decide which one of the six new nuclear technologies is most valuable to our power needs .
The meltdown of the nuclear plant caused 30 immediate deaths along with 100,000 cases of fatal cancers in the years that followed ( Greenpeace UK , 2006 ) .
Nevertheless , with the high cost and the inadequately safe nuclear technology that we have now , convincing people to embrace nuclear power will not be possible without safer and cheaper technology .
Out of the various fourth generation nuclear reactors currently being researched , the Very High Temperature Reactor , also known as the VHTR , is one of the most promising ones .
The VHTR , on the other hand , utilizes the heat to boil helium , an inert gas , which drives the turbine directly .
In conventional nuclear reactors , the radioactive fission products remain in the reactor 's core .
The VHTR , however , is designed such that the fission products are trapped inside the fuel particles .
This is evidenced by the test carried out on one of the VHTR prototypes , HTR-10 in 2004 .
According to a report by the Massachusetts Institute of Technology ( 2009 ) on the cost of nuclear power , the overnight cost ( cost without interest incurred ) of building a nuclear plant is US $ 4000 / kwh ( kilowatt hour of electricity produced ) .
For example , heat can be used for petrochemical reprocessing while hydrogen can be used as fuel in fuel cell plants to produce even more electricity .
Hence , VHTR is actually more profitable to operate as electricity , heat and hydrogen can be obtained altogether .
Besides , non-monetary economics should be considered at the same time .
The environmental damage done , though not measurable in dollars and cents , should also be taken into account as cost .
In less than a minute , a six-storey building was reduced to a pile of rubble .
This was one of the deadliest civil accidents in Singapore , known as the Hotel New World collapse which happened on 15 March 1986 . According to the Singapore Civil Defence Force ( 2009 ) , this misfortune took away 33 lives .
In an article on the collapse , Tan ( 1999 ) claimed that investigations showed the collapse was due to under design made by the engineers , shoddy workmanship and cost cutting made by the contractors ( Tan , 1999 ) .
There are some special scenarios where no amount of logical preventive measures could prevent accidents from happening , but as far as this study is concerned , the devastating loss of human life and the collapse of Hotel New World could have all been avoided with the use of psychology during the design process , eliminating the errors committed by humans in the design and maintenance phase .
All modern buildings are designed to support what the experts call the dead load and the life load .
The dead load is the weight of the building itself and the life load consists of people and objects like furniture which the building has to support .
Calculations made by the draughtsman of Hotel New World in the designing phase was so badly wrong that he only considered the life load and had forgotten about the dead load .
Separating the submission of dead and life load calculations could ensure that both loading types were being considered in the designing phase . To take an even further precautionary measure , safety factors could have been introduced to the design calculations to make way for any unprecedented human calculation errors .
In summary , this accident could have been prevented right from the beginning , taking human errors into consideration in the design phase .
No doubt engineers and contractors had to play a role in erecting the building and also ensuring the safe operation of the civil structure . More importantly , the users or patrons must not assume ignorance .
Upon completing the construction of the building , the building went into the maintenance phase , making the building operational .
The building showed signs of failure in the structural integrity 16 hours well before the collapse , yet people who witnessed the failure did not react appropriately . Staff of the building were alerted but did not know what to expect , whereas the management overlooked and had repair workers to fix the cracks in concrete by bracing it with timber .
This event would have turned out differently if the management teams of the building were psychologically prepared . In other words , educated or briefed on such issues , the building would have been evacuated almost immediately , even having a buffer time of 16 hours on hand to do it , saving the lives of 33 .
In short , this accident could have been prevented with the aid of psychology during the design process in the maintenance phase .
As an additional pointer , the maintenance phase could act as a second safety net to catch any remaining human errors left unsolved in the previous designing phase .
Risks are an integral part of our life . Every day we are making risky decisions unknowingly . It is just a matter of degree in the risk taken : walking on the open street itself would also mean being exposed to aircrafts crashing down on you .
Freak accidents referr to unanticipated natural disasters , such as unforeseen or illogical scenarios like the tsunami that swept across Sri Lanka in year 2004 . No amount of logical preventive measures taken could hav prevented the disaster from happening .
There are no absolute measures to an accident-free world . What can be done is to minimize the risk as much as possible , preventing the occurrence of accidents close to nil , learning from past mistakes and improving if an accident has occurred . In an article on Keeping Building Engineers Well Grounded , Lee ( 2008 ) claimed that Hotel New World is iconic of the construction challenges in the 1970s ( Lee , 2008 ) .
To conclude , it is evident that the arguments involving psychology during the design process in the design and maintenance phase would have prevented the accident in this particular study . The author of Hotel New World Collapse , Hon ( 1987 ) , concluded that the design was bad , the construction was bad and the maintenance was bad . Human errors caused the failure of Hotel New World .
Even though it gained popularity in the 1970s , the partial meltdown of the nuclear power plant 's core on Three Mile Island in 1979 and Chernobyl explosion in 1986 had a serious taint on the popularity of the use of nuclear energy as an energy source .
The Chernobyl explosion caused less than 60 radiation-related deaths and required the resettlement of over 336,000 people .
Although a more serious incident is yet to occur , people are increasingly concerned about the potential hazardous threat posed by nuclear plants .
Nuclear reactors also produce plutonium as a by-product which can be used in nuclear weapons .
It raises a global concern that terrorists or aggressive countries may have easier access to nuclear weapons and may threaten world peace .
Also , nuclear reactors are operational only for around fifty years , requiring regular costly replacements .
However , with increasing demands for energy due to industrialization and the rising price of oil and fossil fuel , nuclear energy remains as an important source of energy despite all the controversies .
On the other hand , the SFR has a closed loop fuel cycle and is designed to reduce waste .
With regard to safety , the VHTR has certain desirable safety measures under both normal and extreme conditions .
Nevertheless , with some innovation , a buffer can be introduced to prevent water vapor from reaching the radioactive sodium in the primary system .
For the VHTR , the cost is mainly associated with the heat exchanger size and the installation expenses which usually total to about US $ 781.5 million .
Although the cost of building a nuclear reactor is great and there are concerns about safety , there are several advantages in using nuclear energy as an energy source .
The small size of the nuclear power plants allows them to be integrated in the already developed regions and makes the long-distance power transfer unnecessary .
Also , nuclear energy does not produce pollution directly into the atmosphere in the form of greenhouse gases .
The use of nuclear energy is also advantageous in a sense that it will never run out while oil reserves and fossil fuels are likely to be used up at some time .
With more research and investment in nuclear technology , the SFR can become a viable energy source in the future .
With the rising demand for energy and the increasingly visible harmful effects of the use of oil and fossil fuel to the environment , nuclear energy offers an alternative and is regaining some of its popularity and early successes in the 1970s .
On 20 April 2004 , contractors and workers were having their usual tea break when they heard a loud thud from the structure that they were working on for the past few months .
Four men were immediately killed
( MOM , 2005 ) .The Nicoll Highway that links Kallang to the Central Business District had collapsed. ( Ahmad,A.,2004 ) .
The collapse of Nicoll Highway was a controversial issue where everyone had his or her own views .
There were views from engineers as well as the parties involved , saying that the collapse was not due to a mistake in design as they followed the code of practice in their design and the safest bottom-up construction method was used .
There were no occupational hazards influenced by the decisiveness and attitude of the project managers .
The parties involved took pride in their work .
In my opinion , I felt that the collapse was due to a mistake in the design , the lack of integrity as portrayed by the parties involved and the management team 's indecisiveness about the situation .
Indecisiveness and negligence of the management team , design mistake and lack of integrity are three factors of psychology which I felt were lacking in the design process which had resulted in the engineering accident .
The reason for the collapse of Nicoll Highway was not solely due to a mistake in the design .
Safety factors were taken into consideration in the design of the loads according to the Code of Practice
Furthermore , the common and safest bottom-up method was used , said a civil engineer working in LTA . It was definitely a mistake in design as the investigation revealed that there was an error in the design of the strut support system and that it was under-designed ( MOM , 2009 ) .
There were omission and misintepretation of the code of practice ( SCOSS , SC/06/102 ) .Therefore , the use of phsychology could have prevented the accident if the parties involved had not made any errors in the design .
The Land Transport Authority was decisive throughout the whole project as it shored up the surrounding ground to prevent further collapse of the repair work .
If they were indecisive , they would not have been able to decide what steps to be taken to prevent further collapse .
However , there was evidence showing that the management teams had neglected their roles .
The management teams failed to provide adequate instrumentation and monitoring works , lacked competent personnel to carry out specified works , and failed to identify adverse trends and implement corrective work ( Ministry of Manpower , 2005 ) .
There were signs of structure failing but they were ignored
The above evidence showed that there were human errors such as the negligence of the management team which had resulted in the collapse .
The parties involved in the construction of Nicoll Highway were carefully selected and one of them was the Land Transport Authority ( LTA ) .
Since it is under severe guidance by the government , there should have been no problems with integrity or dishonesty .
However , there was evidence showing that there was dishonesty and lack of integrity among the parties involved .
From the book on Nicoll Highway Collapse , extracted from New Civil Engineer ( 2005 ) , Nishimatsu-Lum Chang ( NLC ) , being a party involved in the project , was negligent , reckless and dishonest during the design and construction of the retaining wall .
If the parties involved had integrity and knew that cutting costs would result in many casualties , the engineering accident would have been prevented .
It was due to the parties ' lack of integrity , which was one of the psychological factors that they failed to demonstrate , that resulted in the collapse .
In conclusion , the use of psychology could have prevented the accident if the parties involved were careful about the design and made sure that it was not under-designed as in the case of Nicoll Highway .
The carelessness and negligence of the management team caused the accident .
Some people think nuclear energy is good but there are still people who think we should not develop nuclear energy .
Two sides support their views on pro and cons to nuclear energy .
In Butler 's ( 2004 ) article , there are 6 types of generation IV reactor .
This means it is safer to use this kind of reactor .
This reactor can generate a large amount of energy and can undergo waste recycling .
We can see that the future reactor is much cheaper , safer and more environmental-friendly .
We should further develop nuclear power energy since the cons of nuclear energy can be minimized by developing it .
Some people feel that radioactive waste is the main problem of nuclear energy source because it causes cancer .
Although radioactive waste lasts for a few thousand years , fossil fuel will cause more serious damage to the earth because of emission of natural gas that leads to global warming .
Global warming affects the whole world but nuclear waste only affects a certain area .
If we maximize the effect of global warming , all life forms on earth will become extinct eventually .
will finally disappear after a long period .
From the example of Hiroshima , we can see how fast a city is able to rebuild itself after a nuclear warfare .
Furthermore , nuclear waste is not a problem for future generation IV reactors like the Supercritical-water-cooled reactor because it recycles waste .
Many people think that we should not waste money on nuclear energy because the cost of handling or building a nuclear power plant is very high ; we can use the money to contribute to research on finding alternative energy or the development of alternative energy sources like solar and wind energy .
Energy demand each year is rapidly increasing so I do not think alternative energy sources like solar and wind energy can meet that need .
Nuclear energy contributes to almost 15 % of the world 's electricity ( Leipoldt , E , 2006 ) . If we do n't use nuclear energy , what are we going to use to replace 15 % of the world 's electricity ?
Since there is already a solution to meet the energy demands of the future , why do n't we just use it ?
In addition , future generation IV reactors like the Supercritical-water-cooled reactor can produce much more electrical energy than older generation reactors , so we should develop it .
Helium-3 produces much less waste and has a half-life that is 12 years only .
A lot of countries are racing to go to the Moon for helium-3 that is why they keep improving their space technology .
Lasker
( 2006 ) states that NASA is planning to go and harvest it in 2024 so they are developing high technology to achieve it .
We should improve our nuclear technology first while waiting for nuclear sources from the moon .
Using nuclear energy can decrease the emission of natural gas , generate a large amount of energy to meet future needs .
Among these reactor designs , Supercritical-water-cooled reactor ( SCWR ) is the most suitable concept for funding and development due to its usage of advanced material , safety and economical design and high security .
People who oppose nuclear power plants think that SCWR is not safe enough because it has potentially hazardous requirements .
Since the materials are subjected to rigorous safety standards , SCWR should be supported further through research and development funding .
On the contrary , the balance of SCWR plant design utilizes a relatively simple direct cycle power conversion system , which also allows for the incorporation of passive safety features .
SCWR 's efficiency is about 45 % while this one in advanced LWRs is 33 % ( Supercritical-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SCWR ) , 2007 ) .
Another advantage of SCWR that it is very cost-effective because it involves only one cycle .
So the overall simple design of the SCWR will also cut down construction cost .
The attack on September 11 in 2001 has provided a wake-up call to the threat of nuclear terrorism .
According to Li ( 2008 ) , the Molecular and Cellular Biology concentrator in Cabot House , the United States Congress has decided to use 555 billion USD in the formation of an " international fuel nuclear bank " ( p. 54 ) to prepare for safe reprocessing .
That means human intervention will be reduced to the minimum to prevent potential terrorist attacks on nuclear reactors .
Taking everything into account , because of its achievement in research in advanced materials , effective design and security , the SCWR should be so highly appreciated to pursue the GEN-IV through continuous development and funding .
Our natural resources are rapidly consumed to supply energy for society .
Although the construction of new nuclear power plants is strictly restricted , a new concept for the next generation of nuclear power plants has been announced .
Despite criticism about its safety , over the past decades , while still undergoing many restrictions , a small number of nuclear plants alone located in North America and Europe has been providing 15 % of global total power .
With the predicted US shortage of fuel by 2025 and VHTR 's expected delivery by 2020 ( Butler , 2004 ) , and if this new generation of reactors receives enough funding , it would be available at the right time to ease the lack-of-fuel crisis .
The public may argue that the conversion from petroleum-fuelled to hydrogen-fuelled would be very complicated and costly .
A car which runs on hydrogen does not need heavy materials and much space for its fuel tank .
Although the mass conversion to full hydrogen-fuelled vehicles might be costly , it will bring more advantages as a long-term strategy .
Finally , other than nuclear , there is still one source of energy that is believed to bring us an abundant amount of energy -- solar power .
No one can understand the current situation of global power supply better than oil-supplying countries themselves , and these global oil providers are in the Gulf ( Brumfiel , 2008 ) .
With a pessimistic view about the current global oil supply , these countries hope to quadruple their energy supply using nuclear plants .
With a VHTR constructed on the same amount of area , the amount of energy far outweighs that created by solar energy .
The development of VHTR ensures us a safe and abundant source of energy for the next centuries , before solar power technology is becomes advanced to meet our energy demands .
Generation IV ( Gen IV ) reactors are theoretically nuclear reactor designs that are undergoing research and are to be completed in 2030 .
They are projects initiated by Generation IV International Forum ( GIF ) which aims to come up with nuclear reactors that are more desirable for human use .
However , government policies to promote nuclear energy are still met with resistance from the public .
Many of them still see nuclear energy as it was decades ago , when it was expensive , low performing and deemed to lead to nuclear arms proliferation .
Thus , opponents argue that we should stop investing in nuclear energy for security reasons .
If the nuclear reactor runs on an open loop fuel system , nuclear waste will not be recycled .
The SWCR is able to operate on an open looped fuel system which does not recycle nuclear waste ( Butler , 2004 ) .
If nuclear waste is managed well , waste from SWCR can not be used for nuclear arms .
Thus , funding for SWCR should be increased .
The public perceive that nuclear energy is more expensive than conventional energy sources ( Hughes , 1999 ) and thus oppose the use of nuclear power .
However , they do not consider the fact that fossil fuel is depleting quickly ( How much Fossil fuel are left ?
Moreover , the cost of nuclear energy can be made lower through research and adopting nuclear energy in a large scale .
Although nuclear energy is expensive now , we should be far-sighted and consider the potential of nuclear energy becoming an affordable energy source in the future .
With high thermal efficiency , SWCR is able to produce electricity at a price comparable to fossil fuel reactors ( Butler , 2004 ) .
For the sustainability of our modern lifestyle , funding for research on SWCR should increase .
Many people oppose developing nuclear energy because of the large amount of money required for its infrastructure ( Wald , 2008 ) .
Unlike green energy , which is unstable and can not be produced on demand ( Wald , 2008 ) , nuclear power is dependable at all time .
In conclusion , funding for SWCR 's research should be increased as it is the best investment for energy .
In conclusion , the public reject nuclear energy for fear of nuclear arms proliferation , the perception that nuclear energy is expensive and the thinking that a nuclear reactor is costly to build .
However , the use of an open loop fuel system in SWCR can prevent the proliferation of nuclear arms .
Moreover , nuclear energy has the greatest potential for fulfilling our demands .
As such , it is logical that we support research on SWCR .
In 1986 , the Chernobyl Nuclear Power Plant in Ukraine exploded , resulting in a massive power explosion and many deaths caused by radiation poisoning .
Among all the reasons of the explosion , there were three main causes which led to the function failure of the nuclear power plant .
Some people believe that some design problems of the nuclear plant system could not have been properly solved with the condition of technology at that time .
Besides , no matter how advanced and well-designed the control system was , the machine was processed by man and it could never predict human errors which occurred by chance and were dependent on people 's emotions .
By iteration of analysis and systematic feedback to the machine , the mistake could have been detected early even before the machine was built .
It sped up the separation of atoms which caused such a serious explosion .
The workers , who were in charge of the building of engineering segments , would have been aware of the uses of their product and more careful when making important parts of machines .
The information of designing and processing would have been better channeled and translated to all the people concerned , if they iincorporated psychology into the process engineering stage .
Moreover , the main nuclear reactor in the plant had been constructed without any secure containment , which led to radial active containment freely escaping into atmosphere .
According to a 2005 report by the Chernobyl Forumeight U.N. organizations , the nuclear plant was designed by Soviet experienced engineers ( West , 2005 ) .
Most of them had participated in the design of first generation nuclear reactors .
In this case , if a psychologist was employed , he would have seen the engineers ' dilemma and used a psychological approach to help them overcome their bias .
In addition , although human errors were also accounted for in the nuclear explosion , they were not totally unpreventable .
To sum up , if psychology was applied in the design engineering stage , feedback loops would have functioned to minimize human errors in the process .
Psychology can reduce misunderstanding between designers and processors , helping information to be better channeled and decreasing the probability of misunderstanding .
In conclusion , a psychology approach could prevent engineering accidents , regardless of different possible mistakes which may occur in the process .
The world can not forget what happened in Three Mile Island in 1979 .
( World Nuclear Association , 2001 ) . The incident raised the fears of the public over nuclear power .
Therefore , engineers design the Very High Temperature Reactor to make it safer .
However , there come some controversies concerning the issue that the VHTR requires very complicated technologies and very high cost construction compared to the Sodium Cooled Fast Reactor .
Though many people criticize the VHTR for its great cost and immature technology , the VHTR should be popularized . The essay will discuss why based on three aspects : security , performance and cost .
People still worry about the radioactivity a reactor sends out so they think the sodium cooled reactor is safer .
I agree with the idea that safety should always be a concern .
Sodium is very chemically active and it can react with the core .
Moreover , sodium ge radioactive and we can not imagine what it will be like when the coolant is exposed to the outside .
The VHTR has great advantages in security over other reactors like the sodium cooled fast reactor .
Helium is an inert gas ; it will not chemically react with any other material .
Meanwhile , helium is radioactive when it is radiated , unlike other coolants .
Even if all helium comes out of the reactor , it still causes little effect on the environment .
If the system loses control , its core temperature will rise and finally melts .
The possibility of a sodium cooled reactor to melt is about one reactor per year .
A VHTR is about one reactor per year
( Baidu,2007 ) . When the system finds something wrong , it will automatically stop working and cool down the temperature to a safe level .
The VHTR has an average heat efficiency of 40 % , and the one designed by ESKOM company in South Africa even has efficiency of 47 %
( Baidu Baike,2007 ) . The heat efficiency of sodium cooled reactor is only 20 % .
For example , one spends 1 billion dollars to build a 200MW VHTR while one builds a 100MW sodium one that costs 0.5billion dollars .
Thus , the overall benefit of the sodium reactor is too little compared to the Very High Temperature Reactor .
Another group of people thinks the sodium cooled reactor will cause less problems to the materials than the VHTR .
With the advancement in technology , humans can now experience the joy of swimming long hours inside deep waters or even step on the far away moon .
Well , to have the opportunity for those is great ; but unlike many of us with flawless senses , for those with impairments in senses , a blessed feeling would be to see a flower , smell its fragrance , hear a bird or sing along to a song .
Fortunately , those with the talent and education required to invent such things are using existing technologies and extending them to suit human purposes .
For complete understanding of the invention , it is important that we learn its exact built .
The screen displays are of two types : one with a visual of an individual enjoying the music corresponding to the beat or a mosaic of lines and circles triggered by the music .
It is the fact that sound travels through matter as vibration .
The hearing impaired can not detect sound that travels through air but their skin , bone and muscle can detect sound vibrations that travel through solid matter such as wood and cotton .
Studies conducted to test the effectiveness of the chair show that the chair indeed has great potential .
The tests have been done on forty three participants including those who are fully deaf , partially deaf and those who lost their hearing later in their life .
Even though a direct correlation is unseen here , it is the study of sound that inspired the thesis of this design .
Speaking in plain terms would be to admit that their music experience is not fully compatible with that of one with normal hearing where they hear the lyrics , etc .
Musical understanding would be limited to beat , tone and volume alone .
Since it is a new technology , many refinements could still be made .
Given that it is also equipped with many speakers , heavy cushion , and accessories , the chair uses much space and has quite limited mobility .
Since there are foundations for the benefit of the hearing impaired , one step that could be taken is to unite these institutes and the developers of this technology together to ensure that research continues .
This innovation is for the better living of the hearing impaired and with the help of those currently involved , the developers could create an advanced version in the near future .
Innovations are for the betterment of the living conditions of humans , especially and convenience in their life .
It is the energy problem .
In fact , although the problem came into being a long time ago , we started to pay enough attention to it just recently .
We all know that the world 's energy reserves are limited , especially fossil fuel widely used all the time .
It is said that by the end of this century fossil fuel , which consists of gas , coal and oil , will be used up .
In other words , we do not have any fossil fuel to use in nearly ninety years ' time .
Thus , nuclear reactors started being built in some countries .
However , these days fewer and fewer nuclear reactors are being planned to be built because of public opposition .
Here we will use the supercritical-water-cooled reactors to illustrate that among all the generation IV reactors it is the only one which only uses water as its coolant and the wastes are optionally recyclable .
Besides , it does not need very high temperature and can produce a large amount of electricity . The only obvious weak point may be the high pressure needed .
It seems to be the best among the six reactors in my mind .
They think that accidents are possible in nuclear plants .
For example , one of the reactors in Chernobyl plant , Ukrainian Soviet Socialist Republic , once exploded .
What was worse , further explosions and the resulting fire sent a plume of highly radioactive fallout into the atmosphere and covered an extensive geographical area which in fact became a nightmare for the local people .
However , the truth is that in more than 12700 cumulative reactor-years of commercial operation in 32 countries , there have been only two major accidents including the one we have mentioned above .
There is actually no need to be very worried .
To achieve nuclear safety furthermore , we also need to develop high-quality design & construction and invent equipment to prevent operational disturbances developing into problems .
Of course , some people may say that the high risk of nuclear reactors may make them become the target of terrorists .
It was such a disaster that led to over 6000 deaths even though it had nothing to do with nuclear power .
Imagine if the attack happened in a nuclear plant , what would have been the consequence ?
In fact , we do not need to be very scared because of this point .
Tests have shown that concrete structures used in reactor domes can withstand battering .
Besides , governments have emphasized the importance of hardening nuclear power reactors .
Therefore , it is not very easy for terrorists to attack nuclear reactors .
When it comes to the cost , many people may think building nuclear reactors is quite an expensive process .
Moreover , a successfully operated nuclear plant is much more environmentally friendly than coal or gas power stations , which means a relatively lower waste disposal cost .
Indeed , nuclear reactors have their own advantages on both cost and performance .
Also , what people worry about , like security , is actually not very bad .
Therefore , further research and development funding for nuclear reactors is necessary for our society since it is a good way to solve the energy problem .
At the same time , the alternatives have to be cleaner so that the current global warming situation will not be aggravated ( Butler , 2004 ) .
One of the nuclear reactors , the Supercritical Water Cooled Reactor ( SCWR ) , has been proven to be one of the excellent methods to generate cheap and safe power for consumption .
Although there are criticisms cited about its flaws , it is still a reactor which is worth to be developed ( Idaho National Library , 2009 ) .
Among the Generation IV nuclear reactors , the SCWR has the lowest development cost which is based on economic , safety and sustainability factors ( Cogeneration Technologies , 2003 ) .
Comparing with other forms of Generation IV reactors , the SCWR does not require high development cost as it uses existing technologies such as Light Water Reactors ( LWRs ) and supercritical fossil-fired boilers .
Although critics highlighted that further research and development is required for systems components ( such as vessel and pressure tubes ) , which in turn demands more funds .
Secondly , the SCWR systems are able to produce great performance with its unique characteristics .
It is able to produce high thermal efficiency of about 45 % versus about 33 % efficiency for current LWRs , which translates to greater energy output ( Danielyan , 2003 ) .
This is due to its ability to operate at higher pressure and temperature ( at 550 degree Celsius ) in a single phase operation , unlike the current LWRs that need recirculation of heat and components like jet pumps and steam generators .
The other Generation IV reactors , such as Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) , also produce high thermal efficiency at about 50 % and at a high temperature of 1000 degree Celsius ( Butler , 2009 ) .
Hence , SCWR should be used instead of other Generation IV reactors .
Lastly , research and development ( R&D ) is crucially needed as this is the most important aspect needed as part of the implementation of any Generation IV reactor ( Butler 2004 ) .
For example , VHTR requires research to be done on the reactors ( specifically pebble bed type core and prismatic block core ) , power conversion unit , and its production of hydrogen ( supply for future energy source ) .
These are very complex research undertakings could take a long period of time and requires collaboration with partners across the world ( Carre , 2006 ) .
Although Dr Buongiorno highlighted that this " was not easy " to be done , he and his research team collaborated with researchers from University of Michigan , the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and Westinghouse to do research by testing new materials under the supercritical condition ( Buongiorno , 2003 ) .
This is a much promising system for its potential for low development cost , better performance and least research and development processes .
Although there are odds in proving the system 's efficiency , it is a great investment for a better future ( Idaho National Library , 2009 ) .
Assessing Gas-cooled Fast Reactors for Generation IV Services To meet the energy demands of the 21st century , a new generation of nuclear reactors termed as Generation IV , is being developed .
One of the most popular concepts of the Generation IV is gas-cooled fast reactors ( GFR ) , which use a direct-cycle helium turbine for electricity generation or hydrogen production with a high efficiency ( Hejzar , Pope , Williams , & Driscoll , 2005 ) .
However , there are concerns about the impact of its radioactive waste on the environment and its safety in operation ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Although GFR has certain deficiencies at this stage , further R&D funding should be supported because it has three main advantages in terms of sustainability , safety and industrial applications .
Opponents of GFR point out that it is inevitable for nuclear reactors to produce radioactive waste which has destructive effects , and due to the high cost of pollutant management , it seems impossible to install nuclear reactors without any radioactive emissions .
However , a research conducted by the MIT GFR development team ( Hejzar , Pope , Williams , & Driscoll , 2005 ) , shows that it is possible to develop a closed fuel cycle with full transuranics ( TRU ) recycling so that all TRUs will be recycled with losses of 0.1 % or less .
The long-term waste will be substantially reduced in the core with a conversion ratio to be close to 1.0 ( Girardin , et al. , 2008 ) .
Hence , the GFR system is highly-ranked in sustainability among all the nuclear reactors and this makes it a favorable energy supply in the future .
Fortunately , under Generation IV International Forum , a number of research deals with this safety problem using " passive decay heat removal options " ( Girardin , et al. , 2008 ) .
In the design of the GFR system , combined systems of both active cooling and passive cooling are applied : active systems are used to remove the decays of heat at high power level , then passive systems will take over after 24 hours when decay heat is reduced to 0.5 % .The active part defends the system in the first place and the passive part only with the pressure achieved after depressurization .
In this way , less human labor is involved in the operation of GFR and thus accident risks are minimized .
Some also claim that GFR can hardly change the energy supply scenario in the globe because nuclear energy today is mainly utilized to generate electricity , which only accounts for 16 % of the total energy consumption ( Herranz , Linares , & Moratilla , 2009 ) .
However , except for electricity generation , the future GFR is predicted to achieve an excellent thermal performance based on a direct Brayton cycle configuration .
Herranz , Linares , & Moratilla ( 2009 ) predict that GFR can use a few hundred MWs to produce heat at a very high temperature.This will satisfy most heat applications of industrial processes .
Besides , some scientists suggest that the thermal efficiency of GFR can probably be increased from the present level 30 % to higher than 50 % with no additional economic penalty ( Herranz , Linares , & Moratilla , 2009 ) .
To summarize , GRF can be a favorable energy supply because it can achieve a wider range of industry applications with minimized radioactive waste .
Moreover , it better ensures safety during operation so that accident risk is lowered .
Hence , to make such energy supply possible in the future , the development of the GFR system should be funded .
Scientists debate whether using a large amount of nuclear power as an energy resource might bring human benefits .
Although some scientists argue that nuclear power has negative effects on the environment ( it is not safe or secure ) , there is evidence which shows nuclear power yields great benefits such as protecting the environment and is safer than using traditional power .
In addition , the appearance of nuclear weapons can not be avoided when nuclear power is developed .
Opponents of the use of nuclear power claim that it has negative impact on the environment because of some accidents which had happened before .
Despite the fact that nuclear power plant accidents really result in environmental contamination , it is still relatively not very bad contrasted with the pollution produced by traditional power generation .
Nuclear power plants produce electricity by using Uranium , but not burning of fuel .
A research report from University of Michigan ( Ilan Lipper&Jon Stone , 2009 ) shows that USA 's nuclear power plants reduce electric generating emissions of greenhouse gases by 20 percent , or 128 trillion tons per year .
In addition , nuclear power alleviates global carbon dioxide production which is one of the major contributors to global warming .
If 16 percent of the world 's electricity generated by nuclear power plants is replaced by generating using coal , 1,600 million tons of CO2 will be annually produced .
They say that the accidents caused by nuclear power plants caused huge harm to humans .
At Three Mile Island ( World Nuclear Association , 2009 ) , no people died and no one was injured .
At Chernobyl ( World Nuclear Association , 2009 ) , about 50 people died , and 1,500 people suffered from diseases due to radioactive emission .
However , diseases could be treated successfully so less than ten people died .
Compared with people who died in coal mining disasters , this number is very small .
The total number of people who died during the coal mining accidents is obviously far more than this number .
The final argument advanced by opponents of the use of nuclear power is that nuclear power can be used to create mass destruction nuclear weapons .
In addition , in the project Apollo 13 , a huge number of new technologies was developed and applied to spacecraft .
Later Americans used these new technologies to create new powerful missiles .
Hence , the appearance of nuclear weapons can not be avoided when nuclear power is developed .
Moreover , it can help to protect the environment and is much safer than using traditional energy resources .
Hence , in my opinion , using a large amount of nuclear power as an energy resource can bring about human benefits .
Global warming and increasing energy demands revive the need for nuclear energy .
Aiming at providing " safe , abundant , reliable , inexpensive and proliferation resistant " , generation IV nuclear reactors ( six concepts ) would operate at high temperatures that enhance productivity and efficiency .
In spite of the controversies , the " very-high-temperature reactor " which is independent of reprocessing nuclear waste and generates hydrogen as by-product , is the most feasible one among the six .
" says Ed Gersterner , a senior editor of Nature Physics .
In recent years , reprocessing nuclear waste has become an alternative . Reprocessing nuclear waste could cut the final amount of waste produced ; meanwhile , uranium and plutonium could be recovered and reused .
Hence , the supporters believe that the new generation of nuclear reactors should make use of this technology .
" they argue .
Reprocessing the nuclear waste requires great economic and political cost .
The Energy Department of US recently estimated that a reprocessing plant with an annual capacity of 2,000 metric tons of spent fuel would cost up to $ 20 billion to build while the cost premium for reprocessing would need an extra $ 3 to $ 4.5 billion per year .
Secondly , the action engenders global security , which includes preventing terrorism and nuclear weapon proliferation .
To save the environment , we need nuclear energy urgently , excluding nuclear reprocessing .
Therefore , among the six new concepts , only VHTR and SCWR fit the condition .
Due to current technology , hydrogen produced by nuclear reactors is not enough to completely replace gasoline for transport demands , the opponents argue .
They also raise concerns about corresponding infrastructures such as " hydrogen-fuelled cars " and " hydrogen-stations " which have not yet been widely implemented .
" words from Jeffery.D.Sachs , director of the Earh Institute at Columbia Universtiy . This implies that gasoline is replaced not only by hydrogen , but also electricity , biofuel , and solar energy .
The more hydrogen is put into use , the better the situation could be .
Besides , hydrogen technology is developing rapidly .
In conclusion , the Very-high-temperature reactor is the most practical and efficient one among the six concepts .
However , because more resources are used to produce environmental issues are more serious , for example , global warming and water pollution .
To solve these two serious issues , nuclear energy has been proposed as the solution for many years .
Many countries have built nuclear plants which have developed into generation IV .
I think it is necessary and feasible to build VHTR to solve our energy problems , although some people hold opposite ideas .
They say that related departments have to spend too much money on plants and revenues can not cover the cost .
So they think it is not worth it .
However , the cost for VHTR is not as costly as we think it is .
It costs only 670 million dollars .
Furthermore , according to " A Technology Roadmap " ( 2002 ) , the VHTR can generate electricity with high efficiency ( over 50 % at 1000 Â° C ) , whereas other reactors can normally have an efficiency of 33 % -50 % .
Opponents also argue that building VTHR is not safe .
They give the Chernobyl nuclear accident as an example to show how dangerous it is to build such plants .
First , VHTR uses helium as coolant .
Additionally , in " Thermal Performance and Flow Instabilities " ( n..d. ) , it is said that exposing helium to radiation does not make it radioactive , unlike most other possible coolants .
For instance , the reactor and gas turbine system is separated from the hydrogen production plant during abnormal events at a hydrogen production plant .
Some people think that VHTR is not environmentally friendly .
They argue that plants can pollute the environment and waste can not be dealt with well .
However , they do not realize that building VTHR is mainly for solving environmental problems .
If we utilize traditional resources , such as coal , gas and petrol , there will be much more emission of carbon dioxide .
On the other hand , VHTR discharges no carbon dioxide and the hydrogen it produces is the cleanest fuel ever found .
Also , Shropshire and Herring ( 2004 ) ) said that VHTR 's waste will be reprocessed according to form and will meet the acceptance criteria of the repository .
So , compared with the traditional way , building VHTR is much more environmentally friendly .
To sum up , it is better to build VHTR to solve our energy problems .
Engineers have overcome the difficulties with cost , safety and environment .
Hope we can benefit a lot from VHTR .
Dealing with the current increasing demand for energy and the threat of global warming , the Generation IV International Forum ( GIF ) came up with six generation IV nuclear reactors which are believed to be able to help address the problems by 2025 ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Based on studies ( Elder & Allen , 2009 ) , these nuclear reactors are capable of replacing gasoline with hydrogen in the long run with its enhanced efficiencies .
However , the public professes strong opposition against the building of nuclear reactors .
Nevertheless , there is strong evidence that the very-high-temperature reactor ( VHTR ) , one of the six generation IV nuclear reactors , could bring positive results through funding further its research and development .
According to Butler ( 2004 ) , further funding for the research and development of VHTR would mean that there will be increasing demand to build a lot more nuclear power plants with the hope of replacing gasoline with hydrogen .
This would result in an especially high cost for the government to bear .
Yet , the opposing argument ignores the fact that building more nuclear power plants will need time and good management to achieve full results in the long run ( Greenwald , 1991 ) .
Supporters argue that with nuclear power plants being built , it will contribute to countries by the use of hydrogen being produced for other important uss such as direct fuel or as feedstock ( Farbman & Brecher , 1975 ) .
In addition , nuclear power plants offer life-cycle cost advantage over other energy resources ( Perera , 2004 ) .
It is believed that countries will profit with the effort and large investments being made to build the plants .
Next , Butler ( 2004 ) states that incidents such as the Chernobyl and Three Mile Island which occurred years ago , highly traumatized the public , thus casting doubts on the performance of the new generation IV nuclear reactors being proposed by the GIF .
According to Butler ( 2004 ) , it has been found that VHTR has the abilities to convert heat and generate 1.5 times of electricity compared to generation nuclear power plants being used currently .
Then , another opposing argument being raised states that building nuclear power plants will make countries more vulnerable to terrorist attacks as plutonium is a key ingredient to nuclear weapons ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Also , destruction of nuclear plant will emit radioactive substances which will be detrimental to the whole world ( Elder & Allen , 2009 ) .
However , research studies ( Butler , 2004 ) show that VHTR does not undergo waste recycling ; the waste being produced will go directly to a repository leading to less possibility of obtaining plutonium ingredients to make nuclear weapons , thus , increased the security of countries .
The new generation nuclear reactors prove to be more effective in terms of cost , performance and security .
Supporters and experts believe that nuclear hydrogen production by VHTR has the potential to meet the nuclear energy needs of the future .
Hence , VHTR , one of the generation IV reactor concepts , should be supported for further research and development funding .
Nuclear-related issues have always been one of the most important issues .
As early as after World War II ended , the fear for nuclear research will bring about nuclear weapons has created a situation whereby nuclear researches are kept under strict government regulation .
According to a report " World population may reach 9.2 billion by 2050 " from the Associated Press , the world 's population is expected to expand from 6.2 billion to 9.2 million by the end of 2050 which will lead to an increase in the demand for energy .
Therefore , groups of international experts were organized to take up research to develop new concepts for nuclear reactors .
Thus , by comparing the Generation IV reactor concept with the previous generations , we can discover significant advantages .
They are manageable nuclear waste , better safety performance and secure nuclear energy .
Among the concepts , the most beneficial reactor seems to be the Molten Salt Reactor ( MSR ) compared to the Very-High-Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) and other 4 .
According to the Roadmap for Generation IV from an e-book , VHTR is equipped with a Back-Up emergency core cooling system .
MSR , on the other hand , is proved to be much safer compared to VHTR .
In the process of reacting , no high pressure steam is required within the core which means that there will not .
In the event of overheating , instead of using additional coolant , fuel salt will be forced to overflow and the overflow will be safely stored in a tank with the cooling system .
Because VHTR operates at a very high temperature which is near 1000oC , it is proven to have the ability to convert the heat energy to electricity efficiently .
In addition , it is able to produce hydrogen gas which is useful because of hydrogen 's role in emission-free hydrogen fuel cells that can be used in transportation .
But because of the high operating temperature , it means that the materials being used must have the ability to withstand extremely high temperature in order to sustain the process and therefore additional cost is needed to research and purchase these materials .
MSR uses a multi-reheat helium Brayton cycle which is a simplified balance of plants with lower cost and improved efficiency .
Because of the low cost ,
The overall plant efficiency of the VHTR is also greater than that of an MSR .
The attractive feature of this MSR fuel cycle is that the fission products have shorter-lived radioactivity .
Therefore , I conclude that MSR has a better chance over the other reactors .
In the long run , there will be a shortage of non-renewable sources of energy .
This raises a need to apply new technology to create power , and building new nuclear reactors such as the very-high-temperature reactors would be a choice to consider .
Supporters of new nuclear power plants claim that building new plants will provide unemployed people with job opportunities , both in the construction phase and operation phase .
However , building new power plants only provides workers with temporary work .
Moreover , the new generation reactors require skilled engineers to operate .
If governments spend the funds on building nuclear power reactors , which , according to The U.S. Department of Energy 's Office of Nuclear Energy ( 2009 ) , is approximately US $ 70.0 million in Fiscal Year 2009 , to do research on agriculture or some other necessary matters , they could help decreasing famine and poverty and provide work for millions of people .
Although it has been substantiated that smoke released from burning coal is the largest contributor to human-made increase of CO2 in the air , there are still several unpolluted and renewable replacements such as solar , wind , and tidal energy .
They are free and environmental-friendly sources of energy that we can use in the future .
One typical example is the Chernobyl accident in Ukraine in 1986 , which resulted from a flawed reactor design .
Within 4 months , 28 people died from radiation or thermal burns ; another 19 had subsequently died , and there had been around 9 deaths from thyroid cancer apparently due to the accident .
As of 2004 , a total of 56 fatalities had been recorded ( World Nuclear Association , 2009 ) .
In a journal in 2004 , Butler showed that the radioactive waste of very-high-temperature reactors is not recycled ; instead , it goes directly to the repository .
This raises awareness of the possibility that waste may be leaked either inadvertently or purposefully and may cause another disastrous catastrophe .
Nuclear energy is a promising source of energy that can replace the traditional power that we use nowadays .
However , it is still in the researching process , which means that many other problems concerning health matters and the efficiency of the concept could arise before it can reach the final stage .
Hence , developing countries should first focus on dealing with poverty and unemployment before they can use funds to build new nuclear reactors .
Only when the issue is solved and the process of researching generation IV reactors reaches a stable state should these countries channel funding into developing generation IV reactors .
Engineering psychology is defined as the analysis of how man behaves in the designing or constructing of equipment or man-made environments for better usage .
On March 27 , 1977 , at the Los Rodeos airport , a massive shockwave shook the control towers as the airport witnessed the collision of 2 Boeing 747s , PA1736 and KLM4805 , taking the lives of 522 people .
However , in my opinion , the implementation of psychology could have helped to anticipate some events that led to the accident , therefore allowing designers to prepare for such emergencies .
Still , designers failed to improve the airport to accommodate larger planes such as the Boeing 747 , even when it was widely used at that point in time .
The use of psychology in this case could have helped designers to anticipate that the airport would eventually see a Boeing 747 and thus make the necessary preparations .
One step that could have been taken would be to remove sharp 148-degree turns that the PA1736 , a 747 , would not be able to take .
One way to do so would have been by the implementation of psychology in the compilation of radio convention .
Should proper psychology have been used in the development of the phrasing convention initially , the pilot would not have executed take off before the clearance was given and hence preventing the accident .
It is the energy produced by the fusion of atoms in the nucleus .
Infinite nuclear power forms in the nucleus due to the extremely strong force inside every atom in it .
From this the atomic bomb was developed in the Alamogordo close to the desert on July 16 , 1945.The energy produced by nuclei explosion will cause a lot of heat .
Nuclear reactors are being built by engineers who make and distribute the nuclear energy .
This is relatively cheap , safe and it produces greater output efficiency .
The Generation IV International Forum ( GIF ) has researched on the six different types of nuclear reactor methods which they think will produce nuclear energy .
Among this six reactor technologies , I am going to argue why people should make further research and development on Supercritical-water-cooled reactors ( SCWR ) .
After the Three Mile Island Explosion people have had bad impression of nuclear energy .
However , according to a survey done by the Nuclear Energy Institute on September 29 , 2008 , 74 percent of Americans support nuclear energy while 24 percent oppose .
In addition , it does not produce carbon dioxide which can lead to global warming .
Then , there are still technical problems in inventing the next generation of reactors .
That is why if researchers can overcome the problem , then the new generation will have energy which is " clean , secure , plentiful , dependable , cost-effective , secure from terrorist attacks and proliferation resistant " .
In the article " Psychology and the Design Process " , Bernhard asserts that the accident at TMI was caused by the 'little understood interaction of factors ' from different system levels , rather than a 'single component failure ' or technical error ( Bernhard 2007 ) .
In other words , should we have better understood this interaction of factors , and anticipated the possible errors during the design process , we could actually prevent the accident at TMI from happening .
We assert that if these factors had more holistically been considered , then the outcome could have been reversed .
Rather , " It was the subsequent series of baffling and contradictory information that made plant operators shut off the emergence water system that would have cooled the core " ( Chana Gazit 1999 ) , turning the problem into a mishap .
However , due to overwhelming possibilities for error , such introspection for potential sources of error is almost practically impossible during the design process .
This premise leads to their conclusion that nothing could have been done , on the part of psychology , to change the situation should things go wrong .
Such models are set to ensure that there is no chance for an accident to occur , and if it does , be quickly resolved before it becomes a catastrophe .
The fact that such models were not considered during the design process at TMI shows the lack of preparatory work from commitment ( Bernhard 2007 ) , one of Bernhard 's major areas of psychological consideration .
Now , one of the ways the use of psychology could have possibly prevented the accident at TMI would be during the design process ( Bernhard 2007 ) .
Should greater consideration be placed on the designing of the valve to ensure accurate feedback ( and potential safety ) when the reactor core is not functioning as per normal , it can be argued that the problem would have been identified by then , and a meltdown would not have occurred then .
Moreover , it was evident that there was inadequate monitoring and evaluating of implementations at TMI ( Bernhard 2007 ) .
According to the account provided by the World Nuclear association , the operators reduced the flow of replacement water because their training told them that the water level was the only indication of the amount of cooling water in the reactor .
This gives rise to the psychological concept of Schemas or a human 's collection of information and practiced evocation of knowledge , behavior or required action... ( Illinois 2008 ) .
From the above arguments , we can see that the considerations of psychology are much more than a convenient 'tag-along ' during both the design and the execution process .
Hence , design considerations have to be constantly tied into the man-machine interface to ensure that both man and machine are at ease during operation and prepared when problems arise .
But in the meantime , we have definitely proven that the use of psychology is mandatory , and could definitely have prevented the TMI accident , had relevant safety considerations been made during its design process .
However , further research and development of nuclear power plants could also raise widespread concern for human safety that results from worries about both massive radioactive releases due to power plant meltdown or terrorist attack and the access these nuclear reactors provide to the materials that can be used to make nuclear weapons .
In spite of the growing concern , the Supercritical-Water-cooled Reactor ( SCWR ) , representing advances in sustainability , economics , safety , reliability and proliferation-resistance ( Idaho National Laboratory , 2007 ) , is the proper concept for further research and development .
However , the cost-effectiveness is inconclusive .
In October 2008 , the cost of building one nuclear plant was estimated to be roughly S $ 9 billion .
Additionally , since the Supercritical-Water-cooled Reactor uses supercritical water as coolant , its design features considerable simplification by reducing the containment volume and eliminating the need for recirculation and jet pumps , pressurizers , steam generators , steam separators and dryers ( Idaho National Laboratory , 2007 ) .
Moreover , the simplified safety features of the Supercritical-Water-cooled Reactor are independent of all the sophisticated backup systems or experienced operators .
Till date , there are 436 active nuclear power plants and they generate more than 370,221 Megawatts of electricity which constitute 16 % of the world 's total energy consumption .
Therefore , I feel that we should allow further research and development funding for nuclear energy so that it can be our future source of energy .
There are 6 new generation IV reactor concepts which have been developed : gas-cooled reactor , lead-cooled reactor , molten salt reactor , sodium-cooled fast reactor and very-high-temperature reactor .
A concept similar to that of VHTR has been tested out in Oarai , Japan and the test run was successful as it reached its operating goal of 950 Degree Celsius .
As the reactor operates at such a high temperature , it can be used to split hydrogen from water thermochemically .
Furthermore , terrorist attacks on nuclear plants will not be of great destruction as compared to the 911 incident .
The percentage of destruction on a nuclear plant by a large aircraft being used to attack a nuclear facility with the purpose of releasing radioactive materials is close to zero .
However , workers need not worry about them as radiation doses are controlled by the use of remote handling equipment , physical shielding and limiting the time workers spend in the nuclear plant .
( Ball , Roberts & Simpson , 1994 ) Therefore , we can say that nuclear plants are the safest to work in compared to other energy generation plants .
New equipments that will protect workers from radiation doses can be obtained through research and development .
The Bhopal nuclear incident which was due to worker 's carelessness still induces fear among people .
However , critics may argue that human error can not be avoided if humans are involved in the process .
Therefore , we need research and development to explore the possibility of computerizing the operating process .
Cost and performance of nuclear plants are two of the main factors that people will look into before deciding whether to invest in them .
Cost will include the operating and maintenance cost and performance is determined by the amount of output energy a nuclear plant can achieve .
DOE Nuclear Energy Research Advisory Committee and the Generation IV International Forum in December 2002 , the estimated cost of building and maintaining a VHTR nuclear plant is one of the lowest compared to the other generation IV reactor concepts .
The article also stated that the efficiency of VHTR exceeds fifty percent , which is the highest among the six reactors .
We can not deny that the advantages of having VHTR are gained through years of research and development .
Therefore , we can not stop the research and development process if we want to continue to have a better energy source .
As we trace the history of nuclear power since 1942 till today , we can see that there is a vast improvement in the field of nuclear energy in terms of global security , operational safety , automation of the process , cost and performance .
We can not be contended with the results that we currently have .
One of the Generation IV concepts is sodium-cooled fast reactors .
However , opponents may argue that the funding for such reactors may not be useful as they are expensive to construct and the resources used in the funding of the nuclear reactors could be used to further enhance renewable resources currently available .
They also argue that nuclear reactors are not safe as there have been previous accidents in nuclear plants .
However , opponents might argue that resources could be diverted to more research into renewable resources .
However , research has been done and no potential has been reported for further improving the process of tapping renewable energy . But there is potential in nuclear power and hence the funding is required to carry on .
Furthermore , the world today requires more energy and the energy demand is not met with the existing renewable resources as they have their own limitations .
However the Prime Minister of Italy , Berlusconi , and the President of France , Nicolas Sarkozy , signed an agreement which states that the two countries would work together to bring back nuclear power in Italy .
Initially , Italy had no back up energy source on its own and needed to depend on other countries .
In fact , Italy had more than 80 % of its energy supplied by other countries .
If the country supplying power to Italy decides to stop exporting power to it , Italy 's economy would come to a halt .
For example , citizens living in the village Banthara did not participate in the elections in India as they were upset over having little access to electricity ( Hajela , 2009 ) .
This would bring profit for the reactors .
The Massachusetts Institute of Technology reported that more than 40 percent of the greenhouse gases produced would be attributed to the burning of fossil fuels by 2020 ( Sullivan , 2008 ) .
The energy after the uranium is burnt in the fission process is used to vaporize water to produce steam which is then used to turn turbine to produce electricity ( Gache , 2007 ) .
Moreover , if power from six nuclear reactors is used in Australia instead of fossil fuels , the greenhouse emission in Australia alone would be reduced by 4 % .
Hence , further research and funding are necessary for generation IV concepts as they help reduce the effect of global warming .
The generation IV reactors are not only safe to operate as they are machine operated , but they also reduce greenhouse gases that the current energy sources produce .
Whenever people hear of the word " nuclear " , they usually associate this word with nuclear warfare , radiation emitted by nuclear and all the possible detrimental impacts that nuclear power can cause ( Donald , 2004 ) .
People have this misconception because they think that nuclear power is actually a very lethal " weapon " .
However , the public usually forgets the fact that nuclear power can actually be a rich source of energy and is able to have a substantial effect on the reduction of cost and environmental pollution .
Moreover , with the advancement of technology , nuclear fission and waste disposal of nuclear energy can be assured of safety ( Partha , n.d ) .
This is much cheaper compared to using oil which costs 18 cents per KWh or using coal which costs about 4 cents per KWh ( Economics of Nuclear Power , 2009 ) .
However , for fossil fuels , the most optimistic estimate on their remaining years is about two hundred years ( Enzler , 1998 ) .
However , the US Department of Energy , just like France , has vowed to ensure the safe disposal of nuclear waste by transmuting problem components of nuclear fuel into less harmful components and burying them deep into the ground ( Nuclear Power and the Environment , n.d ) .
If we were to compare the amount of greenhouse gases and poisonous gases emitted by fossil fuels in contrast to that by nuclear energy when operating the reactors , there is an astonishing statistics showing the huge amount of harmful gases emitted by fossil fuel .
2249 pounds of carbon dioxide and thirteen pounds of sulphur dioxide are being produced in the production of 1MWh of electricity ( Nuclear Power and the Environment , n.d ) .
When the amount of gases produced by fossil fuels is compared with that by nuclear power plants , the latter will definitely be the wise choice for energy purpose because it produces zero carbon dioxide and zero poisonous gas .
Only with the usage of nuclear reactor are we then able to claim the title of being environmental friendly .
The fear of using nuclear reactors as a cover up for making nuclear bombs is even more prominent .
VHTR is designed in such a way that in the event of an accident occurring , there will be a temperature control sensor to switch off the nuclear reactor automatically .
Security guards and cameras can also be used to monitor the safety operation of a nuclear power plant and ensure that the power plant is free from terrorists .
All the research and funding for the VHTR are definitely worth the money and effort with regards to the security issue of nuclear power plants ( Nuclear Energy Information Centre , 2006 ) .
There is definitely no question that producing an increasing share of electric power using nuclear fuel in lieu of fossil fuels will reduce greenhouse gases emissions .
Furthermore , the cost of operating nuclear reactors is low in comparison to operating fossil fuel power plants .
There is no doubt that more research and funding should be allocated to generation IV reactors , especially VHTR , which opens a new arena for nuclear energy as VHTR incorporates the safety of nuclear reactors and also provides low cost of nuclear energy for users .
Firstly , for security reasons , opponents of the new reactors insist that terrorists could easily make nuclear reactors one of their targets .
However , one could question why the terrorists did not fly the plane into the twin reactors .
In fact , the core of the present nuclear plants is already well protected by strong materials and there is a safety plan ( Goldstein , 23 September 2009 ) .
This causes citizens to oppose strongly against the nuclear waste being stored near them .
Moreover the impact of global warming is growing and is of immediate concern to the world and nuclear power helps solve the problem by reducing the emission of carbon dioxide by a total of 31,243 MtC in 2050 in France and Canada alone .
If the world does not cooperate to support VHTR or nuclear power , it is difficult to find an alternative that could produce energy that is clean and affordable in the long run .
As a result , the world might see an increasing number of casualties due to global warming .
In recent years , oil prices have been soaring to new heights and this reflects the high energy demands all over the world and the limited supply of fossil fuels .
This sounds the siren for us to find an effective source of alternative energy before the fossil fuels that we depend so much on run out .
Since energy harvested from nuclear reactors is highly efficient and has low material cost , it is seen as a good source of alternative energy .
A nuclear reactor is very similar to a typical coal burning power plant where water is heated into pressurized steam which drives the turbine generator .
The only difference is the type of fuel used to heat up the water .
( Butler , 2004 ) But public opposition due to several factors such as terrorism , safety , renewability and environmental issues has caused few reactors to be built over the past decade .
Although nuclear energy should not be seen as the only solution to depleting fossil fuels , due to its ability to generate a huge amount of energy using a small amount of resources , its development should be encouraged .
Further research and development and funding for generation IV reactors such as the Molten Salt Reactor ( MSR ) have benefits outweighing the disadvantages with respect to security , cost and environmental concerns .
Another benefit that comes with this heightened security is the generation of more jobs helping to ease unemployment rate .
Also the containment structures of modern reactors are designed to effectively prevent the escape of radioactivity even if it sustains severe damages .
Also since a wind turbine or solar panel is more unlikely to be in a terrorist 's hit list than a nuclear plant , cost of maintaining security of them are relative less .
But in contrast to what many people would think , even a generation III reactor used today has structures that can sustain a plane crashing into it .
In addition , a MSR uses an integrated fuel cycle system where molten salts are used as its fuel as well as its coolant .
( Advanced Reactors , 2009 ) The construction of wind turbines and solar panels is very space consuming because of their low energy efficiency and they are unreliable as they are weather dependent .
( Gibson , 2007 ) Although nuclear reactors too need large area of land space , the great energy output it has compensates for its use of space .
All the alternative energy sources mentioned are green compared to the burning of fossil fuels in terms of emission to the environment .
Since the first generation of nuclear reactors , advancement in technology has greatly increased the fuel efficiency , thus cutting down on the waste .
( Gen IV Reactors , 2009 ) Furthermore , MSR 's fuel doubling up as its coolant due to the good heat transportation properties of molten salts further reduces the waste produced .
Due to the nature of MSR , its waste has a lower amount of radioactivity , is safer due to passive cooling up to any size and has very low fuel usage .
There is certainly a need to find a replacement for the depleting fossil fuels and any feasible energy source could be a potential candidate .
All the possible candidates should not be conveniently ignored .
Considering that the benefits nuclear energy brings outweigh the disadvantages , further research and development and funding should be provided for more advanced reactors that are safer , more powerful and less costly .
Nowadays , the energy shortage problem tends to be more serious as the demand for energy increases significantly , while most conventional energies , especially oil and coal , are limited because of limited sources
In such a situation , the appearance of nuclear energy becomes so important , for the nuclear power has great advantages over many conventional energies .
For example , to produce the same amount of energy , a nuclear power plant consumes much less fuel ( uranium fuel ) than that a normal coal-fired one consumes .
What 's more , the nuclear power plant almost does not release any greenhouse gases or exhaust gases .
Since the nuclear energy seems so perfect , it is a bit surprising that there are only 439 nuclear power plants around the world .
Why is it not so widely used like oil , even in countries with the ability to deal with nuclear energy ?
The nuclear power reactor is a highly hazardous system that requires extremely high reliability and safety .
This kind of great disasters did happen in the history ( Three Mile Island and Chernobyl ) , and resulted in many people losing confidence in nuclear energy .
Since 1986 when the Chernobyl accident happened , America even has n't set up any new nuclear power plants .
In order to make full use of the advantages of nuclear energy , the primary task for engineers is to improve its safety .
Every time before we try to improve , we should first find out what has gone wrong .
About that disaster , some later investigations showed the design of the nuclear reactor had defects and someone insisted that the causes were all about technical problems .
Actually if there were only the design defects , the final explosion was completely avoidable .
Most of the investigators have come to a consensus that the primary cause for the Chernobyl is the failure of human management .
What 's worse , the makeup of the working team was not adequate , for they did n't have a timely backup system .
All these small human errors came together and finally led to the Chernobyl explosion .
However , some engineers hold the opinion that incorporating social psychology into the engineering processes seems crazy and funny .
It is usually known that human factors .
In their conservative view , they always care more about how productive and reliable the machines are and refuse to focus on the role of humans in safeguarding security .
But from the previous analysis of the Chernobyl nuclear accident , we can see that correct human actions are indispensable in preventing the disaster .
Indeed , the overall system 's reliability and safety in a nuclear power plant is more often dependent on humans instead of on machines . Why is that ?
Once the equipments have been put into use , the maximum reliability is already fixed .
In addition , in an industrial plant with potential hazards , well-organized working team is also very necessary , which has orderly shifts system , immediate backup , and so on .
Without any of the above measures of human resource management , it will not be easy to ensure the reliability of the whole system .
Some conservatives may still oppose that " you insist human management is important .
On the contrary , focusing on improving the management in engineering processes is already a way of applying social psychology .
In the highly hazardous industry like nuclear power plants , everyone should be responsible and devoted .
Applying psychology in engineering design processes is to let everyone work efficiently , such as arranging for psychotherapeutic sessions for operators and staff , can reduce the stress of workers who work for long hours under high pressure and help them relax .
All in all , human errors are avoidable , and psychology in engineering is meant to reduce the risk of nuclear industry failure caused by human errors .
Anyway , all the efforts made by the investigator and engineers are to make the nuclear power plants much safer and the resultant measures can be more widely used to meet the great demand of energy today .
Applying psychology provides us with a new option to effectively improve nuclear industry 's safety and reliability .
I 'm confident that with the help of psychology , the usage of nuclear power will have a brighter future .
16 % of the world 's electricity is supplied by nuclear power plants , and 30 % of the world 's fossil fuels are used to produce electricity .
A clean energy source like nuclear power seems to be the ideal solution for the energy crisis .
However the scars left from the Chernobyl disaster and the Three Mile Island catastrophe has changed the public opinion on nuclear reactors for the worse .
On April 26th 1986 , the Chernobyl nuclear reactor exploded . The whole town was evacuated and almost all of them never returned .
Around 30 people died and several thousands were exposed to radiation .
This works in favor of the VHTR , a scenario where a fast response is needed , as the VHTR would be suitable and safer .
The SFR boasts a recycling system where 99.9 % of the actinides are recycled back as fuels , such as plutonium and since the SFR is a closed fuel system , fuel can be used again in the system .
Unlike the SFR , the VHTR has no waste recycling system and hence It goes directly into the repository where the nuclear waste has a half life of about a few centuries only ( research is currently going on to reduce the half life ) .
In addition , in the SFR the recycled plutonium could be a security threat .
This coolant makes the VHTR significantly much safer since it makes its core highly stable and unreactive .
Even though the SFR has the above mentioned features , it only has a thermal efficiency of less the 40 % whilst the VHTR has an efficiency of above 50 % .
Hydrogen is also a clean fuel as it does not emit green house gasses when it is burned . It is also an alternate fuel which could be used to power vehicles in the future .
The SFR , due to its relatively low operating temperature and pressure , is much cheaper when it comes to material cost and building ; hence , it has a lower capital cost .
On the other hand the VHTR is more expensive to build ; its materials have to withstand high temperatures as well as high pressures .
Though the capital cost of the VHTR is high the operational cost is comparatively less since the VHTR is highly efficient at higher temperatures and hence is a good solution to get cheaper electricity .
Some may argue that the VHTR has too high a capital cost , as a prototype would cost 1Billion US dollars . But many countries have shown great interests in the development of the VHTR , and the cost of Research and Development , therefore , will be split amongst several countries .
People are very performance oriented and yet safety and cost conscious .
Thus it is a common dilemma faced by most engineers nowadays .
People expect the new and upcoming Generation IV nuclear power plants to be efficient and at the same time expecting engineers and researchers to make them safer and cheaper .
Thus with this in mind , I would strongly advocate further research and development on the Very-high-temperature reactors ( VHTR ) as they suit the " requirements " of the public the most .
Firstly , the VHRT had an earlier delivery date than most other designs and that was the reason why I supported it .
In times like this when the price of fossil fuels is sky rocketing , an earlier delivery date of 5 years for an efficient energy alternative is very crucial .
If the VHTR can be realized as soon as possible , public concerns about the hefty pricing on carbon tax and fossil fuels can then be addressed earlier .
Thus it translates to higher electrical production efficiency , meaning that it can produce more electrical energy .
With hydrogen generation made possible , the VHTR can replace future coal fueled hydrogen production plants , taking over the role of supplying energy for other hydrogen intensive industries and may also be able to generate hydrogen as a source of fuel .
Therefore the implementation of the VHTR can offer a wide range of solutions to the fuel crisis that is currently troubling the public .
This includes extensive research on materials that can withstand high temperature and that are stronger and corrosion resistant .
It is also relatively safer than the rest of the Gen IV nuclear power plants as it uses an inert gas , helium , as the coolant .
Nowadays , people are arguing about the research and development for generation IV reactors .
Many people support further research and development for generation IV reactors while others do not .
The most heated argument is how to ensure the safety of the operation of nuclear reactors .
From my point of view , I agree with the continuous research and development on the Very-High-Temperature-Reactor ( VHTR ) , which is one of the generation IV concepts , because it is the technology that brings us solutions to the current energy crisis .
Opponents of developing nuclear reactors claim that we should not put so much money and effort on such a dangerous plant .
Safety is the factor that most people worry about .
There have been two nuclear power plant accidents in history .
The Chernobyl accident caused a huge number of deaths and radiation-related injuries .
In fact , the accident occurred because the nuclear power plant was inappropriately operated and the reactor was not placed in the well-protected area .
As it is well controlled , no deaths were caused .
Nowadays , when building a nuclear plant , the safety issue needs to be considered .
If an accident occurs , the public will be prevented from the impact of the accident .
Besides safety , the cost , performance and environmental issues are also popular in today 's arguments .
A lot of money is also spent on developing these technologies which are still in the experimental stage .
According to a recent report of nuclear plants ( European Nuclear Society , 2009 ) , until 24 September 2009 , 436 nuclear power plant units in 31 countries are in operation and 53 plants in 15 countries are under construction .
About 17 % of the world 's electricity comes from nuclear plants .
It is obvious that spending more money on the development of nuclear power is quite reasonable .
Moreover , the performance of a nuclear plant is very significant compared to conventional thermal power stations .
Finally , under normal operation , nuclear power plants are environmentally-friendly .
It has many advantages compared to the existing technology .
It is able to produce an output temperature of up to 1000oC unlike the existing reactors which can only produce a temperature of about 300oC ( Butler , 2004 ) .
VHTR is more than three times more powerful than the existing reactors .
The safety characteristics of a helium-cooled , graphite-moderated core are employed by VHTR .
VHTR benefits from the high heat capacity and structural stability of the graphite together with the single phase and inert material of the Helium coolant .
The fuel allows high burn-up and because of the characteristics of the cooled uranium-oxycarbide .
The high operating temperature of the core in the VHTR allows emissions-free process .
We have strong evidence to show that with the improvement of technology , the concerns about the operation of nuclear plants will fade away .
It is clean and highly efficient .
In conclusion , the generation IV reactor concept opens a new chapter in the development of nuclear power .
It provides high-efficiency operation , produces not only heat but also hydrogen productions , has lower risk , and offers enhanced waste minimization .
With all these advantages , the generation IV reactors will be one of the best solutions to the world 's energy shortage problem .
