In recent studies , airbag deployment with or without seat belts used , has shown to decrease the risk of head , thorax and spine injuries [ 10 ] .
The challenger accident , which happened on the morning of January 28 , 1986 , was a in history for its catastrophic consequence and the great trauma it brought to people .
The Orbiter challenger , the 25the space shuttle into space , was also well-known as it was the first time that a school teacher had the chance to go into space .
However , only after seventy three seconds into the flight , the Challenger exploded and all seven of its crew died .
Some experts ( Robert E. , 1997 ) claimed that the challenger accident was mainly caused by the mechanical failure due to the flaw of the original design .
In my opinion , human factors were the main cause , as the accident would have been prevented if the decision makers had acted more rationally
From a mechanical point of view , the direct cause for the explosion was " the failure of the right solid rocket booster aft joint sealing , most likely because of the extremely cold temperature in the morning .
" ( Dick , 1986 ) Data and reviews also showed that there were actually essential design flaws of the Challenger . In particular , the O-rings in the SRB could not seal the joint when it was very cold .
Although technological deficiency was behind the failure of the Challenger , psychology could be implemented to stop the disaster from happening .
Before the launch of the challenger , what concerned the chief managers most were the preceding 24 successful space shuttle launches .
If the managers handled the pressure well , rechecked and tested the challenger carefully and decided not to launch the challenger until every safety concern was eliminated , the challenger accident could have been prevented .
( Website ) Unfortunately , even though the engineers told the supervisors of Morton Thiokol about this potential pitfall , their concern did not draw the full attention of the supervisors .
However , what they would get was precious time , and with more time they would have detected the problem and cancelled the launch instead of just delaying it .
Meanwhile , some engineers at Rockwell International also noticed that a significant amount of ice had built up on the fixed service structure that stood beside the shuttle .
To sum up , even though the Challenger was designed with some serious flaws and destined to fail in such a cold environment , appropriate psychology could still be implemented to prevent the accident from happening , as long as the decision of the launch was made with confidence and the potential dangers found by the engineers were cleared up .
And not just in that case , the use of psychology should always be required as a necessity in future engineering designs to enhance safety .
The Chernobyl accident in 1986 and Three Mile Island in 1979 have led to serious concerns about the safety of nuclear power plants .
This indicates that the public support has declined in recent years .
One of the main reasons for the decline is that the nuclear power plant might cause dangerous consequences when it malfunctions , due to its unstable nature .
Actually , nuclear power plants emit one hundredth times less greenhouse gases as compared to coal or gas power plants .
The cost of Uranium Ore is a very small portion of the operating cost of a nuclear power plant .
Fourth Generation Nuclear plants can fully utilize all the energy in natural uranium .
The amount of uranium accessible on Earth is able to support fourth generation nuclear power plants for hundreds of centuries .
Secondly , coal which is believed to be responsible for more quotidian problems such as acid rain and greenhouse gases emission .
In fact , the wastes produced by coal powered plants are 100 times more radioactive than those produced by a nuclear power plant generating similar amounts of energy .
The introduction of fourth generation nuclear power plants allows a new way of disposal of nuclear waste .
VHTR not only solves the nuclear waste problem , but its current wastes are a very valuable source of energy to power VHTR as they can burn plutonium , neptunium and other materials that Generation II and III reactors leave behind ( Smith , 2009 ) .
Generation III reactors are built within a double concealment which will protect the reactor even when the outer layer is penetrated .
Furthermore Generation IV reactors use different fuels and coolants than previous generators . The new reactors are built to be more efficient in absorbing heat through using better coolants , with improved circulation and larger containment structures .
Lastly , the cost of building nuclear power plants has greatly been reduced over the years .
Current reactors will still be usable for a long time ; thus , the construction cost will be spread over the years .
Current Generation III reactors are around $ 2000 per KW which is lower than $ 2300 per KW for a coal power plant .
The first nuclear reactor plant was built in Obninsk , a city in Russia , in 1954 .
Since then , the debate on whether we should use the nuclear energy has never been cooled down .
The catastrophic nuclear accidents such as Three Mile Island event and Chernobyl accident have cast a shadow over the safety of nuclear plants .
Since 2000 , ten countries including US , UK , Canada , France , Brazil , Japan and so on have started to cooperate in the research on a future generation of nuclear energy system , known as Generation 4 .
After two years ' great effort they have come up with a concrete and significant report about Generation 4 reactor concepts .
In this report the concepts of very-high-temperature-reactor ( VHTR ) are attention-getting because the new features of VHTR will greatly improve nuclear energy 's popularity , thus forcefully rejecting opponents ' conservative views .
One of the main opposing views is that nuclear energy is a big potential safety hazard because once nuclear leakage happens people 's health and the environment will be seriously threatened ( Cohen ) .
So a small inducement can cause a huge disaster .
As VHTR has this important feature , disastrous events can be effectively avoided and the prevention does not depend on sophisticated backup systems or experienced operators any more .
So we do not need to worry about big catastrophes like the Chernobyl accident .
Opponents were not satisfied with the performance of the nuclear reactor because the efficiency of current LWRs is 33 % and that of heat engines 20 % to 30 % .
( Lozanova , 2008 ) Now the situation has changed .
At this high temperature the rate of the reaction will dramatically increase and much more energy will be released from the same amount of fuel .
Another great benefit under the extremely high temperature reactors is that the reactors can be used to split hydrogen from water thermochemically .
This feature makes VHTR outstanding among all the reactors .
The opponents thought that it was not worthy to generate electricity by nuclear energy because the cost of building nuclear power plants would be an astronomical figure .
Second , research has been done to extend the tenure of the use of the facilities .
Third , the traditional energy sources like coal and petroleum are getting more expensive because they are non-renewable-resources and will be exhausted one day .
In contrast , with the development of the nuclear technology and the application of nuclear energy on a large scale , the efficiency of nuclear reactors will be improved gradually and the price of nuclear energy will decrease .
The above three points prove that it is worth to build VHTRs because they will pay back in the long run .
Through taking a look at the current energy situation and analyzing the special advantages of VHTR , a Generation 4 nuclear reactor , it should be evident that the VHTR concept is advanced and VHTR will be useful to actual circumstances .
The three outstanding characters of VHTR are passive safety , high efficiency and clean energy .
These distinctive features are significant in the nuclear industry because they can help avoid miserable nuclear accidents , raise the efficiency of nuclear reactors to a new level and decrease the cost of nuclear industry .
" ( Our Energy , 2007 ) Without the public fear and reluctance to accept nuclear power , the world may now be enjoying abundant electricity and accelerating economic growth , especially in some developing countries like India and China .
As expected , every possible ways of generating energy are under research .
However , only nuclear reactors can generate electricity at high efficiency and are viable for a long period of time .
Therefore , it is obvious that nuclear power will be undergoing immense research and development .
Amongst the six most probable concepts at the present stage , the Super-Water-Cooled Reactor ( SCWR ) is the most suitable and worth extensive research , after after its properties are compared with those of the other five .
The first issue is the performance of reactors .
To maximize the level of energy output , it seems that the Very-High-Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) , which could achieve 50 % efficiency level when deployed , is a better choice .
Furthermore , the disparity between the two reactors ( VHTR and SCWR ) in terms of efficiency is not huge .
This is attributed to the existing light water reactor technology on the basis of which SCWR is developed .
On the other hand , the electric efficiency of a conventional thermal power station , considered as saleable energy , is typically 33 % to 48 % .
Hence , it is reasonable to further develop the SCWR system , since its overall performance excels .
Opponents also claim that constructing nuclear power reactors is a huge capital-intensive project , which requires intensive investment of money and research .
After the deployment of a nuclear plant , more funds are needed for insurance coverage , maintenance and labor .
If the ratio of energy output and all inputs is considered , the rate of return of SCWR is faster than that of the others , not mentioning the low price of the electricity when the design is successful .
Moreover , comparing with the other five concepts which use inert gas , liquid compound or metal as coolants , water is much easily accessed and present in relative abundance .
Thus , the manufacturing process of coolant is simpler for SCWR , and thus it is also cheaper .
This saves a lot of experiments for scientists .
The final design proposes a reduction in the size of the reactor coolant pumps , piping , and associated equipment .
Opponents ' views are that the very high pressure SCWR requires may pose risks , which is indeed a realistic concern .
It is greatly simplified after discarding the step of steam-water conversion .
It reduces the probability of making mistakes and the level of seriousness of accidents .
It is hardly possible , as what many nuclear research associations have asserted , to have a second Chernobyl incident .
This feature limited the extent of its nuclear pollution which leads to health problems like birth defects .
Hence , although there are inevitable risks that we have to bear for every type of design , we can still choose appropriately the one that can minimize those risks .
In conclusion , SCWR reactor excels in performance , cost and safety .
As nuclear energy is taking over the world , the development on SCWR will be the stepping stone and will lead us to a " new dawn " .
Nuclear technology has always been a controversial issue , with much public opposition expressing their concerns , such as high cost , security problems and safety issues .
Researchers have proposed new generation IV reactors , which are targeted at answering these pressing concerns .
An example is the Very High Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) which boasts a super helium coolant which is much more effective than water , and yet is both inert and unreactive ( Teri Ehresman , 2009 ) .
With human population rising at an exponential rate , peaking at an estimated 9.1 billion in 2050 , energy consumption is , too , expected to rise proportionally .
Nuclear energy is definitely a viable option that can meet this demand .
As nuclear technology is known for its vast and massive destruction , many policies and measures are taken to ensure that this nuclear technology does not fall into the wrong hands .
Many have also argued that terrorists are able to collect these by-products and use them as a weapon .
All these measures taken will keep the by-products safe from terrorist 's reach .
It is clear that nuclear technology is the best alternative to the current fossil fuel consumption as it produces a relative larger amount of energy .
With the global growth in population and economy , energies needed for either manufacturing industries or home appliances are increasing ; hence , developing nuclear power becomes an important issue .
Among the six generation IV reactors , compared to other similar reactors which are able to generate both electricity and hydrogen power , the Lead-cooled fast reactor requires relatively lower temperature and lower pressure with the support of recycling of the waste .
Although a large scale of energy can be obtained by generating nuclear power , there are critical voices over the use of it in terms of safety concerns and environmental pollutions .
Hence , nuclear energy is definitely a safe and reasonable approach to solve the problem of producing enough energy for both the present and the future needs .
Firstly , the critics claim that the operation of nuclear plant is dangerous because of the only one accident which happened in Chernobyl in history .
The radioactivity escaped from one overheated core into the atmosphere , and caused 28 people to die , 134 people to fall sick and about 70 cases of thyroid cancer in children .
However , such an accident will not happen again . That is because nowadays all nuclear reactors that are currently in operation worldwide are placed inside a containment building .
The containment building helps to keep the radiation inside in the case of a faulty operation of the reactor .
Its ability to prevent the leak of radiation was proved in 1979 , during the reactor core meltdown at the Three Mile Island .
It should have caused major impact to people living there , but in fact , no injuries or deaths occurred because of the presence of the containment building .
As far as accidents are concerned , coal mining is more dangerous , as 100 miners die in mining per year in the U.S and another 100 die in transporting .
Secondly , from an environmental standpoint , the opposing views think that the life-cycle emissions of the nuclear energy are great pollutants .
Furthermore , in fact 15 % electricity which is generated by nuclear power globally greatly reduces the amounts of carbon dioxide emitted into the atmosphere every year by 2.1 billion tonnes ( Position Paper , n.d ) .
About 4.8 million tonnes of sulphur dioxide and 2.6 million tonnes of nitrogen oxides are avoided each year in European countries ( Position Paper , n.d ) .
Thirdly , people oppose the development of nuclear power due to the problem of long term radiation influence caused by nuclear wastes .
Several physicists in Germany claim to have found out a way to speed up the decay process of radioactive waste on timescales of a few tens of years and make it harmless .
The same goes for the discovery of Nuclear Solution Inc. Its president and CEO Dr. Paul M. Brown claims that they have a technology to make the nuclear waste a safe energy by burning it .
( Spirit of Ma'at Online Magazine Feb 2002 ) .The six generation lead-cool fast reactor also provides a function of waste recycling to handle the waste ; this will again ease the work of disposing the waste ( Butler .
To sum up , nuclear energy is safe to develop and use with the continuing evolution of nuclear plants and reactors , and it is also an emission- free energy source which can significantly reduce carbon dioxide gas and acid rains .
The waste produced by it can be recycled and reused to reduce the radiation influence to the environment and our society ; as a result , cost will be also reduced on the whole .
In conclusion , in my opinion nuclear energy can be used to solve the problem of increasing energy demand in various industries , because it is safe to both human beings and the environment , and it is capable to provide relatively larger amounts of energy than other sources .
