Their design errors eventually would result in the malfunction of the products , thus causing accidents .
They claim that the engineers were being unprofessional ( Eschede , n.d. ) , because the engineers were concerned more about the interior facilities of the train .
Passengers could enjoy the radio , the newspaper as well as refreshment , including wonderful meals provided from the luxurious dining car .
The design engineers were said to put so much effort into these trivial factors rather than safety issues .
In fact , over the years ICE expanded throughout Germany , and the safety record was perfect .
They were unprotected by any form of crash barrier .
The train , ICE , did have an adequate protection system as well as a warning system .
( NASA , 2007 ) Passengers would have pulled the emergency break to stop the train as soon as they witnessed the wheel failure .
In fact , one passenger sensed something was wrong , and tried to remind the driver of the hazard .
Technology at that time limited the designing of ICE , thus causing the design failure .
In fact , despite the fact that reprocessing and research cost too much money , the molten salt reactor is profitable in a long term and it is economical compared to other reactors .
All these can compensate for part of the expenses on the reprocessing and research .
With less fuel , it produces electricity and hydrogen four to six times greater than high temperature reactors do ( " Generation IV nuclear reactor , " 2009 ) .
With the demand for energy increasing , it is urgent to find an economical and efficient energy source .
As the developing countries are building more factories and cities throughout the years , the global energy consumption is rapidly increasing over the years .
This is a concern as at the rate countries are consuming energy it is a matter of time before the earth runs out of natural resources .
Countries are spending a large amount of money to develop the Generation IV reactors to meet the demand of energy consumption .
The objectives of Generation IV reactors are to improve safety features , minimise waste output and decrease the construction and operating cost of nuclear reactors .
Although there are many risk hazards involving the VHTR , it is still one of the most promising models , and many countries are keen on adopting this model as the future reactor .
One of the most practical issues of concern is the cost .
All countries want to build reactors that are cheap in cost and that are efficient in producing electricity and hydrogen gases .
The molten salt is preferred as its operation system is less complicated which means that it is cheaper to construct and it does not need to run on very high temperature or pressure .
However , in terms of the overall development cost , the Very High temperature reactor is still much cheaper than the Molten Salt reactor .
This is so as the VHTR is simply the upgrading of existing high temperature reactors while the MSR is a relatively new technology .
Hence VHTR needs less testing and less time to develop whereas extensive testing is required for the MSR .
In terms of efficiency , there is criticism regarding its high fuel burn up and the need to periodically change the graphite core .
The initial design of the VHTR also does not allow the system to produce electricity directly as modifications are required to be made to the plant to achieve generation of electricity .
In comparison , the MSR is considered a better choice as it is safer to operate at lower pressures and temperatures .
The efficiency of the MSR will improve in the near future as scientists are working to increase the output of hydrogen and electricity ( NERAC ) .
Despite the negative points of the VHTR , it is still way ahead of the MSR and all other generation IV models , as only VHR has an efficiency of more than fifty percent .
Not only does it produce more electricity , but the high temperature generated is actually not useless .
This is due to the fact that the VHTR runs on very high temperatures and it will have a higher chance of failure .
For VHTR safety is maintained manually by safety officers and it is not reliable as humans will make mistakes .
Then for MSR about 200 million dollars have been spent on safety testing .
In conclusion , VHTR is still one of the better choices when compared to MSR .
This is so as it will be ready by the year 2025 , five years earlier than MSR .
With the operation of VHTR five years ahead , the revenue generated by VHR will provide more funds for further research and improvement .
Then in term of efficiency it is ahead of MSR and there is no guarantee that after intensive research the efficiency will improve .
Hence VHTR has the potential to be the main provider of electricity in the future .
In 2000 , The Generation IV International Forum ( GIF ) , an international cooperative project representing governments of 13 countries , was initiated .
Scientists from these countries cooperate to develop the next generation of nuclear technology , the Generation IV Nuclear Reactor ( World Nuclear Association , 2008 ) .
In my point of view , among all the six reactors , the Sodium-cooled fast reactor ( SFR ) is the one that should be chosen as one of the prototypes .
The generation IV SFR is a new concept which is safe not only when it operates during electric production , but also when it meets the problem of nuclear weapons and the terrorism attack .
Many people think that compared with traditional ways of producing electricity , using nuclear reactors is not safe .
In fact , SFR is a very safe nuclear reactor operating under low pressures and low temperatures .
The operating temperatures of SFR range from 500 to 550 , one of the two reactors with the lowest temperatures among all the six together .
Moreover the sodium-cooled technique has been in use since 1951 .
Scientists from Japan have also been concerned about the chemical reaction between sodium and water .
Nuclear weapon and terrorism are always sensitive topics to both governments and ordinary people .
The new design for SRF is likely to have all the neutron action in the core .
Yes , this is a drawback of the SFR ; however , scientists are working hard on it to find out the way to reduce the capital cost of the SFR and they have already made some achievements .
On November 27-28 , 2006 , Mr. Kazuo Mukai , from the Advanced Nuclear System Research and Development Directorate Japan Atomic Energy Agency ( JAEA ) , had an international seminar on " Coolants and Innovative Reactor Technologies " in Cadarache , which is a research center for nuclear energy in France .
In this seminar he talked about the JSFR and the achievements Japanese scientists had made to reduce the cost of the SFR .
Kazuo ( 2006 ) said that by adopting high chromium steel with higher strength and lower thermal expansion , the capacity of the heat exchangers and the flow rate in the pipe got enlarged , so that the piping could be shortened and the loop number also got reduced .
This is just an example of the achievements .
The research is still ongoing and scientists have confidence that they will have more findings in the future .
The advanced technology of the SFR will benefit people all around the world in the not too distant future .
The Chernobyl disaster is one of the worst engineering accidents that has ever happened in history .
People usually say that mistakes are inevitable and nuclear power is in fact extremely dangerous so that working with it will always involve a high chance of accidents .
Including psychological factors during the design process is found to be one of the ways to improve safety which might have prevented the Chernobyl incident .
I agree to the point that humans can make mistakes .
The problem lies in the behavior of the plant operators .
In this way , they will be more careful in doing their task and will as a result be able to avoid making mistakes .
Opponents also state that while nuclear power is indeed dangerous for that reason , it is impossible not to have accidents while working with it .
An accident is a situation when there is a failure in the interaction between man and machine ( Stoop , 1995 ) .
Most of the time , while designing a system , engineers are likely to overestimate the ability of the user ( Wilpert , 2007 ) .
Instead of following the safety procedure , the plant operators even blocked the reactor 's protection system ( making automatic shut down impossible ) in order to keep the test running ( Onisawa and Nishiwaki , 1988 ) .
Since men and machines are equally important to achieve safety in design , psychologists ' role is to be concerned about the human resources which are usually neglected by engineers .
If both machines and men are well designed , safety will definitely improve and the possibility of accidents will be reduced .
Without considering psychological factors , there is a big possibility that there will be a bad interaction between man and machine which will then result in an accident such as Chernobyl 's .
Therefore , psychological factors play an important role in reducing the possibility of accidents as well as improving a system 's safety .
Also , the use of psychology could counter the underestimation of the number of errors that will form inevitably .
Opponents argue that psychology would not be useful as the chief cause for the accident is the lack of knowledge of the operators .
They might have been trained to operate even though they do not understand the principles behind it .
Psychology or the employment of psychologists to assist in the design process would thus be futile .
This concept is evident when accounts of the accident revealed that the operator indifferently disregarded safety protocols .
Hence , designers could have brought in psychologists to evaluate the design to inhibit such unauthorized practices and to ensure the safety standards are kept high .
According to Wilpert ( 2007 ) , the design process encompasses both social science and engineering .
This element is the consensual agreement that errors can occur anywhere and every stage should be treated meticulously .
Therefore , psychology could be used in the design process and could perhaps have minimized the possibilities of accidents .
To sum up , the use of psychology could have been used in some phases of the design process .
Since the introduction of nuclear-powered generators , public opposition is one of the reasons why only limited nuclear reactors have been built in the past .
Their concern arises because of a few incidents that have happened in the past which includes a partial reactor meltdown in 1979 at Three Mile Island , Pennsylvania and also the 1986 accident at Chernobyl in Ukraine , where the reactor core exploded and caused the death of 31 people and spewed radioactive debris across Europe ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Nevertheless , the first reason that the public is concerned over the funding of generation IV nuclear reactors is that the nuclear reactors will not reduce greenhouse-gas emissions as compared to natural gas and oil use ( Nature , 2008 ) .
However , this is not the case as there are countries constructing nuclear reactors because they can indeed improve the environment .
According to Ruth ( 2009 ) , medical isotopes used in cancer research can be supplied using accelerators instead of nuclear reactors as using accelerators is a safer and cheaper method .
However , nuclear reactors should continue to be used to supply medical isotopes as they can produce isotopes much faster than accelerators .
Furthermore , the idea of accelerators to supply medical isotopes has still not been put to practical use as they still require further research and development unlike nuclear reactors , which have already been vastly used in medical researches .
This can be shown as many researchers were lamenting on the shutdown of the nuclear reactor located in chalk river , Ontario , and their medical research had to be put to a halt ( Nature , 2008 ) .
The last concern from the public opposition is that nuclear reactors are not safe enough to be built as they are under-designed for earthquakes as the earthquake in Japan killed at least 9 , injured 1000 , caused the evacuation of further 10,000 people , sparked a fire and caused radiation- contaminated water from the nuclear reactor to spill into the sea ( Nature , 2007 ) .
To wrap up , I believe that the new generation IV reactors such as SCWR are nothing like their previous generation of nuclear reactors because technology is constantly improving each day to make the nuclear reactors safer to be built .
Thus , the public opposition should look at the new generation IV reactors in a different light and not just be based on some of the incidents that happened in the past .
All of these reactors have improved safety precautions and higher security levels to ensure the safety of the public .
In addition , the new SFR will be equipped with a better coolant system to prevent a reactor meltdown and stronger containment structures to guard against terrorist attacks ( Smith , 2009 ) .
Thus , less research will be required for SFR , which also means that the research cost will be reduced .
Furthermore , by choosing the SFR 's proven method of cooling the nuclear core , it removes the uncertainties of using new and untested technologies which are present in the other reactors .
SFR is also chosen by the United States as their front runner for generation IV fast reactors due to its strong technology basis ( US DOE/NE 2006 ) .
On top of its technological readiness , SFR is designed for high efficiency as well .
It recycles nuclear fuel through a process whereby a group of chemical elements called actinides are produced .
Plutonium is also included in this group and it can be used for the production of nuclear weapons .
Therefore , to ensure the nuclear non-proliferation , SFR is designed such that plutonium can not be extracted from the nuclear core .
SFR will also be using spent thermal reactor fuel from other older nuclear reactors as its initial fuel ( US DOE NERAC/GIF 2002 ) .
All these designs will lead to a more efficient usage of the nuclear fuel and also help solve the current problem of the disposal of nuclear wastes .
The truth is , we will one day run out of fossil fuels ; hence , we must plan ahead and look for other sources of energy .
Nuclear power plants may be hazardous , but the new SFR boosts many new safeguards .
Nuclear power has been a controversial issue ever since the atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki during World War II .
Over the years , nuclear power has evolved with the help of technological advancement .
Today , scientists have gone step further in developing what we know as the Fourth Generation Reactors .
Firstly , the cost of operating a VHTR is truly subjective .
Naturally , The public would have an impression that VHTR would be much more expensive , compared to renewable energy such as solar and wind .
Barry ( 2009 ) cites that the capital cost of building a solar plant is 25 times more than that of building a plant and the land area a solar plant occupies is 400 times more than that of a nuclear plant .
In addition , building VHTR will boost the economy as it creates job opportunities in the areas surrounding the power plant .
However in VHTR , plutonium is spiked with heat producing and radioactive elements ( Butler , 2004 ) .
These elements cause the plutonium waste to increase in temperature such that it is too hot to handle and therefore prevent anyone from stealing it .
In VHTR , heat resistant materials are used to build the nuclear reactor so that the heat is carefully contained .
For example , helium is used as a cooling agent in VHTR as helium is an inert gas and does not provide any hazardous effect .
It is known that these radioactive wastes have very long shelf life and will not decay until a few hundred years later .
However , in VHTR , an additional processing step is taken to shorten the life span of the wastes and these wastes are carefully contained .
Compared to solar plants , nuclear plants actually produce less carbon dioxide .
Barry ( 2009 ) writes that solar plants produce 25 times more carbon dioxide than nuclear plants .
In conclusion , VHTR is much safer , more environmental friendly , more efficient and much cheaper .
Hence , we should abandon those pessimistic views on nuclear power and embrace this new source of energy .
Nuclear energy has been a hot topic since several decades ago .
It is clean and powerful .
According to Butler ( 2004 ) , nuclear energy is not a source of carbon dioxide . With the emissions of green-house gases now soaring , and the energy demands predicted to double by 2050 , the nuclear option is finding its way back onto the table .
Besides , nuclear reactors produce a great output of electricity and hydrogen .
However , the use of nuclear energy is not without opposing voices .
Because of its safety , no waste and high output , I support funding for its further research and development .
With memories of the partial reactor meltdown in 1979 at Three Mile Island , Pennsylvania , and of the 1986 accident at Chernobyl in Ukraine , during which the reactor core exploded , killing some 31 people immediately and spewing radioactive debris across Europe , the public consider nuclear reactors as something extremely dangerous .
However , sodium-cooled fast reactors are rather safe because they can react under relatively low temperature of 550 degrees in contrast with the above 700 degrees for other reactors ; it also reacts under low pressure .
The low temperature and pressure requirements lower the demands of the equipment and the conditions for the reaction ; as a result , the reactor becomes safer .
Besides , in order to make the reaction safer , the engineers in Japan have found out the methods to prevent the chemical reactions of sodium itself and the leak of sodium by using double-wall piping method , highly reliable equipment with double-wall tube and sensitive leak detector .
Therefore , sodium-cooled fast reactors are very safe and also safer than the other reactors in the fourth generation .
Some pacifists are sceptical about the safety of nuclear energy because reprocessing nuclear waste is controversial as it separates out plutonium , a key ingredient of advanced nuclear weapons .
Besides , they are worried that nuclear reactors would become a terrorist target because of the radioactive waste .
Nevertheless , these terrible things wo n't happen in sodium-cooled fast reactors , because the reaction is within the core and the recycling is closed , which means the recycling is not separated out .
As a consequence , people do not need to worry about the radioactive waste during the production .
Besides the problem of safety , another problem is the cost .
The costs of nuclear reactors which consists of the construction cost , operating cost and decommissioning cost are very high .
Several billion dollars is needed to get a nuclear reactor going and the sodium-cooled fast reactors are even more expensive than the other ones .
Having seen the value of the sodium-cooled fast reactors , many countries are investing in the sodium-cooled fast reactors .
Meanwhile , many engineers are looking for methods to cut the cost of nuclear reactors .
Specifically , the cost can be reduced by reducing the number of refuelling outages , compacting the reactor vessel , sampling the vessel internals , reducing the loop number , shortening the pipes , integrating the primary components and so on .
Thus , we should believe in the bright future of the cost-effective sodium-cooled fast reactors .
As one of the fourth generation of nuclear reactors , the sodium-cooled fast reactor has its own advantages .
It is safer and it is now under further improvement in many developed countries .
Briefly , sodium-cooled fast reactors have brilliant prospects and the public do not need to be much concerned about their safety .
This was partly due to the 1979 incident at Three Mile Island , Pennsylvania where a partial reactor meltdown occurred , and the 1986 incident at Chernobyl in Ukraine , where the reactor core exploded , which resulted in casualties and spewing harmful debris across Europe ( Butler , 2004 ) .
Also , the new reactors are designed with the following objectives in mind : economic competitiveness , enhanced safety , minimal radioactive waste generation and proliferation resistance .
This way , the temperature at the core outlet can reach more than 1000 Â° C ( Corwin , 2003 ) .
It can therefore be used as a significant source of electrical power and hydrogen generation or as a heat source .
Not only is it advantageous to sodium because it can be subjected to high temperature , it is also efficient in the transfer of thermal energy .
Therefore in my opinion , VHTR is rated better in terms of physical protection and performance as compared to SFR .
Active and passive safeguard features against accidents are to be carefully considered .
To reduce the probability of radioactive elements leaking to the atmosphere , there must be an emphasis on the human factors pertaining to plant operations .
VHTR employs the method of burying waste into the floor bed of deep oceans in the middle of inactive oceanic tectonic plates .
Even with deep trenches used , it is possible that life forms living in them would bring back the still harmful nuclear waste back into contact with other life forms .
A key issue on the SFR system is the reduction of cost to competitive levels .
With innovations to reduce capital cost , it can be extended to electricity production , given the proven capability of sodium reactors to utilize almost all of the energy in the natural uranium .
Despite challenges within steps of the nuclear fuel cycle , they can be solved with improvements in technology and with global cooperation .
Although VHTR has the advantage of high fuel burn up , SFR performs better in areas such as having low maintenance and operating cost , passive safety and potential modular construction .
VHTR must overcome these challenges , particularly in reactor safety and costs in order to be comparable with the SFR system .
( ElBaradei , 2005 ) Critics have found out that mechanical errors such as the building of Unit 4 was not up to its highest standards and that some of its safety devices were faulty , while the human management of the whole plant was questionable .
Safety measures , for example installing auto power shut-off for the reactors in the event of an accident or oversight , would have been taken to assist the operators should any human error occurred .
Having said that , the use of psychology during the process is done on the basis of an ideal situation , where the human labour is of the highly skilled and with high capabilities .
Critics have brought out the point that the explosion of Unit 4 was due to the poor management of the whole plant , from the failure to follow certain safety standards , to the design flaws of the reactor and structure , and to the incompetency of the labour .
( North , 2006 ) Furthermore , the state was practicing the policy of secrecy for 35 years , such that only certain information on safety standards was made known and approved , while the design flaws were always hidden from the light .
( Munipov , ND ) Psychology is the study of the mind and if it is included in the design process , the design would be seen from the user 's perspective and thus the end product would have an effective design .
The use of psychology during the design process would have minimized the effects of the accident , but would not have prevented it from happening because the accident happened due to the combination of errors on multiple levels , such as the context of time and national culture .
On the 20 April 2004 at about 3.30pm in the afternoon , a major construction incident occurred in Singapore , the collapse of Nicoll Highway .
This incident has also resulted in 4 fatalities and 3 casualties .
The incident is mainly due to the collapse of a deep excavation work alongside Nicoll Highway .
What could have caused this incident ?
According to the committee of inquiry ( Press Release 2005 , Ministry of Manpower ) , it was concluded that the incident was due to inadequate temporary works and design construction errors .
Very often , such mistakes are always linked to the negligence and carelessness of humans .
Psychological factors play an important role in the root of this incident .
The use of such model then led to serious false predictions of forces which resulted in the fatal catastrophe .
The incident was due to the carelessness of the engineers then .
According to Land Transport Authority 's counsel K- Shanmugam ( 2005 ) , Nishimatsu-Lum Chang maintained that designs were satisfactory even after the discovery of minor designs faults and pressured LTA to allow them to continue their excavation activities .
It was observed that the main contractors wanted to avoid troubles and further expenses for rectifications of minor faults , hence resulting in the negligence .
Psychological factors in the design processes such as negligence , impatience and carelessness led to inadequate instrumentation and monitoring works , improper handling of the instrumentation data .
From the analysis of major accidents , we learnt that human actions always play a major role in triggering accidents as well as mitigating their consequences .
The committee of inquiry for the incidence also pointed out that the temporary works pertaining to deep excavation were not regulated to the same degree as the permanent works .
They tend to have a psychological effect of letting down their guards in the designs where the standards are not as strict , often leading to carelessness , negligence and eventually accidents .
Many of the workplace incidents such as the collapse of Nicoll Highway have been traditionally categorized as a single component failure Design error .
Occupational hazards and individual workplace accidents are very often influenced by individual constructs like motivation , perception , attitude and decision- making ( Fahlbruch and Wilpert , 1999 ) .
The problem is not simply due to design faults , as the root of these design faults is usually psychological factors such as carelessness , lousy moods , fatigue and inability to stay focused .
When there is a strong safety psychological awareness culture , accidents could be prevented !
There are three main reasons for this incident : cost cutting on the temporary structure , the lack of concentration at work and negligence in checking the design of the structure due to its temporary identity .
Erroneous individual action is a crucial link in this chain .
In order to avoid the delay penalty of S $ 25M , Nishimatsu-Lum Chang ( NLC ) , the contractor company for constructing Mass Rapid Transport under Nicoll Highway , did not seek their client Singapore 's Land Transport Authority ( LTA ) 's approval on the replacement of material .
If both NLC and LTA could communicate and negotiate efficiently on the extension of the deadline , NLC might not have resorted to risk compromising safety for fines .
Although the standard legal law set by the Employment Act states that each employee can only work 44 hours per week ( Foreign , 2003 ) , NLC did not obey the law .
Therefore , it is necessary to forbid the company from making the workers work overtime .
As a result , workers tend to pay less attention to the details and surroundings and are more inclined to erroneous action which , in this case , posed great dangers .
If anyone was alert , there would have had enough time to evacuate everybody from the site before it actually collapsed since it took 1 hour for the first failure of the connection to the total collapse of the excavation ( Design , 2005 ) , and the incident might not have happened .
There was no law stating safety rules for temporary structures in 2004 ; thus , it was not compulsory to make the temporary structure a very well-built one .
Problems arise where individual perspectives come to play a part .
Assumption has always been made when some people are doing the 'assuring ' job .
In addition to make the design process worse .
First , the LTA personnel thought that the contractors would do a good job on designing the structure and do the calculations to ensure it is acceptable and assumed that the contractors already did the proper checking for the design .
As a result , they missed out 2 mistakes that could be easily spotted .
The first mistake is that the contractors used the wrong soil analysis at the early stages of the design process .
The second mistake is that the contractors miscalculated the capacity of the loads for the temporary structure .
Moreover , when NLC 's engineers brought out an alternative analysis models , LTA 's engineers rejected them because the latter thought that it was overcautious .
Second , the LTA 's personnel , due to slothfulness , did not do their job on ensuring the safety of building works by performing checks on the construction work .
Currently , there already is a set of Safety Control Process ( Seetoh Hon Hoy , 2005 ) for temporary structure to prevent this from happening again .
By having certain degree of psychology knowledge , we are able to understand human weaknesses so that design processes can incorporate psychological knowledge to improve the system .
This can greatly reduce human errors made during work which may able to reduce accidents from happening .
Acting like a double edged sword , it is hailed as the wonder that can solve current energy crisis while critics believe incidents such as 1986 Chernobyl accidents in Ukraine and 1976 Three Mile Islands reactors meltdown may occur again .
However , due to worldwide soaring increase in carbon emission , a series of new generation IV nuclear generators concepts have been proposed .
Lead cooled fast reactor ( LFR ) is one of them .
Among the six proposed generation IV reactors , three of them belong to fast reactors .
Fast reactors utilize neutrons of much higher energy to cause fission , which differs from present types of reactors that slow down neutrons using moderators such as water .
LFR is a type of fast reactors that rely on lead as coolant in the reactor .
Its ability to provide reliable safety , efficient waste management and effective cost minimization enables itself to have a competitive edge over other energy sources .
Skeptics believe that if nuclear energy replaces oil to further increase its current 21percent contribution of electricity in the United States , the nuclear reactors may become potential targets for terrorist groups .
In addition , there is still no safe guarantee that these new LFRs operate without any malfunction as they have not been presented to the National Regulatory Council for review .
Despite all these factors , general public may not be aware of the refined safety measures that these new reactors possess .
First of all , all generation IV nuclear reactors include passive design that relies on law of nature , which simplifies the current nuclear generator design that has redundant valves and control system .
Therefore , during any emergency process , the required human intervention is minimized .
Moreover , LFR has a safety advantage compared to the other nuclear reactors designs .
Calculation has been done to show that LFR has a better safety design mainly because lead serves as a better coolant that does not react as readily as sodium and air .
( Kamil Tuek , 2006 ) In fact , the number of incidents that may lead to severe accidents has been declining in recent years .
The waste management is another problematic issue in the current generation III nuclear reactors .
An ordinary thermal nuclear reactor is only to extract approximately only 5 percent energy contained in uranium .
( Smith , 2009 ) That shows the other 95 percent of the energy would end up as waste and need to be stored in safety for thousands of years .
Millions of tons of radioactive materials are currently sitting somewhere in this world .
Instead of waiting for them to lose their radioactivity , a fast reactor is able to utilize most energy from the remaining 95 percent energy .
With current nuclear energy wastes sitting in the storage sites , GE Hitachi Company believes the power extracted would be able to meet 70 years of energy demands in USA .
( GE Reports , 2009 ) By supporting the research on LFR , not only would it provide tremendous energy power to the world , but it would also solve the headache waste issue that every OECD nation is facing .
Feasibility also needs to be analyzed in our discussion .
One current LFR research , SSTAR ( Small , Sealed , Transportable , Autonomous Reactor ) offers a good solution in minimizing the capital cost of building a nuclear reactor .
Manufacturing costs including materials , expertise requirement and manpower have effectively been lessened with this concept .
We do not know which research may ripen before the others .
LFR , a highly feasible solution for the earth 's energy crisis , has a clear direction and promising future .
It deserves more human and financial resources in order for it to reach the maturity stage .
Safe , less waste and more affordable , these are the characteristics of our future energy .
On April 26 , 1986 , one of the four nuclear reactors at the Chernobyl power station , Ukraine , exploded .
This disaster has raised great public concern about the safety of nuclear power .
Helium is an inert gas .
Some promising materials like zirconium carbide can allow the plants to perform at the temperature up to 1800 Â° C ( U.S .
The success of this reactor suggests that more advanced temperature-resistant materials can be developed in the near future .
According to research , the radioactivity for the VHTR waste is relatively small compared with the other reactors .
VHTR produces " less heavy metal radioactive waste " and " less plutonium per unit of energy produced " because of VHTR 's high thermal efficiency ( Shropshire and Herring , 2004 ) .It has a high thermal efficiency of over 50 % , while other reactors only have a thermal efficiency of 33 % -50 % ( U.S .
DOE Nuclear Energy Research Advisory Committee , 2009 ) .Thus , VHTR is less harmful to the environment .
Some opponents may think that VHTR would be very costly .
VHTR has the advantage of meticulous safety designs , small environmental impact and relatively low cost .
Therefore , VHTR could be a promising nuclear reactor for the " Nuclear power 's new dawn " .
Although VHTR is designed to be a high-energy-efficient system , there is evidence that shows MSR is the better concept .
Proponents of VHTR claim that it has an inherent passive safety feature for both the fuel and the reactor ( Goethem 2008 ) .
This is due to the nature of molten fluoride salts , which are used as coolant and are mechanically and chemically stable at sea-level pressures ( Forsberg 2004 ) .
In other words the MSR 's core can not have a steam explosion ; thus , it eliminates the need for additional advanced technology to control the high pressure .
But unlike VHTR , MSR uses another kind of fuel cycle called thorium , which is much more abundant in nature than uranium ( David.S 2007 ) . The first advantage of using a thorium fuel cycle is the ability to burn up most of the actinides which produce radioactivity .
Unlike thorium , enriched uranium used in VHTR can potentially produce a bomb .
Moreover uranium is limited in supply and not as abundant as thorium .
The need for expensive fuel-enrichment facilities is unnecessary when thorium is being used as the main fuel cycle too .
Automation throughout the reactors and passive safety features are just some of the technologies implemented to make the Generation IV reactors safer .
With the combination of thorium being used as the main fuel cycle , MSR is a safe reactor with an abundant source of fuel .
In terms of safety and fuel technologies used , MSR stands in a better position than VHTR .
The world 's population will expand further in the next few decades .
Countries around the globe are all working for a better quality of life , driving up the demand for energy .
However , if a mixture of energy production options is continued , it will impact the environment adversely and cause climate change in the long term .
Nuclear power plants are providing 16 % of the electricity in the world , the largest share provided by non- greenhouse-gas-emitting source ( A Technology Roadmap for Generation IV Nuclear Energy Systems , 2002 ) .
Many countries of the world , both industrialized and developing , believe that nuclear energy can be used to meet their demand because of its long-term sustainability and absence of environmental impacts .
The concept of Generation IV Nuclear Energy System ( NES ) is able to meet this demand and its implementation is inevitable .
With ongoing Research & Development ( R&D ) for its related technology , GFR is predicted to be delivered by 2025 .
Though questions have been raised on its pending features of development , GFR should be chosen as the research prototype due to its performance , safety and economics features .
There has been doubt on the safety of the GFR system .
It is also one of the objectives of a Generation IV NES to " increase the assurance that they are a very unattractive and the least desirable route for diversion or theft of weapons-usable materials , and provide increased physical protection against acts of terrorism " ( A Technology Roadmap for Generation IV Nuclear Energy Systems , 2002 ) .
To address this , the GFR system has involved measures to enhance PR & PE and has adopted an actinide management to ensure nuclear waste utilization and availability of fuel in the long term .
With the effort of scientists and researchers , GFR will be safely deployable if the technical hurdles are overcome .
Each of the six prototypes costs about US $ 1 billion ( Butler , 2004 ) .
However in the long term , the cost is justified by the economics-of-scale .
Hence , scientists are researching the fourth generation nuclear reactor which can provide higher power output and at the same time reduce risks .
However , many people are still concerned about the risk of the nuclear energy and aftermath consequences which last long to disperse as what happened in the World War II .
In my essay , I shall discuss about the key features of the nuclear reactor and its comparison with other alternative energy sources .
The main misconception about nuclear energy is its radiation and its possibility to explode once it is under attack .
In the history , only two accidents occurred , the Three Mile Island and Chenobyl incident .
However , we need to know that the latter incident happened at the generation I nuclear reactor , and it did n't follow the safety regulation then , hence causing the accident .
It is highly notable that since Chenobyl incident there has been no more accident .
According to WNA , the current safety standard for nuclear reactors is 1 in 10000 core damage , which means that the core will possibly damage once in 10000 operation years .
The United States reactors now have the safety standard of 1 in 100000 , much better than required .
