However , people are worried about the waste of the conventional reactor which takes millions of years to decay .
The new generation 4 nuclear reactor promises an excellent solution with its byproduct decaying in just decades .
Also , it will produce hydrogen which can be used as another type of fuel .
Hence , the new reactor is more environmentally friendly and at the same time reduces people 's fear of the waste .
Finally , given that people are worried about nuclear power , it is much needed that we should research on it so that it will be safer and more efficient for us .
Hence , we should conduct research on a new generation of reactors even more to replace the old ones .
In conclusion , nuclear power is the solution for the current energy crisis .
By researching the new generation of nuclear reactors , we can enjoy more efficient and safer energy around us .
Further research and development funding for Generation IV nuclear reactors , particularly the Very- High-Temperature Reactor ( VHTR ) , should be supported .
Ever since Mankind has started using fossil fuels for energy , 400 billion tonnes of carbon has been released and eventually would raise world temperatures by 13 degrees Celsius ( Zoe,n.d. ) .
Global warming has become an inevitable issue .
Mankind 's hunger for energy is ever increasing , and experts agree that fossil fuels might deplete within the next 50 years ( John,2006 ) .
Nuclear energy has been proposed to be the solution to this critical issue .
There are , however , concerns about nuclear power with respect to its safety , economic viability and waste disposal .
Nonetheless , the advantages Generation IV nuclear power , specifically the Very-High- Temperature reactor ( VHTR ) , could provide can offset its high start up cost and overcome its disadvantages .
Thus , further research and development funding for VHTR should be supported .
There was a partial meltdown in 1979 at Three Mile Island and there was also an accident in at Chernobyl , causing casualties and spewing radioactive waste across Europe .
It will take a lot of convincing for the public to accept nuclear power as a safe source of energy . However , such incidents are anomalous .
The technology has since improved and many new safety and monitoring features have been included .
Even though there have been several instances of leaks and other safety incidents , there have been no major accidents and no known deaths have been resulted ( The Economist , 2009 ) .
Helium is a noble gas and will not react with other materials even at high temperature , which makes the model safer ( Butler,D .
The start up cost of a nuclear power plant is expensive .
Many might argue that it is more economically viable to continue using fossil fuels for energy . However , continual burning of fossil fuels increases the emission of greenhouse gases .
Furthermore , fossil fuels are a rapidly decreasing limited resource .
The price of fossil fuels will increase exponentially in the near future due to increasing demand and fast decreasing supply .
Some would say nuclear power plants are a source of nuclear weapons and might become potential terrorist targets . Some other concepts for the reactor might involve waste reprocessing and recycling which separates out plutonium , a main ingredient of advanced nuclear weapon ( Butler,D .
Therefore , VHTR is a safe model and would eliminate any such concerns .
VHTR would be an ideal model to supply nuclear energy to resolve the problems .
However , VHTR includes features and benefits that would offset its disadvantages .
Increasing energy needs and global warming are restoring the idea of nuclear power .
According to Butler ( 2004 ) by 2050 the carbon dioxide level in the air is expected to double , causing severe global warming .
There are many different green energy sources such as solar energy , turbine generated energy from wave and wind , but nuclear energy , especially the Very High Temperature Reactor , can be the most reliable source of energy in the future when security , safety and cost of nuclear power could be resolved .
Security issue against terrorist attacks and the use of the energy for nuclear weapons is a major concern when we think about nuclear power .
The destructive power of nuclear bombs can be seen in the history of World War 2 , when two atomic bombs were used on Japan , killing 220000 people .
As technology becomes more advanced , hydrogen bombs which are deadlier are now available and the world would be in trouble if these bombs are in the wrong hands as incidents worse than September 11 may happen .
During the process of recycling , plutonium , a key ingredient for advance nuclear weapon , is produced .
Most countries including The United States has refrained from reprocessing nuclear waste and has discouraged other from doing so too .
Since the very high temperature of VHTR does not allow the waste to be recycled , the problem that people may misuse the technology will be resolved .
Even if there is recycling of waste , convectional reprocessing does not generate weapon grade plutonium and chemicals could be used to spike the plutonium to make it too hot to steal or transport .
Safety issue is definitely a concern as the history of the Three Mile Island in 1979 and the Chernobyl incident in 1986 has left a long lasting bad impression of nuclear plants .
During the Chernobyl incident the plant was blown apart in a very short time and 31 deaths were caused immediately .
The worst thing was not the immediate death but the exposure of humans to radiation .
After the explosion the land was to be vacated and would no longer be usable and the number of cancer cases is believed to have increased in Europe .
However the number of deaths is much smaller for nuclear accidents than that for coal mining ones as cave-in usually results in hundreds and thousands of death .
One of the reasons for the Chernobyl accident was the staff inexperience , but for the newer plant there will be more advanced safety enhancement and inbuilt automatic safety features that will cool themselves in times of emergency .
Although the cost of building a nuclear plant is very high and the price of the energy generated is higher than that we have in the market , development on nuclear plants is still a necessity .
In the long run the price of the energy generated by coal and oil would skyrocket as the tax for carbon emissions will increase exponentially .
The development of nuclear plants , especially the Very High Temperature Reactor , would prevent this .
The very high temperature reactor can generate both electricity and hydrogen and it is 50 % more effective than the conventional reactor and it allows countries to be self sufficient in terms of energy .
Nuclear power is one technology that must be increasingly promoted and relied upon if the world is to stabilize carbon emissions at an acceptable level .
In the modern world , nuclear power is widely used . There are more than 400 nuclear power plants operating in 30 countries , which supply almost 17 percent of the world 's electricity .
However , after research , I think the Gas- cooled fast reactor is the better one .
Actually , it can make use of 99 % of fuel .
The performance of sodium-cooled fast reactor seems so perfect ; however , compared with the performance of the gas-cooled fast reactor , that of sodium-cooled fast reactor is not perfect anymore .
The gas-cooled fast reactor is also a closed fuel cycle and the use of fuel can reach 99 % as well .
The outlet temperatures in the range of the gas-cooled fast reactor are around 850 , so its theoretical value of thermal efficiency is 50 % .
That of the sodium-cooled fast reactor is just 47 % .
Obviously , the most significant part of the safety features of the sodium- cooled fast reactor is the control action .
Thus , no matter which generation IV reactor is used , if its system has control action , it is also relatively safe .
Furthermore , the gas-cooled fast reactor also has its own control action in the system .
This control makes the gas-cooled fast reactor as safe as the sodium-cooled fast reactor .
Some evidence shows the sodium-cooled fast reactor can reduce the cost of the raw material by changing the materials used .
However , as the sodium-cooled fast reactor was developed later than the other kinds of reactors , especially later than the gas-cooled fast reactor , the cost of research and investigation of the sodium-cooled fast reactor is so huge .
Because of this , many developed countries do not have enough money to build a sodium-cooled fast reactor .
Therefore , the application of the sodium-cooled fast reactor is hindered .
Compared with the sodium-cooled fast reactor , the gas-cooled fast factor is an old one which has been developed and widely used since 1979 .
Its cost of development is far less than that of the sodium-cooled fast reactor .
Its main cost is just the annual depreciation which is far less than the development cost of the sodium- cooled reactor .
However , the sodium-cooled fast reactor should be checked for several years before it could be used .
Therefore , the gas-cooled fast reactor is better than the sodium-cooled fast reactor in terms of cost .
It has the larger thermal efficiency and lower cost of expense and time .
Even though the safety of sodium-cooled fast reactor may be better than that of the gas-cooled fast reactor , it can not change the fact that the gas-cooled fast reactor is better than the sodium-cooled fast reactor at the present stage , because there is still no way to make the nuclear power totally safe now .
According to the latest energy consumption statistics in 2008 , the majority of energy consumption was still made up of oil , coal and natural gas , which constituted 34.8 % , 24.2 % and 24.1 % of the total energy consumption respectively .
However , the fact is that at the current consumption pace , within no more than 50 years , oil and natural gas will be used up whereas the coal reserve can also only sustain 120 years more .
When we are faced with the unprecedented energy crisis , finding an alternative energy resource has naturally become the top priority issue .
For the present , nuclear energy is gradually playing an increasingly vital role in energy supply due to its high efficiency and abundant raw materials .
However , some of the public are still concerned about some of the issues associated with nuclear energy , for example cost , safety and performance .
