Therefore , the waste becomes concentrated and easy to deal with .
Lastly , many opponents still doubt the performance of nuclear reactors .
As we all know , the reactor is small in size while large in energy output .
For example , the energy generated by one kilogram of uranium is equal to the energy generated by 2400 tons of coal .
Besides , a study done last year by a group of scientists and economists looked at the potential for the power generated by nuclear energy believed that the production of nuclear energy will triple by 2050 .
Therefore , nuclear energy can take the lead in supplying more energy and decreasing the emission of greenhouse gases generated by the burning of fossil fuels .
In conclusion , I firmly believe that the huge potential benefits the nuclear reactor creates will no doubt attract more support not only from the government but also from the public and once the construction of VHTR is completed , I think the dawn of nuclear energy will also come .
These nuclear reactors , unlike the conventional power plants , do not produce greenhouse gases ( Gerstner , 2009 ) .
Thus , there should be funding for research and development for Generation IV nuclear reactors .
Some people think that the radioactive wastes produced by nuclear reactors are more dangerous than the greenhouse gases .
Furthermore , the nuclear plant produces a large amount of waste ( 12,000 tonnes ) ; thus , disposal becomes an issue ( Gerstner , 2009 ) .
Currently , most of the nuclear reactors use nuclear fission to produce energy and a large volume of radioactive wastes is produced .
It was found that through thermonuclear fusion , it could reduce the radioactivity and the volume of wastes produced by nuclear fission ( Gerstner , 2009 ) .
In this way it reduces the threat that the wastes would be used for developing nuclear weapons .
It also solves the problem of disposal .
Hence there should be funding to research and develop the hybrid concept in the Generation IV reactors .
This would not have happened if there have been funding for research and development to produce a cheaper reactor .
