the nuclear reactors now produce electricity at 6.7cents per kWh after considering the set up cost , cost of fuel , operating cost and cost of disposal . This is comparable as gas and coal plants produce electricity at 3.8 to 5.6 cents per kWh ( Giles , 2006 ) .
After a 50 % more energy is reduced the nuclear reactor would be cheaper power plants using coal and gas .
Hence there should be funding for R&D for the Generation IV reactors .
