If an alarm was sounded when safety distance between the Pan Am and KLM aircraft was breached , the Pan Am crew would have steered their aircraft away from hazard .
Had he been warned by the ringing alarm of a proximity sensor , he would have gotten enough time to respond and not to panic when the impending collision was apparent .
For these reasons , we conclude that the accident in the Tenerife runway could have been avoided , had the use of psychology been applied in the designing process .
